artist.name: Blake Jarrell
artist.bio: Aged just 23, Blake Jarrell has had a rollercoaster of a ride to date. Tipped by John Digweed as “definitely someone to look out for in the future," Blake carved himself a niche in the underground dance music scene in his hometown of New Orleans. At 16, he started to DJ and became a resident at local clubs like Ampersand, 735, and the House of Blues where he crafted his progressive housesound. Not satisfied with only DJing, Blake soon began to produce, releasing singles and remixes on various progressive labels co-produced with the late Adam "Starkid" Spears.

artist.name: Vengeance
artist.bio:
1)Vengeance is a hardcore band from Virginia.    
 2) Vengeance is a dutch melodic-rock/metal band, most known for the famous member Arjen Anthony Lucassen (Ayreon, Star One, Ambeon, Stream of Passion). Other members include Leon Goewie (vocals), Oscar Holleman (guitar), Jan Bijlsma (bass), John Snels (drums).  Discography:  
 Vengeance ( CD 1984 ) 
 Prisoners of the Night ( Single 1984 )
 You Took Me by Surprise ( Single 1985 )
 Only the Wind ( EP 1986 )

artist.name: Mat Zo
artist.bio: UK born, Matan Zohar (aka Mat Zo, Reif, Unripelemon), only 16, has made a sudden appearence on the EDM scene. After 3 years of producing varied electronic music, ranging from Drum and Bass to Trance, he discovered Progressive House. This discovery lead him to being trcklisted by some of the worlds top DJs. But still a teenager, Mat Zo is at the beginning of a long career.  Since his transition into Progressive Dance music, he explored all the flavours the genre had to offer including, Electro Prog, Markus Schulzish Trance, James Holdenish Minimal House and good old fashion Progressive House.

artist.name: Sied van Riel
artist.bio: The Riel Deal:  He is being tipped by Tiësto as “the hottest producer around” and by DJ Magazine as “the next big thing to hit trance”. One of Armin van Buuren’s favourite producers of 2008 and according to Ferry Corsten one of THE new Trance Guys. He won the “best new face”Award at the Trance Awards 2008 in London and has spun across the globe on events such as Trance Energy and Gatecrasher and may many more.

artist.name: Danjo & Styles
artist.bio: When Danjo (Danjo Raijer, 1979) and Styles (Robbert Vroegindeweij, 1980) meet each other at a party in 1998, they discover that one and one add up to more than two. Reinforcing each other both musically and production wise, they fuse into a style that is unique in any way you slice it. No conventional sounds, no cheesy tunes and never predictable: the trance sound of Danjo & Styles is magical, sexy and chockfull with emotion

artist.name: Heatbeat
artist.bio: There are two artists going by the name Heatbeat: 1). An Argentine trance duo. Heatbeat Music is formed by 2 young Argentine DJs and producers, Matias Faint (23 years old) and Agustin Servente (21 years old). This duo was created in the middle of 2006. As children, Matias and Agustin were influenced by artists like The Prodigy, Chemical Brothers, BT, Judge Jules, Paul van Dyk and more. Their productions range from progressive trance, electro trance, tech-trance, uplifting trance, Nu trance (or also known like Minimal trance).

artist.name: FKN feat. Jahala
artist.bio: FKN is Frode Kambo Nilsen from Norway (http://www.myspace.com/frodekambonilsen). Jahala is Jan Hallvard Larsen from Norway (http://www.myspace.com/jahala).

artist.name: Andy Prinz
artist.bio: Andy Prinz love for Electronic Music was born in the 1980s. Fascinated by new developments and innovations in synthesizer and sampler technologies and bands such as Depeche Mode, Andy soon also desired to make his mark in the electronic field. His musical talent already began while he took his first lessons in classical piano and on a simple keyboard when he began to create his own first melodies.

artist.name: A State of Trance
artist.bio: One of the first imprints of Armada was the ‘A State Of Trance’ label. Based on Armin van Buuren’s radio show, with over 27 million listeners and transmitted through 22 radio stations worldwide. From instant classics like ‘Signum - Push Through’ and ‘EnMass - CQ’ to the freshest tunes from top producers like Robert Nickson, C-quence and Roger Shah.

artist.name: Simon Patterson
artist.bio: Simon Patterson the DJ.... is one of the hottest properties in dance music. From being the driving force in the engine rooms of two of the biggest shows on Radio 1, he utilised his finely tuned ear working as the tastemaker behind Seb Fontaine and Judge Jules peak-time Saturday nighters. Drawing on all the knowledge gained, and an unparallel passion for music, he has now thrust himself firmly at the forefront, and is firmly forging his own career as an in-demand DJ, producer and remixer.

artist.name: Luke Chable
artist.bio: http://www.myspace.com/lukechable http://www.discogs.com/artist/Luke+Chable

artist.name: Michael Tsukerman
artist.bio: Michael Tsukermanis is a successful musician living in Israel.

artist.name: EDX
artist.bio: EDX is a worldwide acclaimed remixer, well-known for his brilliant work for as likes as Dubfire, Deadmau5, Armand van Helden, Steve Angello, Sucker DJs, Michael Procter, Kool & The Gang, Lauryn Hill andArmin van Buuren, to name but a few. Enormous Diverse Xample (of a genius) might not be an accurate, but for sure a possible interpretation of the three letters EDX. Productive and successful for more then a decade, Italian native artist, producer, DJ and multi-talent EDX, has been and still is a well-known name in the dance scene in and outside of his home base Switzerland.

artist.name: 8 Wonders
artist.bio: Growing up in a small town, he did what all the kids his age did: go outside and play sports. His dad would always play rock classics and domestic music and subconsciously he thinks this turned him off from music for a long time. He had too much in too short of a time period.  It was not until the age of 14 that he expressed interest in music. He really did not know what was out there. The first electronica track he's ever heard was an .S3M (back in the MOD days) by "Purple Motion". He eventually progressed onto Euro Dance, listening to Sash, Scooter, etc.

artist.name: Hydroid
artist.bio: Itay Steinberg, better known as Hydroid, was born on the 5th of April 1986 in Ramat-Gan, Israel.  Since childhood he was attracted to EDM, those banging beats and powerful basslines, combined with beautiful melodies, it was love at first sight.  In the year of 2002, Itay discovered a program named "Impulse Tracker" which was a sample based DOS program. Itay was excited with the idea that he could finally make his own music using just his home PC. Producing music gave him a different feeling, something he hadn't felt before, a feeling that soaked him to the very core of his sole.

artist.name: Wippenberg
artist.bio: The project WIPPENBERG started in 1995 as a simple side-project, with its first release NEURODANCER on the German underground label Hyper Hype Records. OLAF DIECKMANN - a German producer and dj, who made his first steps as a teenager in the early eighties in the EBM scene - created a big and worldwide club-tune with the hymn NEURODANCER, which was f.e. licensed in UK to the genius techno label Prolekult.

artist.name: Yans
artist.bio:
yans - electronic composer, arranger, performer & producer... All in One...
 Club, dance, trance, electronica... My style is mixture of all this genres... :-)  "Yans Energy Line" is my new club/dance/trance Project - energy, rthymic & melodic dance music, superb fo party/club...

artist.name: Jaytech
artist.bio: Hailing from Australia’s capital, Canberra, James “Jimbo” Cayzer’s musical pedigree extends way back to his early years as a pianist and composer. However, at the tender age of 14, Jimbo commenced work on his first digital production and hasn’t looked back since. After the initial success of “Music 101” and his remix of Lens’ “Let The Light In,” Jaytech hit the studio with partner-in-crime Mark Dynamix, and shot to prominence with the release of “Identify Me" in 2004, appearing on the Ministry Of Sound 2005 Annual and dominating Australian radio.

artist.name: Ben Gold
artist.bio: At just 23 years old Ben Gold is one of the most multi talented names in the electronic dance scene. Ben combines a highly acclaimed career as a leading studio engineer with that of one of the brightest young stars in the trance scene, djing at some of the worlds leading clubs alongside world class dj's who all regularly fill their cd wallets with his latest works.  Ben

artist.name: Manvel Ter-Pogosyan feat. Jenni Perez
artist.bio: Manvel Ter-Pogosyan was introduced to Trance music by ATBs famous track, 9PM (Till I Come). Born in Yerevan, Armenia, in 1987, Manvel was constantly exposed to music while growing up in a family appreciative of the arts. After immigrating to the United States in 1991, he continued to surround himself with beautiful music which led him to engage in music composition and production. In the years to come, passion and inspiration would take control as song after song was produced.

artist.name: Tiddey
artist.bio: DJ Tiddey, a.k.a. Darek Plaza, is from Poznan (Poland), and from his youth on, he was interested in music. At age five, he was playing piano and guitar.The Dutch DJ Peran inspired him so much, that in 2002 he became a DJ and producer. At the present time,  Tiddey is one of Poland’s most important DJs. This is due to his energetic way of performing during a DJ set, and his choice of music. Tiddey became the first Polish DJ who performed in Spain, Holland and Belgium.

artist.name: Jens
artist.bio: Jens, full name Jens Mahlstedt, is a german artist best known for his big hit Loops & Tings. Aside from producing music, Jens is also a popular DJ. Jens can also refer to Jens Unosson, most well known as a member of Swedish psychedelic band The Spacious Mind. He has released one album titled If You

artist.name: Signum
artist.bio:
There is more than one artist under the name of Signum  1. Signum from Netherlands
 2. Signum from Serbia
 3. SignuM from Lithuania (rock band)  Signum is the combination of two talented producers in the European music industry. They are Pascal Minnaard, (age 29) and Ronald Hagen (also age 29). Both live in Zoetermeer, a little city nearby Hague, their home base in Netherlands.  Pascal & Ron first met each other in high school.

artist.name: Leon Bolier
artist.bio:
Leon Bolier was born in 1980 somewhere in the middle of Holland, and always was in love with moody music.
 When he heard Energy 52's Cafe Del Mar he fell in love with melodic trance, and quit producing hardcore house.
 In 2002 and 2003 he got his first record deals, together with his brother Bart. They released some tracks on Bonzai/Banshee and FTM sublabels. Back then the first contacts with Armada frontman Maykel Piron were established via Armin van Buuren, and this resulted in Leon remixing the first ever Armada release.

artist.name: Steve Forte Rio
artist.bio: Steve Forte Rio is an alias used for several tracks featured on Tiësto's In Search Of Sunrise series. The name is an anagram for Tiesto Forever and there is a rumor Tiesto himself is behind the productions, but nothing has been confirmed. Daniel Joaquin is credited as a co-producer for two of the tracks.

artist.name: Thomas Bronzwaer
artist.bio: Born in Nijmegen (The Netherlands) on the 30th of September, 1984, he became interested in dance music around the age of 13. Early inspirations were the soundtracks to the WipeOut series on the playstation, featuring artists like Paul van Dyk, Sasha, the Chemical Brothers, FSOL and the Prodigy. Around 2000 Tiesto, Push and others came into the picture. Thomas released his first record in 2003 - a collaboration with Greg Murray who took care of the technical aspect of producing while Thomas wrote the themes.

artist.name: PROFF
artist.bio: Real Name: Vladimir Ershov (Владимир Ершов) is a progressive house DJ & producer from Moscow, Russia signed to a UK record label Anjunabeats/Anjunadeep.  PROFF's earlier releases include "My Personal Summer" which was featured on CD1 of Anjunabeats Vol.6 and "Aguilas" which has been played lately in numerous Above & Beyond dj sets and podcasts.   He collaborated with his fellow countryman, Mango, to release the track "5th in Blue", which had two separate remixes from both artists.

artist.name: DJ Shah & Fast Distance pres. Samara
ID vs. Sia
artist.bio: Instead of ID being the actual name of an artist, in many cases, ID stands for an artist who has yet to be identified, which is common in dj sets when the official tracklist is not available and the artist of a particular track within the set is unknown to the identifier at the time of tracklist identification OR has requested that he/she not be identified yet for various reasons.  -OR-  Id is also the name of an American psych/prog rock band that recorded one extremely rare album "Where Are We Going" in 1976 and then disappeared off the face of the Earth.

artist.name: Kyau & Albert
artist.bio: Official Web Site : http://www.kyauandalbert.com Kyau & Albert is the working name for two trance music producers and DJs from Germany named Ralph Kyau and Steven Moebius Albert. They were formerly known as Kyau vs. Albert but changed their working name to Kyau & Albert in 2006, with the release of the album Worldvibe. Ralph Kyau had his first experience with the production of electronic music in 1990 and gained a reputation for DJ-ing as well as Live PA sets at several underground techno parties in Germany before releasing his first record "Modulation Experiments" at the end of 1993.

artist.name: Riva feat. Dannii Minogue
artist.bio: 1) Band from former Yugoslavia, won the Eurovision Song Contest 1989 with the song "Rock me"  2) Guss van Vlaanderen and Horst Pulmann

artist.name: Arctique
artist.bio: Daniel Agarici, also known as Arctique, was born in 1988 in the seaside city of Constanta, Romania. Since  his early years, he discovered a huge interest in music and never stopped pursuing it by going through  several music genres and improving the originality of his creations.  His debut in the music scene was a collab with one of his closest friends Fjor nrg. The track called Prelude  - Tenerife was released on May 2008 under Bonzai Music lablel as no. #1 trackitdown progressive trance  track.

artist.name: OceanLab
artist.bio: OceanLab is a vocal trance group formed in London, England in 2000, consisting of Jonathan Grant, Tony McGuinness, Paavo Siljamäki (Above & Beyond) and the vocal talents of Justine Suissa. Discography: Upcoming Singles 2009-07-06: Lonely Girl (Part 2) Albums 2009-06-07: Sirens Of The Sea Remixed 2008-07-21: Sirens of the Sea Singles 2001-08-09: Clear Blue Water 2002-09-11: Sky Falls Down 2003-04-07: Beautiful Together 2004-02-02: Satellite

artist.name: David Newsum
artist.bio:
David Newsum started DJing in 1997 in London and his on air experience consisted of doing Pirate (Illegal) radio from a crack den in Hackney that had drug induced comatose people inside and police batten marks on the door as it was regularly raided by the police. He managed to avoid being locked up in prison and in May 2004 he moved to Dubai to take up residency to DJ at Tangerine.
 In September 2004 David was spotted by the radio station Dubai 92 and offered a weekly dance show,

artist.name: Trance Around the World
artist.bio: Trance Around the World is the title of UK trance trio Above & Beyond's radio show. For listen visit, www.trancearoundtheworld.com.

artist.name: Sundriver
artist.bio: Sundriver is a Polish trance producer from Hatfield. He has made a name for himself in 2008 with beautiful atmospheric tracks. He was influenced by the likes of Paul van Dyk and Chicane. His two big breakthrough tracks of 2008 were

artist.name: DeRelict
artist.bio:
There are 2 bands by the name of Derelict  
 1. Derelict is a solo project fronted by multi-instrumentalist Jesse Ditson. His songs are influenced by artists like Elliott Smith, Erlen Oye, Thom Yorke, Belle and Sebastian, Wilco, and Jeff Mangum, creating a sound ranging from pop to industrial. Instruments used in recording include Cello, Mandolin, Recorder, Tambourine, Omni Chord, and a plethora of other instruments, in addition to the standard Kit, Guitar, Keys, and Bass.

artist.name: Super8 & Tab
artist.bio: See Super8 & DJ Tab

artist.name: Sean Tyas
artist.bio: "Sean Tyas has to be one of the hottest producers around at the moment." - Armin van Buuren (August 2006)  After being blown away by some of his recent productions, John Askew has signed up Sean Tyas to join the existing Discover ranks. His first outing on the label will come in the form of a kicking remix he has done of Aled Mann's "Cold Fusion" which will then set the standard for his first Discover single "Lift" which is sure to be another classic release for the label. "Mark my words... Tyas will be f**ing huge!!!!" Askew December 05.

artist.name: Oliver Smith
artist.bio: Oliver Smith has been working in the music industry for most of his adult life. Over the past 6+ years he has worked as a music producer, remixer and DJ. He records under a number of names including Smith & Pledger, Whitewater, Aspekt, Les Voleurs and Scalar. Record labels he has worked with include the major labels Universal, Sony and EMI as well as a host of independents such as Anjunabeats, Good Looking and Ministry of Sound.

artist.name: Signalrunners
artist.bio: Signalrunners started as a trans-Atlantic trance project in 2003 with members Alan Nimmo (Scotland) and Andrew Bayer (USA). Alan Nimmo, an experienced DJ and producer has been DJing since the tender age of 12 and has DJed in most of Scotlands top venues. His passion for dance music started with DJing in the UK Rave scene in the early nineties and evolved to Trance as music styles progressed in the UK.

artist.name: ID
artist.bio:
There is more than one artist with this name:  1) iD is an experimental hip hop artist from the U.S.
 2) Id is also the name of an American psych/prog rock band.
 3) id is a thrash metal band from Brazil.
 4) D, tu identificación, con quién TU te identificas.
 5) ID is the name of a Canadian boy band,
 6) Id is a solo space drone artist.  1) iD is an experimental hip hop artist from the U.S. Influenced by beat poets, punk rock, and underground Hip Hop, iD’s sound is explosive and thought provoking.

artist.name: Sia
artist.bio: Sia Kate Isobelle Furler, to use the name her musician parents gave her, already has a staggering track record. If her name itself - pronounced 'See-ah' - isn't familiar to millions, her voice undoubtedly is. In 2000, the Adelaide born singer scored a bolt from the blue Top 10 hit with her debut single, Taken for Granted. Pairing her unique Australian drawl with the strident strings from Prokofiev's 'Romeo & Juliet', the track was championed by Trevor Nelson and had Sia performing live on Jo Whiley's Radio 1 show.

artist.name: Airbase
artist.bio: The Airbase story begins in 1994 when he got his hands on the software Scream Tracker pitched to him by a Finnish cousin. A few years later, Airbase switched to better software that came highly recommended from others called Fast Tracker. The following years were kept busy with hard work which rendered numerous tracks, but also a lot of knowledge and understanding in how to produce, arrange and write melodies.

artist.name: Mark Norman
artist.bio: Mark Norman are the award winning Dutch production duo, responsible for a series of high profile original productions and remixes. Dubbed by Tiesto as his hot prediction for the future, dance floor anthems such as Touchdown, Phantom Manor, Overkill, RUSH, and Mark Norman pres. Celine have assisted in their meteoric rise from hopefuls to fully fledged international artists in just a few years.  Signed to Black Hole Recordings on Tiesto’s own Magik Muzik label, original tracks such as Stream, which was featured on Tiesto’s DVD ‘Another Day at the Office’...

artist.name: Paul Miller pres. Motion Blur
artist.bio: Motion Blur is an a.k.a. of Polish producer Paul Miller, he has currently released 5 singles/ep’s under this name: Take a Look and See / Curler One More Time CSR Liquidity Chieftec / Universe http://www.myspace.com/djpaulmiller

artist.name: Andy Moor feat. Carrie Skipper vs. Motorcycle
Telefon Tel Aviv
artist.bio: Telefon Tel Aviv is a music collective started by Josh Eustis and the late Charlie Cooper of New Orleans, Louisiana.  The two originally met in high school, but did not begin working on music together until after university studies.  Since 1999 the two have been working to cultivate their sound, one that is based largely in electronic music, but that also shows flourishes of classical, vintage soul, ambient drone, and noise, among other things.

artist.name: Above & Beyond
artist.bio: Above & Beyond is a trance music group formed in 2000 by Jonathan "Jono" Grant, Tony McGuinness, and Paavo Siljamäki. The trio are popular in the trance scene for their uplifting trance productions and collaborations with many vocalists. They are consistently voted as one of the top DJs and are currently ranked number 4 in the official DJ Magazine top 100 poll. They also host their own weekly radio show, Trance Around the World.

artist.name: Push
artist.bio: There are four Artists with the Name 'Push': A Belgian DJ, the band Push, the other band Push and an old soulgroup (no description available, but you can find it on some soulsamplers) with the same name. Push (not to be confused with the band) is a pseudonym for popular Belgian DJ Mike Dierickx (M.I.K.E.). Best known for the song "Universal Nation", he has also released other singles including "The Legacy" and "Strange World". His style is primarily progressive trance. Push - The Band

artist.name: Michael Angelo
artist.bio: There are at least 2 artists with the name Michael Angelo, one is an obscure American psychadelic band and the other a guitar player.  Michael Angelo Batio (pronounced "Bah-tee-ohh") is an American instrumental rock guitarist from Chicago, Illinois. He attended Northeastern Illinois University and received a bachelor's degree in music theory. Having played guitar since the age of ten, Batio is often referred to as the fastest guitar shredder of all time.

artist.name: Deadmau5
artist.bio: Born and raised in Niagara Falls, Canada, Joel Zimmerman (aka "deadmau5" or "Halcyon441") has become one of the most sought-after artists on the electronic music scene.  He first started his career as co-producer of the Niagara Falls radio show "The Party Revolution" (101.1 The Planet). After gaining exposure to all the many facets of electronic music, Joel then moved on to collaborate with many other artists and record labels in many studios throughout the globe.

artist.name: Chicane
artist.bio: Chicane is a pseudonym used by UK-based Electronical Composer, Musician and Producer Nicholas Bracegirdle. He was born on February 28th - 1971, in London, England. Chicane is known for the single Offshore, an Ibiza anthem included in thousands of compilations in both chill-out and dance form; Saltwater, which featured vocals by Clannad member Máire Brennan; Autumn Tactics; No Ordinary Morning , and the #1 hit Don't Give Up, which features vocals by Bryan Adams.

artist.name: DJ Preach
artist.bio: Label manager, producer, radio and dancefloor igniting DJ, Preach has achieved international fame in a young but eventful career. With a string of acclaimed releases for Black Hole, InCharge, Intec, Terminal M or his own Relic Recordings, DJ Preach releases a new 2008 remix of his best seller production of 2007 ?Broken Inside? taken from his artist album ?Transatlantic?, on Future Beat Instructions (FBI), the techno-centric sister label to Tiesto?s Black Hole Recordings.

artist.name: Ohmna
artist.bio:
Ohmna (aka Johan Cyber) is a DJ and producer. Ohmna is a sound from Buddha. His focus is always about the feeling and the realness of the music .   
 Over the course of his exciting career, Ohmna has traveled the world.
 Ohmna has quickly become a highly respected DJ, recognized worldwide.
 Space Ibiza (Closing party Carl Cox),Hoaman 17 Israel,Nicky Beach Miami, Bali,Love Parade Berlin,Love Parade Tel Aviv,Street parade Zurich,Carl Cox&Friends Rotterdam,Dancevalley Velvet London,ect.  
 As a Producer Ohmna proved that he has the capability to set also standards in this area.

artist.name: Stoneface & Terminal
artist.bio: Stoneface & Terminal are two dynamic German producers and Djs with a long list of releases and remixes under various names on a number of high profile labels. Their productions are hammered by the likes of Paul van Dyk, Tiesto, Armin van Buuren, Paul Oakenfold, Ferry Corsten and Markus Schulz.  In 2004 Henry & Matthias founded their label Electric Department Records and brought up tracks like Merkur, Sidewinder or Summerscape/Miami. Paul van Dyk chose Merkur for his exclusive DJMAG Mix-CD.

artist.name: Global DJ Broadcast
artist.bio: Global DJ Broadcast is NOT a performer. It's a show hosted and made by Markus Schulz at an online-radio station called Digitally Imported Radio or di.fm. He's one among many DJs on DI. And the show is one among many can be hear on DI (visit DI calendar).

artist.name: Coldplay
artist.bio: Coldplay is a British alternative rock band, formed in London, United Kingdom in 1997. The band comprises vocalist and pianist Chris Martin, lead guitarist Jonny Buckland, bassist Guy Berryman, and drummer Will Champion. Having released four successful albums, (all of which debuted at #1 on the UK album chart) Coldplay have also achieved great success with their singles, such as Yellow, Speed of Sound, the Grammy-winning Clocks and the US and UK #1 single Viva la Vida. Frontman Chris Martin credits 1980s Norwegian pop band a-ha for inspiring him to form his own band.

artist.name: Airwave
artist.bio: Laurent Véronnez aka (DJ) Airwave lived in Brussels until he was 20 years young, experimenting with computers and synthesizers at his home. After sending his first demo to Lightning Records - the original home of the infamous Bonzai label -, he became one of the main artists of the new age in electronic music. After the first small successes with PLG, North Pole, Montera and Magnetix, he had his first breakthrough with the first release of Fire & Ice, produced together with DJ Fire. He decided to move to Antwerp so he could concentrate more on his productional work.

artist.name: Mirco de Govia
artist.bio: Already as a little boy Mirco de Govia was interested in electronic music (such as Kraftwerk and Tangerine Dream). Because of this, he handcrafted his first sound generator.  In 1991 he jumped onto the booming German techno wave. After a period of time as a party animal, he felt like trying to develop the trance and techno scene himself. He bought music equipment and began to work in his own studio.

artist.name: Tritonal
artist.bio: Tritonal consists of two DJ's at the forefront of trance music production and live sets. Chad Cisneros and Dave Reed produce cutting edge performances that trigger your emotions to dance and rival the best in music today. In the studio, their extensive sessions are filled with boundless creativity and an unrivaled passion for producing new sounds and slamming tracks. The two met online while discussing sound design and production techniques. They quickly developed a relationship and came to realize that together they could achieve much greater things.

artist.name: Ferry Corsten
artist.bio: Ferry Corsten is a Dutch DJ, producer and recorder who first started out in 1991 producing underground hardcore gabber tracks. He soon expanded into clubhouse and trance music. But don't put Ferry into the trance corner, because his sound encompasses several genres of electronic music. In 1999 Ferry Corsten was voted Best Producer of the Year at the Ericsson Muzik Award in London. In 2000, he was awarded Best Remix for Adagio for Strings (Ferry Corsten remix) at the Dancestar 2000 awards.

artist.name: Jochen Miller
artist.bio: Jochen van der Steijn, born in the Dutch city Mill, started his career by the name DJ Jochen. In 2003 he changed his artist name into Jochen Miller. The young deejay / producer already managed to create his own recognisable sound, which can be described as style-blending tech-trance: energetic, uplifting and high quality. Characterized by up-tempo powerful melodies, few breaks and constant pumping bass lines. The charismatic Jochen Miller is filled with passion for music and ready to make it to the top.

artist.name: Dyor
artist.bio:
After a long time of music experience as a deejay and producer ,
 DYOR this new italian talent that grew up with a new music philosophy
 with a electro rhythm and Melodic Progression.
 He is a perfect mix between Sentimental sound and emotions like his first song called EMOTIONS.
 ITALIAN CARISMA and STYLE in the world... called... DYOR !!

artist.name: Element One
artist.bio: Mauricio Vaca Aka Element One was born with music beating in his blood. As a young boy, he always aspired to be that guy on stage making the crowds move. Having grown up in Miami, the Electronic Dance Music scene came and went, and at the age of 17 it really stuck with him! In a city known for its diversity, Mauricio had a new aspiration...to become an Internationally known producer. The beauty that pulsates from Trance & Progressive has had his attention for years now, and its time for the world to put their attention on what is the essense of Element One.

artist.name: Lost Witness vs. Sassot
artist.bio: Lost Witness is one of the UK's top trance artists, specializing in the extremely melodic vocal trance anthems.  Lost Witness are DJ / Producer Simon Paul and producer Simon Kemper.  The dynamic duo met and formed in May 1998 as Dusk Til Dawn and enjoyed the underground success of Fine Night, which in turn brought songwriter Ed Barton into the frame as the third, if more silent member, to complete the happy union.

artist.name: Giorgio Moroder vs. Danny Tenaglia
artist.bio: Giorgio Moroder (born Giovanni Giorgio Moroder on April 26, 1940 in Ortisei, Italy) is an Italian record producer, songwriter and performer, whose groundbreaking work with synthesizers during the 1970s was a significant influence on techno and electronic music in general. Particularly well known are Donna Summer's disco hits produced by Moroder, including "Love To Love You Baby" and "I Feel Love". Moroder also produced a number of electronic disco hits for The Three Degrees.

artist.name: Matthew Dekay
artist.bio: From an early age it seemed as if Matthew Dekay was destined to be a musician. With both parents with strong backgrounds in music, he was brought up in a house filled with music. Inspired, he quickly took up the Piano and by the age of 12 was writing his own songs daringly exploring the world of analogue snyths and 909 drum computers after hearing the likes of Kraftwerk and Jean Michel Jarre.

artist.name: Blank & Jones feat. Bobo
artist.bio:
Blank & Jones is a trance duo based in Cologne, Germany, consisting of Piet Blank (Jan Pieter Blank) and DJ Jaspa Jones (Rene Runge), with help from producer Andy Kaufhold. They have released eight albums and more than 16 singles since their first single release "Sunrise" in 1997.  They also continue to DJ a couple of radio shows in Germany.
 _________________________________________________________________

artist.name: Andrelli & Blue feat. Hila
artist.bio: The fusion of Andrelli And Adrian Blue is one of the most exciting colabs this year. The progressive sound of Adrian Blue merges into the uplifting sound of Andrelli and we got a storm on the dance floors. The duos first release Imagine featuring the amazing vocalist Hila is one of the hottest release this year, with remixes from Mike Nichol , Ben Gold , Rozza , Six Senses and two exclusive remixes from the duo itself. Above are samples of some of the future releases.

artist.name: Elevation
artist.bio: There are several artists called Elevation. 1. Rock Band Elevation, the Atlanta-based rock band, consists of members Nathan Smith (Vocals), Andrew Averso (Lead Guitar), Stephen Bailey (Drums), Matt Perez (Bass), and Luke Hickok (Guitar). Smith, formed Elevation in 2002. The band’s debut album “Strangelove” was recorded in Atlanta in the winter of 2007. The album was produced by Dan Hannon (Manchester Orchestra, King Konga, Aaron Shust) and mastered by Grammy Award winner Adam Ayan (Nirvana, The Rolling Stones, Foo Fighters, Incubus). http://myspace.com/elevation

artist.name: Danilo Ercole
artist.bio: Up-and-coming Brazilian trance producer Danilo Ercole was born in Curitiba City on August 8th 1981. He started DJing at the age of 15, when he was playing dance music at friends' parties. His music taste developed over those years & in 2000 Danilo began mixing trance. Now seven years later he is one of the top few DJs in the genre in Brazil, having played at all of the major clubs & events. His sets encompass progressive, uplifting & tech-trance, always with plenty of energy.

artist.name: Armin van Buuren feat. Audrey Gallagher
Marco V
artist.bio: From well-known tracks like 'Indicator', 'Simulated' and 'Godd' through to present-day productions such as 'Second Bite', 'More Than A Life Away' and 'Red Blue Purple', and his successful updates of widely regarded classics such as 'Café Del Mar' and 'Loops & Tings Relooped', Marco V's discography is considerably extensive. On the decks he develops his personal style, incorporating anything from electro to techno.

artist.name: Pryda
artist.bio: Pryda is an alias of the Swedish musician Eric Prydz. Other aliases used by Prydz include Cirez D, Moo and Sheridan. Pryda's music has been released under the labels Pryda Recordings, Pryda and Pryda Friends. The music released by Pryda falls into a variety of electronic-music sub genres, most notably house (Including electro house and tech house).

artist.name: John O'Callaghan & Bryan Kearney
artist.bio:
john O'Callaghan and Bryan Kearney are two legends in trance. There planet love live set blew millions away and 2gether they prefom great gigs. 
 This duo is responsibile for one of the greatest medollic trance songs of the decade entitled 'exactly'.

artist.name: Evgeny Bardyuzha
artist.bio: Evgeny Bardyuzha was born in Chelyabinsk in 1987. During the childhood was dreaming to compose music. At the age of 16 his dream started to realise with the help of computer sequencers. And when he was 18 he signed his first track on the Belgian small digital label Trance4m8 (4-Stroke) under the alias of Dr. Bardujja. After a number of releases, that were not very succesful, Evgeny continues working in the home studio.

artist.name: Cass & Slide
artist.bio: British production and remix duo famous for their  progressive trance anthems and expert remixes. They released "Diablo" in 1999.  The duo were given world-wide exposure when the Evolution remix of "Diablo" appeared on John Digweed's Hong Kong Global Underground mix CD, and their massive trance anthem "Perception" was featured on Sasha's Ibiza Global Underground mix CD.   The duo released an album in 2002. Cass & Slide's production/remix out-put halted when Cass' Fire label folded in early 2003. The duo has remained largely inactive since.

artist.name: Offer Nissim feat. Maya
artist.bio: Offer Nissim is an Israeli DJ, producer and remixer who, over the past 25 years, has become one of the top names in Israel's huge club scene.  Offer Nissim's entrance into the industry started by accident when in 1979, the 15 year old DJ played his first ever live club set after being asked to replace a DJ that failed to show up. Since then, and over the years, Nissim has played in dozens of clubs across Israel, such as the "Forum", "Ha-Oman 17", "Alenby 58" and for the past few years in the "TLV" as the resident of the "FFF" - the most successful line of gay parties in Israel.

artist.name: Eurythmics vs. Ronski Speed
artist.bio: Hugely successful synth-pop/rock/soul music duo consisting of musician/producer Dave Stewart and songwriter/vocalist Annie Lennox. Formed in 1981 after the breakup of their former band The Tourists. Best known for their 1982 album and single Sweet Dreams (Are Made of This) and their striking visual image, most notably Lennox's androgynous persona. They have described their music style as "for intelligent dancers". Both Stewart and Lennox have had success outside of Eurythmics. They have sold over 75 million albums worldwide.

artist.name: Jochen Miller vs. Armin van Buuren
Ali Wilson
artist.bio: Ali Wilson is one of the most exciting young artists the UK has to offer. In just under 7 years he has established himself as a producer many look to for inspiration, his unique innovative approach to music shines through in every aspect. Where he leads others follow

artist.name: Albert Vorne
artist.bio: Born under the shade of Switzerland ‘s grey mountains in 1982, Albert Vorne (real name Albert Candiani) quickly moved some few miles south into Northern Italy where at the age of seventeen he started his Dj / Producer career.  The new Millennium has represented a fundamental corner stone for Albert’s career, as the young DJ became Mazeman’s manager and A&R. The label sky rocketed in a few months with the release of tracks as Albert’s own “Indigo” (Mazeman/Above The Sky) followed by “A leaden day”, the hit single that, also thank to the smashing M.

artist.name: Rank 1
artist.bio: They’re one of Europe’s most established and respected dance acts. Their debut release, ‘Airwave’ was the first Dutch record ever to hit the #1 position in the European dance charts and went Top 10 in the UK. Over the last 8 years, they have continued to pack the record boxes of world’s A-list spinners with floor-monsters like ‘Symsonic’, ‘Such is Life’, ‘Breathing’ & ‘Life Less Ordinary’… Performing to tens of thousands of dance fans every week, they play at some of the biggest dance events in the world. Meet Piet Bervoets & Benno de Goeij - better known as Rank 1!

artist.name: Markus Schulz
artist.bio: Markus Schulz is a german progressive trance producer renowned for his unique style of dark, brooding yet melodic productions and DJ sets. He is head of his own label Coldharbour Recordings in co-operation with Armada and he is infamous for surprising his fans with his own edits and reconstructions of well-known songs. He is currently living in Miami, Florida ------------------- Markus Schulz is a man on a mission. He dreams of meeting the world. This dream just might be possible. Currently number 8 on the DJ Mag Top 100 DJ’s Poll and 5th on the TranceAddict.

artist.name: Timmy & Tommy
artist.bio:
Timmy Gibson & Tommy Conway have been Djing togetther since 1995. They are both fully qualified sound engineers and currently lecture in Dublins Sound Training Centre in "The Temple Bar Music Centre".
 They had their First Release in Jan 2007 with their Cover of Blondies "Rapture" This release got support from the like of Mason & Tall Paul and was picked up by Kontor Records for "Top of the Clubs 34" Compliation. The debut single also got picked up by RPM Dance to Feature on Bump 20 Complaition in South Africa which sold in Excess of 100,000 Copies.

artist.name: Chance Jumpers
artist.bio: 'Chance Jumpers' started in August 2004 as three friends carried away by electronic dance music, in the very beginning their main goal was bringing and promoting modern electronic sound directions in their native city of Saint Petersburg in Russia and later producing their own tracks which Chance Jumpers describe as 'progressive trance'; but during the first year of team-work they found themselves in deep/progressive house with some elements of tech house.

artist.name: John O'Callaghan feat. Audrey Gallagher
artist.bio: Collaboration between Irish trance producer and DJ John O'Callaghan and Irish singer/song-writer Audrey Gallagher. Their only production together so far (as of March 2008) is a vocal trance song called 'Big Sky'. This was released in November 2007 from the Dutch trance label 'Armind', along with a remix by Agnelli & Nelson. This remix was voted the 'tune of the year 2007' in Armin van Buuren's radio show 'A State of Trance' in 20th December 2007. Four new remixes - three by EDX and one by City Zen were released in March 2008 from the same label.

artist.name: Zoo Brazil
artist.bio: John Andersson and Johan Emmoth are the creative force behind Zoo Brazil. Also recording as Laid, Cuba Computers, Nars and Outcold, they have steadily carved out a reputation as a highly innovative and respected production and dj team.  The pair are prolific producers and DJs, having worked with some of the world's best known artists - for example Human League. With their remix work contributing to the catalogues of a host of admired underground dance acts, like Blaze (Slip N Slide) and Zoot Woman (Wall of Sound).

artist.name: Oryon
artist.bio: "I’ll find a way." Those are the words that singer/songwriter Oryon lives by. "No matter how difficult things might get or how impossible they might seem, I always find a way to make it through.  Undoubtedly it is this outlook that has carried Oryon into the arms of success. Even as a child growing up in Wisconsin, Oryon seemed destined for a life of great achievements. A professional model at the age of 12, Oryon appeared in numerous fashion shows, print ads and commercials.

artist.name: Royal Sapien
artist.bio: Royal Sapien is producer and DJ, Ben Mautner from Brooklyn, New York. He creates all sorts of electronic music, particularly breaks and house, and runs Olaris Records, on which his most recent two albums have been released.

artist.name: Markus Schulz feat. Andy Moor
artist.bio: Markus Schulz is a german progressive trance producer renowned for his unique style of dark, brooding yet melodic productions and DJ sets. He is head of his own label Coldharbour Recordings in co-operation with Armada and he is infamous for surprising his fans with his own edits and reconstructions of well-known songs. He is currently living in Miami, Florida ------------------- Markus Schulz is a man on a mission. He dreams of meeting the world. This dream just might be possible. Currently number 8 on the DJ Mag Top 100 DJ’s Poll and 5th on the TranceAddict.

artist.name: 4 Strings - Take Me Away (Into The Night) (Re
Arnej
artist.bio: Music first claimed a presence in Arnej’s life during his childhood, which saw him endure the musical taste of his father. The various genres of music continuously bumping in his household conspired to turn him off from music and drive him towards the more conventional interests of a small town kid.  Music regained weight in Arnej’s life at the tender age of 14, when an early computer-composed electronica track snagged his interest.

artist.name: Mr. Pit vs. Above & Beyond feat. Ashley Tomberlin
artist.bio: Adrian Ivan aka Mr. Pit discovered electronica back in 1996 and got heavily influenced by the dance scene. As the years passed, his style went along with the trance movement, adding agressive elements and various influences to the sound. In time, the love for music took hold and what followed were countless hours in his studio experimening with sound. In 2003, he has his debut onstage, creating and manipulating live sounds at Romania's premiere electronic music festival TM03BASE.

artist.name: Above & Beyond pres. Tranquility Base vs. ID
artist.bio: Alias of uplifting/melodic trance trio Above & Beyond. In their words: "The Tranquility Base project is an excuse to flex our club production muscles, try out new things and have some fun".

artist.name: Leon Bolier vs. Bedrock vs. ID
artist.bio:
Leon Bolier was born in 1980 somewhere in the middle of Holland, and always was in love with moody music.
 When he heard Energy 52's Cafe Del Mar he fell in love with melodic trance, and quit producing hardcore house.
 In 2002 and 2003 he got his first record deals, together with his brother Bart. They released some tracks on Bonzai/Banshee and FTM sublabels. Back then the first contacts with Armada frontman Maykel Piron were established via Armin van Buuren, and this resulted in Leon remixing the first ever Armada release.

artist.name: Guru Josh Project - Infinity 2008 (Jerome Isma
artist.bio: The Guru Josh Project got together in 2007 and consist of Guru Josh (Song Writer) Dj DazPerkz (DJ/Producer) and Snakebyte (Producer). They formed the project as three people who have a love for electronic music and old school 90 rave music. Their aim is to bring back the magic of the 90?s dance scene with a fresh and up to date new sound, starting off with Guru Josh's 1990 worldwide smash hit Infinity, the first ever cross over track.

artist.name: Markus Schulz feat. Departure
artist.bio: Markus is renowned for his unique style of dark, brooding yet melodic DJ sets. Markus is infamous for surprising his fans with his reconstructions of well-known songs. His productions include Electronic Elements, Armada, Anjunabeats, Lost Language and many more respected labels.  -------------------  Markus Schulz is a man on a mission. He dreams of meeting the world. This dream just might be possible. Currently #8 on the DJ Mag Top 100 DJs, Markus has been traveling the world this past year playing his personal brand of ?dark, moody, melodic trance? and meeting as many people as possible.

artist.name: Giuseppe Ottaviani feat. Stephan Pickup
artist.bio: Giuseppe Ottaviani is one half of the well-known italian project: Nu NRG (www.nunrg.it) who have been releasing on Vandit Records , Paul van Dyks renowned label, since 2001. In 2005 Giusseppe Ottaviani started his solo career, and he also began to produce his own tracks, and he continues to tour the world, with his unbelievable live acts.

artist.name: Mr. Pit feat. Vicky Fee
artist.bio: Adrian Ivan aka Mr. Pit discovered electronica back in 1996 and got heavily influenced by the dance scene. As the years passed, his style went along with the trance movement, adding agressive elements and various influences to the sound. In time, the love for music took hold and what followed were countless hours in his studio experimening with sound. In 2003, he has his debut onstage, creating and manipulating live sounds at Romania's premiere electronic music festival TM03BASE.

artist.name: Humate
artist.bio: Humate (real name Gerret Frerichs) is a producer who has released singles with labels such as Yoshitoshi and Prolekult. His work has been featured on many compilations including the Global Underground series and Sasha and John Digweed's Northern Exposure series. Oliver Huntemann and Patrick Kjonberg are former members of Humate.

artist.name: Mr. Pit
artist.bio: Adrian Ivan aka Mr. Pit discovered electronica back in 1996 and got heavily influenced by the dance scene. As the years passed, his style went along with the trance movement, adding agressive elements and various influences to the sound. In time, the love for music took hold and what followed were countless hours in his studio experimening with sound. In 2003, he has his debut onstage, creating and manipulating live sounds at Romania's premiere electronic music festival TM03BASE.

artist.name: Majai
artist.bio: MAJAI – Tetsuo – Monster Tunes – Afterhours FM - Washington, DC  The next Progressive/Trance team from the U.S.A.  Majai is MK and Anna.   The Washington, DC-based DJ and production team soared through 2008 on a wave of recognition which has been steadily building since their first collaboration in 2001. Since then, the duo have DJ’ed alongside great names such as ATB, The Thrillseekers, Sean Tyas, Rank 1, Cosmic Gate, Darude, Kyau & Albert, Gareth Emery, and Lange among many others.

artist.name: Sunlounger feat. Zara
artist.bio: There are two artists with the name Sunlounger: 1. An alias of German producer, electronic composer and DJ Roger Shah, also known as DJ Shah. 2. An earlier incarnation of rock band G.U. Medicine. 1. Roger Shah has released a number of tracks as Sunlounger, such as "White Sand" in 2006 and "Aguas Blancas" in 2007. The first Sunlounger album, "Another Day On The Terrace" was released in 2007, and comprises two CDs, "Chill" and "Dance".

artist.name: OneWorld
artist.bio: Alias of First State

artist.name: Sander van Doorn vs. Robbie Williams
artist.bio: Sander Ketelaars, born on the 28th of February 1979. Sander debuted in DJMag?s prestigious Top 100 poll at a very impressive no.32 in 2006 and then climbing 17 places to no.15 in 2007.  Sander's passion for music already started at a young age. At the age of 16 though, Sander discovered the thru thrill of making music when he played some records for the first time on 2 really bad turntables! This new hobby was to be expanded with producing when he began experimenting with a drum computer at the age of 17.

artist.name: Mirror Music
artist.bio: Mirror Music is the new project comprising of Dave Donaldson and Graeme Reedie. Graeme needs no introduction. As half of Silicone Soul, Graeme has scaled the heights of a DJ career that has lasted for a decade, playing at the world's most incredible parties, even flirting with chart success. Dave is a long-time friend of Silicone Soul. Darkroom Dubs label manager and other half of Silicone Soul, Craig Morrison tells, "We first met Dave when he tracked the vocal session for The Answer and he has since mastered our last 3 albums and the majority of our singles.

artist.name: Ashley Wallbridge feat. Meighan Nealon
artist.bio: Ashley Wallbridge started his career very early on as a DJ. Known as a prodigy for winning some over 18 dj competitions in the UK with fake ID. Ash has been featured on Radio 1 at the tender age of 16 alongside Fergie and Dave Pierce. During this time he also played at Newcastle superclub IKON to over 2500 people. Age has never been a factor for him and 2008 sees him sailing his way into the production world with his first signing to Lyon Echo in NYC followed by the Definitive VOL 1 EP on Auryn Music and CAPTIVE on DBR.

artist.name: In Flagranti
artist.bio: In Flagranti is the duo of Sasha Crnobrnja and Alex Gloor. They both have been in and around various scenes on opposite sites of the globe between New York and Europe. What they share is the simultaneous discovery of the italian cosmic scene from the late 70's early 80's. Both were hooked after hearing some of the mixed tapes in the early 80's, which had this hypnotic blend of electro-disco-afro-rock-funk-dub.

artist.name: Sue
artist.bio: Sue

artist.name: Solarity
artist.bio: SOLARITY are a DJ and Production duo from London spawned in 2008 from the fresh talents of Alfie Granger-Howell and Nick Harriman. Within a few short months of their initial collaboration, a fresh and exciting sound was developed. Their productions have since caused a sensation worldwide, gaining dancefloor and radio play from some of the world's biggest DJs. Support includes Ferry Corsten, Dave Dresden, Jody Wisternoff, Max Graham and Tiësto.

artist.name: The B-52s
artist.bio: The B-52's are an American rock band formed 1976 in Athens, Georgia, United States, the first of many from this college town that has become one of the most important centers in alternative rock. The band formed as Fred Schneider (vocals), Kate Pierson (vocals, organ), Cindy Wilson (vocals, guitar), Ricky Wilson (guitar) and Keith Strickland (drums). After Ricky Wilson died in 1985, Strickland replaced him as a guitarist.

artist.name: KOS
artist.bio: KOS continues his steady rise after an amazing year which saw him deliver a highly acclaimed debut album plus 25 new singles and a tour schedule which took him around the world from opening for Sasha & Digweed at Miami Winter Conference to the Dance Arena at Exit festival where he played after Sven Vath & Francois K.  Touted as ‘The Hottest New Name In Dance Music' (DJ MAG April 2008), The DJ most likely to break through in 2008' by Nic Fanciulli (DJ MAG)...

artist.name: Alan Braxe feat. Killa Kella & Fallon
artist.bio: ?Gonna getcha getcha??A devastatingly potent mix of french house, soul, pop, hip-hop and R&B, scheduled for release in July, this track will stab you in the ears as it makes its way into your head. Starting life as Alan Braxe?s instrumental ?Addicted?, Killa Kela Snoop Dogg/ Neptunes/ Justin Timberlake ] and Fallon add vocals to sublimely fit this genre-warping track. Check out the new video for 'Nightwatcher ' by Alan Braxe featuring Killa Kela & Fallon.

artist.name: Rex The Dog
artist.bio: Rex the Dog (real name: Jake Williams) makes energetic electrohouse. His debut album is due to be released in August 2008 by Cooperative Music. He has remixed tracks by The Knife, Depeche Mode, Client, Mylo, The Prodigy, R

artist.name: Markus Schulz & Departure with Gabriel & Dresden
Markus Schulz feat. Dauby
artist.bio: Markus Schulz is a german progressive trance producer renowned for his unique style of dark, brooding yet melodic productions and DJ sets. He is head of his own label Coldharbour Recordings in co-operation with Armada and he is infamous for surprising his fans with his own edits and reconstructions of well-known songs. He is currently living in Miami, Florida ------------------- Markus Schulz is a man on a mission. He dreams of meeting the world. This dream just might be possible. Currently number 8 on the DJ Mag Top 100 DJ’s Poll and 5th on the TranceAddict.

artist.name: Ronski Speed
artist.bio:
Civic name: Ronny Schneider
 Born: 1975
 East German producer and DJ, Ronski Speed aka Sun Decade, has created some of the most in demand tracks and remixes of the past few years. His records 'E.O.S', 'Iris', '2Day E.P', 'Asarja' together with labe mate Mirco De Govia, the 2005 smasher 'Incognition' with Stoneface & Terminal and the Sun Decade singles 'Follow You' and the groundbreaking 'I'm Alone' were genuine club smashes and were hammered by the likes of Paul van Dyk, Tiësto, Armin van Buuren, Paul Oakenfold, Above & Beyond and Ferry Corsten.

artist.name: Musetta
artist.bio: The careers of Milan, Italy's bass player/dj/producer Matteo Curcio and singer/art director Marinella Mastrosimone converged in 2006 to form Musetta. The duo’s backgrounds are rather different: while Matteo has his roots deep in electronic music, with a love for Kraftwerk and 70’s German cosmic music, but grew up studying jazz, Marinella’s main influences are Italian 70’s prog rock and Indian classical music.

artist.name: Mike Foyle
artist.bio: England based DJ and Producer Mike Foyle has certainly made a name for himself over the last few years as a producer, composer and DJ that you can rely on. From progressive trancer Space Guitar spotted by a certain Markus Schulz and promptly signed up to his Electronic Elements label, to Firefly, third in his piano-trance series which has just dropped on Armind Recordings along with a take-no-prisoners rework from tech trance man-of-the-moment Mark Sherry, this guy delivers anthems like your postman delivers the mail...

artist.name: Dinka
artist.bio:
DINKA is a swiss progressive house act. Stomping house grooves, combined with catchy melodies and spherical harmonies. That's Dinka!  With their 1st three releases over the swiss label "Unreleased Digital" they made it in beatport top 15 progressive charts. Their tracks are played by the biggest DJs all around the globe.  Album Release Dates; (can't post album art here for some reason???) - Pomodorro  The Sin (Dec 1, 2007)
 Chemistry (Mar 14, 2008)
 Temptation (Jan 16, 2008)

artist.name: Mike Saint-Jules
artist.bio: Born on August 12th, 1983, it was Mike's destiny to be a part of the musicalenviorment. Mike has always been listening to music ever since he was but an infant. His father had (and still has) a record collection before he was even born. Gradually listening to the old classics like The Commodores, Gladys Knight & The Pips, etc. Mike slowly began to learn the dancing element of music. Being in the Haitian culture he grew up in, the music played under this culture is always dance music orientated. Not the same genre of Dance as most of you may think, but its a dance style in the Haitian culture.

artist.name: Sunlounger
artist.bio: There are two artists with the name Sunlounger: 1. An alias of German producer, electronic composer and DJ Roger Shah, also known as DJ Shah. 2. An earlier incarnation of rock band G.U. Medicine. 1. Roger Shah has released a number of tracks as Sunlounger, such as "White Sand" in 2006 and "Aguas Blancas" in 2007. The first Sunlounger album, "Another Day On The Terrace" was released in 2007, and comprises two CDs, "Chill" and "Dance".

artist.name: Foundry
artist.bio: FOUNDRY was formed in 1995 in Boston, Massachusetts through a series of advertisements placed in the Boston Phoenix "Guaranteed Gigs" section and through music related pages on the Internet. Within a few weeks, a band of young, talented, technically proficient musicians was formed which would go on to create some of the most energetic rock music to come out of Boston in years. The current band lineup consists of: Allan Stratton (guitar), Jay LaBelle (bass), Matt Dodge (drums), and Steven Carr (vocals).

artist.name: Melodia
artist.bio: Melodia is a trans-atlantic musical duo composed of two sisters, Caitlin and Scotia Gilroy. Melodia's sound was established with the twang of Caitlin's electric guitar and the drone of Scotia's accordion at the core, spun around half-asleep rhythms of xylophone, piano, guitar, banjo and mandolin craziness. It is a project of compiling musical ideas, with Caitlin and Scotia sending recorded songs to each other on 4-track tapes through the mail when they're apart, and playing til their fingers ache when they're together.

artist.name: Sonic Division
artist.bio:
Sonic Division is a project of two electro freestyle music producers from Poland. Damian Politanski (eXtatic) and Maciej Gapys (mAKuSh1no) have been composing this type of music for about five years (since 2002). For sometime they have also experimented with trance, progressive trance and club music.  As of March 2008, they have the following releases:  A) Productions:  1. Painting the Silence E.P. (CD/MP3)  (March 2007)
 2. Painting the Silence (12")  (March 2007)

artist.name: Paul Keeley
artist.bio: Progressive house, deep house, tech house, minimal house, microhouse producer/DJ on the Anjuna / Baroque / EQ Grey / Epsilonlab / Morrison/ Thinner record labels.

artist.name: Energy 52
artist.bio: Energy 52 was a short-lived project from German DJs Kid Paul (aka Paul Schmitz Moorman, aka Paul M) and Cosmic Baby (aka Harald Bluechel).   Back in 1991 they released a couple of tracks, but it is in 1993 that they release their Magnum opus. After hearing Wim Mertens

artist.name: Joop
artist.bio: 1)Joop was born in 1975 in the city of Leeuwarden in The Netherlands. His first contact with the world of vinyl, headphones and turntables was at the tender age of thirteen. Three years later he started spinning the decks at a local club in his hometown on Friday's and Saturday's. Playing in this club Joop fell in love with deejaying, getting to know how to read the crowd and giving them what they want, without losing his own specific sound. This is still his big trademark as a deejay and producer today, which people all over the world acknowledge on the dancefloor.

artist.name: Andy Moor
artist.bio: There is more than one artist with this name:  1) Andy Moor (real name Andrew Beardmore), was born in 1980. DJ/producer/remixer from Stoke On Trent, UK. This is a discography of all releases by his (Sworn, Dub Disorder, Dwight van Mann) and related projects (Indigo, Leama & Moor, Tilt, Whiteroom, Zoo DJ’s) known by me.  This DJ/Producer and musician’s talents were picked up on at 5 years old when he had his first keyboard and instantly started playing songs which he subconsciously knew.

artist.name: Mango
artist.bio:
Mango is a name that has been used more than once:
 (1) A popular Italian singer.
 (2) A pop band from Lithuania.
 (3) A pop punk / ska band from Latvia.
 (4) A progressive house producer and DJ from Moscow, Russia.  ---  Mango (1) is the pseudonym of Giuseppe Mango, an Italian singer, born in the little town of Lagonegro in South-Italy. Mango since many years is one of the favourite artists of the Italian music scene.  ---

artist.name: Tim Royko & KeeMo feat. Cosmo Klein
Nic Chagall
artist.bio: Claus Terhoeven aka Nic Chagall is best know one half of the German trance duo Cosmic Gate, though more recenly has found success as a solo artist, with a number of successful releases on High Contrast Recordings, most notably of which is the highly acclaimed vocal anthem "What You Need".  In his solo guise "Nic" has also remixed a number of other artists tracks, most recently of which is his beautifully techy remix of Filo & Peri's smash hit "Anthem".

artist.name: Robert Babicz
artist.bio:
German techno producer from Cologne,has recorded a number of records as Rob Acid , Acid Warrior and Department of Dance for Force Inc in the nineties. 
 He also had records released by acid and techno labels such as Important and Labworks and at some point had launched his own label too, Junkfood. 
 His most recent output is a blend of minimal and deep tunes with a lot of care taken for the detail.

artist.name: The Asteroids Galaxy Tour
artist.bio: The Asteroids Galaxy Tour are an alternative dance band from Copenhagen, Denmark which formed in 2006. They consist of Mette Lindberg (vocals), Lars Iversen (bass, keyboards), Miloud Carl Sabri (trumpet), Sven Meinild (sax), Mads Brinch Nielsen (guitar, keyboards), Jesper Elnegaard (drums).  The Asteroids Galaxy Tour are musicians on a mission.  Formed less than a year ago, the band and their unique style of psychedelic pop are heading for fame at a speed even they didn?t expect.

artist.name: Setrise feat. Bas van Platen
artist.bio: After being born on the 5th of August 1991, Melle Bakker lived throughout the whole world in which he got in contact with many different styles of music. From Classical, Hip-Hop, Pop, R&B to Trance which he discovered back in the Netherlands. All these styles were to be combined in his own style house which he started in 2006. Gradually Melle started to love melodic House & Trance more and more. In 2007 he started under the artist name Setrise, which stands short for Sunset to Sunrise.

artist.name: Brian Cross
artist.bio: Brian Cross is an accomplished 26 year old Spanish DJ ,a resident DJ for the Amnesia Ibiza Trance World Tour. Brian is also a producer having remixed tracks like Armin van Buuren?s ?Burned With Desire? and Smith & Pledger?s ?Forever?. Sunny Rain and 4U are 2 of his biggest hits.

artist.name: tyDi
artist.bio: When most of us were contemplating which direction to go in life, a 21 years young DJ Producer firmly etched his worth in stone in the wonderful world of electronic dance music in such a way most can dream of in their entire career. Ranked the #1 DJ in Australia, productions signed to the #1 DJ in the world Armin Van Buuren’s record label, Armada and being play listed by artists such as Above & Beyond, Sander Kleinenberg, Andy Moor and Markus Schulz has become all in a days work for Tyson Illingworth.

artist.name: Markus Schulz feat. Carrie Skipper
artist.bio: Markus is renowned for his unique style of dark, brooding yet melodic DJ sets. Markus is infamous for surprising his fans with his reconstructions of well-known songs. His productions include Electronic Elements, Armada, Anjunabeats, Lost Language and many more respected labels.  -------------------  Markus Schulz is a man on a mission. He dreams of meeting the world. This dream just might be possible. Currently #8 on the DJ Mag Top 100 DJs, Markus has been traveling the world this past year playing his personal brand of ?dark, moody, melodic trance? and meeting as many people as possible.

artist.name: Morandi
artist.bio: The Romanian composers Marius Moga and Andrei Ropcea are joining their forces for a major dance project - Morandi. The group's name derives from the first two letters of Moga's name and Ropcea's nickname, Randi, creating Morandi.  Morandi has released 3 albums. Reverse 2005 (the first album), became a really big hit with totally unique sound. The album and the project was kept secret. In Romania the first release "Love me" breaked the tops and people were asking who was the mastermind behind this new sound.

artist.name: Paul Webster pres. JPW
artist.bio: Paul Webster, began DJ?ing 6 years ago, and over the past few years he has established himself on the dance scene in Ireland playing his tough energetic trance style in some of Irelands biggest clubs. He also showcased his sound on Irelands biggest dance music radio station every week on Dublin's 'Club FM for two years having weekly guests on his show supplying guest mixes, DJ's who appeared on his show included Judge Jules, Marco V, Sander Van Doorn among others.

artist.name: Kosmas Epsilon
artist.bio:
Born: May, 1978
 Based: Greece
 Style of Music: Tec-housey, Electrogressive Sounds.  Kosmas Epsilon, born in the small town of Xanthi, in Greece, is considered to be one of the most talented & upcoming producers of the last couple of years. 
 After having his remix of FC Kahuna's ?Hayling? top-charted by James Holden and included in his Balance 005 compilation, things turned out being a lot easier for Kosmas to showcase his productions and Djing skills.

artist.name: Re-Ward
artist.bio:
Biography  Re-Ward a.k.a. Wardt van der Harst, is an 20 (26-12-1988) years young boy from Breda, The Netherlands...   At the age of 11 Wardt heard the track ''Komodo'' by Mauro Picotto, from that on, he wanted to spin and produce trance music.
 He was 14 when he bought his first turntable, and began to practise. At the age of 15 he discovered the software ''Fruityloops v3.0'' which made him very happy, now he could produce his own tracks!

artist.name: Steve Allen & Ben Alonzi vs. Lars Hansem
Guru Josh Project - Infinity (Jerome Isma
artist.bio: The Guru Josh Project got together in 2007 and consist of Guru Josh (Song Writer) Dj DazPerkz (DJ/Producer) and Snakebyte (Producer). They formed the project as three people who have a love for electronic music and old school 90 rave music. Their aim is to bring back the magic of the 90?s dance scene with a fresh and up to date new sound, starting off with Guru Josh's 1990 worldwide smash hit Infinity, the first ever cross over track.

artist.name: Anhken
artist.bio: Petrisor Dima aka Anhken - newcomer on the trance and especially progressive scene. Discovered by John Grant (Above and Beyond), he makes a good entry, by signing his first track "First Division" with Anjunabeats, and that’s really what it got him started. His next productions received good reviews worldwide and he's currently working with other big labels such as: Monster Tunes, Enhanced and Create(Cloud 9) Recordings...

artist.name: Soliquid
artist.bio: Soliquid (David Biczók) in contempt of his young age (21-year-old) has reached huge success all over the world. He is the only one internationally recognized trance producer / remixer / dj next to Shane 54 (Elod Császár) in Hungary. In his own techtrance style he is told to be incomparable. He has been dealing with producing electronic music more seriously since he was 8. He had been learning to play the piano earlier.

artist.name: Gianluca Motta feat. Molly - Not Alone (Martin Roth Nu
Justin Xara feat. Alista Smilga
artist.bio: Justin Xara got interested in electronic music when he was 15.  In 1997 he visited his first massive Strokes Temple rave party and felt its magic atmosphere.    In 1998 Justin Xara starts experimenting with music production, collects vinyl records, trains to play with turntables. His name becomes familiar to Lithuanian clubbers.  In 2005 Justin Xara and Lithuanian producer Art G create CCCP project. The same year Innovate recordings (UK) release their first vinyl record called I want your body.

artist.name: C-Systems
artist.bio: C-Systems were founded in 2005 with both Staro and Akki combining talent. They had already met earlier that year by coincidence, as they both had songs playing at Norwegian commercial radio stations. One day they met up in Akki's studio, and already the first time they made some good melodies together. By 2006, Staro & Akki spent most of their time producing trance music together.  Christian Zechner knew Akki before that time. He and Akki had been cooperating on music for a while. In 2008 he joined the group as he co-produced a song called Guitar Heaven.

artist.name: Agnelli & Nelson pres. A&N Project
artist.bio: Vocal trance project from Agnelli & Nelson.

artist.name: Trentem
artist.bio: Anders Trentem

artist.name: Jon O'Bir
artist.bio: ?This is how trance is meant to be: beautiful bosh that takes you to another place? Mixmag feature February 2003.   A lot can happen in 12 months, for Jon O?Bir, 2002 started off with him mixing in his bedroom like thousands of others dreaming of the big time, but as the hours counted down to 2003 his dream came true and he was warming up the crowd at U.K. super club, Godskitchen. It all started back in September 2002, when he entered a DJ competition for Passion and M8 magazine along with 300 other hopeful DJ?s.

artist.name: Kamui
artist.bio:
"PhoTone Musicproductions" consists of two
 young guys from Stuttgart, south-west Germany.  Dominik Felsmann, born on June 12th 1987 in
 Stuttgart,began his interest in music with
 drumming, soon followed by playing the
 guitar and piano at the age of 6.
 Dominik soon enough discovered the genre of
 electronic music with ?Notator? on the
 ?Atari?, owned by his father and began to
 produce his first tracks. Since then, he
 expanded his studio equipment ten fold, so

artist.name: Daniel Portman
artist.bio:
Daniel Portman was born and raised in the suburbs of Zurich, Switzerland. He fell in love with electronic music at a very young age. It was the late 90s, with all its ups and downs, when young Daniel started to test his musical abilities on an Akai2000 sampler and an old sequencer.
 After a long ride of experimenting, he ended up with a bunch of tracks.  Daniel went back to his small bedroom studio, made another bunch of tracks and along the way he stumbled into the porn industry.

artist.name: First State
artist.bio: First State is a project of two trance producers, Ralph Barendse and Sander van der Waal. Their first album Time Frame was released on the 19th of November 2007. Their songs are often influenced by many genres. 'House, trance, minimal, pop and classical, it's all in there somewhere' as quoted from their album.

artist.name: Andain vs. Fragma
artist.bio: Andain is a San Francisco-based musical group founded in 2002. Group members are Josh Gabriel and David Dresden (producers), Mavie Marcos (vocalist and songwriter) and David Penner (guitarist). The group performs a mix of trance, rock, house and world music. Andain's songs combine live instruments, vocals and electronics.  The group's first release was the single "Summer Calling" in 2002 under Black Hole Records.

artist.name: Moonbeam
artist.bio: The two bothers, Pavel & Vitaliy, formed Moonbeam in 2003 in Nizhny Novgorod (Russia).  2005, they launched their own label - Moonbeam Digital. The label saw them collaborate with some renowned producers such as Jeff Bennett, Joshua Collins, Stephan Hinz, LeRon & Yves Eaux, Clubbervision and others. From here the brothers continued to prove their talent in a board spectrum of sounds through numerous vinyl and digital releases.

artist.name: DJ Eco
artist.bio: Hailed by Martin Roth as "New York's uncut diamond" and a new addition to "the elite league of the upcoming young rebelling producers," the young 20 year-old American DJ, Eco, is no stranger to the electronic dance music scene. Having been influenced by a wide variety of such legendary artists from Scot Project to Sven Vath, Dumonde to Mauro Picotto, among many others, Eco has been producing music since age 14.

artist.name: Lens
artist.bio: Lens is music producer/international FM and Internet radio DJ Ken Spector.   Ken began writing music on the piano when he was 6 years old. His first dance music single release, "Let the Light In", was released on Armada/Coldharbour, and later appeared on Markus Schulz's critically acclaimed Miami '05 CD.  His debut single received massive international radio and DJ support. His follow up single, "Dusk Till Dawn" was also released on Coldharbour, with remixes from Stalker and Alex Stealthy, and the track appeared on Markus Schulz's Ibiza '06 compilation.

artist.name: Marcel Woods
artist.bio: Even though his star is rising exponentially, Dutch ‘bon vivant’ Marcel Woods really knows what it’s like to stay down to earth.  With a respectable list of banging floor fillers to his credit Woods refuses repetition and is on a constant quest for new innovations.  It is because of this attitude that he is in the same league as the greatest trance oriented DJs in the Netherlands.  However, hating the confinement of being tagged, Woods therefore always thinks outside the box, leaving the techno and trance label far behind him.

artist.name: D-Formation - D-4
artist.bio: There are at least two bands with the name D: 1. D is a Japanese visual kei band which formed in March 2003 by ASAGI (vocalist; formerly of JE*REVIENS), Ruiza (guitarist; formerly of Distray, LAYBIAL) and Sin (guitarist; formerly of with sexy, Vasalla). They were all originally members of Syndrome, a band formed on January 16 2000 by Kisaki (formerly of La:Sadie's, Stella Maria and others), but the band had later disbanded in 2002.

artist.name: Andrelli & Blue
artist.bio: The fusion of Andrelli And Adrian Blue is one of the most exciting colabs this year. The progressive sound of Adrian Blue merges into the uplifting sound of Andrelli and we got a storm on the dance floors. The duos first release Imagine featuring the amazing vocalist Hila is one of the hottest release this year, with remixes from Mike Nichol , Ben Gold , Rozza , Six Senses and two exclusive remixes from the duo itself. Above are samples of some of the future releases.

artist.name: BSOD
artist.bio: BSOD stands for Better Sounding on Drugs and is Steve Duda vs. Deadmau5

artist.name: Patrice Baumel
artist.bio: Born in Germany and currently living in Amsterdam, Patrice B

artist.name: Techno Squirrels
artist.bio: TechnoSquirrels is a Los Angeles-based techno collaboration. Both Lisa and Ryan have been active musicians for years, playing in rock bands and making their own techno music.  Lisa grew up in Sweden - a country known for its long winter nights. But where there are long nights, there are long raves and Lisa quickly found herself immersed in Sweden's techno scene in the early 90s. "Fluke and Underworld," says Lisa. "That was my awakening. I instantly traded in my collection of Black Sabbath vinyl for a Korg MS-10 and a Roland 606 drum machine."

artist.name: Armin van Buuren feat. Jennifer Rene
artist.bio: A collaboration between dutch trance producer Armin van Buuren and american singer-songwriter Jennifer Rene. Their lone track to date is "Fine Without You" on Armin's 2008 album Imagine. It is set to be the 4th single from the album.

artist.name: Three Drives
artist.bio: Erik de Koning, alias Enrico, has been producing music for 12 years now and is famous for "WaterVerve" (in some countries also called WaterWave). However, one is probably most impressed by his work under the name of Three Drives (co-productions with Ton TB)."Greece 2000", "Sunset on Ibiza", "Carrera 2" and "Air Traffic" are just a few titles that did very well, especially in the UK.  Erik has produced an enormous amount of tracks but how did it all start? His musical career started in 1990. He used to work, together with his buddy Mark van Dale, at Mid-town records.

artist.name: Meck feat. Dino
artist.bio: Meck is the DJ and recording alias of Craig Dimech, the former head of free2air recordings and now Frenetic Music, one of the UKs most respected labels. Having started his A&R career at Ministry Of Sound imprint Incentive Music,  Craig has been responsible or had a hand in countless Top 10 and Top 20 UK hits and scores of underground sensations which have placed his skills firmly in the epicentre of cool, clubbing culture.

artist.name: Solarscape
artist.bio: Solarscape Music was launched in 2005 by producer Joe Romano. The label's sound ranges from tech-trance to progressive trance, with an emphasis on driving beats and distinct melodies. We have already received great feedback and our first few releases have gained support from top DJ's including: Armin van Buuren, Ronski Speed, Stoneface & Terminal, DJ Precision, Kyau vs Albert, DJ Shah, Les Hemstock and many others. Our current artist projects include "Solarscape" and "Protogen" which you will also find on releases from our partner labels, including some big-name remixes.

artist.name: Groove Garcia
artist.bio: Bio  Groove Garcia is a young dj, musician and producer with more than 15 years of experience and a solid and rising career. He began in the world of music at the early age of 4. He played his first piano concert when he was just 5. Some years later he completed the solfa, piano, harmony and composition studies. Thanks to what he learnt and to an unquestionable talent, Groove Garc?a debuted in publishing with labels like Sushi Productions, Nitro o Cassagrande. Precisely, it was on Cassagrande where he published ?Spanish Guitar? and ?Mainland Spain?, two anthemic tunes which sold more than 4.

artist.name: David West
artist.bio: Although David West might be a new name to many of you he has been around for a very long time. He began his musical journey at the age of 2 when his father, who is a musician himself, put him behind the black and white keys of the piano. David was taught by his father until the age of 6, then it was time for some serious classical training. By the age of 7 David had his first meeting with a synthesizer, and he immediately fell in love with the weird sounds that came out of it.

artist.name: James Harcourt
artist.bio: James Harcourt is chiefly a producer, but more recently the founder of Twisted Frequency recordings and an occasional DJ too. Born in Hitchin, James has always been intensely passionate about music and as a youngster was happiest making voyages to the local record shops to buy music. Inspired constantly by alternative music shows such as The Tube and the Old Grey Whistle Test James was also taught music from a young age.

artist.name: DJ DLG
artist.bio: Arguably, the Ibiza song of the summer, the world awaits the highly anticipated DJ DLG vs. Erick Morillo “Where are you Now” release on Subliminal Records, slated for fall 2008.  With such an early buzz around this song, and his string of hits, DJ DLG is a most sought after producer, remixer, and DJ.  For over six years, DJ DLG has been releasing his unique brand of electro, new wave, disco and big room house music.

artist.name: Holden & Thompson
artist.bio: Holden and Thompson is a collaboration of producer (and DJ) James Holden and singer Julie Thompson.  James Holden is an electronic music artist and DJ who has released numerous singles and remixes on different labels such as Lost Language, Perfecto Recordings, and Positiva Recordings. He currently runs his Border Community record label. He is also one-third of Mainline, which was responsible for the double single of "Narcotic" and "Innerspace". He studied Mathematics at Oxford University and released his first record at age 19.

artist.name: Sensitize
