artist.bio: The first Sensitize was a short lived Workington, UK band who recorded two baggy EPs "Maniac" and "Falling Through" in 1991, playing the Reading Festival the same year before recording a never released album, losing their record deal and breaking up in 1992.  Tom Jurczyszyn was born on February 8th, 1984 in small town called Chelm (near Lublin) in the east Poland. He has been interested in instruments since he was a child.

artist.name: M6
artist.bio: DJ Producer Mark Sixma (aka M6) was born in the Netherlands in â€˜83. Being raised in Breda, the hometown of DJ TiÃ«sto, it was only a matter of time till he caught the trance virus. After mastering the art of DJâ€™ing at high school parties and in local club â€˜De Spockâ€™, Mark got interested in producing music as well.  With a helping hand from his friend Paul Moelands (aka Re:locate) he started to produce his first trance tracks.

artist.name: Andy Blueman
artist.bio: Andrej Komatovic, better known as the music producer Andy Blueman, was born in 1982 in Slovenia, Europe. He discovered trance music in 1997 when buying a CD album called Dream Dance. Since then his interest in trance music has grown very much. Near the end of 2001 Andy finally started to produce his own music, taking inspiration from his older brother, who started producing a year before him.  Until recently...

artist.name: Matt Hardwick feat. Melinda Gareh
artist.bio: Matt Hardwick ,is the epitome of an international DJ. He lives and breathes electronic music. Since his inception into club culture Matt Hardwick has completely immersed himself in it. His rapid ascendency into dance music with the global phenomenon that is Gatecrasher is something which has been well documented. The association with Gatecrasher, the first of many landmark achievements in his career...

artist.name: Talla 2XLC feat. Susana
artist.bio: Talla 2XLC (b. Andreas Tomalla, Germany) is a producer, musician, and DJ whose work has spanned from industrial music to trance music.  Tomalla started as a DJ, founding in 1984 the Technoclub at Frankfurt's Dorian Gray club. He was also at the time involved with a band called Moskwa TV. In 1988, he started a new project called Bigod 20, which would go on to be one of Europe's most successful EBM acts of the early 1990s.

artist.name: Simon Bostock
artist.bio: London based Trance Generation resident DJ Simon Bostock is starting to make big waves in the scene and is a star in the rising with his blend of driving, uplifting and tech trance getting fantastic reviews across London.  2007 was a big year playing at gigs in London at Trance Generation, Vaccine, Turnmills, Electronic Sessions and Wildchild along side DJs such as Kyau & Albert, Stoneface & Terminal, Oliver Smith, Nicklas Harding, Alex Morph & Woody van Eyden. He?s also been a guest DJ on DI.FM, ETN.FM and PureFM internet radio stations.

artist.name: A.M.R.
artist.bio: trance music group edited by origals and remixes of sucessfull dj's and producers such as daniel kandi

artist.name: Armin van Buuren feat. Justine Suissa
Talla 2XLC vs. Carl B feat. Katie Marne
artist.bio: Talla 2XLC (b. Andreas Tomalla, Germany) is a producer, musician, and DJ whose work has spanned from industrial music to trance music.  Tomalla started as a DJ, founding in 1984 the Technoclub at Frankfurt's Dorian Gray club. He was also at the time involved with a band called Moskwa TV. In 1988, he started a new project called Bigod 20, which would go on to be one of Europe's most successful EBM acts of the early 1990s.

artist.name: Passenger 10
artist.bio: Passeger 10 is a house artist, who has released his/her first single on august 22, 2008. It were two songs, Passenger 10 Chris Reece Mix and the Original Mix

artist.name: Armin van Buuren feat. Sharon den Adel vs. Jochen Miller
San Antonio Harbour
artist.bio: Alias of German Electronical Composer and Producer Roger-Pierre Shah. Roger is also releasing under alias' such as Sunlounger and his own main project Roger Shah (as of late 2008 Roger changed his Dj Shah alias into "Roger Shah"). Roger has produced several remixes under this San Antonio Harbour guise, but "Romantic Avenue" is his first single released under this name. www.rogershah.net www.myspace.com/rogerpshah

artist.name: Orjan
artist.bio: Real name is

artist.name: Kerli
artist.bio: Kerli K

artist.name: Pulser
artist.bio: Andy Perring, otherwise known as Pulser, is credited by many as being one of the worlds top producers of trance music. His tracks and remixes have graced the decks of the worlds best clubs and appeared on countless compilations, radio and television shows.   In 1998, Andy teamed up with friend Westy to form 'The Olmec Heads'. Initially a live outfit they secured a deal with German label Colourbox and had a string of releases including 'Lift Off', 'New Skies' and 'Promises', all of which gained big DJ support.

artist.name: Waterspark
artist.bio:
Waterspark, by his real name Daniel Costache, is a new trance producer from Romania. At about the
 age of 12 he came in contact with electronic music through a radio show, thus being charmed by the
 sounds of trance music in particular.  He was introduced to a computer program named Rebirth and... thus sounds started comming into
 his mind. Later inspired by sounds like that of Armin Van Buuren or Ferry Corsten, he made up his

artist.name: Alex Pich & Dmitry Federov
artist.bio: Young Russian producers from St.-Petersburg. Russia

artist.name: Nucvise
artist.bio: Adventure with music started a long time ago when he was only five years old. At that time he got from father a Casio keyboard. It occurred then that small Adam was gifted after his father in the music area. He was so inspired by music that he started learning playing on a harmonica, the guitar (classical and electrical). Thanks to that he learned perfectly the rhythm. When he got his first computer he went deep in the area of sampling, at that time he made his first production of sampling.

artist.name: Jamaster A
artist.bio: 'Jamaster A' is an alias of Hong Kong EDM producer and DJ 'Alex Baboo'. So far, the only release under this alias of his, is 'Bells of Tiananmen', produced and released on the album 'Pop Goes to Dance - MTV Nonstop Hits' in 12 Asian countries in 2003 by EMI. He created a new style of trance which he calls 'oriental trance' for this production. As a single, 'Bells of Tiananmen' was released on 26th December 2005 from the 'Kickin Records' label.

artist.name: Robert Nickson
artist.bio: If you visit a club it probably won't be too long before you are hearing one of Robert's productions. Robert is currently one of the most highly sought after producers of the moment. His productions also appear on nearly every dance CD that hits the shops. There's no escaping this guy, he's here to stay.  Robert's background is a multi-national affair with his Father from England and Mother from Norway.

artist.name: Avenger
artist.bio: There are at least 6 bands of this name: 1) Sanjeewa Chandrasiri, Trance producer based in New Rochelle, New York, signed to Armin Van Buuren's A State Of Trance label 2) Avenger was Heavy/Speed Metal Band from Germany. During 1983-86 they released an Album (Prayers of Steel), an EP and 4 Demos under this name. In 1986 they changed their name to Rage. 3) A NWOBHM band from Newcastle, released "Blood Sports" in 1984, and "Killer Elite" in 1985. They reformed in 2005 under the name Avenger UK.

artist.name: Tom Colontonio
artist.bio: Tom Colontonio has had music flowing through his veins since the age of 11. By age 14 Tom had already moved into the studio as a musician. For years Tom studied all types of musical genres from rock to classical but he soon found his true passion in dance music. In 1996 Tom picked up his first set of turntables and never looked back. Tom spent years as a DJ developing his technique and by late 1998 he was introduced the sound of trance music. Being a native of the Philadelphia region, Tom has played at some of the biggest parties and most prestigious clubs in the region.

artist.name: Viframa
artist.bio:
Real Name:	Francisco Ruiz, Vicente Ruiz, Marcos Ruiz  Viframa was the name created by the producers and brothers Vicente, Francisco and Marcos 
 Ruiz for making music together. With more five years in producing for themselves they 
 decided to released their first work together, this one was the track Viframa - Cristalle. 
 It has been supported by the biggest djs and producers like Paul Oakenfold, Armin Van

artist.name: Mr Sam feat. Cloud 9
artist.bio: Mr Sam was born during the mid seventies just as punk was emerging from beneath the ruins of stadium-rock, he grew up in a small idyllic village near the Belgian border in the north of France.  From an early age, Sam had no escape from his parents own musically mixed cocktails of Giorgio Moroder, Klaus Schulz combined with a dash of Elvis Presley. Through this heavy involuntary dose of electronically initiated influence, he developed an early fascination for squelchy synthesizer sounds and after buying his first Depeche Mode single, he was firmly hooked.

artist.name: Purple Mood
artist.bio: Purple Mood are DJ Shah and DJ Cosmo. As of 2009 they have two singles: One Night In Tokyo, which was released on Anjunabeats in 2007, and was featured on Anjunabeats Volume 5 -- and Chinese Theatre which was released on Shah Music in 2008, and was featured on Armin Van Buurens Radio Top 15 in October.

artist.name: Algarve vs. Cold Blue
artist.bio: Algarve is a progressive/trance DJ/Producer from Sweden.  His real name is Ludvig Holm.  He has worked closely with Selu Vibra and Sebastian Brandt.  He currently has releases on Supra Recordings, Armada Music, and Somatic Sense.  He is known for his single "Seashore".

artist.name: Reminder feat. Alynn Carter
artist.bio: Chicago underground jazz/electronica/beat fusion with yummy vibrations. Reminder is the solo outing of Chicago scene staple Josh Abrams, whose bass playing has held the groove for many artists over the past ten years. A departure from the avant and jazz roots of his Town & County and Sticks & Stones projects, Abrams takes a cue from his residency as a member of Prefuse 73's backing band (if you've seen Prefuse live and felt your body vibrate, it was more than likely thanks to Josh's bass).

artist.name: Activa
artist.bio: In a relatively short time since his first release on Somatic Sense, Rob Stevenson, better known as Activa, has been one of the most hard working producers in the Trance genre. He has created many new alias’ such as Solar Movement, Mekk, Substate, Force One, Aira Force, CMR and Eluna to showcase the range of his production skills, while continuously developing the sound of his main Activa alias.

artist.name: Filo & Peri feat. Eric Lumiere
artist.bio: FIL0 & PERI BIOGRAPHY:  Five short years; that?s the short span of time it has taken New Yorkers Filo & Peri to go from newborn duo to international DJ/producer superstars. In the highly competitive world of DJing, that?s a tremendous feat in itself!  Then when you figure into their resume consecutive listings in the prestigious DJ Mag Top 100 DJs Poll, signings to Armin van Buuren and Paul Van Dyks?s recording labels, both a Billboard Number 1 and UK Top 40 hit...

artist.name: Paul Miller
artist.bio: Paul Miller's real name is Pawel Meller. He was born on 12 march 1985 in Thorn, where he lives today. Paul Miller is an artist already known on worldwide dance music market. Thanks to cooperation with such artists like Manuel Le Saux (single "Sunny Day" and EnTrance 2008 anthem), Aly & Fila (massive support, tracks "Galaxy" and "Memories Of Love" in their label, Offshore, coming up in 2008), Jon O'Bir ("Crystal Source" release in Conspiracy), John Askew (a start of cooperation with Discover Records) Paul entered a circle of top dj's/producers.

artist.name: Lustral
artist.bio: Ricky Simmonds and Stephen Jones form the backbone of Lustral. Together, they have also been the driving force behind major acts such as Chakra, The Space Brothers, Oxygen, The Realm, Kaleidoscope, Force Majeure and Ascension (they also had two releases under the moniker Essence).  Over the last decade they have released over 50 singles with independent and major labels including Manifesto, Virgin, Zomba, Perfecto, MCA, Ministry Of Sound, 3Beat Breaks, Hooj Choons, East West, Platipus, Ultra, Media, Sony, AM:PM, Cheeky, ZTT, Captivating Sounds, Additive, Xtravaganza, Boss and Warner Brothers.

artist.name: Virtual Vault
artist.bio: A new name in the world of Trance Music: Virtual Vault   Their first release Request is already supported by the top trance DJ's around the globe. Ben Huijbregts and Carlos Sun Juan teamed up as Virtual Vault (also known as Trebbiano).   They have know each other for years already, and during their regular beer drinking and durum eating nights they started producing trancier stuff.   Under the motto: "The more beers we drink, the better the tracks get"...

artist.name: Chakra
artist.bio: There are at least five artists by the name of Chakra:  1) Progressive rock band from Huntington Beach, CA, USA, who released one album (independently) in 1979.  2) Producers Stephen Jones & Rick Simmonds, who peaked around 10 years ago producing many trance tracks. One of their greatest productions, 'Love shines through', was relaunched in 2006 under the label Captivating Sounds.  3) A Korean Pop group consisting of four ladies: Im Sun Hong, Hwang Bo Hye Jung, Jung Yeo Won and Lee Kyung Eun (see picture; names not necessarily in corresponding order).

artist.name: David Forbes
artist.bio: For all info on David Forbes check out www.davidforbes.com www.myspace.com/davidforbescom

artist.name: Signalrunners feat. Julie Thompson
artist.bio: Signalrunners started as a trans-Atlantic trance project in 2003 with members Alan Nimmo (Scotland) and Andrew Bayer (USA). Alan Nimmo, an experienced DJ and producer has been DJing since the tender age of 12 and has DJed in most of Scotlands top venues. His passion for dance music started with DJing in the UK Rave scene in the early nineties and evolved to Trance as music styles progressed in the UK.

artist.name: Dave202
artist.bio:
Dave202 (real name: Davide Tropeano) is a swiss Trance DJ.  He published his first own production in May 1998. It was the Latenight Compilation Vol. 1 of Oxa Club, where he has been a resident for the last couple years.  And then in summer his career really started to take off.
 Dave202 was the main man at the Streetparade 2000. He mixed the official Streetparade Compilation "Believe in Love". Dave produced the title song (the accompanying red-hot videoclip was a smash hit all summer long, by the

artist.name: Bissen
artist.bio: Georg Bissen is a German national living in New York. He has written and collaborated on well over a thousand pieces of music and projects in his still brief professional music career. Bissen got his start in the music business six years ago, when he began working in New York City as a composer and engineer in the music for advertising industry. He formed his own music production company MetaTechnik soon after, which now boasts two offices in New York and Los Angeles.

artist.name: Orjan Nilsen
artist.bio: Ørjan Nilsen, born the 14th of June 1982 in a place called Kirkenes in Norway, started his interest in music at a VERY early age. He started banging on drum sets at the age of 1 and was thoroughly instructed by his father and brother for the first 9 years of his life.  At the age of 7, Ørjan got his first keyboard, and started to practice on it every single day for the next couple of years, but started to think this little keyboard lacked what he was looking for... And then it began...

artist.name: Ian Brown
artist.bio: Ian Brown (born February 20th 1963 in Warrington, England) was the lead singer in former British band The Stone Roses and following their split in 1996 has gone on to have a successful solo career releasing a total of five studio albums, with one greatest hits compilation, and remixes disc. With each new release in his solo career each one shows him developing as an artist. He is considered to be an influential artist with followers such as Oasis, The Verve, Blur, Kasabian, Arctic Monkeys and many more. He has had twelve UK top 40 singles and has sold over 9 million albums as a solo artist.

artist.name: Richard Durand
artist.bio: Without doubt the hottest new trance DJ / producer to emerge from Holland this past year is Richard Durand. Recommended by the mighty Tiësto as his 'Tip For The Top in 2007' in DJ Magazine a year ago, Richard has responded with a string of stunning productions and remixes in recent months, including official reworks of Tiësto's 'Lethal Industry', 'Flight 643' and 'Break My Fall', plus a DJ diary that has exploded due to demand from high profile shows and festival appearances...

artist.name: Sander Kleinenberg
artist.bio: Sander Kleinenberg is a Dutch DJ and producer. Born in Delft in 1971, he started DJing in his early teens playing at local bars. After getting his start in production in 1996, some of the biggest DJs in the world, including Sasha, Deep Dish, and Max Graham have used his tracks on their mix compilations. "My Lexicon" and "Sacred" are examples of his trancier production work, while "The Fruit" and "Work To Do" are examples of a more funk-tinged house. His most recent compilations fall under the "Everybody" moniker, and reflect the style of DJing that he is playing out at the time.

artist.name: Kaskade
artist.bio: Kaskade is the stage name for Ryan Raddon, a DJ/producer/remixer/artist who was born in Chicago, Illinois in 1972, raised in Salt Lake City, Utah as a teen, and now calls San Francisco, California home.  Prior to being a recording artist, he was a record store owner and a club DJ at a nightclub in Salt Lake City as a way to make ends meet for him and his wife. After he and his wife moved to San Francisco he landed a job as a A&R man at OM records, where in addition to reviewing demos for the label he also submitted his own material, which would pay off big time for him.

artist.name: Tatana & Andrew Bennett feat. Tiff Lacey
Filterheadz vs. Prydz
artist.bio: Here?s a story about two brothers. The Wilmaers brothers. Kids of the seventies. Both having the ball of their lives when vinyl was king and 8 track tapes were creating history. Then, mid-eighties arrived. The brothers grew up. They got influenced immensely by The Police, U2 and Simple Minds. With the older brother on the guitar and kid brother on the drums, they formed a band with few close allies, all felt strongly destined to become rock stars of the future.

artist.name: Funkagenda vs. Santiago & Bushido
artist.bio:
If you havent heard of Funkagenda by now then where have you been hiding?
 Over the last 18 months, Groovedigitals in-house engineer has become a name synonymous with quality house music.
 Already having featured on labels as prominent as SUBLIMINAL, POSITIVA, BIG LOVE and TOOLROOM, his production and remix skills are highly sought after worldwide.
 In fact he is now fixed firmly in the 24 Management stable, home to NIC FANCIULLI, STEVE MAC, SEB FONTAINE and CHRIS LAKE amongst others  And production is not the only string in his bow.

artist.name: Substate
artist.bio: Substate is a collaboration between Rob Stevenson, the UK uplifting trance producer (better known as Activa), and Chris & Matt Kidd brothers. In 2006 they made a great single called 'Horizon' released on Liquid Recordings with Mac Zimms remix. Later on, singles 'Release' and 'The Following' were released on Joyride and Reload Music correspondingly.

artist.name: L.S.G.
artist.bio: There are multiple artists with this name: 1) L.S.G. is one of many aliases of Frankfurt artist and producer Oliver Lieb. Under the L.S.G. alias he released many singles (such as Blueprint and Netherworld) and albums (including Volume 2, Into Deep and The Hive) albums. In 2005 Lieb ended his L.S.G. 'project' and now produces minimal techno under the Solieb alias. 2) L.S.G. is a hip-hop/rap crew from Switzerland.

artist.name: Giuseppe Ottaviani
artist.bio: Giuseppe Ottaviani is one half of the well-known italian project: Nu NRG (www.nunrg.it) who have been releasing on Vandit Records , Paul van Dyks renowned label, since 2001. In 2005 Giusseppe Ottaviani started his solo career, and he also began to produce his own tracks, and he continues to tour the world, with his unbelievable live acts.

artist.name: DJ Tatana
artist.bio:
Tatana (Tatana Sterba, born 7th October 1976 in former Czechoslovakia) is a swiss Trance producer and dj.
 Tatana is one of the most successful artists of the 2000s in the Swiss charts, with several successful trance albums since her debut album 24 Carat was released in February 2000.  After having the adorable voice of Jael (Lunik, Delerium, Mich Gerber) singing on her last years smash hit 'Always on my mind', Tatana chose to collaborate for her new single 'All that I feel' with another star of the Swiss music scene.

artist.name: Emilio Fernandez
artist.bio: When a friendship spawned by a mutual passion, combined with over 15 years of industry experience, develops into a music production partnership, you can guarantee that when both talents collide, the resulting productions will be devastating. This is no exception. Emilio Fernandez is a breath of fresh air in today’s stagnating and over saturated dance scene.  The joint efforts of Andy Duguid and Iwan de Kuijper...

artist.name: Utah Saints
artist.bio: Utah Saints are a British dance band from Leeds in West Yorkshire. The music is produced by Jez Willis and Tim Garbutt, who are joined on-stage by other musicians whenever the band plays live. Utah Saints were one of the early pioneers of bringing sampling technology into mainstream dance and pop music, and have also gained a certain notoriety for the long gap between releases - their follow-up, Two, came seven years after their debut.

artist.name: Andy Duguid feat. Leah
artist.bio: Andy Duguid is a producer from Aberdeen, Scotland, who has a very bright future ahead of him. After making his mark with his debut single ‘Hypocrisy’ and some strong remixes, he really hit the big time with this track, ‘Don’t Belong’. Landing a prime position on In Search Of Sunrise 6, compiled and mixed of course by a certain Tijs Verwest, it has already had a release on the samplers of said album. Now it has a full release on Black Hole Recordings complete with a clubbier mix from Tiësto protégée Phynn.

artist.name: Ultimate
artist.bio: Disco group Ultimate was the brainchild of producers Giuliano Salerni (Juliano Salerni) and Bruce Weeden. They also produced the excellent "Score" for Carol ...

artist.name: Star Industry
artist.bio: This Belgian gothic orientated rockband saw the light of day somewhere in 1996.   The year after that they entered the studio to come out of it with the first CD ?Iron Dust Crush?. Immediately they gained a lot of positive response in the press all over Europe. This resulted in their first festivalgigs in Germany, Belgium and the UK.   The song Nineties topped the alternative charts in Israel and is even now still a dancefloorfiller in alternative clubs.

artist.name: Digital Nature
artist.bio: BIOGRAPHY  Iulian Cuculea is the man behind the Digital nature guise. Listening to electronic dance music most of his childhood, he decided to start making his own beats late 2005. To get right to the point he is now working with top labels such as: VANDIT, SPINNIN' RECORDS, DISCOVER RECORDS, MONSTER TUNES, HIGH CONTRAST, ALTER EGO RECORDS, BONZAI / CAMOUFLAGE and many more. His productions find their way into all top DJ?s record box, getting massive support from the likes of: Paul van Dyk...

artist.name: Sylvia Tosun
artist.bio: Sylvia is a music goddess. Her luscious voice, and sparkling presence scream out star! Her voice is hypnotic. She is beautiful, born to stand out... check her out at sylviatosun.com

artist.name: Dan Stone
artist.bio: Dan has been a regular dj on the club circuit for 10 years, but its only the last 2 years that he has established himself as one of the UK's up and coming producers.  His first solo single 'Tauro' (released in April 2005), soon gained worldwide recognition and stamped his named firmly on the trance circuit, getting plays from Armin Van Buuren & Paul Van Dyk and also reaching no.9 in the World DMC trance charts.

artist.name: iiO
artist.bio: iiO (sometimes written as IIO, pronounced "eye-oh") is a New York City based house music act consisting of producer/songwriter Markus Moser and singer/songwriter Nadia Ali. iiO are best known for their 2001 hit "Rapture (Tastes So Sweet)". The name iiO is derived from the Sony PC laptop model VAIO, on which the duo was creating much of their early work, and the duo was in fact first known as Vaiio.

artist.name: Leon Bolier feat. Simon Binkenborn
artist.bio:
Leon Bolier was born in 1980 somewhere in the middle of Holland, and always was in love with moody music.
 When he heard Energy 52's Cafe Del Mar he fell in love with melodic trance, and quit producing hardcore house.
 In 2002 and 2003 he got his first record deals, together with his brother Bart. They released some tracks on Bonzai/Banshee and FTM sublabels. Back then the first contacts with Armada frontman Maykel Piron were established via Armin van Buuren, and this resulted in Leon remixing the first ever Armada release.

artist.name: Filterheadz vs. Eric Prydz
artist.bio: Here?s a story about two brothers. The Wilmaers brothers. Kids of the seventies. Both having the ball of their lives when vinyl was king and 8 track tapes were creating history. Then, mid-eighties arrived. The brothers grew up. They got influenced immensely by The Police, U2 and Simple Minds. With the older brother on the guitar and kid brother on the drums, they formed a band with few close allies, all felt strongly destined to become rock stars of the future.

artist.name: Sphinx vs. Plexland
artist.bio:
There are four bands with name Sphinx.  1) Spanish metal band formed officially in 1994.  They have a very personal style with influences of the classic spanish metal, but they have introduced power metal elements, developing a faster and more modern style.  
 2) A hardcore producer from Enschede, the Netherlands.  He has also produces some hardstyle, industrial and the so-called "teringherrie". His songs "Sell me your soul" and "Survivors of judgement day" are well-known in the hardcore scene of Twente, especially around the Dommelstreet.

artist.name: Embrace
artist.bio:
There is more than one artist with this name:  1) A 5 piece band from Leeds, England
 2) Emo band from Washington feat. Ian Mckaye
 3) Dutch Trance duo  1) Embrace are a 5 piece band from Brighouse, West Yorkshire, in England who released their fifth studio album album "This New Day" on the 27th of March 2006. They were also chosen to record the official England World Cup song. The band consist of brothers singer Danny McNamara and guitarist Richard McNamara, bassist Steve Firth, keyboardist Mickey Dale, and drummer Mike Heaton.

artist.name: DJ Shah feat. Adrina Thorpe
artist.bio: Short: Collaboration between German Electronical Composer, producer & Dj Roger-Pierre Shah (Roger Shah, formerly DJ Shah) and American Singer / Songwriter and Pianist, Adrina Thorpe. Together they have produced two tracks so far (as of March 2008) - a progressive vocal trance song called 'Who Will Find Me' and the late 2008 single 'Back to You', released on Shah's own label Magic Island Records.

artist.name: Jochen Miller vs. Armin van Buuren feat. Sharon den Adel
artist.bio: Jochen van der Steijn was born in The Netherlands in a city called Mill. He started his career as DJ Jochen, which he changed to Jochen Miller in 2003. In his early teen days Jochen was lucky, cause of his father having a disco, he could practise his mixing skills. This is probably one of the reasons he won the Dutch Mixing Championships at Dance Valley in 1999, where he had advantage over the rest for spinning three turntables.

artist.name: Paul van Dyk
artist.bio: Grammy nominated artist and globally acclaimed DJ and Producer Paul van Dyk continues to dominate the electronic music charts and appears at the pinnacle of every Top DJ list across the globe. His fifth original album In Between was released August 2007 and features collaborations with David Byrne and Jessica Sutta of the Pussycat Dolls.  PvD is renowned as one of the hardest working artists, with sold-out tours that cross each continent, headline spots at every major festival, and a hugely successful recording career.

artist.name: Evol Waves
artist.bio: Evol Waves, real name Gigi Bezhanishvili was born 18th of October 1986 in Tbilisi, Republic of Georgia. He is a student in Georgian University, studying on the business economy specialty.  In 20 years of age (2006) he started creating electronic/club music. also learned DJing by himself when he was 18. Evol Waves had several gigs in the cities of Georgia, also in the most popular clubs in Tbilisi.

artist.name: Paul van Dyk feat. Ashley Tomberlin
EnMass
artist.bio:
We are now under a new name:  Randy Boyer & Eric Tadla.  Please visit our myspace pages: myspace.com/randyboyer and myspace.com/erictadla
 for the latest blogs, newest choons, and the link to our website.  ericTadla

artist.name: Sultan & Ned Shepard vs. Coca & Villa vs. David Forbes meets Michael Paterson
Filterheadz
artist.bio: Here?s a story about two brothers. The Wilmaers brothers. Kids of the seventies. Both having the ball of their lives when vinyl was king and 8 track tapes were creating history. Then, mid-eighties arrived. The brothers grew up. They got influenced immensely by The Police, U2 and Simple Minds. With the older brother on the guitar and kid brother on the drums, they formed a band with few close allies, all felt strongly destined to become rock stars of the future.

artist.name: Bryan Kearney
artist.bio: Bryan Kearney began DJing when he was 19 years old and in this time has established himself firmly on the dance scene in Ireland. His sets contain the very best in upfront trance and techno with the emphasis always on energy and the unexpected.  He was a permanent fixture on the airwaves of Dublin throughout 2002 and 2003 with prime time shows on Energy Fm and Kiss Fm providing the capital with the very best in brand new material each week.

artist.name: Armin van Buuren feat. Sharon den Adel
artist.bio: A collaboration between the Dutch DJ and trance producer Armin van Buuren and Sharon den Adel who is the vocalist of the Dutch symphonic rock band Within Temptation.

artist.name: Nature One Inc.
artist.bio: Nature One is a Festival of electronic dance music. It´s alwasy on the first weekend in august at Raketenbasis Pydna bei Hasselbach near Kastellaun im Hunsrück (Germany). Nuclear Weapons were stored there in the years 1983 - 1989. The Nature One Inc. brings every year a hymn for the event. Its the biggest open air festival in europe für electronic music. http://www.nature-one.de Project name for the official hymns of the famous gig Nature One, which were produced by the following varying House & Hard Trance producer teams:

artist.name: Joint Operations Centre
artist.bio: An alias of trance music producer John O'Callaghan.

artist.name: Chicane vs. Natasha Bedingfield
artist.bio: Chicane is a pseudonym used by UK-based electronical composer, musician and producer Nicholas Bracegirdle. He was born on 28 February 1971, in London, England. Chicane is known for the single Offshore, an Ibiza anthem included in thousands of compilations in both chill-out and dance form; Saltwater, which featured vocals by Clannad member M

artist.name: Josh Gabriel
artist.bio: One half of the Progressive trance and Electronica duo know as Gabriel & Dresden which is no longer. They have broken up, and currently each member is creating on his own.

artist.name: Jon O'Bir feat. Solar Movement
artist.bio: ?This is how trance is meant to be: beautiful bosh that takes you to another place? Mixmag feature February 2003.   A lot can happen in 12 months, for Jon O?Bir, 2002 started off with him mixing in his bedroom like thousands of others dreaming of the big time, but as the hours counted down to 2003 his dream came true and he was warming up the crowd at U.K. super club, Godskitchen. It all started back in September 2002, when he entered a DJ competition for Passion and M8 magazine along with 300 other hopeful DJ?s.

artist.name: Andy Tau
artist.bio: Andy Tau is the production alias of Andy MacDougall, a Scottish born producer and dj now based in London. Andy originally became interested in trance over 15 years ago and followed the sound, frequenting some of the most iconic clubs and hearing some of the best djs in the world through the peak of trance towards the end of the 90's. Iinspired by the music, the djs and the clubs It was around this time that he initially started producing. It wasn't until late in 2007 that Andy signed his first track with Bonzai, which was released on their sub label Progrez.

artist.name: Jochen Miller vs. Sander van Doorn
artist.bio: Jochen van der Steijn was born in The Netherlands in a city called Mill. He started his career as DJ Jochen, which he changed to Jochen Miller in 2003. In his early teen days Jochen was lucky, cause of his father having a disco, he could practise his mixing skills. This is probably one of the reasons he won the Dutch Mixing Championships at Dance Valley in 1999, where he had advantage over the rest for spinning three turntables.

artist.name: Exposure
artist.bio: Exposure, also known as M.I.K.E..

artist.name: Sindre Eide
artist.bio:
Sindre Eide is a new and young artist coming from the cold norths of Norway.
 Born the 13th of June in 1991. Not so long after , he discovered EDM-dance music around year 2001. After a long pursuit of trance and progressive knowledge, Sindre finally started to produce trance-music in 2005.  At the tender age of 15, he signed his first deal. Not long after, a deal with world-known Enhanced Recordings appeared and Sindre stepped into the trance-scene quicker than imagined. With a progressive sound with uplifting elements, Sindre is ready to capture listeners with his sound.

artist.name: LavKastor
artist.bio: 18 year old producer from a small city Belzyce in eastern Poland whose got something to prove, already produced a couple of tracks with Enyo Giove, his remix of Storm - CJ Stone was featured in the CDS.

artist.name: Ernesto vs. Bastian
artist.bio: Luck played its part to form this great and remarkable act; remarkable because of their track record so far, with hit single after hit single from the very start of their musical career. Apart from Dark Side of the Moon, these guys had you dancing on the tables at Bora Bora with their smash hit Ibeatza - then under the alias Poisoncub. Ibeatza shot up in the UK-charts - with good reason. Within a year of that chance meeting, Ernesto vs.

artist.name: Temple One
artist.bio: Temple One aka Joe Garrett was born on the 24th October 1986 in the south of england. From since Joe can remember, music has always been an interest to him but it wasn't untill around the 98-99 period where Joe really took to the sound of 'Trance'.  Fasicnated by the sound and melodys, Joe began to collect and listen to all the trance he could get hold of.. and was especially inspired by the 'Gatecrasher' compilations.

artist.name: Darren Tate
artist.bio: There are two artists called Darren Tate, A DJ/Producer from London, and an ambient/drone artist, also from the UK. 1. UK DJ / Producer Darren Tate is an international producer and DJ born in London, England. As a classically trained musician, Darren has earned his reputation as one of Europe's leading producers, having worked with a wide range of international artists and writers. He is also one of the worlds most successful dance producers, having had huge international hits with the likes of Jurgen Vries, Angelic, Orion, Citizen Caned and most recently DT8 Project.

artist.name: Rex Mundi
artist.bio: There are about three bands with the name "Rex Mundi." Or King of the World, translated in Latin.   (1. Dj/Producer Rex Mundi (2. French Black Metal act (3. Thrash/Progressive band from Greece  (1. Rex Mundi  Boy Hagemann started producing music on his computer while his friends practiced in local rock bands. He was fascinated about the sounds that could be created using just a computer, He sometimes skipped college to have fun with his music.

artist.name: Slava Flash
artist.bio: Slava has already been a Dj for 18 years. He played as Lounge-Jazzy-Deep overtures in chamber bar-clubs, as also Techno-Trance at large raves. Nowadays he chooses HOUSE in all its manifestations as his main style. He is the participator of different actions and parties in Ukraine, Russia, France, of the popular rave-festival Tochka Sborki. So, step by step: 1992 Dj Slava Flash appears on the Kharkovs club-scene as the resident of the most advanced at that time Meridian-club.

artist.name: Ehren Stowers
artist.bio: Ehren Stowers is Dj and producer from Great Britain.

artist.name: Underworld
artist.bio: Hailing from Romford, UK Karl Hyde and Rick Smith started out in 1983 as members of quirky new-wave pop band Freur. Freur became Underworld in 1986 and in 1988 the band struck chart success with single Underneath The Radar. This initial lineup consisted of Hyde, Smith, Alfie Thomas, Bryn Burrows, Baz Allen and Pascal Consoli before sinking back into obscurity and disbanding in 1990. British DJ Darren Emerson hooked up with Hyde and Smith in 1992 and helped them refine their sound into something more sleek and beat-oriented...

artist.name: Gareth Emery
artist.bio: Ranked at number 23 in the world in the 2008 DJ Mag Top 100 Poll (up 8 places from 2007) and tipped by both Paul van Dyk and Ferry Corsten as a future star, Gareth Emery is well on his way to becoming a fully paid up member of the global DJ elite. His podcast (The Gareth Emery Podcast) has fans all around the world and is regarded as one of the most consistent and exciting podcasts around. In 2009, Gareth Emery launched his own label - Garuda and has released tracks such as Exposure, Metropolis etc.

artist.name: Freemasons
artist.bio: The Freemasons are a dance / house / electronica production team from England. The act consists of DJ/Producer/composer/remixers Russell Small and James Wiltshire. The duo have become one of the most successful dance acts in the UK thanks to their remixes of major artists like Beyonce and Faith Evans as well as their own productions for which they have earned three 20 top hits. In 2005 the duo transformed Jackie Moore's 1979 #1 Billboard Hot Dance Music/Club Play track "This Time Baby" and...

artist.name: Aurosonic
artist.bio:
'Aurosonic' is a trance music project of four Russian producers: Evgeniy Smirnov (JVS), Sergey Klimov, Natalya Buzurnaya (DJ Nataly), and Dmitry Chernikova (Chera). The first release of this project was their remix of Tenthu's 'Dark Horizon', which was released on 28th February 2006 under the 'Flux Delux Digital (UK)' label. Their other releases so far are:  1. Hawaii  (2006)
 2. Memories  (2006)
 3. Missing You/Gemini EP  (2006)
 4. Underwater  (2006)
 5. Rainbow EP  (2007).

artist.name: ATB
artist.bio: André Tanneberger aka ATB (born February 26, 1973 in Freiberg, Saxony, Germany) is a DJ, musician, and producer of trance and dance music. Among his most famous songs is "9pm (Till I Come)", which topped the charts in the United Kingdom in 1999 and is widely regarded as the UK's first Trance number one. The track features a guitar riff which became hugely popular. This guitar sound, which he accidentally found while experimenting with a new producing deck, became the trademark of his early hits. ATB continues to evolve and change with every album.

artist.name: Armin van Buuren & DJ Shah feat. Chris Jones
Cressida
artist.bio: There are currently two artists known as Cressida: 1. A British progressive rock group formed in 1969, best known for a mellow, symphonic sound and heavy use of the Mellotron keyboard. They released two great LPs titled Cressida (1970) and Asylum (1971). 2. An electronic dance producer/DJ duo from Munich, Germany comprised of Matthias Baumann & Roland Geringer, with tracks appearing on labels such as AVA Recordings and Euphonic. They have also been known to produce under the name of Callisto.

artist.name: Cosmic Gate
artist.bio: Cosmic Gate is a German trance, progressive trance and hard trance duo made up of Claus Terhoeven (aka Nic Chagall) and Stefan Bossems (DJ Bossi). They are best known for their singles "Exploration of Space", "The Drums", and "The Truth." Cosmic Gate has done remixes for popular DJs including Dj Tiesto, Armin van Buuren, and Ferry Corsten. Cosmic Gate's heavy, analogue trance sound is considered by many to be the definition of hard trance. Discography Albums: * Rhythm & Drums (2001) * No More Sleep (2002)

artist.name: Inertia
artist.bio:
INERTIA (1) and the most important one is an alias of trance producer duo John O'Callaghan and Neal Scarborough.
 They are known to have released three tracks: The Emerald (2004), The Chamber (2005), The System(2008) all of them released at Discover Label. Another LP was released in 2006 at Discover Digital, having as side A Inertia - The Chamber (Activa Remix), and side B Askew & O'Callaghan - Game Over (Ian Betts Mix). The System was remixed by many uplifting trance artists such as Sean Tyas, Tom Colontonio and Thomas Bronzwaer.

artist.name: Orkidea
artist.bio: Orkidea (real name Tapio Hakanen) is the most well-renowned Finnish DJ. His albums to date are; 'Metaverse', 'Taika - Selected Works 98-03', 'A place called happiness', and 'Music speaks in thousand languages' (check out also DJ Orkidea and Dj Orkidea group and the Orkidea Wiki Page )

artist.name: Dazzle
artist.bio: Dazzle is a dj/producer who recently again proved to hold a firm position in the Dutch dance scene with the release of ‘FFWD 2007-The Album’ and tracks like ‘Continuous’, ‘Backwards’ and ‘Area 51’. Besides four releases in the Freedom-series with Black Hole Recordings Dazzle also released Soundbox, Maxim, Forward and the two official albums of FFWD Dance Parade 2006 & 2007. From the first Freedom on his sound has developed into the style of music he plays nowadays: very rhythmic and energetic electro-trance.

artist.name: Lange
artist.bio: An innovator of the trance sound that exploded in '98, Lange is universally recognised as one of the scene's strongest and most-consistent producers. His first major success was his remix of DJ Sakin's 'Protect Your Mind', swiftly followed by his famous Lost Witness – ‘Happiness Happening’ mix which also entered the UK Top 20. www.lange-music.com

artist.name: Glenn Morrison
artist.bio: Glenn Morrison has undoubtedly been gaining international recognition for his skills in the DJ booth. He formerly worked at Release Records for the better part of four and some odd years, and it aided in his development as a DJ, giving way for a fuller understanding of the music. Glenn has been instrumental in contributing to the success of several record labels in Europe through his A&R work, namely, Twisted Frequency in the UK, Babylon Records in France, and DK Records in Holland. In accordance to this, Glenn started/owns Morrison Recordings.

artist.name: Andrew Bennett vs. Tatana feat. Tiff Lacey
artist.bio: Andrew Bennett is one of the most talked about up-and-coming artists on the dance scene at the moment. Over the past two years he has released various tracks and remixes, which have received world wide recognition and praise. But Andrew Bennett is anything but a newcomer on the scene: he has been spinning the decks since 1996, he is a resident DJ at the acclaimed ?Trance Nation? events and has secured regular DJ slots both in and outside of Germany, like in world-renowned clubs as ?Space? on Ibiza as well at the biggest events and festivals.

artist.name: Solarstone
artist.bio:
Producer
 Solar Stone is a UK based producer Rich Mowatt(formely with Sam Tierney & Andy Bury) who is responsible for some of the trance scene's most defining moments. Solarstone are firmly supported by every trance and progressive dj worth mentioning since the first Solarstone single 'The Calling' way back in 1997. "SolarStone means 100% quality and consistently evolving the genre" (Dj Orkidea, 2008)  DJ

artist.name: Active Sight
artist.bio: Active Sight is a successful artist collaboration between (Dirk) Mike "M.I.K.E." Dierickx and Fr

artist.name: Timbaland feat. OneRepublic
artist.bio: Timbaland (born Timothy Z. Mosley in Norfolk, Virginia on March 10, 1972) is a hip hop and R&B record producer and rapper, whose style of production and arranging was very influential in both genres of music during and after the mid-1990s. With partner Magoo, he is a member of hip-hop group Timbaland & Magoo.  Timbaland is similar to producers such as Phil Spector, Brian Eno, or Norman Whitfield in that he helped to redefine the sound of an entire genre of music with an immediately recognizable production style.

artist.name: Paul Trainer
artist.bio: Paul has always had a passion for music at an early age, but it wasn't until 2001 that he bought himself his first set of decks after coming back inspired and influenced from the sounds of the Miami WMC. Being a keen clubber himself, this led to attendance at all the well known festivals and gigs in the U.K and beyond, so as the years progressed Paul got more and more into modern day dance music.

artist.name: Leon Bolier vs. Kamaya Painters
artist.bio:
Leon Bolier was born in 1980 somewhere in the middle of Holland, and always was in love with moody music.
 When he heard Energy 52's Cafe Del Mar he fell in love with melodic trance, and quit producing hardcore house.
 In 2002 and 2003 he got his first record deals, together with his brother Bart. They released some tracks on Bonzai/Banshee and FTM sublabels. Back then the first contacts with Armada frontman Maykel Piron were established via Armin van Buuren, and this resulted in Leon remixing the first ever Armada release.

artist.name: The Thrillseekers feat. Aruna
artist.bio: The Thrillseekers  Steve Helstrip has been at the very forefront of the global dance scene for over 7 years now. From his breakout hit 'Synaesthesia', through to the anthems 'Dreaming of You' and most recently 'By Your Side', he has continued to produce a powerhouse of the most emotive, evocative music going. He has remixed for luminaries such as Tiesto, Timo Maas, Sonique and Chicane, lending them all his trademark melodic, euphoric sound.

artist.name: Sasha
artist.bio: There are currently several Artists using the name Sasha: 1) Sasha, born Alexander Coe (born September 4, 1969), is a Welsh DJ and record producer. He is best known for partnering with fellow English DJ, John Digweed, as Sasha + Digweed. The pair released several mix albums together, including the Northern Exposure series (released between 1996 and 2001). They also released one of the all time best selling mix albums, The Renaissance Mix Collection part 1, in 1994.

artist.name: Mark Otten
artist.bio: While most dance-producers start their careers as dj?s, Mark comes from a musician?s side. Both parents were involved in making music, which always meant plenty of instruments at hand as well as lots of positive stimulation. Born in The Netherlands in 1978, multi-instrumentalist Mark started out as a drummer and quickly expanded his interests to other more melodic instruments, such as percussion, (bass-) guitars and keyboards.

artist.name: Cass Fox
artist.bio:
“I’m an army of one/ Don’t you know, don’t you see me coming through?/ Better all get out of my way / I’m feeling so strong ” – ‘Army of One’
 You’re broke. You have no job. You’ve been trying to make it as a singer. Then you write your first record and it goes to number one. But it quickly becomes clear that if you want to work on a follow-up, you’re going to have to make compromises. Big compromises. So what do you do next?

artist.name: Scott Bond vs. Solar Stone
artist.bio: As a resident at Gatecrasher in Sheffield, England, Scott Bond's reputation grew quickly, making him one of the U.K.'s most esteemed trance DJs at the end of the '90s. Voted Resident of the Year 1999 and fifth in the Best DJ poll by the readers of Mixmag, a popular U.K. dance magazine, Bond was also featured on Radio 1's Essential Mix show multiple times, further illustrating his popularity in England.

artist.name: Armin van Buuren
artist.bio: Aged just 32, Armin van Buuren has been named number one in the prestigious DJ Top 100 poll twice in a row, in 2007 and 2008– voted for by over 350,000 people across the world, and an indication of his prolific output over the 10 years he’s been dj’ing and producing. Being the official World’s Most Popular DJ is just one of his many achievements, but the driving force behind his success is an overriding passion for dance music.

artist.name: Recluse
artist.bio: Producers Thomas N

artist.name: Whirlpool
artist.bio: There are a number of artists called Whirlpool. 1) A 90s US band formed as a side project by Rodney Sellars of Southern California's Sense Field. Their self-titled 1995 debut was followed by 1996's Liquid Glass, both on Revelation Records. 2) A 90s UK band signed to Creation Records and featuring Gem Archer. 3) An alias for techno duo Filo & Peri.

artist.name: Dogzilla
artist.bio: Dogzilla are London-based duo Richard Kayvan & Simon Patterson, a production team responsible for some massive tracks and remixes over the last 18 months.  Their eponymously titled debut was featured in the cult Britflick 'The Football Factory' and was followed by the massive 'Your Eyes?. Thus began an impressive first foray into the club scene which garnered support from household names such as Judge Jules, Tiesto, Paul Oakenfold and John '00' Fleming..

artist.name: Jonas Steur
artist.bio:
Jonas Steur, born in 1982 in Belgium, (also known under his alias Estuera) has been into music since he was very young. Influenced by his father's favorite 70's progressive rock with its wealth of synth sounds and his mother's classical music, Jonas got his taste for both beautiful melodic and rougher electronic music.  
 After a lot of messing around with cheap Casio keyboards, Jonas got his hands on a set of turntables when he was 15, and started discovering the world of vinyl. The urge to make his own tracks grew, resulting in his first record deal when he was 17. (Silvertear - so deep)

artist.name: The Doppler Effect
artist.bio:
Produced by The 16 Bit Lolitas (Peter Kriek and Ariaan Olieroock) together with vocal writers, co-producers Sir Adrian & Raz Nitzan. Beautifully performed by the diva Carol Lee (of Rock Alternative band Bettie Serveert) "Beauty Hides In The Deep" has all the ingrediants of becoming a house classic.... Support from a wide range of DJs include Nick Warren and Sasha on the one side to Tiesto, Armin van Buuren & Ferry Corsten on the other...
 Band member are:
 Carol Lee
 Peter Kriek
 Aad Olieroock
 Adrian Broekhuyse

artist.name: Veracocha
artist.bio: A collaboration of two famous, almost legendary trance music producers. Coming from the Netherlands, Ferry Corsten and Vincent de Moor made an outstanding and remarkable track named 'Carte Blanche'. Despite the fact it was released in 1999, it is still a fresh and fantastic tune, by many trance fans called as the best track representing this genre so far! Unfortunately, Veracocha was not a long-time project. After producing 'Carte Blanche', 'Drafting' (a B-Side track to 'Carte Blanche' on the vinyl) and a remix of Ayla's song - 'Ayla' (also worth listening) they stopped the co-operation.

artist.name: Duncan Sheik
artist.bio: Duncan Scott Sheik (born November 18, 1969) is an American singer-songwriter. Born in Montclair, New Jersey, Sheik's upbringing was split between his parents' home in South Carolina and that of his grandparents in New Jersey. His grandmother, a piano graduate of The Juilliard School, taught him to play the piano and encouraged his musical development. He graduated from Phillips Academy in 1988, after which he studied semiotics at Brown University.

artist.name: Perasma
artist.bio: Perasma hails straight from Greece and consists of Sotiris Noukas, Diana Tsandekidou.They are an ambient electro group with melodic tones and smooth vocals. They are known for their single "Swing 2 Harmony". They also have a website at www.perasma.net and www.myspace.com/perasmaband , http://www.facebook.com/pages/PERASMA/52126265881?ref=ts.

artist.name: Interstate
artist.bio: There are 3 groups that go by the name Interstate and one alias.  (1) Interstate was a punk rock band from Salt Lake City from the late 90s/early 00s that were heavily influenced by legendary Jade Tree act, Lifetime. They released one record called "Find Your Own Way Home" from Young@Heart Records.  (2) "Interstate" is a collaborative group project from music producers Mike Burns and Mark Lewis. Their unique synergy blending house with trance elements and old school flavor created their hit song "I Found U".

artist.name: Solid Globe
artist.bio: Solid Globe is a Dutch progressive trance project, a collaboration of many talents led by Nic Vegter. The band took off in 2003 with the hit song "North Pole" which stayed at the top of Dutch dance charts for two consecutive weeks. The project is supported by leading DJ's such as Armin van Buuren and Tiesto. "North Pole" was soon followed by "Sahara" which was nominated for best Dance song of the year 2004.

artist.name: ATA
artist.bio: 1) Adi Tudoran (aged 23) - ATA, is an uplifting/progressive trance producer from Iasi, Romania.  2) Ata is two people. Ata is a German Dj and producer who runs the label Playhouse, and the club Robert Johnson.

artist.name: Jose Amnesia vs. Karen Overton
artist.bio:
1996
 Rob Aker aka Jose Amnesia bought his first synthesizer , a cheap Atari and started to compose electronic tracks.  1998
 Age One records (UK) were interested in his works, and in 1998, "Jose Amnesia" was born.  "Last sunset in Ibiza" was an essential new tune on Judge Jules BBC Radio Show, followed by the epic "The Eternal"which soon became a classic trance track gaining support from all the top dj's such as Paul Van Dyk, Tiesto, Ferry Corsten and Armin Van Buuren.  Rob also produces tracks under the guise of Jamnesia together with Dino Lenny.

artist.name: 4 Strings
artist.bio: 4 Strings currently consists of Carlo Resoort (who mostly makes the music) and Jan Loechel (who mostly works on production and arrangement, and performs some songs). In 2004, there were some rumors of singer Vanessa van Hemert leaving the group, due to some new 4 Strings songs that were released that did not feature van Hemert. On the official 4 Strings website, Resoort debunked the rumors. Although in 2005, van Hemert did leave the group. While Jan De Vos isn't actually a part of 4 Strings, he took up the name DJ 4 Strings and does all live performances in place of the actual group.

artist.name: Akesson
artist.bio: Björn Åkesson was born in 1986, in a town called Lund (southern Sweden). He first noticed electronic music in the middle of the 90es when he heard music from a videogame called Wipeout 2097. With artists such as Future Sound of London, The Prodigy and Orbital the interest grew. A few years later a friend from school introduced Björn to trance/club music. This sounded a lot better and much more interesting than the techno he heard before.

artist.name: Chainsaw
artist.bio:
There are nine bands playing under the name "Chainsaw":  1) Chainsaw from Poland, formed in July, 1997.
 There music is a Melodic influenced Heavy Metal.
 They've just released their 3th album called "A SIN ACT"
 Discography:
 - ELECTRIC WIZARDS*
 - THE JOURNEY INTO THE HEART OF DARKNESS
 - A SIN ACT
 Their early, unprofessional albums:
 - METAL WORKS
 - FROGS
 - LIVE AT KU?NIA
 - SECOND STEPS - MC
 - FIRST STEPS - MC
 - CHAINSAW

artist.name: Serge Devant - Sweet Harmony (Jerome Isma
artist.bio: When you're personally hand picked to share the stage with the worlds top DJs , including being tagged by DJ Tiesto himself to open and close for him in NYC, youve got something. Now armed with his new residency at Crobar, what he has is your attention. Hear him perform and you will witness a skillful exhibition from one of the most promising young talents in the electronic industry todaywe are talking about Serge Devant.

artist.name: Audible
artist.bio: Audible began in 2000 as a four-track collaboration between Philadelphia musician Mike Kennedy and his then-girlfriend Mary Garito. As Mike was busy playing drums in several popular area groups (Matt Pond PA, Mazarin, Lefty's Deceiver), the two never intended to become an actual band. But after releasing a few home recorded EPs, Kennedy was dared by Philly producer Brian McTear to record a proper full-length record at McTear's Miner Street Studio. The resulting album Sky Signal was picked up and released by Polyvinyl Records in 2005 to glowing reviews.

artist.name: Daniel Wanrooy
artist.bio: Daniel Wanrooy is signed to Black Hole Recordings and releases track under his own name, and also as one half of a team with Robin van de Wiel under the aliases of Progression and Odyssee, among others. Wanrooy has contributed releases over the past few years to not only the parent label Black Hole Recordings, but also its two main sub-labels, In Trance We Trust and Magik Muzik.

artist.name: Shy Brothers
artist.bio: Running your own label is no easy feat and neither is releasing a string of hits, coming up with a new sound and single handedly producing the largest dance events in the country. Well that?s exactly what the Shy Brothers do and now they are ready to take their careers to the next level. With hundreds of shows under their belts, an impressive list of releases and a number of visits to some of the biggest Dance Festivals in the World such as Dance Valley, Defcon and Sound Factory, the Shy Brothers are right on the verge of their international breakthrough.

artist.name: Max Graham
artist.bio: Max Graham is a house music producer and remixer from the United Kingdom. Graham grew up in Spain and the United States of America before settling in Canada in 1989. He started his professional production career in 2000, having played house music for ten years previously in Ottawa, Canada at the well-known Atomic night club. His first two releases, "Airtight" and "Tell You" helped him become well-known around the world, and led to him being asked to remix the popular Transport CD series in 2001. A world tour followed, which furthered his popularity across the globe.

artist.name: Joonas Hahmo
artist.bio: Only 24 years old, Joonas Hahmo has done this and that

artist.name: Envotion
artist.bio: Envotion consists of three people, Hugo Alberts, Laurens Alberts and Stijn Halfens. Envotion will be dedicated to making music without compromise. Hovering between the musical and the pure dancefloor oriented approach they will deliver music with more than one face. As the past lies in producing (with releases on Armada, Extrema Records, Plastic Fantastic, Extrema Outdoor 2006 Tune and film music ) and DJ..ing (plays @ Paradiso, Panama Extrema Outdoor, 3FM and Tribehouse) this trio will deliver during clubnights as well in the studio, both under the name of Envotion.

artist.name: Moussa Clarke vs. Terrafunka
artist.bio: Moussa Clarke is an inspirational DJ/producer with a worldwide reputation for igniting dancefloors from London to Moscow to Tokyo and back again. Never far from the madding crowd ? apart from when he?s cooking up monster basslines and electrochemical beats in the studio ? he?s also founder of the thriving London-based label and DJ agency Oven Ready. Born in Switzerland, half English, half Senegalese, he found his feet in France and Italy, and then travelled the globe before moving to the UK aged 12.

artist.name: Sunny Lax
artist.bio: Sunny Lax, real name Levente Marton (born August 6, 1986) is a Hungarian trance music producer. He debuted on the music scene with the 12" P.U.M.A. / Cassiopeia EP as his debut release on Anjunabeats in 2005.  Marton followed this up with M.I.R.A., on Anjunabeats on 9 October 2006 (featuring a remix from Daniel Kandi). This was followed up with his latest effort, Blue Bird, released on 21 May 2007.

artist.name: Headstrong feat. Tiff Lacey
artist.bio: Headstrong is a Canadian alternative metal band formed in 1998. They released one eponymous studio album under RCA Records before being dropped from the label and ultimately disbanding in 2003. The band members all met while attending University of Western Ontario where they each a received a degree. Their group initially began in the late 1990s under the name bomb32 in their native London, Ontario.

artist.name: Carl B
artist.bio: Having recently remixed high profile tracks for big names in the trance industry such as Armas, Acues & Elitist, Selu Vibra, Summer Sessions, Armin van Buuren and JPL, Carl B (Carl Barrdahl) has definitely merited his growing reputation as a trance remix specialist! Yet he has also written and produced quality tunes of his own in his Carl B guise, including the tracks Solitude and Social Suicide. Barrdahl also has an alias called PEAK, and in 2006 he collaborated with Joni Ljungqvist on a project named Peak vs.

artist.name: The Killers
artist.bio: The Killers are an alternative rock band from Las Vegas, Nevada, formed in 2002 and made up of Brandon Flowers (vocals, keyboards), Dave Keuning (guitar, backing vocals), Mark Stoermer (bass guitar, backing vocals) and Ronnie Vannucci Jr. (drums, percussion). Their first two albums to date have sold in excess of 12 million copies worldwide combined. They got their name from the fictional band "The Killers" in the video for New Order's "Crystal."

artist.name: 16 Bit Lolitas
artist.bio: The 16 Bit Lolita's are Ariaan Olieroock & Peter Kriek. Both with a firm background in religious choir music and country they decided in 2003 to try and do something new. For their latest album entitled: 'Lord we miss the groove!', they decided to reset their careers and started making dance music.   After moving from New York to Amsterdam , they instantly started working on a new 'dance' sound. In the beginning it was hard to remove all the country elements and that occasional 'Sanctus' that Peter always seemed to want to slip in.

artist.name: Cassandra Fox
artist.bio:
“I’m an army of one/ Don’t you know, don’t you see me coming through?/ Better all get out of my way / I’m feeling so strong ” – ‘Army of One’
 You’re broke. You have no job. You’ve been trying to make it as a singer. Then you write your first record and it goes to number one. But it quickly becomes clear that if you want to work on a follow-up, you’re going to have to make compromises. Big compromises. So what do you do next?

artist.name: Arctic Quest
artist.bio: Arctic Quest was born and raised in Dutch boulder city Amersfoort in 1976. Playing piano since the age of 9, his musical interest and talents were obvious from the start. By mainly playing jazz, rhythm and blues a solid base was formed for his bright future.  The introduction of personal computers early 90s, wakened his electronic interests and he changed the piano for software like Scream Tracker and Impulse Tracker.

artist.name: Yves Larock feat. Jaba
artist.bio: After more than ten years in hip hop and just three years in making house music, the 28 years old, Yves ?Larock? Cheminade is establishing himself as a new fresh producer in the house scene  At the end of the 80?s, Yves started his love for music with the discovery of Hip-Hop, then he began rhyming on the mic.  During the late 90?s, Yves Larock got caught by the House Music vibe and in  2001 made his debut as a house music producer, in parallel with his work on Hip-Hop

artist.name: Super8 & DJ Tab vs. Nadia Ali
artist.bio: Super8 + Tab by combining dark and driving progressive elements with more traditional melodic trance sounds, the pair have created a unique sound that has had the worlds A-list DJs clamouring for their music.  Super8 + Tab's "Helsinki Scorchin" is arguably the biggest instrumental trancer of the year 2006 and has featured on 15 compilations to date, including the latest from Tiesto, Above & Beyond and Armin van Buuren.

artist.name: Home Video
artist.bio: It is five in the morning and still dark outside. Your eyes flutter and open heavily. You see a disembodied blue glow pulsating on the ceiling. You have no idea where you are, but you know you are alone. The only sound you hear is the hiss of a nearby radiator, but in the movie version of your life this moment would be punctuated by the music of Home Video.  Home Video are Collin Ruffino and David Gross, transplants from the misunderstood landscape of New Orleans, before The Great Deluge, now living in the brooding brownstones of Brooklyn, New York.

artist.name: Petar Dundov
artist.bio: Petar Dundov is a Croatian producer and DJ, born in 1973 in Zagreb. From an early age he was fascinated with synthesized sound and the concept of developing new ways of composing. In 1989 he bought his first synthesizer and started making music influenced by Kraftwerk, Jean M. Jarre and Depeche Mode.  In 1993 he composed an anthem for the first Croatian rave party “Under City Rave,” which was soon after released as his first 12” single on Formaldehyde Records from Berlin.

artist.name: Ladytron
artist.bio: Ladytron are a contemporary electropop band formed in Liverpool, England. The band takes their name from the song "Ladytron" on the 1972 self-titled d

artist.name: Tiger Stripes vs. Ladytron
Miikka Leinonen
artist.bio: Miikka Leinonen is 27 years old producer living in Jyv

artist.name: Dennis Sheperd
artist.bio: Dennis was born in September 1985 in Germany (Essen, Northrhine-Westfalia).  He discovered the sound of Electronical Dance Music in 1998 and his interest in this genre grew and finally transformed into the love that he feels today. In 2004 he began creating his own music although he didn't possess any basic knowledge and he had never played an instrument before.  Because of his great ambition and volition he isn't an unknown name anymore.

artist.name: Super8 & Tab vs. Nadia Ali
artist.bio: Super8 + Tab are the antidote to anyone who says the trance scene has gone stale. By combining dark and driving progressive elements with more traditional melodic trance sounds, the pair have created a unique sound that has had the worlds A-list DJs clamouring for their music.

artist.name: Riva
artist.bio: 1) Riva was a pop band from Croatia, then Yugoslavia, in the late 1980s. The group debuted on Zagrebfest 1988. Their song Rock Me won the Eurovision Song Contest 1989 in Switzerland, with a score of 137 points. 2) Guss van Vlaanderen and Horst Pulmann 3) Alias of Ismael Rivas 4) Alias of Zki & Dobri (Gaston Steenkist and Rene ter Horst), DJs from the Netherlands who have produced multiple dance hits under various group names since the early 1990s, and who had a hit named Who Do You Love Now? with singer Dannii Minogue.

artist.name: Evbointh
artist.bio: Krzysztof Michalak (17) was born on 29/08/1990 in Eastern Poland where he lives to this day. Music is his passion and has been his hobbyhorse for a long period of time. On 31st October 2006, his official debut took place on the famed and respected radioshow "Trance Around The World" (#137) with Above & Beyond, playing his production "One Wish" (now out on Anjunabeats). The track was also tested out at a similarly early stage on ?Trance Experience? (episode 6) with Adam Nickey.

artist.name: Redstar
artist.bio: Redstar is a 21 year old trance producer known as Steve Bolger, hailing from Pennsylvania, USA. Although Steve has been producing for many years it wasn't until mid-2006 that he started to make his mark and ever since things have just got better. His breakthrough came early this year when he signed two tracks to a leading UK label Deep Blue, to compliment the release of his debut single 'Innocent' under his Perfect Pitch guise on his own label Red Force Recordings. Steve is currently working on his own productions as well as a host of remixes for labels worldwide.

artist.name: Daniel Kandi
artist.bio: Recognizing the elements of a strong melody in a trance track after just a few seconds of sound. That is what this artist has been striving to make possible from the earliest of his productions, coming to full fruition in the present day...  Daniel Kandi, a producer already a known in his home country denmark, not so much for trance, but for his remixes in more commercial genres, having formed the remix-team called Hit'n'Run.

artist.name: Darren Tate feat. Pippa
artist.bio: There are two artists called Darren Tate, A DJ/Producer from London, and an ambient/drone artist, also from the UK. 1. UK DJ / Producer Darren Tate is an international producer and DJ born in London, England. As a classically trained musician, Darren has earned his reputation as one of Europe's leading producers, having worked with a wide range of international artists and writers. He is also one of the worlds most successful dance producers, having had huge international hits with the likes of Jurgen Vries, Angelic, Orion, Citizen Caned and most recently DT8 Project.

artist.name: Steve Slight
artist.bio: Steve Slight started out at the tender age of 15. Influenced by the music of Marco Bailey, Dave Clarke and Chris Liebing he heard from friends, Steve soon began making his own productions with some basic software. With a little help from the internet, he slowly developed his skills and passed his demo?s to various people, learning the tricks of the trade while doing so.  When he was asked to play some of his tracks on a party next to RedHead, Tom Hades and Cyrix...

artist.name: Talla 2XLC
artist.bio: Talla 2XLC (b. Andreas Tomalla, Germany) is a producer, musician, and DJ whose work has spanned from industrial music to trance music. Tomalla started as a DJ, founding in 1984 the Technoclub at Frankfurt's Dorian Gray club. He was also at the time involved with a band called Moskwa TV. In 1988, he started a new project called Bigod 20, which would go on to be one of Europe's most successful EBM acts of the early 1990s.

artist.name: Chris de Seed
artist.bio: Chris de Seed aka krystian polak coming from zielona Gora, producer and Dj at the same time. Professionaly started in 2006, when he bought his first .....(konsole). Step by step he lernt to know more about technique of mixing, about 6 mounths later he get firt offer to performed. In the middle of 2006 became to be a resident of regular event "2be connected" kept in trance type of music. Soon after that he performed for few other clubs in Poland.

artist.name: Komytea
artist.bio: Komytea is a finnish production team consisting of Matti Heininen and Erkka Lempiäinen. Besides Komytea they produce also Squash 84 and Michael Cassette, whose track Zeppelin offered a great opening for Anjunabeats' Volume 5 compilation and is also featured on the massive Ministy Of Sound - Clubbers Guide To 2008 compilation.  Komytea's debute release was Soldiers Of Karkadu E.P in 2007, although the duo had been making electronic music together since 1998. Before their first E.

artist.name: Nitrous Oxide
artist.bio: Krzysztof Pretkiewicz aka N2O/Nitrous Oxide was born in Poznan, Poland in 1984. He first listened to electronic music in the early `90s. Artists such as Jean Michel Jare, Mike Oldfield and Depeche Mode were the first to make such a big impression on him that he knew this is the genre of music he loves to hear. He started creating his own music in 1998 when he discovered that tracks can be created on his PC. It became his hobby and he spent all his free time making new sounds and tracks. Krzysztof doesn`t have any musical education and he doesn't play on any instrument.

artist.name: Paul van Dyk, Starkillers & Austin Leeds feat. Ashley Tomberlin
Olive
artist.bio: There are two bands called Olive. A trip-hop group from the United Kingdom and a doom metal band from the Syrian Arab Republic. There is also a french rock singer, born 1955 & died 2006. 1. Olive (United Kingdom) : Two of its members, producers Tim Kellett and Robin Taylor-Firth, had departed from their respective groups, Simply Red and Nightmares on Wax, prior to forming Olive with vocalist Ruth Ann Boyle, who Kellett had met while recording her vocals for live manipulation at a Durutti Column concert.

artist.name: Darude
artist.bio: Darude is known worldwide for his anthemic trance style. He is an electronic dance music producer, DJ and lives in Turku, Finland. He debuted in 1999 with the smash single Sandstorm (#1 hit in numerous charts around the world) and subsequent album Before the Storm. Virtanen started his career as an amateur musician while in high school, making music using his PC's tracker software. As his interest in music production rapidly grew, he moved on to more serious production techniques.

artist.name: Tatana with Andrew Bennett feat. Tiff Lacey
Kopi Luwak feat. Tiff Lacey
artist.bio:
Kopi Luwak weaves a new and fresh production, with Down Tempo beats, New Age textures, Ethnic Soundscapes, Chill Out and Ambient athmospheres.  Kopi is the Indonesian word for coffee, and Luwak is a local name of the Palm Civet.
 Kopi Luwak is currently working on a new CD, ft several singers, Tiff Lacey, Miranda Dickinson, and Sam Mollison among others.

artist.name: Missing Hours
artist.bio: Emma and Anthony Hewitt started playing music together when they were in high school. At 15 Emma was singing in bands, with Ant - a year younger - tagging along with his guitar and and hoping they would ask him to play.   Later, they began writing their own songs and started recording and pitching demos. Through cold calling and determined enthusiasm the pair were rewarded with the support of a passionate producer in Barry Palmer who helped them make some demo recordings and develop their song writing. They later signed to his indie label.

artist.name: Angel Ace
artist.bio: Currently, Angel Ace is one of the most promising and rising stars in the Spanish Trance scene. He has been awarded best Spanish Trance Producer in 2005 and 2006 by Dj One Magazine, and was nominated for best trance track in 2003, 2004 and 2005. Moreover, some of his tracks have been included in many sets of the top Djs around the world (Paul Van Dyk, Armin Van Buuren, Judge Jules, Markus Schulz, Johan Gielen, Dj Precision and a few more).

artist.name: Reminder feat. Carter
artist.bio: Chicago underground jazz/electronica/beat fusion with yummy vibrations. Reminder is the solo outing of Chicago scene staple Josh Abrams, whose bass playing has held the groove for many artists over the past ten years. A departure from the avant and jazz roots of his Town & County and Sticks & Stones projects, Abrams takes a cue from his residency as a member of Prefuse 73's backing band (if you've seen Prefuse live and felt your body vibrate, it was more than likely thanks to Josh's bass).

artist.name: Dinka - Chemistry (Jerome Isma
artist.bio: DINKA is a swiss progressive house act. Stomping house grooves, combined with catchy melodies and spherical harmonies. That's Dinka!  With their 1st three releases over the swiss label "Unreleased Digital" they made it in beatport top 15 progressive charts. Their tracks are played by the biggest DJs all around the globe.

artist.name: Paul van Dyk & Starkillers & Austin Leeds feat. Ashley Tomberlin
Matt Hardwick
artist.bio: Matt Hardwick ,is the epitome of an international DJ. He lives and breathes electronic music. Since his inception into club culture Matt Hardwick has completely immersed himself in it. His rapid ascendency into dance music with the global phenomenon that is Gatecrasher is something which has been well documented. The association with Gatecrasher, the first of many landmark achievements in his career...

artist.name: Paul van Dyk feat. Ryan Merchant
John Askew
artist.bio: John Askew is tech/trance producer/djs From The UK. After the huge success of his debut single "Vellum" in 2001, he has delivered release after release of consistently high quality club music - either through his own Discover label or via one of his many remixes for high profile labels such as Duty Free, Ministry of Sound, Euphonic and Paul van Dyk's legendary Vandit. See discography below:  From guest appearances on BBC Radio One, to hosting his own show on London's prestigious Kiss 100, from exclusive residencies at 3 of the World's most influential clubs (The Gallery...

artist.name: Sander van Doorn
artist.bio: Sander Ketelaars, born on the 28th of February 1979. Sander debuted in DJMag?s prestigious Top 100 poll at a very impressive no.32 in 2006 and then climbing 17 places to no.15 in 2007.  Sander's passion for music already started at a young age. At the age of 16 though, Sander discovered the thru thrill of making music when he played some records for the first time on 2 really bad turntables! This new hobby was to be expanded with producing when he began experimenting with a drum computer at the age of 17.

artist.name: Bob Marley
artist.bio: Bob Marley (February 6, 1945 ? May 11, 1981), born Robert Nesta Marley, was a Jamaican singer-songwriter, guitarist, and activist. He was the most widely known writer and performer of reggae, and more specificaly roots reggae. He is famous for popularising the genre outside of Jamaica and the Caribbean. Much of his music dealt with the struggles of the spiritually wealthy rasta and/or spiritually powerfull Jah Rastafari.

artist.name: Arcane Science
artist.bio: For many people across the globe Trance music has played such a fundamental part of their lives. An essential, audible, necessity for expressing emotion, personality, energy and depth. For some Trance is not a past time but a direction, a path leading to a unique gathering of others, connected in such a way, that it is incomprehensible to a world outside. Passion that only true cult members will ever really understand.

artist.name: Projex
artist.bio: Projex are, or were, a collaboration between MOBO Award winner Lynden David Hall and former Technotronic emcee, Eric Marin, who more recently has started a solo career under the psuedonym Me One.  Their debut album was almost completed but was cut short by "unforseen circumstances".  The two artists returned to their solo careers, through which some of their work survived.  "Eventually" was released by Lynden David Hall on his 2005 LP "In Between Jobs" and "Introducing Her" was released by Me One on his 2005 EP "Still Concerned".

artist.name: Arksun
artist.bio: Arksun is a professional freelance music producer and sound designer from UK. Visit http://www.arksun.co.uk

artist.name: Maor Levi
artist.bio: Maor Levi is a highly original up and coming producer hailing from Israel.  At the tender age of just 17 and after already releasing a track under the Pillow One alias on the Future Heroes 2 compilation via Lost Language, he now joins forces with Anjunabeats' hot new label, Anjunadeep.   Producing since the age of 11 and inspired by the Tiesto Magik series, he took his unique style of trance to the internet. Garnering many reactions and taking onboard all the resources he could find, with the help of FL Studio, he honed his skills to the point where labels started taking him seriously.

artist.name: Alan-M
