artist.bio: 1)  alan is a Chinese singer and Erhu player from Sichuan province who debuted in 2005 with the album Sheng Sheng Zui Ru Lan. Alan is her real Chinese family name. She made her Japanese debut in 2007 under Avex Trax with the single Ashita e no Sanka. alan grew up in the Meiren valley in the Rongxar county of the Garze Tibetan Autonomous Prefecture in China. Her father is a civil servant  while her mother is a former singer.

artist.name: Mansun
artist.bio: Mansun were formed in chester in 1995 by vocalist/ rhythm guitarist Paul Draper, lead guitarist/ backing vocalist Dominic Chad, bassist Stove King and drummer Andie Rathbone. They were known for regularly changing their sound (and attire), often between each EP release - liberally mixing beatrock, prog, psychedelia, pop and 80s noir influences - along with being a fearsome live act who drastically rearranged their songs for the stage.

artist.name: Ti
artist.bio: Born as Tijs Verwest in Breda, Netherlands, Ti

artist.name: Alex Kunnari
artist.bio: Alex Kunnari hails from the trance hotbed of Helsinki, Finland and has been involved in the DJing/producing business for fair few years now, in fact a good 15 of them. To me, he is new name but you may be familiar with the alias Modulation who, with Heikki L, he has made some hard-hitting trancers like ‘Sky’ and ‘White Flame’. His debut solo single, ‘Lifter’ has been picked up by Black Hole Recordings for their In Trance We Trust sub-label and been beefed up with a bumper pack of mainly Finnish remixes.

artist.name: Above & Beyond vs. Mr. Pit
artist.bio: Above & Beyond are a trance music group formed in 2000. The group is famous for remixes and their own productions. The group's tracks are regularly played by well-known DJs, such as Tiësto, Armin van Buuren and Paul van Dyk. They are also known under other aliases, like Tranquility Base, OceanLab, Dirt Devils and Rollerball. Jono Grant and Paavo Siljam

artist.name: Yvel & Tristan
artist.bio: Yvel and Tristan have been working on electronic music for 6 years, but they got the real appreciation from 2003. At first, as it use to be, the hungarian electronic music scene discovered the talent of the guys. They became a general favourite nubreed producer duo for the hungarian DJ's. Their fame rested upon the amount of new productions what were filled with emotions and melody. In the beginning they left a good impression in expert electronic music lovers with their couple of remixes then they made a name for themselves with their own productions.

artist.name: Michael Cassette
artist.bio: Michael Cassette is a finnish progressive house duo made up of Matti Heininen & Erkka Lempiäinen, also known as komytea.

artist.name: Way Out West
artist.bio: A world-renowned progressive house and remix act, was conceived in the bowels of Bristol, UK in early 1993. DJ and producer Jody Wisternoff had just been introduced to Nick Warren, and after a few hours in the studio together, they realized they had a common musical vision. Jody Wisternoff and Nick Warren have also maintained careers as successful DJs, both individually and together as Way Out West.

artist.name: Menno de Jong feat. Re:Locate
artist.bio: Menno de Jong is a 24 year old DJ from the Netherlands. He is the owner and founder of Intuition Recordings, also has his very own podcast at http://www.mennodejong.com, released and aired on ETN.fm's trance stream the first Wednesday of the month. Menno has played at noteworthy and some of the biggest events including Gatecrasher and Godskitchen. His other huge successes have been at events such as The Love Parade in Berlin and many others. He has travelled extensively the world over.

artist.name: Lost Witness vs. Pierre Pienaar
artist.bio: Lost Witness is one of the UK's top trance artists, specializing in the extremely melodic vocal trance anthems.  Lost Witness are DJ / Producer Simon Paul and producer Simon Kemper.  The dynamic duo met and formed in May 1998 as Dusk Til Dawn and enjoyed the underground success of Fine Night, which in turn brought songwriter Ed Barton into the frame as the third, if more silent member, to complete the happy union.

artist.name: Amurai vs. Saint-Jules
artist.bio: Manvel Ter-Pogosyan was introduced to Trance music by ATBs famous track, 9PM (Till I Come). Born in Yerevan, Armenia, in 1987, Manvel was constantly exposed to music while growing up in a family appreciative of the arts. After immigrating to the United States in 1991, he continued to surround himself with beautiful music which led him to engage in music composition and production. In the years to come, passion and inspiration would take control as song after song was produced.

artist.name: Roland Klinkenberg
artist.bio: Real Name: Roland Klinkenberg  Dutch producer, born 6 March 1972.  Aliases: Cruz Control, Cruzeman, Low Tech Style, Prefab Planet, Radiance (2), Simsalabim, Sound Of Sim  Roland Klinkenberg has been producing house music since 1992. Ever since, Roland has been producing numerous tracks and remixes (see Discography). You may find his house records with different artist names, like Cruzeman and Freak Force (with Danny Bakker).

artist.name: Jaytech vs. Flux Capacitor vs. Marcus Sch
artist.bio: Hailing from Australia?s capital, Canberra, James ?Jimbo? Cayzer?s musical pedigree extends way back to his early years as a pianist and composer. However, at the tender age of 14, Jimbo commenced work on his first digital production and hasn?t looked back since. After the initial success of ?Music 101? and his remix of Lens? ?Let The Light In,? Jaytech hit the studio with partner-in-crime Mark Dynamix, and shot to prominence with the release of ?Identify Me" in 2004, appearing on the Ministry Of Sound 2005 Annual and dominating Australian radio.

artist.name: Maarten Hercules
artist.bio: www.maartenhercules.net

artist.name: Corderoy
artist.bio: Corderoy formed in 1999 are international producers based in London, the heart of the UK. Chris and Dale being brothers work as a vigorous team, constantly contributing to the music scene. Multi-talented musicians coming from a background in bands, both are highly adaptable to style and play piano, guitar, bass, drums.   Their first commercial dance release 'Sweetest Dreams' which burst into clubland in 2003...

artist.name: Arpegia & Oliver P pres. Fast Distance
Michael Angelo vs. Salo
artist.bio: There are at least 2 artists with the name Michael Angelo, one is an obscure American psychadelic band and the other a guitar player.  Michael Angelo Batio (pronounced "Bah-tee-ohh") is an American instrumental rock guitarist from Chicago, Illinois. He attended Northeastern Illinois University and received a bachelor's degree in music theory. Having played guitar since the age of ten, Batio is often referred to as the fastest guitar shredder of all time.

artist.name: Ali Payami
artist.bio:
ali payami is a persian dj
 he borned is  tehran-iran

artist.name: George Acosta feat. Aruna
artist.bio: Trance, whether you like your trance melodic and uplifting, or hard and fast, trance by any definition is here to stay. From the warehouse parties of the late 80?s to car commercials in 2001, trance has become part of the new millennium, part of our lifestyle. And all because of DJs like George Acosta. George proves every time he puts a needle on a record that "trance", whatever the label, has changed, evolved, become a lifestyle, a culture? as well it should.

artist.name: Monogato
artist.bio: Monogato is a fresh new project by young producer Marninx. Peter Smit already had some hot releases under his Marninx guise but the love for progressive and minimal grows so a new project is launched. Monogato holds a fresh style of progressive trance to minimal. Influenced by producers like Wippenberg, Andy Moor, Nic Chagall, Deadmau5 etc. The first release, a remix for young Romanian trance label Well Mixed Recordings, was supported by Markus Schulz and Armin van Buuren. The second, an EP on Andy Moor's imprint AVA Recordings, is being scheduled now as we speak.

artist.name: Fei-Fei
artist.bio: Take a deep breath. Because once Fei-Fei takes the decks, you won't have time to come up for air. She's at the top of her game and has taken the industry by storm. She

artist.name: Ashley Wallbridge
artist.bio: Ashley Wallbridge started his career very early on as a DJ. Known as a prodigy for winning some over 18 dj competitions in the UK with fake ID. Ash was been featured on Radio 1 at the tender age of 16 alongside Fergie and Dave Pierce. During this time he also played at Newcastle superclub IKON to over 2500 people. Age has never been a factor for him and 2007 sees him sailing his way into the production world with his first signing to Lyon Echo in NYC. Also recently signing 3 tracks to new UK label Currupt Music (in conjunction with known label Born to dance).

artist.name: Suncatcher
artist.bio: Bogdan's passion for music started in his early youth, but didn't materialize until a dear friend of his, Mihai Mogos, talked about this program... Fruity Loops. That was happening in early Spring 2003. It's not hard to see that he became quite familiar with it and it wasn't much before his passion became a hobby. Being influenced by producer Andre Tanneberger (aka. ATB), Bogdan started producing his on music and also tried to create his own particular style.

artist.name: Re:Locate feat. Menno de Jong
artist.bio: There are at least 2 artists known as Relocate: 1) Re:Locate is an alias of Paul Moelands, young trance producer, also known as Octagen, Palanya and Scratch Bandicoot. Rocketed into the trance scene late 2003, Paul Moelands has become one of the leading upcoming producers that trance land has to offer nowadays! Both "Re:Locate ? Waterfall" and "Octagen & Arizona (his project with Thomas Bronzwaer) ? Starburst" releases were shot into orbit and picked up by every self respected DJ around!

artist.name: Klems
artist.bio:
Borned in 1982 in a little town from west of France, this young boy starts to learn drums very soon, and understand that he gives a particular interest to electronic sounds and beats.
 At the age of 17, he starts to enter the nightlife, and discovers clubs and EDM, where the music sounds perfectly with what he was looking for. Fascinated by the dj and the sounds playing there, he stays during all nights long looking at this man, with whom a real friendship will born.

artist.name: Josh Gallahan
artist.bio: Josh Gallahan IS also know as RuDee, Who Is ATB best friend and who you can always see on tour with ATB. Now Rudee Has His started his own projects with Josh Gallahan (State Of Trance) & Jades. For More Infomation Check Out These Links - http://profile.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=user.viewprofile&friendid=271480275 http://profile.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=user.viewprofile&friendid=100839332 http://profile.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=user.viewprofile&friendid=372832648

artist.name: Glockenspiel feat. Blackfeel Wite
artist.bio: Here is a description and some reviews of Glockenspiel..  Glockenspiel started as the title for Adrian Dollemore?s cd-r collections of minature bedroom experiments using tapes, electronics and guitars through chains of effects who then progressed to playing with Steve D?Enton (old friend of the ?sHRiMP & ex-Quickspace sticksman) on drum kit - Steve?s ?direct but tactile style driving straight through the x-axis of Adrian?s skyward guitar, as cymbals and hi-hats delicately ring and splash over his motorik anchor.

artist.name: Hydro-Aquatic
artist.bio: There are multiple artists or groups who have recorded using the name ?Hydro?. Robbie Bronnimann, of dBA, created ?Hydro? as a side project, with his wife Shaz Sparks, Ray Goudie, and Andy Hunter among the contributors. Their albums "Spiritualisation" and "Aborigination" are now out of print. Ben Settle's releases include "Tech Steppin" and "The Zone"; it is apparently he who is pictured here (as of this writing). Lotz & Wollny recorded "Come With Me" and "Utopia" under this name.

artist.name: U2
artist.bio: U2 is an Irish rock band which formed in 1976 in Dublin, Ireland. Since the band's formation, they have consisted of Bono (real name Paul Hewson) (vocals, guitar, harmonica), The Edge (real name David Evans) (guitar, keyboards, backing vocals), Adam Clayton (bass) and Larry Mullen, Jr. (drums, percussion). The band is the biggest selling alternative rock act of all time, having sold 140 million albums worldwide as of 2008. They have won 22 Grammys and were inducted into the Rock & Roll Hall of Fame in 2005. As of 2009, they have released 12 albums and 58 singles.

artist.name: First State feat. Anita Kelsey
artist.bio: First State is a project of two trance producers, Ralph Barendse and Sander van der Waal. Their first album Time Frame was released on the 19th of November 2007. Their songs are often influenced by many genres. 'House, trance, minimal, pop and classical, it's all in there somewhere' as quoted from their album.

artist.name: Tiësto
artist.bio: Born as Tijs Verwest in Breda, Netherlands, Tiësto is one of the greatest dance DJs on the scene. He started out DJing professionally at school parties, and then moved on to become a resident DJ from 1985 to 1993 at several clubs in The Netherlands. It was at a club called 'The Spock' where things really took off for Tiësto; he stopped producing hardcore/gabber tracks and started to produce his own sound from 10pm until 4am on weekends. In the mid 1990s, Tiësto started to produce trance and the rest, as they say, is history.

artist.name: Sander van Doorn vs. Funkagenda
artist.bio: Sander Ketelaars, born on the 28th of February 1979. Sander debuted in DJMag?s prestigious Top 100 poll at a very impressive no.32 in 2006 and then climbing 17 places to no.15 in 2007.  Sander's passion for music already started at a young age. At the age of 16 though, Sander discovered the thru thrill of making music when he played some records for the first time on 2 really bad turntables! This new hobby was to be expanded with producing when he began experimenting with a drum computer at the age of 17.

artist.name: Adymus
artist.bio: THE BEGINNING  In the aisles of a small, obscure California manga shop, time stood still for just one moment. As the piercing sounds of a Signum remix pulsated through the large, dusty speakers, a life long love of trance music was born. In that one euphoric instant, all else was quickly forgotten as intoxicating trance vocals and synthetic patterns overtook Adymus

artist.name: Jay Lumen
artist.bio: His real name is Csaba Lumnitzer. Music is part of his life since his childhood years. He learnt music in a conservatoire for eight years, which provides a good basis to his ambition of making music. Besides composing music he became to be more and more open to the dj scena. In the beginning he played at parties that he organized on his own, then later he started with his career with complying occasional invitations.

artist.name: Matt Cerf vs. Envolio feat. Jaren
artist.bio: DJ/Producer Matt Cerf started his career in 1998 after attending a rave during his Junior year at McGill University, in Montreal, where he was studying Agricultural Engineering. He quickly dropped schooling to study the ins and outs of music production on his own. In 2000, he and three friends created the group Second Sun and Matt's first track, Empire, quickly caught the attention of DJ Paul Van Dyk. Empire was signed to Paul's label, Vandit, and Second Sun appeared on Quebec?s version of MTV, Music Plus.

artist.name: Krivi
artist.bio: Although all of his beginning steps were connected to the town of Herceg Novi-Montenegro , this young producer proves,in spite of the bad conditions and almost no perspective in his home country, that success is possible. The roots of his great passion for music go deep into the childhood when pop/rock music of 80's fascinated him.Smiths,Dire Strait,Cindy Lauper,Police,The Cars are just few names.

artist.name: Paul van Dyk feat. Rea Garvey
artist.bio: Grammy nominated artist and globally acclaimed DJ and Producer Paul van Dyk continues to dominate the electronic music charts and appears at the pinnacle of every Top DJ list across the globe. His fifth original album In Between was released August 2007 and features collaborations with David Byrne and Jessica Sutta of the Pussycat Dolls.  PvD is renowned as one of the hardest working artists, with sold-out tours that cross each continent, headline spots at every major festival, and a hugely successful recording career.

artist.name: Myon & Shane 54 pres. The Black Army
Bobina
artist.bio: Real Name:Dmitry Almazov The project was founded in Moscow in 2003. The debut album “Catchy” detonated the trance stage in 2004 and became the best selling trance album in Russia. The first official European release “Lazy World” had become the visit card of the project at the international dancing stage. European critics were delighted with the track. In Europe the project Bobina is famous not only by his own music, but also by many remixes of different artists. The Bobina remake of the track by Three Drives«Air Traffic» has got the place in the chart UK Top 40 at BBC Radio 1.

artist.name: Plastic Boy
artist.bio: This is one of the MANY aliases that Mike Dierickx uses in his trance endeavours. He is better known as Push.

artist.name: Datt & Bissen feat. Tiff Lacey - Take Your Time (Martin Roth Nu
Snow Patrol
artist.bio: Snow Patrol is an alternative rock band which formed in Dundee, Scotland in 1994 and currently based in Bangor, Northern Ireland, where most of the band members are from. They consist of Gary Lightbody (vocals, guitar), Nathan Connolly (guitar, vocals), Paul Wilson (bass), Tom Simpson (keyboards) and Johnny Quinn (drums). Lightbody and Quinn are the only original members who remain in the band. The band became wildly successful on both sides of the Atlantic on the back of their fourth record...

artist.name: Marco Torrance
artist.bio: Marco Torrance, aka Marco Tust, is an ambient, chillout and trance musician based in Leipzig, Germany. He was born on January 15, 1981 in Leipzig (German Democratic Republic).  Inspired by so called dancefloor era in the early 1990s, Marco began making his first electronic dance music by using simple sample tools and tracker related programs. Finally he found the way to the since then unemployed software synthesizers.

artist.name: Oakenfold feat. Ryan Tedder
artist.bio: Paul Oakenfold (born August 30, 1963 in Greenhithe, Kent[1] England) is a world famous DJ and producer, whose works have helped define the subcategory of trance music called Goa.  Not only does Paul Oakenfold produce records, but he also mixes them. In 1987 he spent several months in Ibiza with a few friends and fell in love with dance club music. Oakenfold produced "Happy Mondays' Pills 'n' Thrills and Bellyaches" before producing for U2, Massive Attack, Simply Red and New Order (to name a few), many of which were released on his label Perfecto Records.

artist.name: Absolute
artist.bio: There are at least 3 artists sharing this name:  1) New Wave/Synthpop band from North London, produced by Vince Clarke and Eric Radcliffe's label Reset records. They released the single "T.V Glare" which became a huge dancefloor hit in the mid 80s.  2) Absolute, AKA M.I.K.E., is Mike Dierickx. Formerly known as Dirk Dierickx, he resides in Antwerp, Belgium. In 2000, he decided to change his real name from Dirk to Mike.

artist.name: Radiohead
artist.bio: Radiohead are an English alternative rock band from Abingdon, Oxfordshire. The band is composed of Thom Yorke (lead vocals, rhythm guitar, piano, beats), Jonny Greenwood (lead guitar, keyboard, other instruments), Ed O'Brien (guitar, backing vocals), Colin Greenwood (bass guitar) and Phil Selway (drums, percussion).  Radiohead released their first single, "Creep," in 1992. The song was initially unsuccessful, but it became a worldwide hit several months after the release of their debut album, Pablo Honey (1993).

artist.name: Myon
artist.bio: There are 3 artistes named Myon: 1. Myon is an artist name variation of Hungarian trance producer Márió Égető (Mÿon), better known as Orange Project. The alias Mÿon was created to define a separate style in his music and was first introduced with the progressive vocal trance song called Albion. This track contains a reversed vocal sample of US group Andain's 2003 progressive vocal trance hit Beautiful Things. Albion was released in December 2007 from the Dutch trance label In Trance We Trust along with a radio edited version of the original track.

artist.name: Solarstone & Orkidea
artist.bio: A collaboration between Orkidea and Solar Stone. The only track they produced together is Slowmotion and it appeared on Orkidea's Metaverse (2008) album.

artist.name: Adam K & Soha vs. Marcella Woods
Hawk
artist.bio: There are 5 artists with the name Hawk.  1)Chicago band serving straight up rock'n'roll with roots in garage and Americana. Their music is "inspired by 'the badass orange Camaro my brother had when we were growing up' Hawkins says, 'We'd drive around, getting stoned, listening to AC/DC, Zeppelin, Humble Pie, and the Stones...you know, REAL music. That's where these songs came out of.'"   2) "Hawk" is the main alias for the norwegian producer & dj H

artist.name: Claudia Cazacu
artist.bio:
Moving to the UK from Romania 7 years ago Claudia Cazacu soon found herself at home in the London club scene. Attending events week after week it wasn?t long before she decided her destiny was a life behind the decks. 
 Launching her career in 2006 Claudia Cazacu has in a short space of time propelled herself to become the most anticipated new DJ on the scene. 
 UK appearances have included The Gallery, Inside Out, Goodgreef, Sundissential, Riot! & Wildchild.

artist.name: Carl B feat. Elsa Hill
artist.bio: Having recently remixed high profile tracks for big names in the trance industry such as Armas, Acues & Elitist, Selu Vibra, Summer Sessions, Armin van Buuren and JPL, Carl B (Carl Barrdahl) has definitely merited his growing reputation as a trance remix specialist! Yet he has also written and produced quality tunes of his own in his Carl B guise, including the tracks Solitude and Social Suicide. Barrdahl also has an alias called PEAK, and in 2006 he collaborated with Joni Ljungqvist on a project named Peak vs.

artist.name: Mr. Sam vs. Human Resource
artist.bio:
Mr Sam was born during the mid seventies just as punk was emerging from beneath the ruins of stadium-rock, he grew up in a small idyllic village near the Belgian border in the north of France. 
 From an early age, Sam had no escape from his parents own musically mixed cocktails of Giorgio Moroder, Klaus Schulz combined with a dash of Elvis Presley. 
 Through this heavy involuntary dose of electronically initiated influence, he developed an early fascination for squelchy synthesizer sounds and after buying

artist.name: DJ Shultz & The Immoral Monkeys vs. Elad Efrati
Andy Hunter
artist.bio: Andy Hunter

artist.name: Bart Claessen
artist.bio: Barthezz (Bart Claessen) was born in the Netherlands on January 22nd, 1980, always loved music and got his first piano lessons at the age of seven. Impressed by electronic music at the end of the nineties, he worked hard during high school to buy his first studio equipment: a synth, a sampler, an Atari computer and a small mixer. With this equipment, he changed the attic of his parental house into a small studio and there it all began..

artist.name: Armin van Buuren with Gabriel & Dresden
D-Mark
artist.bio: There are at least two bands with the name D: 1. D is a Japanese visual kei band which formed in March 2003 by ASAGI (vocalist; formerly of JE*REVIENS), Ruiza (guitarist; formerly of Distray, LAYBIAL) and Sin (guitarist; formerly of with sexy, Vasalla). They were all originally members of Syndrome, a band formed on January 16 2000 by Kisaki (formerly of La:Sadie's, Stella Maria and others), but the band had later disbanded in 2002.

artist.name: Armin van Buuren feat. Jacqueline Govaerts
artist.bio: Armin van Buuren (born December 25, 1976) is a trance music producer and DJ. He was born in Leiden, Netherlands, but grew up in Koudekerk aan den Rijn. He has been voted #1 Dj in the world by Dj Mag's Annual Top 100 Djs of the Year this year. He was also the #1 for 2007.  Armin van Buuren pursued his career as a professional musician despite the promise of a career in law in his native country, the Netherlands, where he completed his law degree in 2004. Armin started working as a DJ in a local night club called Nexus, finished high school in 1995 and went on to university to study law.

artist.name: Armin van Buuren feat. Vera Ostrova
Blank & Jones feat. Bernard Sumner
artist.bio:
Blank & Jones is a trance duo based in Cologne, Germany, consisting of Piet Blank (Jan Pieter Blank) and DJ Jaspa Jones (Rene Runge), with help from producer Andy Kaufhold. They have released eight albums and more than 16 singles since their first single release "Sunrise" in 1997.  They also continue to DJ a couple of radio shows in Germany.
 _________________________________________________________________

artist.name: Robert Nickson feat. Elsa Hill
artist.bio: If you visit a club it probably won't be too long before you are hearing one of Robert's productions. Robert is currently one of the most highly sought after producers of the moment. His productions also appear on nearly every dance CD that hits the shops. There's no escaping this guy, he's here to stay.  Robert's background is a multi-national affair with his Father from England and Mother from Norway.

artist.name: Esmaye
artist.bio:
"In the centre of your inner beauty
 Lies a frame of what is meant to be
 Almost hidden in the darkest forest
 Lies your inner destiny"  From:

artist.name: DJ Shultz & Immoral Monkeys vs. Elad Efrati
Dreas
artist.bio: 1) Hip-hop producer from Chicago, USA.  Recent production credits include: Mestizo, Robust, Kool Keith, and Kid Sister.  2) Dreas?s interest for dance music started in the early 90s. Back then it was Eurodance that first got his attention way before he had ever heard of today?s trance sound.  Back in those days Dreas had also learnt to DJ. At an early age he started hosting school parties to raise money for his class trips.  Over the years Dreas?s technical ability on the decks has greatly improved to the world class standards that they are today.

artist.name: Wendy & Lisa
artist.bio: When Prince broke up the Revolution in 1986, guitarist Wendy Melvoin and keyboardist Lisa Coleman, friends since childhood, decided to team up for a new musical project. The two had grown up together in Los Angeles, where both of their fathers were session musicians and encouraged their musical development from a young age. Coleman joined the Revolution in 1979 for Dirty Mind, and Melvoin signed on in 1984; in addition to their instrumental skills, the two also provided some of Prince's arrangements.

artist.name: Cold Blue
artist.bio: Cold Blue is the 22 year old Tobias Schuh from Germany who had his break through in 2007 with the big melodic trancer "11 Days" which is still being played worldwide by a lot of DJs. His music is full of emotions and often his euphoric melodies give you goosebumbs when listening to it at home or on the dancefloor as well. Make sure to watch out for this guy!

artist.name: Cosmic Gate feat. Roxanne Emery
artist.bio: Cosmic Gate is a German trance, progressive trance and hard trance duo made up of Claus Terhoeven (aka Nic Chagall) and Stefan Bossems (DJ Bossi). They are best known for their singles "Exploration of Space", "The Drums", and "The Truth." Cosmic Gate has done remixes for popular DJs including DJ Tiësto, Armin van Buuren, and Ferry Corsten. Cosmic Gate's heavy, analogue trance sound is considered by many to be the definition of hard trance. Discography Albums * Rhythm & Drums (2001) * No More Sleep (2002)

artist.name: Matt Hardwick vs. Gulf
artist.bio: Matt Hardwick ,is the epitome of an international DJ. He lives and breathes electronic music. Since his inception into club culture Matt Hardwick has completely immersed himself in it. His rapid ascendency into dance music with the global phenomenon that is Gatecrasher is something which has been well documented. The association with Gatecrasher, the first of many landmark achievements in his career...

artist.name: DT8 Project feat. Roxanne Wilde
artist.bio: DT8 Project is the brainchild of legendary producer Darren Tate, the man who gave the world Jurgen Vries, Angelic, Citizen Caned, Orion and many other massive cross over dance hits. The project was created with the goal of creating electronic music that married intelligent songs, sung from the heart, with emotional chords and cutting edge production. This was the very heart and soul of Darren?s desire to bring a modern but truly touching listening experience to the general public, and so the act bearing an acronym of his own name was born.

artist.name: Adam White vs. Rozza
artist.bio: Hailing from London, Adam White has been a recognised professional DJ for the past 10 years. Adams thriving musical interests led to the successful completion of his Grade 8 piano by the age of 16. Adams continued enthusiasm for music led to the study of Music Technology at HND level. His time at college initiated his immense enthusiasm for dance music, and subsequent passion for DJing. The recent years have seen Adams DJing career excel to a highly professional level, resulting in regular bookings at some of the worlds most prestigious clubs including Ministry Of Sound...

artist.name: Alex M.O.R.P.H.
artist.bio:
With gigs all over the globe and an impressive array of highly respected productions, Alex M.O.R.P.H. is one of today’s most wanted producers/remixers in the uplifting trance genre. He made over 70 Remixes for fellow artists and released more than 20 own productions as well as big collaborations, which all found their way into the record boxes of the worlds’ top jocks.
 He always tries to show his versatility in multiple aspects, including a well-known radioshow (HeavensGate on Air) and a solo artist debut album. He also teams up with Woody van Eyden to perform legendary Back2Back sets.

artist.name: Mind-X
artist.bio: 1. Some discoband from somewhere. 2. Punk band from Oakland, CA. Members of Total Abuse, Never Healed, Ham & The Chokers, Lights Out and Streetwalkers. 3. Old italian post-punk band.

artist.name: Hernan Cattaneo & John Tonks
artist.bio: Born in Buenos Aires, Hern

artist.name: Parker & Hanson
artist.bio: SB Parker was born January of 1980 in Flatbush, Brooklyn. Alvin J. Hanson was born in May of 1979 in the South Bronx. These New Yorkers are men of the streets, intimately familiar with its codes and its violence, but still, Parker and Hanson are incredibly intelligent and deliberate men.  Both were born into the notorious New York drug dyansty during the early '80s. Parker & Hanson both lost close friends at early ages. They were raised without mothers and fathers, as both their parents were found dead in different situation under mysterious circumstances before they could hit their teens.

artist.name: Manuel Le Saux
artist.bio:
Manuel Le Saux started his carrer in 1989 when he received his first turntables.
 One year later he became resident dj at Palladium Club in Rome and stayed there for over 10 years.
 In 1996 he’s been Guest Dj in many famous Italian Clubs like Red Zone, Area 51, Exogroove, Gheodrome, Hollywood and Cyborg and became one of most popular dj all over the Nation working alongside with many famous italian dj and in front of thousand massive people.

artist.name: Above & Beyond feat. Hannah Thomas
artist.bio: Above & Beyond are a trance music group formed in 2000. The group is famous for remixes and their own productions. The group's tracks are regularly played by well-known DJs, such as Tiësto, Armin van Buuren and Paul van Dyk. They are also known under other aliases, like Tranquility Base, OceanLab, Dirt Devils and Rollerball. Jono Grant and Paavo Siljam

artist.name: Carl B feat. Tiff Lacey
artist.bio: Having recently remixed high profile tracks for big names in the trance industry such as Armas, Acues & Elitist, Selu Vibra, Summer Sessions, Armin van Buuren and JPL, Carl B (Carl Barrdahl) has definitely merited his growing reputation as a trance remix specialist! Yet he has also written and produced quality tunes of his own in his Carl B guise, including the tracks Solitude and Social Suicide. Barrdahl also has an alias called PEAK, and in 2006 he collaborated with Joni Ljungqvist on a project named Peak vs.

artist.name: Andy Moor vs. Orkidea
artist.bio: Andy Moor joins forces with Orkidea, one of Finland's top DJs and producers. The story goes that Moor needed a new angle on some melodies and basslines he had written and, being the busy man that he is, he drafted in Orkidea to help add the finishing touches. The result is "YearZero", a record that has been doing the rounds for a while now and has clearly won over many trance followers already, breaking into Armin van Buuren's A State of Trance end of year top 10 of 2006, and now finally getting an official release in January on digital, CD, and vinyl.

artist.name: Greg Downey
artist.bio: Greg Downey began DJing over 6 years ago and in this time has established himself firmly among the best young DJs in the UK. Born in Belfast - Ireland, Greg developed a taste for tougher electronic dance music from a young age. He has reflected this in his unique style which combines underground and uplifting trance with elements of techno? The result... An Explosive sound!  2007 has been an amazing year so far for Greg? He has a full summer ahead with dates across the UK including top notch clubs Lush...

artist.name: Underwater
artist.bio: Ethereal/trip-hop band 'underwater' released several EPs and LPs, including the hugely successful, 'RED.' single and their greatest artistic success, 'This Is Not A Film'. Founding members Jeremy Wilkins and Melissa Mileski own recording/publishing rights and usage of the name 'underwater' in both the US and UK.  Other musicians, past and present, include George Lewis, Nikolas Ahlstam, Alec Irvin, Matthew Jeanes, Deborah Lutz, Daniel Rosen, Dan Dixon, and Denver Bon. In 1998, they recorded 'I Could Lose' with producer Chris Vrenna (Nine Inch Nails).

artist.name: Midway
artist.bio: There are multiple artists with this name: 1) Ralph Barendse is the man behind Midway, and he produces hard trance music for the In Trance We Trust label under this alias. The first Midway track - Monkey Forest - was released in 2002. Inca was then released a year later, and in 2004, probably his most famous tune to date Amazon was released twice, including one whole vinyl release devoted to remixes from Mesh, Plastic Angel and Sander Van Dien. Barendse concentrated on other projects throughout 2005 but he returned to the Midway project in 2006, releasing a track named Cobra.

artist.name: Sean Marx
artist.bio: sean marx hails from dublin, ireland and for the past few years has slowly but surely been carving his own path into the electronic music scene.  what started out as a minor interest quickly developed into a new avenue opening up which sean sought to explore, and potentially conquer. the launch of the internet was a catalyst for sean, as it allowed him to explore many artists, sounds and styles outside of Ireland's narrow minded and extremely insular music scene.

artist.name: Squash 84
artist.bio: Squash 84 is a new venture by finnish producers Matti Heininen and Erkka Lempi

artist.name: Mario Basanov & Vidis
artist.bio: Mario Basanov & vidis gathered together and made a "Test" Next their creation is feat. Jazzu called I'll Be Gone

artist.name: J.O.C.
artist.bio: J.O.C. is an alias of John O'Callaghan

artist.name: Nish
artist.bio: Nish, short of Ken-Ichiro Ishi, is one of Japan's leading hard trance DJs and also a regular guest at Yoji Biomehanika's parties. He started his DJ career about 8 years ago, and has been involved in producing the club music and live PA for about 3 or 4 years. After many releases across a number of labels in Japan, Nish started the invasion of UK by releasing "Slap Down" from AlienTrax in 1998. He had many successive releases mainly from the UK labels and all releases got also strong support among the DJs worldwide.

artist.name: Eric Prydz
artist.bio: Eric Prydz is a Swedish DJ and producer best known for his 2004 hit single "Call On Me", his remix of Pink Floyd's "Another Brick In The Wall" (known as "Proper Education") and more recently the anthem "Pjanoo". He also releases music under the aliases of Cirez D, Pryda and Sheridan. Prydz produces electronic music which falls into a variety of sub genres, most notably house (Including electro house and tech house), minimal and techno. Aside from producing music Prydz also runs the record labels Pryda, Pryda Friends, and Mouseville, which release most of his own music.

artist.name: DJ Shog
artist.bio: DJ Shog was born in Hamburg, Germany in 1976. In the middle of the nineties he began to develop his interest for electronic music and deejaying. After the usual first steps at school- and private-parties DJ Shog entered several DJ-Contests, which took him to his first residency jobs in the north of Germany.  His breakthrough into the world?s music scene came with the start of his own double-cd compilation-series "Technics-DJ-Set". Therefore one CD was mixed by himself and the other one by well-known guests like Cosmic Gate, Dumonde, Talla 2XLC, Green Court and many others.

artist.name: Markus Shulz feat. Dauby
artist.bio: You probably want Markus Schulz.

artist.name: Richard Grey
artist.bio:
Real Name: Richard Jacquin 
 Profile: Richard Grey is a DJ & Producer. He contributed to the world success of the “French Touch” at 28 years. His discography which forces the respect. 
 With an early love of music, heavily influenced by his father’s record collection, Richard grew up on classic Jazz, Funk and Disco acts such as George Duke, The Crusaders and Chic. 
 Soon, he finally began to record solo in ’99 with 'I Need You' on France’s Cyber Productions. This came to the attention of Erick Morillo who immediately picked up the highly successful 'Deep Down' for Subliminal.

artist.name: Chad Cisneros
artist.bio: Chad Cisneros was born in Houston, Texas, in April of 1980. Having grown up in a musical family, Chad's love of rhythm and sound was sparked at a very early age. His mother and her four sisters had always sung, traveled, and recorded, and his grandmother was not only a singer herself, but a piano player and teacher, and had Chad playing tunes at the age of five. Although he did not continue to study piano technique and theory, his love for music grew stronger with age. While many people love to listen to music, Chad knew from early on that he had a burning desire to create and compose music.

artist.name: Alex Costa
artist.bio: FLASH digital artist www.myspace.com/flashrec

artist.name: Erik de Koning
artist.bio: Erik the King, also known as Enrico, has been an all around dance-produce for 12 years and known by the public through "WaterVerve", a production with Mark van Dale. Their production "Higher and more high" (with DJ Jurgen) reached the number 5 position of the Dutch top 40 and became world-wide brought out.   Perhaps one is yet most under the impression of his releases under the name "Three Drives" (together with DJ Barrel TB). "Greece 2000", "Sunset on Ibiza", "Carrera 2" and "Air traffic", his single titles that (certainly in the UK) grew into club-anthems.

artist.name: Adam Nickey
artist.bio: Adam Nickey a.k.a. Kai Del Noi - music producer and Dj. He was born in Poland.He's 25 years old. He's been interested in music for a long time. His adventure with making music started in 1997. Nowadays he makes music for the people who wants to listen to the tracks full of emotions. He makes music in two different styles so he has two nicknames. In the past as Kai Del Noi he had a lot of released in Poland.

artist.name: N2O
artist.bio: Krzysztof Pretkiewicz aka N2O/Nitrous Oxide was born in Poznan (Poland) in 1984. He first listened to electronic music in the early `90s. Artists such as Jean Michel Jare, Mike Oldfield and the Depeche Mode were the first to make such big impression on him that he knew this is the genre of music he loves to hear. He started creating his own music in 1998 when he discovered that tracks can be created on his PC. It became his hobby and he spent all his free time making new sounds and tracks. Krzysztof doesn`t have any musical education and he doesn`t play on any instrument.

artist.name: Simon & Shaker vs. Groove Garcia
artist.bio: They began their artistic career, after entering in touch with DJ Dimas, with the maxi 'Outstreet' under the pseudonymous "The Sundayprayers". From this moment, Simon Garcia y Karim Shaker have been evolving as producers reaching a musical enviable quality.

artist.name: Mark Pledger & Matt Hardwick feat. Melinda Gareh
Tatana feat. Stephan Maria
artist.bio:
Tatana (Tatana Sterba, born 7th October 1976 in former Czechoslovakia) is a swiss Trance producer and dj.
 Tatana is one of the most successful artists of the 2000s in the Swiss charts, with several successful trance albums since her debut album 24 Carat was released in February 2000.  After having the adorable voice of Jael (Lunik, Delerium, Mich Gerber) singing on her last years smash hit 'Always on my mind', Tatana chose to collaborate for her new single 'All that I feel' with another star of the Swiss music scene.

artist.name: Ferrin & Low
artist.bio: Josh Ferrin & Chris Low are two german producers with a love for uplifting and powerful, energetic trance. They produce tracks with german trance legend Alex M.O.R.P.H. (Unification, New Harvest), as well as single Ferrin & Low productions, such as the successful trance bomb Breeze, released on Fenology Records in 2006. www.ferrinandlow.com www.fenology.com

artist.name: Boom Jinx feat. Key
artist.bio: Despite a limited number of releases since Boom Jinx's inception in 2005,

artist.name: Funabashi feat. Angelina
artist.bio:
TOM PORCELL
 Tom Porcell fell in love with electronic music already in the mid nineties. Music was always his true passion and a dream became true when he started to do his own productions back in 1997.   After releasing some stuff on German underground labels he had his major breakthrough in 2001 with Norman Bass "How You Like Bass", a massive big room anthem which was released on Ministry of Sound in the UK.

artist.name: Anjunabeats
artist.bio: Anjunabeats is Jono Grant and Paavo Siljamaki. They were later joined by Tony to become Above & Beyond.  Anjunabeats was formed when Jono Grant and Paavo Siljamaki met at Westminster University and discovered a mutual love of electronic music. The pair kicked off the label in 2000 with ?Anjunabeats Volume 1?, a massive club success which instantly ear-pricked the likes of Pete Tong, Paul Oakenfold and Paul van Dyk. The bomb had dropped and the Anjunabeats name was firmly on the map.

artist.name: Jonathan Allyn
artist.bio: Jonathan Allyn has been consistently recognized by the media, its artists and crowds across the nation for his tough yet melodically progressive, techno trance DJ style and productions.  Globally his productions have crossed the boundaries of the United States and have been recognized by some of the World's top artists such as Christopher Lawrence, Noel Sanger, Nicholas Bennison, Above & Beyond, Andy Moor and many more.

artist.name: Vibrasphere
artist.bio: Vibrasphere are Rickard Bergl

artist.name: Madonna
artist.bio: Madonna Louise Veronica Ciccone (born August 16, 1958 in Bay City, Michigan, United States), known as Madonna, is a dance-pop singer-songwriter, record and film producer, dancer, actress, author and fashion icon. She is noted for her ambitious music videos and stage performances as well as using political, sexual, and religious themes in her work. In 2000, Guinness World Records listed Madonna as the most successful female recording artist of all time...

artist.name: Junkie XL feat. Willoughby & Nicole Morier
artist.bio: Junkie XL (also known as JXL) is musician Tom Holkenborg, born in Lichtenvoorde, The Netherlands on 8 December 1967. After producing and touring with the Dutch group Weekend at Waikiki, he split with them in 1995 and began writing his own tracks as Junkie XL in 1997. He has worked with many electronic music artists, including Sander Kleinenberg, DJ Tiësto and Sasha. In 2002 he left The Netherlands to live and work in the United States where he works on soundtracks for movies and computer games.

artist.name: Luminary
artist.bio: Now defunct collaboration between british producer Laurence Rapaccioli (Arksun) and Ashley Tomberlin, a previously unknown vocalist and musician from the United States. After completing a few initial tracks, they lost touch until the fall of 2003 when they began to take another look at the music they had created the previous year. With a renewed sense of purpose, the musical partnership finally gelled, and Luminary was born. They created and released 4 productions together, and uploaded one final track to their Myspace page upon the announcement of their split in October, 2007:

artist.name: Ben Gold feat. Senadee
artist.bio: At just 23 years old Ben Gold is one of the most multi talented names in the electronic dance scene. Ben combines a highly acclaimed career as a leading studio engineer with that of one of the brightest young stars in the trance scene, djing at some of the worlds leading clubs alongside world class dj's who all regularly fill their cd wallets with his latest works.  Ben?s weekdays range from engineering for the likes of Judge Jules to providing killer remixes and mashups for the highly competitive house music scene and its leading labels such as DATA and Hit! Records.

artist.name: Sami Saari
artist.bio:
Sami Saari is a Finnish funk/soul artist. He performed in Veeti & Velvets before his solo career.
 He began his solo career in 1997 with the album 'Do Re Mi' and continued to 1999 with the album 'Sam The Man'.

artist.name: Luke Terry & Kopi Luwak feat. Tiff Lacey
Sebastian Brandt
artist.bio:
18 years young Sebastian Brandts professional music career started off in early 2005 from hooking up with super producer Marcus Schossow for a collaboration project. 
 The result was the project Under Sun with their respected summer smasher 'Capoeira', released on Armada Music.
 Later that year Sebastian met Ludvig Holm at a party and they decided to collaborate aswell.
 Selu Vibra (Sebastian Ludvig Brandt) - Stargazing was signed to Dj Precisions label Somatic Sense and got hammered by them all.

artist.name: Marco Demark feat. Casey Barnes
artist.bio: Marco Demark is an Italian born house music producer who now resides on the Gold Coast of Australia.

artist.name: Tegan & Sara
artist.bio: Tegan Quin and Sara Quin (born in Calgary, Alberta, Canada on September 19, 1980) are identical twins and Canadian singer-songwriters, performing as Tegan and Sara. They initially played as Plunk in 1995, and lacked a drummer and bass player. In 1997, they both used their school’s recording studio to record two demo albums: "Who's in Your Band?" and "Play Day". In 1998, they made an early breakthrough by winning Garage Warz Battle of the Bands, a local music competition in Calgary.

artist.name: Li Kwan
artist.bio: Matt Darey, who is from Leicester, England, has been a trance music DJ since 1994 and is considered one of the founders of the trance genre.  He is also a member of Lost Tribe with Red Jerry. He is perhaps best known for his work in the Euphoria trance series and for "Gamemaster" (as Lost Tribe) and his remixes of and Agnelli & Nelson's "El Ni

artist.name: Ferry Corsten feat. Howard Jones
artist.bio: Ferry Corsten is a Dutch DJ, producer and recorder who first started out in 1991 producing underground hardcore gabber tracks, he soon expanded into clubhouse and trance music. But don't put Ferry into the trance corner, because his sound encompasses several genres of electronic music. In 1999 Ferry Corsten was voted Best Producer of the Year at the Ericsson Muzik Award in London. In 2000, he was awarded Best Remix for Adagio for Strings (Ferry Corsten remix) at the Dancestar 2000 awards.

artist.name: Store N Forward
artist.bio: Store n Forward are Christian Steinweg and Thomas Boldt, German trance producers and DJs. They are also known as 'Boldt & Steinweg'. The roots of Store N Forward go back to the year 1998 when two young men from Hamburg, Germany got to know each other by chance. Interning in the same firm and sharing the interest of the "new" electronic sound, trance, Thomas Boldt and Christian Steinweg became friends quickly. Store N Forward was finally founded in 2001. As the years have gone by, not only has their studio developed, but also the quality and sound of their music.

artist.name: Carlo Resoort
artist.bio: Carlo Resoort originally began working with Jan De Vos when they found a mutual interest in dance music. The two spent all of their free time in the studio, and later Jan went on to become "DJ 4 Strings" while Carlo headed 4 Strings. All of his albums as 4 Strings have been released in the U.S. via Ultra Records.  Carlo had his first hit with "Day Time", and later released "Take Me Away (Into the Night)" his second hit.

artist.name: Envio
artist.bio: Ashkan Fardost is an 18 year old wizkid set to take the trance scene by storm! He has Persian roots but was born and raised in Stockholm, Sweden. Music has always been a large part of Ashkan's life and for as long as he can remember he has been influenced by sounds and melodies. His early passion for music and musicians was obvious and at the tender age of 5 he became amazed by the works of Jean Michel Jarre.

artist.name: Seth Hutton feat. Judie Tzuke
artist.bio: Seth is a DJ, producer, and songwriter from the northwestern United States. He has written music for several MTV programs, collaborated with legendary number one UK recording artists Judie Tzuke and Kirsty Hawkshaw, and is a national resident DJ on Seattle?s C89.5 "The Vortex" with Drew Bailey. He has produced tracks for Malicious Recordings in Tampa, Florida as well as Captured Music in Sweden and has written lyrics for Armada artists.

artist.name: Mike Mikhjian
artist.bio: At the age of only 18, Mike Mikhjian has set himself up as one of the worlds youngest and biggest upcoming producers & DJ's in electronic dance music. He discovered electronic dance music at the very young age of 10 and was intrigued with how it was made and set out to create his own sounds. Over the years he spent most of his time producing countless tracks that were favored by friends and family.

artist.name: DT8 Project
artist.bio: DT8 Project is the brainchild of legendary producer Darren Tate, the man who gave the world Jurgen Vries, Angelic, Citizen Caned, Orion and many other massive cross over dance hits. The project was created with the goal of creating electronic music that married intelligent songs, sung from the heart, with emotional chords and cutting edge production. This was the very heart and soul of Darren’s desire to bring a modern but truly touching listening experience to the general public, and so the act bearing an acronym of his own name was born.

artist.name: Aalto
artist.bio: Behind the project Aalto are the 2 Finnish producers Miika Eloranta and Paavo Siljam

artist.name: Armin vs. M.I.K.E.
artist.bio: Armin van Buuren (born December 25, 1976) is a trance music producer and DJ. He was born in Leiden, Netherlands, but grew up in Koudekerk aan den Rijn. He has been voted #1 Dj in the world by Dj Mag's Annual Top 100 Djs of the Year this year. He was also the #1 for 2007.  Armin van Buuren pursued his career as a professional musician despite the promise of a career in law in his native country, the Netherlands, where he completed his law degree in 2004. Armin started working as a DJ in a local night club called Nexus, finished high school in 1995 and went on to university to study law.

artist.name: Above & Beyond feat. Zo
artist.bio: Above & Beyond are a trance music group formed in 2000. The group is famous for remixes and their own productions. The group's tracks are regularly played by well-known DJs, such as Tiësto, Armin van Buuren and Paul van Dyk. They are also known under other aliases, like Tranquility Base, OceanLab, Dirt Devils and Rollerball. Jono Grant and Paavo Siljam

artist.name: Sufjan Stevens vs. Signalrunners
artist.bio: Sufjan Stevens (born July 1, 1975) is an American musician, songwriter, and multi-instrumentalist from Petoskey, Michigan. He is known for his lyrically focused and instrumentally rich songs that often relate to faith and family. He has enjoyed wide critical success in the United States. He is considered part of the folk revival in indie pop, but his influences are very broad, including electronica, the jazz of Vince Guaraldi, and the academic minimalism of Steve Reich and Philip Glass.

artist.name: Above & Beyond feat. Ashley Tomberlin
artist.bio: Above & Beyond are a trance music group formed in 2000. The group is famous for remixes and their own productions. The group's tracks are regularly played by well-known DJs, such as Tiësto, Armin van Buuren and Paul van Dyk. They are also known under other aliases, like Tranquility Base, OceanLab, Dirt Devils and Rollerball. Jono Grant and Paavo Siljam

artist.name: Ti
artist.bio: Born as Tijs Verwest in Breda, Netherlands, Ti

artist.name: Filterfunk
artist.bio: Filterfunk is house project from UK. It cooperation between Sander van Doorn, Hi Tack and Tom Novy .The biggest hit was remake of The Police - S.O.S Message in the bottle.

artist.name: Cara Dillon vs. 2Devine
artist.bio: Cara Dillon was born in 1975 in Dungiven, County Derry, Northern Ireland. She has formerly been a member of the folk groups 'Oige' and 'Equation'. She and Sam Lakeman (whom she married in 2002) left Equation and signed to Blanco y Negro records going under the name 'Polar Star'. Dillon released her eponymous first solo album in 2001, a mixture of tradtional songs with 2 original compositions. This album garnered the best newcomer award and the best song for 'Black Is the Colour' at the 2002 Radio 2 folk awards.

artist.name: Boom Jinx
artist.bio: Despite a limited number of releases since Boom Jinx's inception in 2005,

artist.name: Whiteroom
artist.bio: There are two artists with the name Whiteroom.   The first is collaboration of Adam White & Andy Moor. Awesome instrumental trance.  The second hails from Montreal Canada as an answer to this generations Radiohead:  Bio:   Sunlight is made up of a full spectrum of colors. As it reflects off an object, certain shades of light are absorbed and others are reflected. These reflected colors form the images that reach our eyes. Unfiltererd White Light contains every image you have seen and will ever see.

artist.name: Britney Spears
artist.bio: Britney Jean Spears (born December 2, 1981 is an Emmy and Grammy-winning multi-platinum American pop singer, songwriter, dancer and occasional actress, director and author from Kentwood, Louisiana, United States. She's ranked the eighth best-selling female musician in America and has sold more than 85 million albums and 35 million singles worldwide, with nine #1 singles and 6 #1 albums in the United World Chart. Spears also holds the title to multiple Guinness World Records.

artist.name: Above & Beyond feat. Richard Bedford
artist.bio: Above & Beyond are a trance music group formed in 2000. The group is famous for remixes and their own productions. The group's tracks are regularly played by well-known DJs, such as Tiësto, Armin van Buuren and Paul van Dyk. They are also known under other aliases, like Tranquility Base, OceanLab, Dirt Devils and Rollerball. Jono Grant and Paavo Siljam

artist.name: Mark Pledger vs. Matt Hardwick feat. Melinda Gareh
Bolier & Coenraad
artist.bio: A collaboration between dutch dj's Leon Bolier and Cliff Coenraad. Leon is well known from singles like "Back in the Days" released as Surpresa and "Beyond" released as Inner Stories. He made also several mixes with his brother Bart under the Subsphere guise. Cliff made in 2005 some mixes under the name Astatic. In 2006 they made 2 tracks, called "The Mighty Ducks" and "Mohawk". Both are releasing in Intuition Recordings label.

artist.name: Stephen J. Kroos
artist.bio: Stephen J. Kroos is a talented producer and DJ from the Netherlands. He grew up listening to the likes of Depeche Mode, OMD, Jarre, Kraftwerk and Art Of Noise and found home with Electronic Dance Music in 1988 during the Summer of Love. He soon found himself buying decks and started Djing, securing his first residency in Amsterdams Roxy club, from where his Djing talent went from strength to strength with regular gigs at clubs like Pacha and Ministry Of Sound.

artist.name: Mike Koglin vs. Jono Grant
artist.bio: Mike Koglin burst onto the scene in 1998 with his club anthem and UK top20 hit 'The Silence', one of the defining tracks of the UK trance phenomenon which put Mike firmly onto the map as one of the key players in dance music.  Since then the Grammy-nominated Producer, Remixer and DJ has has released aconstant string of productions, under his own name or under one of his various aliases, as well as over 70 remixes in the last 7 years.

artist.name: Nitromethane
artist.bio: Nitromethane is used in the amination of 3,4-methylenedioxy-phenyl-2-propanone, which is a precursor of MDMA, used instead of the heavily watched methylamine in order to avoid detection by the authorities. As such was the perfect name for a side project for Above & Beyond's Tony McGuinness (above, foreground) when he's with his brother, the chemically clever Liam (above, on orange Lilo).  The McGuinness brothers have been in bands together for years and started spending the odd night knocking up dance tracks. "Time To Die" came out of one such session in 1999.

artist.name: Young Parisians feat. Ben Lost
artist.bio: Young Parisians is a group formed by two British producers; Rich Mowatt & Andy Bury. They are better and more famously known as Solar Stone.

artist.name: Super8
artist.bio: There are two artists or projects named Super8, one from Finland and one from France: 1) Super8 from Finland: Alias of the Finnish DJ and producer Miika Eloranta who is also one half of the project Aalto . Miika has produced a string of successful remixes, including Rollerball "Albinoni", Space Brothers "One More Chance" and the monstrously enormous remix of Aalto's "Rush". His first solo release "Alba/Dawn" blew everyone away in 2004, with two quality slices of trance mayhem cemented his fanbase right across the world and earned huge support from the likes of Above & Beyond...

artist.name: P.O.S.
artist.bio: There are currently several Artists using the name P.O.S.: 1) P.O.S. began as a punk rock musician. In high school. A rapper on the label Rhymesayers Entertainment, P.O.S is an original hip-hop artist, combining heartfelt and meaningful lyrics with powerful melodies on various instruments. P.O.S is a member of Doomtree and Building Better Bombs. He has only two full lengths out at the moment, titled 'Ipecac Neat' and 'Audition', and is amazing in concert.

artist.name: Smith & Pledger
artist.bio: Smith & Pledger are London-based producer/DJ's Olie Smith & Mark Pledger. Olie and Mark met whilst at Westminster University in 2000 and soon set up a studio together. Since then a series of high profile solo releases and remixes have cemented the duo's position as one of most exciting new dance music talents in the UK.   Smith & Pledger's style is best categorised as classy and melodic, leading Mixmag to recently describe them as "the best thing happen in trance this year".

artist.name: Yilmaz Altanhan
artist.bio: Trance producer that's currently living in Melbourne, Australia. He took some time to pull it back together. His track called Eighties is world famous amongst trance dj's around the globe.

artist.name: Mike Shiver
artist.bio: Producer, DJ & Label Manager; Mike Shiver has been one of the most talked-about upcoming talents over the last years. Since breaking onto the scene in 2003 with one of the year's most exciting productions: 'Mike Shiver - Feelings (Lost Language)', Mike has worked with labels like Armada Music, Nebula Records, Euphonic Records, Lost Language and the list just goes on.  December 2003 saw Mike start his own label, Captured Music (www.capured,nu). The first release on Captured 'Sonicvibe & Mike Shiver - Lunation' received massive support from many of the world top DJ?s.

artist.name: Matt Hardwick vs. Smith & Pledger
artist.bio: Matt Hardwick ,is the epitome of an international DJ. He lives and breathes electronic music. Since his inception into club culture Matt Hardwick has completely immersed himself in it. His rapid ascendency into dance music with the global phenomenon that is Gatecrasher is something which has been well documented. The association with Gatecrasher, the first of many landmark achievements in his career...

artist.name: Kaste
artist.bio: Kaste (aka Dyyni) consists of two Finnish producers Jani Kervinen and Mika Savela and are renowned for their uplifting sounds and emotional melodies.  Before Kaste was born, Jani made his own music under the alias Mystery Islands, and it has become one of the biggest names on the Finnish Trance scene. Jani still produces under this alias, as well as producing new tracks with Mika. Mika is also no stranger himself to producing his own tunes under the aliases Clublimit and Soundfall.

artist.name: Breakfast
artist.bio: There are 2 artists with the name "Breakfast": 1. Casey Keyworth is a new upcoming producer for Ferry Corsten's own label 'Flashover Recordings' www.caseykeyworth.com. 2. A Japanese thrash/hardcore band. They also use about every genre of music you could think of. www.geocities.jp/breakfast_oneweek/

artist.name: Above & Beyond vs. Unkle & Petter
artist.bio: Above & Beyond are a trance music group formed in 2000. The group is famous for remixes and their own productions. The group's tracks are regularly played by well-known DJs, such as Tiësto, Armin van Buuren and Paul van Dyk. They are also known under other aliases, like Tranquility Base, OceanLab, Dirt Devils and Rollerball. Jono Grant and Paavo Siljam

artist.name: Endre
artist.bio: Endre is Swedish producer, Alex Sj

artist.name: Cosmic Gate feat. Denise Rivera
artist.bio: Cosmic Gate is a German trance, progressive trance and hard trance duo made up of Claus Terhoeven (aka Nic Chagall) and Stefan Bossems (DJ Bossi). They are best known for their singles "Exploration of Space", "The Drums", and "The Truth." Cosmic Gate has done remixes for popular DJs including DJ Tiësto, Armin van Buuren, and Ferry Corsten. Cosmic Gate's heavy, analogue trance sound is considered by many to be the definition of hard trance. Discography Albums * Rhythm & Drums (2001) * No More Sleep (2002)

artist.name: Summer Sessions
artist.bio: Originally born in Haifa, Israel, Ron Bercovitch moved to Toronto, Canada at the age of four. He was brought up traditionally, enjoying a typical childhood. Surprisingly, he was not drawn to music until he was 16. He disliked and avoided music while growing up. It was not until his brother introduced him to EDM that he started to develop an understanding and appreciation for music. The genre of Trance, with its' increasing popularity became Ron's favourite type of music, and his love for this music led him to collect the famous Trancemaster compilations.

artist.name: Tilt
artist.bio: Tilt is a name used by four different musical groups:   1. A Polish rock group, consisting of <a href="http://www.last.fm/music/+noredirect/Tomasz+Lipi%C5%84ski" class="bbcode_artist">Tomasz Lipi

artist.name: Art Of Trance
artist.bio: Simon Berry runs his solo trance project Art of Trance on the Platipus record label. Back in the mid 90's 12" releases of classics such as Cambodia, Gloria and Octopus were hits with DJ's and featured as strong points on the early Platipus Compilations. In 1998 Art of Trance released the single 'Madagascar' featuring the now seminal remix by CygnusX. In years to come 'Madagascar' received numerous makeovers and re-releases, and formed the core of Art of Trance's second album, 'Voice of Earth'.

artist.name: Sarah McLachlan
artist.bio: Sarah McLachlan (born Sarah Ann McLachlan January 28, 1968 in Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada) is a Grammy-winning musician, singer and songwriter. She is known for the emotional sound of her ballads. Some of her most popular songs include "Angel", "Building a Mystery", "Adia", "Possession", "Fallen", "I Will Remember You", and "World on Fire". Her best-selling album to date is Surfacing, for which she won two Grammy Awards and four Juno Awards.

artist.name: Existone
artist.bio: The “Existone” project was founded in 2004. This project is a new stage in musicmaking, sounds and style. It’s a vivid specimen of such musical genres as progressive, uplifting and melodic trance. The sound-designer and producer of “Existone” project is Sergey Zarubin. Sergey has found himself in music by pure luck in 2000. Since then it has changed his life. Continual experiments with different styles focused his preferences for progressive and melodic trance. Existone made his debut in 2006 on an Emotive Sounds label with exciting single «Deep Blue Sky».

artist.name: Late Night Alumni
artist.bio: Late Night Alumni are Becky Jean Williams, Finn Bjarnson, John Hancock, Ryan Raddon (aka Kaskade).  Late Night Alumni is the alias of DJ/producer Kaskade, currently signed to 'Om Records' and loaned to the Hed Kandi label. They tend to mix Dance/house music with strings and soft trance like vocals from their lead singer, Becky Jean William's smooth voice. Their current album Empty Streets was successful enough to be made into a polyphonic ringtone.

artist.name: Headstrong feat. Shelley Harland
artist.bio: Don Jackson aka 'Headstrong' is one of the fastest rising stars in the Dance Music scene and is also a prolific song writer.  Headstrong's latest releases have been massive globally and Don now finds himself working with the top singers and names in the industry with top new tunes soon to be released and an album.   Discovered by the brilliant Judge Jules, all Headstrong tunes and songs have recieved massive radio support from BBC Radio 1, Galaxy FM, Kiss FM and radio stations globally.

artist.name: Cabala
artist.bio: There are several artists known as Cabala. 1) Cabala is an alias of a trance producer Nick Muir. He had four releases under this name. He is also known as Floorjam, Marshal Stax, Monumental, Nemo, One Note Jam and Sony All Stars. 2) Cabala was a British death metal band that released two demos in 1994. The lyrics dealt with occult and horror topics. 3) A Spanish rock band

artist.name: Vimana
artist.bio: Vimana is the name of two different artists:  Before the famous Gouryella name was created, Ferry Corsten and Tijs Verwest had already teamed up together for another project. Under the name

artist.name: Mr Sam
artist.bio: Mr Sam was born during the mid seventies just as punk was emerging from beneath the ruins of stadium-rock, he grew up in a small idyllic village near the Belgian border in the north of France.  From an early age, Sam had no escape from his parents own musically mixed cocktails of Giorgio Moroder, Klaus Schulz combined with a dash of Elvis Presley. Through this heavy involuntary dose of electronically initiated influence, he developed an early fascination for squelchy synthesizer sounds and after buying his first Depeche Mode single, he was firmly hooked.

artist.name: Jonas Steur feat. Julie Thompson
artist.bio:
Born in 1982 in Belgium. Born for the night...  
 Jonas Steur has become a familiar name in the trance scene the last few years. With several big hits like “Tales from the south”, “Castamara” , “Second turn” and “Fall to pieces” , just to name a few , and remixes for all the major labels in the trance scene, he did his part for the melodic yet progressive minded side of trance. He's allergic to supersaws and minute long snare rolls and doesn't shy away from playing techno and house in his sets nowadays.

artist.name: A Boy Called Joni
artist.bio: Having received huge support in 2006 from such esteemed names as Tiësto, Ferry Corsten, Mark Norman and Markus Schulz, Joni Ljungqvist is now considered one the biggest rising talents in the industry despite only being born in 1987! Joni also releases trance music under his own name and his initials JPL. He has also remixed a track called Stealth for Kyamoto, whilst collaborating on projects with fellow rising stars Carl B and Galen Behr.

artist.name: Andain
artist.bio: Andain is a San Francisco-based musical group founded in 2002. Group members are Josh Gabriel and David Dresden (producers), Mavie Marcos (vocalist and songwriter) and David Penner (guitarist). The group performs a mix of trance, rock, house and world music. Andain's songs combine live instruments, vocals and electronics.  The group's first release was the single "Summer Calling" in 2002 under Black Hole Records.

artist.name: Allure
artist.bio: There are multiple artists with this name: 1) Allure is a pseudonym used by Tiësto, or Tijs Verwest. He made several singles as Allure which include "No More Tears", "Rejected", "The Loves We Lost", "When She Left", and "We Ran At Dawn". Most of them can be found on his compilations and all received major airplay by the top DJ's. Especially the track "The Loves We Lost" has achieved anthem status since it was released in 2006 and is famous for its mellow melodic sound and fading vocals.

artist.name: Stereo MC's
artist.bio: Stereo MCs are a British rap group formed in 1985 in London, England. The group consists of Rob Birch (vocals), Nick "The Head" Hallam (turntables, production), Cath Coffey (backing vocals) and Ian "Owen If" Rossiter (drums). They are best known for their 1992 single "Connected" which was a major hit in the United Kingdom and the United States, as well as a crossover success on American alternative rock radio.

artist.name: Solee
artist.bio: German producer Normen Flaskamp is producing techno & house music for many years now. He was working under different project names, releasing on different labels. He did remixes for artists such as John Dahlbäck, John Acquaviva, Robbie Riviera, DJ Chus, Danny Tenaglia, Francesco Diaz & Gui Boratto just to name a few.  End of 2006 Normen Flaskamp decided to start his own label to release his very own powerful melodic techno/tech-house sound: Parquet Recordings was born.

artist.name: Albion
artist.bio: There are multiple artists with this name: 1) Albion is an alias of Ferry Corsten. 2) Albion was a short lived four piece British indie band formed in late 2006, based in York, England. The line up included singer/songwriter Alistair Griffin, Shed Seven songwriter/Guitarist Paul Banks, Walt on drums and Foda on bass. After releasing several tracks as free downloads, Albion split up in August 2007.

artist.name: Mystery Islands & Stefan Cambridge pres. Chapter G8
Mac Zimms
artist.bio: Real Name: Willem Jelle Faber Profile: Born on January 2nd 1970 in Hoogezand, The Netherlands. Competed in the Dutch National DJ-Mix Championships in 1987 and 1991. Both times he reached the finals. Nowadays he's a resident-producer on the BPM-Dance-labels under various nicknames. URLs: http://www.maczimms.com/

artist.name: DJ Tatana & Andrew Bennett feat. Tiff Lacey
Adele
artist.bio: Adele Laurie Blue Adkins (Born 5 May 1988 in London, United Kingdom) is an English soul singer/songwriter from Brixton, London. Signed to XL Recordings, a music label which primarily focuses on independent talents within Britain, Adele manages to incorporate a variety of flavours into her music, incredibly striking many people with her ability to vocalise lyrics with an extremely soulful voice accompanied by her jazzy beats.

artist.name: DJ Taucher
artist.bio: Short: German Electronical Trance Producer and Dj, by the name of Ralph Armand Beck  ..His name is Taucher ? the German word for Diver. When thick fog fills the room, deep, abysmal sounds start setting in and intensity & temperature are on the rise, then you know it?s Taucher time. .....  "If the night develops into something you cannot fathom nor explain, if something important happens which strikes you with almost supernatural awe, then the night is complete and the mission fulfilled."

artist.name: Robert Vadney
artist.bio:
~BIOGRAPHY~  
    
 Robert Vadney, Greek-American, born in Greece - on Rhodes island and raised in Greece and the US - by American Dad & Greek Mom, started writing music at the tender age of 12, after accidentally coming across the first computer music software he ever saw..   After seeing what he had inside him & what he could do, he saw things more serious and decided to take it to the next level - learning to play keys, which seeing that even without any knowledge of notes at all, he could play just about anything.

artist.name: Seal
artist.bio: Seal Henry Olusegun Olumide Adeola Samuel (born February 19, 1963 in Paddington, London, England) is an English soul singer and songwriter, professionally known only by his first name, Seal. He won three Grammy Awards for his 1995 single "Kiss from a Rose". Seal is of Brazilian and Nigerian descent. A childhood battle with discoid lupus left him with distinctive facial scarring and hair loss. Music career Seal (1991)

artist.name: King Unique
artist.bio: King Unique are two guys called Matt who make rough-edged dirty house music, Matthew Roberts and Matt ?Watkins? Thomas, a pair of studio junkies with a taste for bulldozer beats and sick synthesizers.  Over the last five years their records, remixes and re-edits have hit home with house-heads, nu-ravers and electro-rockers alike, being championed by everyone from Sasha to Soulwax, Danny Howells to Tiesto, and Pete Tong to Zane Lowe. Their music has turned up everywhere from Hollywood soundtracks to mobile ringtones, not to mention countless compilations and mix albums.

artist.name: Denga & Manus
artist.bio: Dennis Gertner, Manuel Schleis, Denga & Manus,

artist.name: Chris Lake
artist.bio: Globally recognised as one of the most exciting, forward thinking and cutting edge producers on the scene, Chris Lake's rare ability to create tracks that fuse elements of house, electro and techno has not been lost on his fellow peers. His innovative productions continue to receive wave after wave of support from such luminaries that include Sasha, Danny Howells, Justin Robertson, Sander Kleinenberg and Carl Cox, whilst Pete Tong leads the way in championing the unique sound that has established Chris as one of the world's elite.

artist.name: Dave Dresden
artist.bio: About Dave Dresden  Here's to the crazy ones. The misfits. The rebels. The troublemakers. The round pegs in the square holes. The ones who see things differently. They're not fond of rules. And they have no respect for the status quo. You can praise them, disagree with them, quote them, disbelieve them, glorify or vilify them. About the only thing you can't do is ignore them. Because they change things. They invent. They imagine. They heal. They explore. They create. They inspire. They push the human race forward.

artist.name: Mark Knight & Funkagenda vs. Paul Thomas
Viper
artist.bio: There is more than one artist with this name:  1) VIPER is one of the pioneers of heavy metal bands in Brazil. Its history starts in 1985 with the brothers Pit and Yves Passarell, bass and guitar players respectively. Still teenagers, they join with the guitar player Felipe Machado, and the drum player Cassio Audi, and also Andre Matos and they record their first demo, ?The Killera Sword?.  2 years later, ?Soldiers of Sunrise? was released, one of the most worshiped Brazilian heavy metal albums.

artist.name: The Viceroy
artist.bio: Still only 21 years old, The Viceroy has just been unveiled as the latest Gallery main room resident alongside main room stalwarts such as Tall Paul, Sister Bliss, Sander van Doorn, John Askew and Gavyn Mytchel.Also resident at Turnmills for Vaccine, The Viceroy helped steer the night from its Thursday night slot to hosting a room at The Gallery and is seen playing monthly and booking the best new talent and UK debuts from the likes of Yahel, Fabio Stein, Richard Durand, Kyau and Albert through to Matthew Dekay and Oliver Prime among many more.

artist.name: Rui Da Silva feat. Ben Onono
artist.bio: Rui da Silva is a Portuguese producer and DJ, whose single "Touch Me" (featuring the vocals of Cassandra Fox) topped the UK Chart in 2001. At the time, he was the only Portuguese musician to have a UK hit and hence was the first to score a UK number one.  Rui started producing house music in 1992, just as club culture was getting established in Lisbon. Noticing the lack of dance music labels in Portugal, Rui teamed up with DJ Vibe to form Kaos Records, the first label in Portugal specialized in house and electronic music.

artist.name: Eddie Sender feat. Marcie
artist.bio: Eddie Sender as producer/dj was born in 1985 in slovak town Senica. His real name is Eduard Palkovsky. His major production is uplifting trance and progressive trance. His career started with remix of track Pilgrim, because it was played by Armin Van Buuren in his show A State Of Trance in year 2006. Eddie signs contracts with some Uk and Holand labels since year 2006 for example: Wildchild (sublabel of Baroquerecords), KYR recordings, Totaldigital (sublabel of Bonzai music)...

artist.name: Thirty Seconds To Mars
artist.bio: 30 Seconds to Mars is a rock band hailing from Los Angeles, California. Created in 1998 by brothers Jared Leto (Vocals, Guitar) and Shannon Leto (Drums). First album was recorded entirely by the two of them, the tour formation was with three more members: Solon Bixler (Lead Guitar, Back Vocals) - left in 2003, now has a band called Great Northern`; Kevin Drake (Guitar) and Matt Wachter (Bass, Keys occasionally).

artist.name: Sean Dexter
artist.bio: Sean Dexter (Cengiz

artist.name: Gareth Wyn
artist.bio: Gareth Wyn is taking clubland by storm, setting dance floors alight worldwide. Mixmag Future Hero, Cream UK & Ibiza Resident, he's part of the nu breed, and his unique style combined with the ability to read and interact with the crowd is fast earning him a reputation as one of the scene's rising stars.  Gareth's production skills are also gaining serious recognition. As a DJ producer his appreciation transcends genre - signed to Paul Van Dyk's Vandit for his up tempo productions and Ministry of Sound for house...

artist.name: Chainside
artist.bio: Chainside is a Dj from Ontario Canada

artist.name: John Dahlback
artist.bio: This is an incorrect tag for John Dahlbäck. If this non-artist appears in your charts, do last.fm and yourself a favor. Fix your artist tags.

artist.name: Tarkan
artist.bio: Tarkan Teveto?lu (born October 17, 1972), popularly known as Tarkan, is a successful World Music award-winning pop music singer in Turkey. He has released several platinum-selling albums during his career, with an estimated 15 million albums sold, and is also involved in producing music through his own music company HITT Music, which he established in 1997.
