Noted for his live stage performances, the Washington Post has compared Tarkan's effect on Turkey as analogous to Elvis in America circa 1957...

artist.name: Moussa Clarke vs. The Police
artist.bio: Moussa Clarke is an inspirational DJ/producer with a worldwide reputation for igniting dancefloors from London to Moscow to Tokyo and back again. Never far from the madding crowd ? apart from when he?s cooking up monster basslines and electrochemical beats in the studio ? he?s also founder of the thriving London-based label and DJ agency Oven Ready. Born in Switzerland, half English, half Senegalese, he found his feet in France and Italy, and then travelled the globe before moving to the UK aged 12.

artist.name: Accadia
artist.bio: Accadia is a monicker used by the music producer Michael Woods. Most of the tracks he composes are downtempo, chillout, or trance.

artist.name: Carl B vs. Talla 2XLC
artist.bio: Having recently remixed high profile tracks for big names in the trance industry such as Armas, Acues & Elitist, Selu Vibra, Summer Sessions, Armin van Buuren and JPL, Carl B (Carl Barrdahl) has definitely merited his growing reputation as a trance remix specialist! Yet he has also written and produced quality tunes of his own in his Carl B guise, including the tracks Solitude and Social Suicide. Barrdahl also has an alias called PEAK, and in 2006 he collaborated with Joni Ljungqvist on a project named Peak vs.

artist.name: Kamaya Painters
artist.bio: Kamaya Painters is a group name used by Dutch artists Tijs Verwest (better known as Tiësto) and Benno De Goeij, from Rank 1. All tracks were released on Black Hole Recordings, and were subsequently licensed to the Planetary Conciousness and Data Records labels. Endless Wave, in 1998, was the first tune to be released by Kamaya Painters and it has been heralded as one of the true trance classics, even though it actually hints towards the similar melody as Liquid Child - Diving Faces.

artist.name: Ex-Driver vs. Ben Parker
artist.bio: There are at least 7 bands with the name Ex: 1: A Chilean band, with a little of punk, rock and an own style. Its vocalist and leader is Colombina Parra, daughter of the famous anti-poet, Nicanor Parra. Its only album is Caida Libre, and they have some singles, and an unreleased EP called "Perro que habla". Later, they updated their name as los ex. 2: A Korean band [ Ex ] that performed for the 2005 MBC University Song competition.

artist.name: Paul Webster
artist.bio: Paul Webster, began djing 6 years ago and over the past couple of years he has firmly established himself on th edance scene in Ireland, playing his tough energetic trance style in most of Irelands big clubs, he also showcases his sound on Ireland biggest dance radio staion for two years on Dublin 'Club fm' having weekly guests supply mixes including Judge Jules, Marco V and Sander van Doorn among others.

artist.name: Maor Levi vs. Orjan Nilsen
artist.bio: Maor Levi is a highly original up and coming producer hailing from Israel.  At the tender age of just 17 and after already releasing a track under the Pillow One alias on the Future Heroes 2 compilation via Lost Language, he now joins forces with Anjunabeats' hot new label, Anjunadeep.   Producing since the age of 11 and inspired by the Tiesto Magik series, he took his unique style of trance to the internet. Garnering many reactions and taking onboard all the resources he could find, with the help of FL Studio, he honed his skills to the point where labels started taking him seriously.

artist.name: Guru Josh Project
artist.bio: The Guru Josh Project got together in 2007 and consist of Guru Josh (Song Writer) Dj DazPerkz (DJ/Producer) and Snakebyte (Producer). They formed the project as three people who have a love for electronic music and old school 90 rave music. Their aim is to bring back the magic of the 90

artist.name: Arpegia & Oliver P. pres. Fast Distance
Cary Brothers
artist.bio: Cary Brothers is a singer/songwriter, best known for "Blue Eyes," the ballad he contributed to the Grammy-winning Garden State soundtrack. Brothers's songs have appeared on the NBC sitcom Scrubs, the FOX mystery Bones, the WB's Smallville, and the successful medical dramas Grey's Anatomy and ER. Brothers's song "Ride" appeared on the soundtrack to the feature film The Last Kiss, starring Zach Braff, Rachel Bilson, and Casey Affleck and in second season's 8th episode of Kyle XY as well as in the 14th episode of season 5 of One Tree Hill.

artist.name: Nadia Ali
artist.bio: As with any great era of music, there are always a handful of tracks that can be considered genre defining. For dance music -from the late 90's to the new millennium - there were only a select few tracks that caught fire around the world. Most of these tracks came from the godfather's of the recent dance music explosion: We're talking about tracks like Underworld's "Born Slippy," and The Chemical Brother's "Block Rockin' Beats.

artist.name: One Night Only
artist.bio: One Night Only are a UK indie pop rock band, from Helmsley, North Yorkshire. The band consists of singer and guitarist George Craig, guitarist and backing vocalist Mark Hayton, bassist Daniel Parkin, drummer Sam Ford and keyboardist and backing vocalist Jack Sails.  Formed in 2003 (which seems an awfully long time ago when you consider that singer George has only just turned 18), One Night Only started out as a bunch of school friends ?just making noise? in their rural hometown of Helmsley, North Yorkshire.

artist.name: Delerium feat. Leigh Nash
artist.bio: Delerium is from Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada, formed in 1987, originally as another side project (Intermix being the more techno-sounding project) of the influential industrial music act, Front Line Assembly. Delerium has traditionally been a two-person project, but the only constant member throughout its history has been Bill Leeb. After Michael Balch left both Front Line Assembly and Delerium, Bill Leeb worked with Rhys Fulber, and the two released several albums under the Delerium moniker; these years saw a gradual stylistic change from darker ambient to a more danceable sound.

artist.name: Adam Foley
artist.bio: Dj/Producer from Galway Ireland now based in Manchester uk, find out more at www.myspace.com/adamfoleymusic

artist.name: Allure feat. Christian Burns
artist.bio: There are multiple artists with this name: 1) Allure was a short-lived emo band in the mid 1990s, similar to bands such as Indian Summer. Their only official release was the song Little Engine, which appeared on the Eucalyptus 2 x 7" Compilation (Tree Records, 1996). They have also released a demo cassette with 7 Untitled songs. 2) Allure is a pseudonym used by Tiesto, or Tijs Verwest. He made several singles as Allure which include "No More Tears", "Rejected", "The Loves We Lost", "When She Left", and "We Ran At Dawn".

artist.name: Natasha Bedingfield vs. Chicane
artist.bio: Chicane's trance anthem "Saltwater" was mashed-up with Natasha Bedingfield's "I Bruise Easily" to produce the track "Bruised Water".

artist.name: Nifra
artist.bio: Nifra born in 1988 in the eastern part of Slovakia and raised in a little town called Michalovce, where nobody expected what that little girl will reach in the future. Nifras dreams were always to be dj and producer, and by the age of 19, she has accomplished what most of us ever only can dream of. Addicted to edm, especially trance, she started to make it herself by the age of 16 but it didnt went so well.

artist.name: Steve Allen & Ben Alonzi feat. Tiff Lacey
Tenishia
artist.bio: Winners of ‘The Best New Comer Award' for 2005, and the talent behind Malta's most requested bootleg, ‘Floyd's Girl', Joven Grech and Cyprian Cassar – better known as Tenishia – have established themselves as among the best of Malta's electronic dance producers. Popular with their cutting edge live shows and loved for their outstanding productions, Tenishia has quickly gained a reputation in Malta's clubbing culture, including winning the best newcomer award just eight months after their debut in the clubbing scene.

artist.name: Solar Stone
artist.bio:
Producer
 Solar Stone is a UK based producer Rich Mowatt(formely with Sam Tierney & Andy Bury) who is responsible for some of the trance scene's most defining moments. Solarstone are firmly supported by every trance and progressive dj worth mentioning since the first Solarstone single 'The Calling' way back in 1997. "SolarStone means 100% quality and consistently evolving the genre" (Dj Orkidea, 2008)  DJ

artist.name: Tom Cloud
artist.bio: Thomas Blum (aka Tom Cloud) appeared on the scene for the first time in 2006 with his hit single “Told You So”, which was used by Tiesto on his mix album “In Search Of Sunrise”. It became the most requested track of this mix album and it went immediately to #1 in the Beatport Download Charts. A remix for Leama and Moor produced in partnership with Andrew Bennett followed, as well as a single on Armada Music called “Secretly”, featuring the famous vocals of Tiff Lacey, which got support from numerous top DJs worldwide.

artist.name: Mr. Sam feat. ClAud 9
artist.bio:
Mr Sam was born during the mid seventies just as punk was emerging from beneath the ruins of stadium-rock, he grew up in a small idyllic village near the Belgian border in the north of France. 
 From an early age, Sam had no escape from his parents own musically mixed cocktails of Giorgio Moroder, Klaus Schulz combined with a dash of Elvis Presley. 
 Through this heavy involuntary dose of electronically initiated influence, he developed an early fascination for squelchy synthesizer sounds and after buying

artist.name: Tenishia feat. Anthya
artist.bio: Winners of ?The Best New Comer Award' for 2005, and the guys behind Malta's most requested bootleg, ?Floyd's Girl', Joven Grech and Cyprian Cassar more known as Tenishia, established themselves along side Malta's top Electronic dance producers. Popular with their cutting edge live shows and loved for their outstanding productions. Tenishia quickly gained reputation in Malta's clubbing culture and won the best newcomer award just eight months after their debut in the clubbing scene.

artist.name: C.M.
artist.bio: C.M. is an alias of Marino Stephano and Crisci Mauro. It means Crystal Manoeuvres. They have produced some popular songs such as Dream Universe.

artist.name: Blue Tente
artist.bio: The man behind Blue Tente is the 21 years old Sergiu Teremtus, who is hailing form Baia Mare, Romania. His passion for music production started a long time ago, but more seriously in 2007. The first project of Blue Tente, entitled 'Antarctic Night', will be released under SA-UK Music & Sensate Recordings in 2008, along with other future projects.  His work includes tracks like: ' Next Journey', 'Tears from the sky', 'Summer sun', 'Elements of tomorrow', 'The dream', 'Without you', 'Sunset Explosion', and other.

artist.name: DJ DLG feat. Reinita Nunez
artist.bio: Arguably, the Ibiza song of the summer, the world awaits the highly anticipated DJ DLG vs. Erick Morillo ?Where are you Now? release on Subliminal Records, slated for fall 2008.  With such an early buzz around this song, and his string of hits, DJ DLG is a most sought after producer, remixer, and DJ.  For over six years, DJ DLG has been releasing his unique brand of electro, new wave, disco and big room house music.

artist.name: Michael de Kooker
artist.bio: A brand new track on Combined Forces by the Dutch Talent Michael de Kooker. With the first hour support by Ti

artist.name: T4L
artist.bio: T4L is the collaboration of two Italian DJs and electronic music producers, Alessandro Carusi and Manuel Toso. As of late 2006, they have released two singles: Moonwalk in 2005 and Maximus in 2006. Website - http://www.t4lmusic.com/

artist.name: J-Punch & Harland
artist.bio: There are at least five artists who use "J" as their name. 1. Jun Onose, or J, is the former bassist of the Japanese band LUNA SEA. He was born August 12, 1970. He still plays bass, but also sings lead vocals in his own band. 2. J is a rapper from Stuttgart. He made his first appereance on the "Lass Spitten EP" from Ronald & Ca$. At the time he was working on a mixtape called "Mein Mixtape". 3. J is a South African rock artist, making his 2006 debut with the album "Closure" released by Just Music. The album is notable for being released on CD and USB memory stick.

artist.name: Memento
artist.bio: There are at least two bands named Memento:  1. An Australian alternative metal band.  2. A Serbian alternative rock band from Belgrade.  Further information:  1) Formed in 2001, Memento was comprised of Australian natives in vocalist/keyboardist Justin Stewart Cotta, guitarist Space, bassist Leighton Kearns, and American drummer Steve Clark.  The band released their debut album Beginnings on February 25, 2003.

artist.name: Rachael Starr
artist.bio: Combining skill with modernism, and her aptitude for style with ingenuity, Rachael is breaking new ground in the electronic and dance music industries. One of the only female producers on the scene, she feels it necessary to prove herself and work very hard at what she does. "I guess that one of the most important things to me is to not forget why you are doing what you are doing. Take yourself seriously, and other people will too." She says, "In the end what it comes down to is the music, what it is as a whole and how it makes me who I am."

artist.name: David Murtagh
artist.bio: House, electo, trance and techno. With plays from MArco V, Gareth Emery, Kuffdam, Solarstone, Ernesto & Bastien, Fabio Stein, Bryan Kearney, Graham Gold, Mark Eteson and DJ Choose to name a few. My first original release is forthcoming on Rapid Response/Fine Line recordings with remixes from Jerome Isma-Aa and Frase

artist.name: Adrian Ivan
artist.bio: Adrian Ivan, known as Mr. Pit aswell was born in 1977 with the love for music. He is one of the first and subtle trance and electro / house music genre producers in his country. Back in 1996 he discovered electronica and the passion for music. As the years passed, Adrian's music style was changed and took differently shapes, each of his tracks having a unique feeling and multiple messages, as he was influenced by many genres of music. The countless hours in the studio brought him experience and creativity in playing with sounds or composing electronic music.

artist.name: Dave Joy
artist.bio: His DJ-Carreer began in little steps as a 16 year old gifted young Music freak in a popular Pub. He started to collect all kinds of records and CDs until he gradually had enough together to present his own music and DJ sets. With commercial Party music he gained the chance to harvest his first gage. The piles of records and CDs grew bigger and bigger.  Many years later he had the opportunity to put on his music as an official Trance-DJ at a local club in Switzerland, where he was presented under his new guise Dave Joy.

artist.name: Fast Distance
artist.bio: Fast Distance is a project between Belgian producer Franz Hlusek aka Arpegia and Olivier Picart from France. Franz and Olivier have always had a passion for electronic dance music, especially for melodic, euphoric and uplifting trance. When they met in winter 2005 they discovered that they had the same interest for trance music and they decided to start producing together.  Since he was very young, Franz has always had a passion for music lessons.

artist.name: Clear View feat. Jessica
artist.bio: A project from Tijs Verwest aka <span title="Unknown artist" class="bbcode_unknown"> DJ Ti

artist.name: Jerry Ropero feat. Cozi
artist.bio: JERRY ROPERO  The beginning of Jerry Roperos career, was located in Belgium, when nine years ago, he became a member of "N.B.G.(Natural Born Grooves), known for their smashing hits "Forerunner" and "Groovebird"!  5 years ago ,in Hamburg, Germany, his biggest project was born, when he got together in the studio with the excellent vocalist Terri B. and , the voice from several other projects like "2 Eivissa", "Future Breeze", etc. and Dj Maui!

artist.name: Taxi Girl
artist.bio: Taxi Girl were a New Wave French rock band formed in 1978 and disbanded in 1986. The group still has a very strong fan base in France and the 1980 single Cherchez le gar

artist.name: Mekka
artist.bio: Jake Williams a.k.a. Mekka  Jake's lucky break came in 1993 when the then 16-year-old sent a batch of demos to various record companies and Red Jerry of Hooj Choons invited him down to his studio. Soon after, he signed a deal with FFRR and under the guise of JX, enjoyed a raft of Top 10 hits with classic nineties dance anthems such as 'Son Of A Gun', 'You Belong To Me', 'There's Nothing I Won't Do' and 'Close To Your Heart', selling over half a million copies between them.

artist.name: Salt Tank
artist.bio: Salt Tank are two English music producers, David Gates and Malcolm Stanners, and percussionist Andy Rose, from Surrey, UK. Their music ranges from laid-back trance such as their hit Eugina (some of its many versions includes a sample from Me And A Gun by Tori Amos) to tougher sounds. They have collaborated with other music artists such as Chicane, in the track Leaving Town which can be found in Chicane's album Far From The Maddening Crowds.

artist.name: Nenes vs. Cosmic Gate
artist.bio: The Nenes are a group of four women who sing Okinawan folk songs, and perform on traditional instruments and in traditional costumes. While Okinawa is today considered part of Japan, it has its own distinct culture, of which residents are very proud. Okinawa is also a tropical island and resort oriented locale, which many people enjoy visiting. Traditional Okinawan music is usually played on a three stringed instrument called a sanshin, which is similar to the Japanese shamisen, and perhaps related to the banjo.

artist.name: Adam K
artist.bio: Adam Kershen has been locked up in the studio for the past 10 years. His vast knowledge of audio engineering and sound design has allowed him to manipulate sounds into a vision of his own. His years of experience in composing, production, and engineering, have brought him to collaborate with/remix world renowned artists, Deadmau5, Tiesto and Hatiras to name a few.  In February of 2007 Adam launched his own record label, Hotbox Digital, and in a short period of time has turned it into a trusted name in house music.

artist.name: CJ Bolland
artist.bio: C.J. Bolland is electronic music producer and remixer Christopher Jay Bolland, born June 18, 1971 in Stockton-on-Tees, Yorkshire, England. He is most known for his song "Sugar Is Sweeter," which hit #1 on the Hot Dance Music/Club Play chart in 1996, thanks to a remix from producer Armand van Helden. Bolland is also a prolific remixer with a long resum

artist.name: Tiesto & Junkie XL
artist.bio: A collaboration between Tiësto and Junkie XL. They released Obsession in 2002.

artist.name: Tatana
artist.bio:
Tatana (Tatana Sterba, born 7th October 1976 in former Czechoslovakia) is a swiss Trance producer and dj.
 Tatana is one of the most successful artists of the 2000s in the Swiss charts, with several successful trance albums since her debut album 24 Carat was released in February 2000.  After having the adorable voice of Jael (Lunik, Delerium, Mich Gerber) singing on her last years smash hit 'Always on my mind', Tatana chose to collaborate for her new single 'All that I feel' with another star of the Swiss music scene.

artist.name: Baby D
artist.bio: There are 2 Artists that go by the name Baby D. 1.Baby D were a UK-based dance (house/techno) band best known for their UK Number 1 single "Let Me Be Your Fantasy" in 1994.  Vocals were provided by Dorothy Fearon (also known as Baby D) and Nino (also the MC and keyboardist). Floyd Dyce was the writer/ producer for the band and also credited as keyboardist on occassion.  The band had 2 other Top 10 singles, I Need Your Loving (which was a cover of The Korgis 80s hit Eveybody's Gotta Learn Sometime) and So Pure, as well as numerous other less successful hits.

artist.name: Vicky Devine
artist.bio:
Vicky Devines Profile
 Vicky Devine is one of the leading female Trance DJs to break out of the UK, with her successful career taking her all over the world and seeing her become weekly main room resident at one of the most popular and well known nights in Ibiza?.Judgement Sundays. Vicky Devine?s success as a DJ and Producer is growing year on year gaining amazing support and recognition for her talent and ability from leading DJs such as Judge Jules, Marco V and Sander Van Doorn.

artist.name: Muzzaik
artist.bio: Real Name: D

artist.name: Andrew Bennett
artist.bio: Andrew Bennett is one of the most talked about up-and-coming artists on the dance scene at the moment. Over the past two years he has released various tracks and remixes, which have received world wide recognition and praise. But Andrew Bennett is anything but a newcomer on the scene: he has been spinning the decks since 1996, he is a resident DJ at the acclaimed “Trance Nation” events and has secured regular DJ slots both in and outside of Germany, like in world-renowned clubs as “Space” on Ibiza as well at the biggest events and festivals.

artist.name: The Roc Project feat. Tina Arena
artist.bio: The Roc Project is an electronica act composed of New York City-based DJ Ray Roc and, most often, vocalist Tina Novak. Their debut single, "Never (Past Tense)" was released in the fall of 2003. However, because of difficulty getting the song released due to Novak's and Roc's being signed to different record labels, Ray Roc decided to recruit Australian singer Tina Arena to sing Novak's vocals instead. Arena's version of the song was the version that ended up as the final single release.

artist.name: Basto
artist.bio: Basto! is an Belgian DJ hailing from the city of Antwerpen in Belgium. He is best known for his single ''Rock With You'', which received large amounts of play time on the Dutch dance station Fresh FM.

artist.name: Playboy
artist.bio: Plejboj je muzi?ka grupa iz Beograda. Grupa je postojala od jeseni 1992. godine do prole?a 1999. godine. Sastav su ?inili bubnjar Miladin Radivojevi? (1992-1994), bubnjar Goran Milo?evi? (1995-1999), basista Roman Gor?ek, gitarista Igor Perovi? i saksofonista Du?an Petrovi?. Grupa se ponovo kratkotrajno okupila zarad nastupa na festivalu EXIT 06 (koncert odr?an 7. jula 2006. godine)....

artist.name: Marcos
artist.bio: Spearheading the new wave of UK hard trance producers, Marcos aka Mark Dearden has literally exploded on to the scene over the last two years. At only 21 he has produced a staggering number of high quality anthems! Working closely with Jay K Walker for a number of years it was inevitable the two would eventually produce a track together. In April 2003 they released 'NIGHTFINDER' EP. Mark's career to date has charted a meteoric rise from bedroom producer to highly respected craftsmen of techie driving anthems.

artist.name: Oliver Moldan vs. Harada
artist.bio:
OLIVER MOLDAN, THE RHINE RIVER MAN, HAS BEEN APPEARING BEHIND THE DECKS AT RENOWNED DANCE CLUBS NOT ONLY IN GERMANY BUT ALL OVER THE WORLD FOR MANY YEARS. OLIVER'S INSPIRED MIXING SKILLS COMBINED WITH HIS ECLECTIC MUSIC SELECTION HAVE CLEARLY DEFINED HIS UNIQUE AND TRAILBLAZING STYLE. HE HAS STEADILY WORKED HIS WAY UP THE LADDER TO BE RECOGNIZED AS ONE THE LEADING
 DJS ON THE TECH AND PROGRESSIVE HOUSE SCENES AND ONE MAJOR REASON FOR THIS HAS BEEN HIS RESIDENCY AT THE LEGENDARY TRIBEHOUSE IN D

artist.name: Lazy J
artist.bio: Lazy J are a four piece band from the Midlands. Their music is a clear and defined fusion of funk, blues and rock that draws influence from a range of artists such as Led Zeppelin, Jane?s Addiction, James Brown, Red Hot Chili Peppers, George Clinton and Reef.  Having played with various different band members since the band was formed, founder members Dave Cotterill (guitars) and Marc Plant (vocals) had worked hard to build a solid reputation in the Midlands music scene for polished live performances and inventive song writing.

artist.name: Cloud 69
artist.bio: Cloud 69 is Laurent V

artist.name: Firestorm
artist.bio: There are at least 4 bands with the name Firestorm: 1) FIRESTORM are North London's finest melodic heavy metal act. www.firestormrock.co.uk 2) Firestorm are Hugh Tolland and Kevin Coll and live in Glasgow, Scotland. Together they produce emotional, energetic, uplifing trance under the alias of Firestorm, and are argueably the biggest up and coming duo in the world of trance. 3) Firestorm - an Austrian Heavy Metal Band. www.thefirestorm.com

artist.name: Mekk
artist.bio: Rob "Activa" Stevenson established Mekk to produce harder techno-edged tunes.

artist.name: Urban Astronauts
artist.bio: ?Urban Astronauts? are the new ?Rocktronica? sensation from London and brainchild of rock / dance producer & DJ Matt Darey. The band are Richard James Smith on guitars, Leon Michael King on Bass guitar, Graham Sowberby on Drums and various guest singers including Lucia, Bonse and Larry Love. Already making waves in the Alternative Rock & Dance circles of North America as the latest signing to USA?s biggest Indie label Koch Records based in NYC USA. The band fuses rock influences with the latest cutting edge production creating a unique sound.

artist.name: Jose Amnesia
artist.bio:
1996
 Rob Aker aka Jose Amnesia bought his first synthesizer , a cheap Atari and started to compose electronic tracks.  1998
 Age One records (UK) were interested in his works, and in 1998, "Jose Amnesia" was born.  "Last sunset in Ibiza" was an essential new tune on Judge Jules BBC Radio Show, followed by the epic "The Eternal"which soon became a classic trance track gaining support from all the top dj's such as Paul Van Dyk, Tiesto, Ferry Corsten and Armin Van Buuren.  Rob also produces tracks under the guise of Jamnesia together with Dino Lenny.

artist.name: Adam Sheridan
artist.bio:
Adam is a DJ and producer from Leeds, England. 
 He is currently a resident at England's northern hard dance club GoodGreef. Works with Joe Thompson (Will Holland/Satori).   Adam's passion for dance music began at a very early age, staying up late to listen to Essential Mixes when he was just 11 and becoming especially interested in Sasha and Carl Cox. Adam says he enjoyed the "energy and feeling" the music gave him and he purchased his first record Gat Decor - Passion and first set of decks at only 12 years old.

artist.name: Inhaler
Linkin Park
artist.bio: Linkin Park is a band from Los Angeles. The band consists of Joe "Mr. Hahn" Hahn, Mike Shinoda, Dave Farrell (a.k.a. Phoenix), Chester Bennington, Brad Delson and Rob Bourdon. Released under the band name "Hybrid Theory", the band's first album, Hybrid Theory EP was released in 1999. Only 1000 copies of this very rare original EP were made. The band's first full studio album, Hybrid Theory, released in 2000, had a huge success, selling 24 million copies worldwide as of October 2006. Among its singles were One Step Closer, Crawling, and the band's highest-selling single, In the End.

artist.name: Yahel
artist.bio: The number 28 DJ for the second year in a row, DJ Yahel has been on a roll. A versatile artist with influences and techniques ranging throughout the Trance spectrum, Yahel's music resides in a lush synthesis of Club effects, Deep Trance beats, and psychedelia from the Goa scene. As evident from his solid standing on the DJ List, Yahel's fans worldwide consistently support him, and Yahel knows just how much that means.

artist.name: Tyler Michaud vs. JPL
artist.bio: With his diverse and energetic sound, Tyler Michaud has emerged as a leader of next generation DJs and producers. His impressive production repertoire has been released on numerous labels including System Recordings, Armada Music, Aurium, and Baroque Records, while having been playlisted by top international DJs including Paul Van Dyk, Tiesto, Sasha, John Digweed, Paul Oakenfold, Hernan Cattaneo, Dave Seaman, Markus Schulz, Nick Warren, and Armin Van Buuren.

artist.name: Motorcycle
artist.bio: Motorcycle is a cooperation between the producers duo Gabriel & Dresden and female vocalist Jes Brieden. Together they made the track 'As The Rush Comes' which became one of the most famous vocal trance tracks around the world. Also another track 'Imagination' can be found on Gabriel & Dresden's album titled 'Bloom', which is only known as an acoustic track with the vocals of Jes Brieden.

artist.name: Sinead O'Connor
artist.bio: Sinéad Marie Bernadette O'Connor (born December 8, 1966) is a Grammy Award-winning Irish singer and songwriter. Brash and outspoken

artist.name: Lost Shade
artist.bio:
A three man Band from South-Germany / North-Switzerland which started as raw black metal project and fade into viking metal
 H. - d,v
 P. - g,b
 T. - key, harmonica

artist.name: Marcus Schossow
artist.bio: The years have passed since Marcus released his first single "Stockholm" in 2003. The huge hit supported by ALL major top jocks, was Marcus' major debut into the scene.  When Marcus was 15 years old he entered a local DJ competition, completely crushing swedens no. 1 DJ, Marcus was hailed as THE biggest upcoming talent in Sweden. After that Marcus wanted to touch people with his own productions aswell. So he started producing his own tracks.

artist.name: Green Velvet
artist.bio: During the early days before he became a house musician, he earned a degree in chemical engineering from the University of California, Berkeley. Up until this point music had been a hobby fueled by cobbling together tracks on his "sixty buck keyboard, a cheap four-track and a cheap drum machine" while still an undergraduate at the University of Illinois. This DIY method of production was never taken seriously and when childhood plans to become a doctor were shelved Jones was firmly committed to a career as a chemical engineer...

artist.name: Talla 2XLC vs. Sean Tyas
artist.bio: Talla 2XLC (b. Andreas Tomalla, Germany) is a producer, musician, and DJ whose work has spanned from industrial music to trance music.  Tomalla started as a DJ, founding in 1984 the Technoclub at Frankfurt's Dorian Gray club. He was also at the time involved with a band called Moskwa TV. In 1988, he started a new project called Bigod 20, which would go on to be one of Europe's most successful EBM acts of the early 1990s.

artist.name: Headstrong feat. Kirsty Hawkshaw
artist.bio: Headstrong is a Canadian alternative metal band formed in 1998. They released one eponymous studio album under RCA Records before being dropped from the label and ultimately disbanding in 2003. The band members all met while attending University of Western Ontario where they each a received a degree. Their group initially began in the late 1990s under the name bomb32 in their native London, Ontario.

artist.name: Johan Gielen
artist.bio: Johan Gielen, born February 23rd, 1968 in the Belgium town of Mol, is a world renowned trance artist, DJ and remixer.  Johan Gielen started DJ'ing at the age of 17 in his homecountry Belgium, and has during the latest 15 years build up an international fame spinning as a DJ in Japan, Australia, Germany, Spain, Holland, Belgium, England, Northern Ireland, Israel and now also as resident DJ at Club Gorgeous in Copenhagen, Denmark and annual Trance Energy event.

artist.name: Duderstadt feat. Kirsty Hawkshaw
artist.bio: At the age of 15 and 13 Dirk and Marco Duderstadt discovered a hobby and indeed a talent: making music. As the hobby can be very expensive, the two had to fight their way as LJ

artist.name: Amex feat. Anna Basel
artist.bio: Rory Allen Phillips Has been Involved with such projects as The Impossibles, Slowreader, and his newest project is called Rory and the Artificial Heart. Andreas Marx (amex) does produce Techno-DNB together with his studio partner Kaiza, see http://www.last.fm/music/amex%2B%2526%2BKaiza

artist.name: Yoav
artist.bio: Imagine a record that matches the leftfield edge of Beck or Radiohead with the kind of sure-footed pop hooks Justin Timberlake's people would write a blank cheque for. A record which vividly conjures the life of an insightful outsider, set to the dark, loping rhythms of Massive Attack or Portishead. A record built around a voice that's as sweetly expressive as it is richly soulful. Then imagine that every single sound of it, including the bass & the drums, is performed by one man on his amazingly versatile guitar. That record is Charmed & Strange.

artist.name: Everything But The Girl vs. Noel Sanger
artist.bio: The duo of Ben Watt and Tracey Thorn have successfully pulled off one of the greatest stylistic changes in modern music; originally a folk-pop group with jazz influences, their fortunes changed when Todd Terry successfully remixed 'Missing' (from Amplified Heart). Since then, EBTG have become more widely known as an electronic act, with Walking Wounded being a well-received example of their latter-day sound.

artist.name: David & Carr feat. Jenna Colaizy
artist.bio: Born and raised in sunny Minnesota, Peter "Petrogad" Carr began listening to electronic music at the age of 16. Soon after, he decided to delve deeper into the world of trance, quickly becoming familiar with mainstream DJs. He attended his first event later that same year, and he was hooked. Before long, Carr was the proud owner of two new CDJ's and a beat-up mixer, playing non-stop until finally he made the plunge to vinyl.

artist.name: Airscape
artist.bio: Airscape is one alias of the two famous DJs Johan Gielen and Sven Maes (better known as Svenson) with many remixes released under that alias. Johan Gielen was born in Belgium (23/02/1968). At the age of 12 he left his native country for the Netherlands. At the age of 17 he started DJing, for some parties close to where he lives. Soon he was DJing in different clubs and shows his preference for trance music. In 1995 he started to produce with Sven Maes, one of his friends. Sven was into music very young; inspired by groups like Depeche Mode.

artist.name: Phynn
artist.bio: Dutch producer/DJ Phynn, in real life known as Finne Jager and currently living in the USA, was born on the 6th of December 1984 in Nieuwegein, The Netherlands. His passion for music already started at a young age, as he learned to play several instruments back in his early years; an experience he still profits from in his current productions.    Phynn’s participation in a remix contest in 2002 paved the path for an ever growing list of superb releases.

artist.name: Coca & Villa - La Noche (D
artist.bio: David Villa and Tito Coca are important figures of the House music of the capital Madrid-cradle of many of the best DJs of the House scene of this country. For a long time they have been residents of the hall Kapital and of other emblematic halls of Madrid nightlife, such as their stage as DJs in the after hours of Madrid. Their professional path as DJs is long and extensive, but it is in this last period when their name as DJs and producers has settled itself firmly in the panorama of club and electronic music of our country (House).

artist.name: Robbie Rivera feat Denise Rivera
artist.bio: Riberto Louis Rivera, better known as Robbie Rivera, is a prolific house music producer and DJ born in Puerto Rico. He has an extensive catalog of original productions and remixes to his credit, ranging from tribal to progressive house, as well as incorporating garage and latin elements. As a solo artist he has hit #1 on the Hot Dance Music/Club Play chart twice: in 2001 with "Feel This 2001" and again in 2003 with "The Hum Melody".

artist.name: Grooveyard
artist.bio:
Please note:
 There are MANY artists with this name  One of the artists under this name is Jeroen Verheij, also known as Secret Cinema. Judging by tags, most listeners probably refer to this artist when scrobbling for Grooveyard. The greatest hit Jeroen produced under this name is "Mary go wild", all the way back in 1996. Another hit was "Let the music be your guide", co-produced with Michel de Heij.

artist.name: Robbie Rivera
artist.bio: Riberto Louis Rivera, better known as Robbie Rivera, is a prolific house music producer and DJ born in Puerto Rico. He has an extensive catalog of original productions and remixes to his credit, ranging from tribal to progressive house, as well as incorporating garage and latin elements. As a solo artist he has hit #1 on the US Hot Dance Music/Club Play chart 3 times: in 2003 with "The Hum Melody", in 2004 with "Burning" and "Which Way You're Going".

artist.name: Graeme Harrison
artist.bio: Graeme is a trance dj from Hull but now living in Southampton, UK. His music ranges from progressive trance right through to the most uplifting pumping trance the industry has to offer .Inspired by the likes off Armin Van Buuren, Matt Hardwick, Guy Ornedel and many more of the trance industrys most uplifting deejays Graeme takes a style from his inspirations and joins it in to one musical journey.

artist.name: Serge Devant
artist.bio: When you're personally hand picked to share the stage with the worlds top DJs , including being tagged by DJ Tiesto himself to open and close for him in NYC, youve got something. Now armed with his new residency at Crobar, what he has is your attention. Hear him perform and you will witness a skillful exhibition from one of the most promising young talents in the electronic industry todaywe are talking about Serge Devant.

artist.name: P.A.F.F.
artist.bio: Pawel Kasperski aka P.A.F.F. (b.1990) - Electronic music producer from Wroclaw, Poland. Pawel started his adventure with music producing at the age of 9, having discovered he could produce on eJay and Magix Music Maker, and deciding this was something he wanted to learn more about. By the age of 12 he started producing with FL Studio. In 2004 he really began to enjoy trance music.  At the end of 2006 he started experimenting with the trance sound, combining it with electro, techno and progressive.

artist.name: Sonorous
artist.bio: Rough Mullar aka Sonorous seems to be the forthcoming man of innovative Trance and House styles and he is from Germany!  Back in the middle of the 90?s he started his musical career in Punk and Rock bands as a trained guitar player. Later on he became more interested in Electronic Dance music and began to spin records. At this time he met Ralph Kyau, a Trance music producer for years and a pioneer in the East German Techno scene. These were his first steps toward producing his own music and together with Ronski Speed, a good friend and DJ, Rough Mullar started to build up his own studio.

artist.name: Di Feno & Alls feat. Karine Lima
Progresia
artist.bio: Side Project of Marcus Schossow.

artist.name: Mike Koglin vs. Mark Pledger
artist.bio: Mike Koglin burst onto the scene in 1998 with his club anthem and UK top20 hit 'The Silence', one of the defining tracks of the UK trance phenomenon which put Mike firmly onto the map as one of the key players in dance music.  Since then the Grammy-nominated Producer, Remixer and DJ has has released aconstant string of productions, under his own name or under one of his various aliases, as well as over 70 remixes in the last 7 years.

artist.name: Ascension
artist.bio: (1): Perhaps lesser-known during the "holy terror" wave of the 90's, Ascension (from Cleveland, OH - probably the "holy terror" capital of the world simply due to Integrity's presence) was another band whose relationship to hardcore was fairly minimal from a musical standpoint, as their riffing was very directly influenced by straight up thrash metal - while still retaining a certain level of that undeniably effective 90's chug.

artist.name: Depeche Mode
artist.bio: Depeche Mode is an English electronic band, founded in 1980, originally from the town of Basildon, United Kingdom. They are one of the most enduring and successful bands to have emerged during the new wave/new romantic era. As of 2006, it was estimated that Depeche Mode had sold over 91 million records (56 million albums / 35 million singles) worldwide and have had 44 songs in the UK singles chart. They are the best selling band to have never had a UK number 1 single.

artist.name: Gabriel Batz
artist.bio:
BIOGRAPHY  Name:  Gabriel Batz 
 Born:  July 07, 1982 
 Location:  Montreal, Quebec 
 Occupation:  DJ / Producer   2005 marked the introduction of a talented Canadian, from Guatemalan descent, new comer to the electronic dance music scene, Gabriel Batz.   Originating from Montreal, Quebec, Canada, Gabriel Batz opted for a career as a professional tennis player, but his love for the game of tennis was quickly replaced and pushed aside by his other passion: music.

artist.name: Starecase
artist.bio: Paul and Al met at Bristols infamous Lakota club in the summer of 1996, They built a studio rigging up an Atari ST, a Sampson mixing desk with an Roland S760, a Zoom 9120 and an HM Heavy Metal pedal and a Pro1 Paul had bought from a geezer in a pub for

artist.name: Lamai
artist.bio: Stephen Jones, Tony Rapacioli & Ricky Simmonds

artist.name: Mike Koglin vs. Marc Vedo
artist.bio: Mike Koglin burst onto the scene in 1998 with his club anthem and UK top20 hit 'The Silence', one of the defining tracks of the UK trance phenomenon which put Mike firmly onto the map as one of the key players in dance music.  Since then the Grammy-nominated Producer, Remixer and DJ has has released aconstant string of productions, under his own name or under one of his various aliases, as well as over 70 remixes in the last 7 years.

artist.name: Vincent de Moor
artist.bio: Vincent de Moor is a Dutch trance artist. de Moor started his music career in 1993, recording under the pseudonym "Fix to Fax". It wasn't until 1996 that he released his first major hit, "Flowtation", which reached the UK charts in 1997. In 1998, de Moor released his first album, "Orion City", featuring the single of the same name.  1999 is widely considered to be the year in which trance's popularity peaked, and de Moor was responsible for one of the most prominent tracks from this time.

artist.name: Kasper Koman & Ruslan B feat. Lisa Nicole
In Progress
artist.bio: 1) In Progress - russian trance music producer & DJ. Real name - Pavel Radko. His productions supported by world-famous DJs such as Armin van Buuren, Markus Schulz, Mike Shiver etc. 2) IN PROGRESS - Deutsch rock group. Check out www.myspace.com/inprogressde ;).

artist.name: Brisker & Magitman
artist.bio:
Who would have thought that the conception of two Israeli gents would have brought one of the hottest progressive acts seen this year?
 At the ages of 22 and 24, Magitman Igal and Brisker Roman are in their prime. Their music can be variable in every ways, starting from breaks, house, trance, progressive and each day some new ideas and the music keeps flowing as theyve had countless records released in 2006.

artist.name: Sequentia
artist.bio:
There are 2 artists/groups with the name Sequentia.  Sequentia - Medieval revival
 Sequentia is an early music ensemble, started in 1977 by Benjamin Bagby and the late Barbara Thornton. The group specializes mainly in Medieval music. Sequentia focuses particularly on music with texts, specifically chants and other stories with music, such as the Icelandic Edda. They are interested in the interplay between drama and music, and sometimes do partially staged performances, such as that of Hildegard of Bingen's Ordo Virtutum.

artist.name: Lorraine
artist.bio: Lorraine are a 3 piece electro-pop band from Bergen, Norway.   The members of the band are: Ole Gundersen (vocals), Anders Winsents (guitar) and P

artist.name: System K feat. Marcie
artist.bio: Karim Khaled a.k.a System K , a fresh sound coming from Egypt . Born in the 26th of july .. a Leo Sign. karim comes from a musical family .. his inspiration came from listening to some classical music and oldies then he listened to some rock music (as his father was a rock fan) , then it all started when he went with his friends to clubs and liked the style of the music played there .. he knew that this was house music , so he was introduced to the EDM. And started to listen more and search for more as the scene in egypt wasn't that big and it was hard to get the latest tunes.

artist.name: Insigma
artist.bio:
Insigma  'Insigma'/'Evolution'/'Open Our Eyes'
 Steve Helstrip & Andy Perring's Insigma outfit certainly had innocent begginings. When Steve sent Andy a 3 minute short of a track he'd been working on Andy rejigged it into a fully functioning 12" mix. Discovered 9 months later on a CDR, Tim Stark coaxed and cajoulled the pair into signing it and Insigma's self titled debut was born. They followed that quickly with the clubbing anthem that is 'Open Our Eyes'. Released on ATCR it then moved on to Virgin where it's geniune power was discovered.

artist.name: Carl Kennedy vs. MYNC Project feat. Roachford
artist.bio: In October 2003 when Pete Tong, of BBC?s Radio 1, proclaimed Carl Kennedy ?one the world?s best undiscovered DJs,? he clearly was able to see what vast numbers of club goers were soon to discover; that Carl was destined to become the a big name in dance music. Born in Birmingham, England, Kennedy made the bold move to New York when he was 20 with his eyes set on the bright lights of big city life. No one could have imagined, least of all him, the extent of excitement life had in store for him.

artist.name: Accessive Rhythm
artist.bio: An alias of a trance producer, Robin Fitter. He had two releases under this alias, Activate (2001) and Activate/Structural Beat (2002). He is also known as Fitalic and Robin Fitter.

artist.name: Golden Girls
artist.bio: Collaboration between Orbital's Paul Hartnoll and Michael Hazell. Released Kinetic in 1992 on R & S records. The track was then re-released & remixed various times up until 2001.

artist.name: Imogen Heap
artist.bio: Imogen Heap (born December 9, 1977) is a British singer-songwriter from Romford, Essex, England. She grew up playing music from an early age, and by her eleventh birthday she was writing her own songs. From the age of 15, she studied at the BRIT School Of Performing Arts & Technology in Croydon, South London, recording three tracks for the school's annual CD between 1994 and 1995, "Aliens" being the title track of the latter.

artist.name: Yanou feat. Liz
artist.bio: Yanou (real name Yann Pfeiffer) is a German trance musician and producer. He is most famous for collaborating on DJ Sammy's chart-breaking hit "Heaven" with vocalist Do. Yanou makes up one third of electronic group Cascada alongside DJ Manian and Natalie Horler.

artist.name: Jos
artist.bio: <a href="http://www.jose-gonzalez.com/" rel="nofollow">Jos

artist.name: Red Carpet
artist.bio:
From their website: 
 They have released two albums - Halfway in 2003, and The Noise Of Red Carpet in 2005  (also Japanese edition available) - and a seven-inch single. In late 2003, a video was made for the song "Tangled". Some people claim to have seen it. Some people say Red Carpet sound a bit like Buffalo Springfield, Teenage Fanclub, Love, CSN or The Beatles.   Nevertheless, they have the capability to write magnificent pop songs and present them with huge showmanship - and, more importantly, soul.

artist.name: Ti
artist.bio: Born as Tijs Verwest in Breda, Netherlands, Ti

artist.name: Nenes & Pascal Feliz
artist.bio: In the last few years, Nenes developed his own style as a dj and producer. Bringing this style to the clubs, he creates an atmosphere full of energy. After his huge clubhits ?Turbulence? and 'Polestar', Nenes is now ready to conquer the rest of the world with his music and his performance.  It all started, several years ago, when he began to spin his records in some small local clubs in his hometown Haarlem, The Netherlands.

artist.name: Andy Duguid feat Leah
artist.bio: "To live a dream is a dream come true, for those who dont dream dont live". This is Andy Duguid's philosophy and his dreams are coming true. With the release of his debut single "Hypocrisy" and notable remixes to his name 2007 was the year Andy made the EDM world stand up and take notice.  Andy's career started back in September 2006 when his production "Hypocrisy" fell into the hands of DJ Tiesto.

artist.name: Pascal Feliz
artist.bio: Pascal Feliz started his career as a dj at the age of 17. Before that he was already involved in making music because he was the lead guitarist and songwriter of a band he played in for 5 years.  Pascal was soon invited to play at a trendy dance cafe in the city of Eindhoven where he became a resident dj. There he obtained a lot of experience and he was able to develop his dj skills before a large crowd. After 2 years Pascal was asked to play at the amazing Modern Dance Club Hollywood. There he became resident dj together with Marcel Woods.

artist.name: Skunk Anansie
artist.bio: Skunk Anansie were a British rock band, notable for having a black, skinhead (not ideologically), female singer, named Skin (born Deborah Anne Dyer, on 3 August 1967, in Brixton, London). Other members included Cass (Richard Lewis) on bass guitar, Ace (Martin Kent) on guitar and Mark Richardson, who replaced the original drummer, Robbie France. The group formed in 1994, but broke up in 2001. They were named after the West-African folk tales of Anansie the spider-man, with "Skunk" added to "make the name nastier".

artist.name: Terry Ferminal vs. Mark Sherry
artist.bio: Mark Sinclair (aka Terry Ferminal) burst onto the global dance scene in the summer of 2006, under the guise ?Terry Ferminal? with first solo release titled ?Nymph?. Since then he has had huge success with releases such as ?Deep Inside?, ?Walk Away?. Signed to record labels including Armada, High Contrast and Vandit. With worldwide airplay and full support from the industry?s elite, the future looks great for this 27 year old DJ/Producer.

artist.name: Ralphie B
artist.bio: Ralphie B's real name is Ralph Barendse and he is one of the most successful artists signed to the In Trance We Trust record label. Under this, the Ralphie B guise, he produced a massive hit, which was aptly named 'Massive'! In 2002, Barendse had a very successful hit in the Midway guise called 'Monkey Forest', which was played by all of the world's top DJs at the time. He followed that up with releases such as Inca, Amazon and Cobra.

artist.name: Onova
artist.bio: Christian Lejon , known as the music producer 'Onova' and 'Substorm', started making music at the age of 16, after listening to club music at an early age. The idea of starting producing his own tracks, came when he and a friend came over a software called ReBirth. Due to Christian?s big taste for the early type of "Acid" music, this was the perfect tool for him to get things rolling. After making a number of tracks, his friend and he started practise on their dj skills on the local cafe, which held dj lessons for youngsters.

artist.name: Randy Boyer
artist.bio: Randy Boyer Years active 1996 - present Labels Armada, Flashover, Vandit, Coldharbour URL http://www.randyboyer.com/ Massachusetts native, Boyer, is a veteran of the game. For the past 12 years, Boyer has been audibly assaulting his audiences with a progressive approach to dance music that has earned him numerous accolades and world wide respect. Now living in Los Angeles, CA Boyer is going solo—taking his career to a whole new level proving that his experience and success transcends worldwide.

artist.name: Native
artist.bio:
There is more than one artist with this name:  Native 1:  Native is an indie dance rock band residing in Northwest Indiana.
 They began their journey in the spring of 2007 and continue to grow and branch out to this very day. Their sound is often compared to Minus The Bear, These Arms are Snakes, and So Many Dynamos. The four piece has self released two demos in multiple pressings with and an EP in April 2008 that is now in its third pressing.

artist.name: 4Mal feat. Gliss
artist.bio: 4Mal is one of the most brilliant musical alliances on the Russian dance scene of the recent years. Anton Guzev and Evgeny Svalov duet formed in 2002 and in the spring of 2005 really made themselves known in the Western world of dance music. They were the first of all the Russian musicians to make their debut on the famous British label ?Baroque Records? and release the single ?Twilight? on vinyl.

artist.name: Secret Cinema vs. Michel de Hey
artist.bio:
Introduction
 Jeroen Verheij aka Secret Cinema started producing as Meng Syndicate in 1990. His first record 'Sonar System ' came out on the Hithouse label in Belgium (ARS) and was an instant rave classic. In 1993 Michel de Hey recognized Jeroen 's excellent producing skills and convinced him to release his music on Michel 's Immaculate Music record labels. A string of tracks that shattered dance floors and charts followed under many aliases like Grooveyard, Point Blank and his most powerful identity: Secret Cinema.

artist.name: John O'Callaghan
artist.bio: "One of the most exciting producers in the world today." Paul van Dyk, 2007 John O'Callaghan's rapid rise to fame upwards through the ranks of world's DJ/producer elite has been nothing short of meteoric. He has stamped his authority on the global Trance community over the past 18 months emerging as one of the most prolific authorities in one of the most competitive scenes in the industry. Having long since won favour with the scenes major players through a catalogue of floor shaking releases & jaw dropping DJ performances...

artist.name: Gilbert Renoir pres. Dyor feat. Ken Spector
Miko
artist.bio: Miko is the project of Yokohama, Japan's Rie Mitsutake, a singer/multi-instrumentalist who began recording her dream pop-inspired songs on an eight-track recorder in the early 2000s. In 2005, she switched to making music on her laptop, adding more electronic and acoustic elements to her music. Her debut album, Parade, arrived in 2008 on the Plop label. This artist also refers to "miko", a sole member of Alternative ending that sings with various doujin groups, like IOSYS for example.

artist.name: Seal vs. Starkillers
artist.bio: Seal Henry Olusegun Olumide Adeola Samuel (born February 19, 1963 in Paddington, London, England) is an English soul singer and songwriter, professionally known only by his first name, Seal. He won three Grammy Awards for his 1995 single "Kiss from a Rose". Seal is of Brazilian and Nigerian descent. A childhood battle with discoid lupus left him with distinctive facial scarring and hair loss. Music career Seal (1991)

artist.name: Schiller
artist.bio: Short: Grammy nominated German Electronical Composer & Producer by the name of 'Christopher von Deylen'. Schiller is a pop/ambient project begun in 1998 by German music composer and producer Christopher von Deylen. Schiller's best known track is called "Das Glockenspiel", which became a hit in many European countries in 1999. Schiller's albums feature many well-known German and international guest vocalists and musicians such as Colbie Caillat, Lang Lang, Sarah Brightman, Moya Brennan...

artist.name: The Thrillseekers feat. Sheryl Deane
artist.bio: The Thrillseekers  Steve Helstrip has been at the very forefront of the global dance scene for over 7 years now. From his breakout hit 'Synaesthesia', through to the anthems 'Dreaming of You' and most recently 'By Your Side', he has continued to produce a powerhouse of the most emotive, evocative music going. He has remixed for luminaries such as Tiesto, Timo Maas, Sonique and Chicane, lending them all his trademark melodic, euphoric sound.

artist.name: The Orange
artist.bio: The Orange is the name of multiple artists.  One of these was a mid-eighties band from Dunedin, New Zealand, signed to Flying Nun Records. It notably featured Andrew Brough, best known for his subsequent role in Straitjacket Fits. This particular Orange was short-lived, releasing just one EP, entitled Fruit Salad Lives..

artist.name: Lange vs. Glenn Morrison
artist.bio: An innovator of the trance sound that exploded in '98, Lange is universally recognised as one of the scene's strongest and most-consistent producers. His first major success was his remix of DJ Sakin's 'Protect Your Mind', swiftly followed by his famous Lost Witness ? ?Happiness Happening? mix which also entered the UK Top 20. www.lange-music.com

artist.name: Dave Schiemann
artist.bio: Dave Schiemann was born on December 5th, 1988. He was fascinated by the DJ art since he was 13. At the beginning he practiced, as a young, unexperienced hot head should, at home on a PC, using various mixing software. But that was not enough for him. In search of his music fulfilment he tried audio editing software to remix but that still was not giving him full satisfaction. He realized that he must to give a try as a producer and since 2004 most of his time he spent on improving his skills in music production.

artist.name: First State feat Anita Kelsey
artist.bio: First State is a project of two trance producers, Ralph Barendse and Sander van der Waal. Their first album Time Frame was released on the 19th of November 2007. Their songs are often influenced by many genres. 'House, trance, minimal, pop and classical, it's all in there somewhere' as quoted from their album.

artist.name: Ernesto vs Bastian
artist.bio: Please tag as Ernesto vs. Bastian (with a . behind vs). The Dutch trance duo of a DJ (Ernesto van der Meij) and a producer (Edwin Koelewijn) was created in 2001 under the name of Ernesto vs. Bastian. They have their own radio show at ETN.fm (http://etn.fm/) web radio station. Pics & videos: http://www.myspace.com/officialernestovsbastian

artist.name: Thomas Datt
artist.bio: Thomas Datt has been slowly breaking through to the very forefront of the world’s trance scene for the past 3 years now. From his first remix release to his breakout hit “Alone”, he continues to produce an onslaught of the most emotive music going. He has done remixes for labels such as A State Of Trance, ID&T, Vandit, Bostich and Adjusted, lending them his trademark melodic and banging trance sound.

artist.name: John Huijbers
artist.bio: Dutch producer John Huijbers started his musical journey by playing the piano, back in 1999. He started producing music back in 2001. The ability to put ideas into music was really fascinating. Working his way through the marvelous adventure of music production, quickly producing music became an addiction.  Inspired by the great pioneers of trance John developed a true love for trance music and he decided to share his music with the world.

artist.name: Daniel Kandi with Matt Hardwick vs. Smith & Pledger
Oliver Moldan - Fortune Cookie (Isma
artist.bio:
OLIVER MOLDAN, THE RHINE RIVER MAN, HAS BEEN APPEARING BEHIND THE DECKS AT RENOWNED DANCE CLUBS NOT ONLY IN GERMANY BUT ALL OVER THE WORLD FOR MANY YEARS. OLIVER'S INSPIRED MIXING SKILLS COMBINED WITH HIS ECLECTIC MUSIC SELECTION HAVE CLEARLY DEFINED HIS UNIQUE AND TRAILBLAZING STYLE. HE HAS STEADILY WORKED HIS WAY UP THE LADDER TO BE RECOGNIZED AS ONE THE LEADING
 DJS ON THE TECH AND PROGRESSIVE HOUSE SCENES AND ONE MAJOR REASON FOR THIS HAS BEEN HIS RESIDENCY AT THE LEGENDARY TRIBEHOUSE IN D

artist.name: John Dahlb
artist.bio: Born in Stockholm, Sweden 1985. Moved to a small village outside Stockholm at an early age. Both his mother and father are musicians, and almost everyone in his family too. Got in touch with house music by his older cousin Jesper Dahlb

artist.name: M.I.K.E
artist.bio: M.I.K.E. is Mike Dierickx (Dirk Dierickx before changing his first name officially), a Belgian producer and DJ from the Antwerp area. (Another M.I.K.E., known as Mike, is an Indonesian Singer who won the finals of Indonesian Idol. His songs are tagged on this page.) Although mostly known for his productions under the aliases M.I.K.E., Push and Plastic Boy, Mike has released hundreds of records under more than eighty aliases and collaborations since 1992 in a wide variety of styles ranging from rave...

artist.name: Judge Jules feat. Cara Dillon
artist.bio: Judge Jules is a British dance music DJ. Born on October 26, 1965 as Julius O'Riordan, he was educated at University College School and the London School of Economics. He studied law at the LSE, giving rise to his stage name "Judge Jules", though he obtained a lower second class honours in his degree. Jules began his music career as a DJ on the then pirate radio station Kiss FM before he joined BBC Radio 1 in 1997, where he now has a regular Saturday night slot. He also has an internationally-syndicated radio show called "The Global Warm Up" www.

artist.name: Kris Benton
artist.bio: 1977 born in Pasewalk, grown up in Templin, a city in East Germany. As time went by, a melancholic, housy and technoid sound evolved.

artist.name: Sting
artist.bio: Sting (born Gordon Matthew Sumner on October 2, 1951) is an English musician from Newcastle upon Tyne. Prior to a distinguished solo career, he was the lead singer, principal composer and bassist of the 1970s/1980s rock band The Police. Biography Sumner was born in Wallsend, near Newcastle upon Tyne in northeast England, to Audrey Cowell and her husband, Ernest Sumner. He is the eldest of four children and has a brother, Philip, and two sisters, Angela and Anita. His father managed a dairy, and as a boy Sumner would often assist him with the early morning milk delivery rounds.

artist.name: Ti
artist.bio: Born as Tijs Verwest in Breda, Netherlands, Ti

artist.name: Terk Dawn
artist.bio: From Norway... More to come...

artist.name: Menno de Jong vs. Re:Locate
artist.bio: Menno de Jong is a 24 year old DJ from the Netherlands. He is the owner and founder of Intuition Recordings, also has his very own podcast at http://www.mennodejong.com, released and aired on ETN.fm's trance stream the first Wednesday of the month. Menno has played at noteworthy and some of the biggest events including Gatecrasher and Godskitchen. His other huge successes have been at events such as The Love Parade in Berlin and many others. He has travelled extensively the world over.

artist.name: Cinema Bizarre
artist.bio: Summary Cinema Bizarre is a German glam-pop/glam-rock band, consisting of now four members since one member, Luminor, left the band on November 27, 2008. While their style is showing very few visual kei influences, they stated that they are not a part of the VK scene, genre, or have any intention to join it, produce music similar to it or whatsoever. "ipop" is what their label describes as their genre, which may be slightly misleading...

artist.name: Marscruiser
artist.bio: Real Name: Paul Determan & Alex Hall URLs: http://www.marscruiser.com/

artist.name: Misja Helsloot
artist.bio: DJ Misja Helsloot is a Dutch Trance and Progressive DJ. Misja was born January 21, 1973 in Rotterdam and in 1992, at the age of nineteen started to purchase albums and organize his own parties. Mixing music with a friend, Misja worked hard for six years until he became friends with DJ Tiesto in 1998. Tiesto allowed Misja to mix his album In Trance we Trust 001. It was later released in September of the same year to a good reception in his home country The Netherlands, and also caught on in Israel and Norway.

artist.name: David Vendetta feat. Rachael Starr
artist.bio:
David Vendetta, Dj-producer & Remixer is a growing value on the international house scene.
 He shares his passion for this music by appearing in Paris,
 first as a resident at  ? Les Bains ?, ? Folies Pigalle ? , ? Amnesia ?, and now at ? Redlight ?.
 Resident Radio FG Paris on Tuesday evening from 11pm to midnight.  David is showing regularly in the best clubs throughout the world :
 Ibiza (Amnesia) , New-York (Centro Fly) , Moscow (Zona) , Barcelona (Atlantida) ,
 Bogota (Tantra) , Copenhagen (Vega), St Petersburg (Jet Set, Buddha Bar) ,

artist.name: San feat. Oliva Lewis
artist.bio: There are several artists named San. One of them is an alias used by Benno De Goeij of Rank 1. Following is the description for another San: When you like a dj and producer that plays and writes music with lots of energy, breakbeat or 4/4, aggressive basslines and lots of percussion, San suites the job perfectly. After delivering tunes under various monikers, such as the worldwide classic tune 'Solid Sessions - Janeiro' and the SanProject stuff, San got stuck into his own sound and started releasing under his own name; SAN, to showcase his diversity and wide selection of musical taste.

artist.name: Jan Johnston
Kris O'Neil vs. Daniel Kandi
artist.bio: Though Kris has only wandered on this planet since December 1986, he already achieved to play in more countries and produce/remix for finer artists and labels than most DJs will in a lifetime.  Known and complimented by promoters worldwide for his unique style in electronic dance music, flawless mixing skills and infectious enthusiasm and energy behind the DJ booth, Kris is definately among the finest and fastest rising talents to come out of Scandinavia.

artist.name: The Veil Kings
artist.bio: Searching For Truth is the only track produced under this alias. It appeared on Fantasy Trance - Volume One and In Search Of Sunrise 6.

artist.name: Justin Timberlake
artist.bio: Justin Randall Timberlake (born January 31, 1981) is a six-time Grammy-winning American singer and occasional actor. He came to fame for being one of the front men of the pop band *NSYNC in the '90s as well as for dating popstar Britney Spears. Timberlake released his debut solo album, Justified, in 2002. It went on to sell over seven million copies worldwide, solidifying Timberlake's position as a pop superstar.

artist.name: Tracey Thorn
artist.bio: Tracey Thorn (born September 26, 1962, in Brookmans Park, Hertfordshire) is an English pop singer and songwriter. She is best known as being one half of the duo Everything but the Girl. She grew up in Hatfield, Hertfordshire and studied English at the University of Hull, where she graduated in 1984 with First Class Honours. She lives with her EBTG partner Ben Watt in North London. The couple have twin daughters born in 1998, and a son born in 2001. Career: Marine Girls (1980-1983)

artist.name: Reeves feat. Alanah
artist.bio: Reeves is a 1 person supergroup coming straight out of Westfield, New York. His techno beats melt all the little girls hearts and you know he gets the babes. His main listener is Matt Dibble who is also his partner in ADN Productions. Any further information about Reeves or any upcoming tracks can be found on http://www.myspace.com/teamdv8 (<<< REEVES' MYSPACE!) Goodbye. -Matt Dibble

artist.name: Mauro Picotto
artist.bio: Mauro Picotto aka CRW and RAF (born December 25, 1966 in Cavour, Italy) is a famous Italian techno producer, remixer and DJ. Formerly a contributor to Italian Eurodance outfit Cappella, he became popular with tracks like "Proximus", "Komodo", "Iguana", "Pulsar" and "Lizard". He has cooperated with many popular trance musicians like DJ Tiësto.  He now promotes his own club night called "Meganite", now in its fouth year at Privilege Ibiza, the worlds largest nightclub. He produces under his own label, Bakerloo.

artist.name: Sharam
artist.bio: Sharam Tayebi mans the turntables as one half of the Grammy award winning DJ/production duo Deep Dish. The Iranian/American is characterized by a harder style than his partner Ali "Dubfire" Shirazinia, Sharam performs as Deep Dish featuring Sharam, when he takes to the road to deliver his signature half of the distinct Deep Dish sound.  Having recently completed a solo tour of Canada, Sharam was met by packed houses at some of the country's top clubs, including The One Lounge in Victoria, The Plaza in Vancouver...

artist.name: Sophie Sugar
artist.bio: Sophie Sugar is a 25-year-old trance DJ and Producer from the UK. She has released four singles, "Fearing Nothing" in 2003, "Call of Tomorrow" in 2005, "Isis" in 2006 (released on e-tcr), and "Fallen Too Far" in 2007. "Call of Tomorrow" was featured in the A State of Trance 2005 compilation, with her new single "Day Seven" featured on A State of Trance 2007.  Sophie Sugar is one of the most exciting names on the UK trance scene at the moment.

artist.name: Matt Cerf vs. Eric Menza feat. Jaren
artist.bio: DJ/Producer Matt Cerf started his career in 1998 after attending a rave during his Junior year at McGill University, in Montreal, where he was studying Agricultural Engineering. He quickly dropped schooling to study the ins and outs of music production on his own. In 2000, he and three friends created the group Second Sun and Matt's first track, Empire, quickly caught the attention of DJ Paul Van Dyk. Empire was signed to Paul's label, Vandit, and Second Sun appeared on Quebec?s version of MTV, Music Plus.

artist.name: Gareth Emery pres. Rue de Gar
JPL
artist.bio: There are several artists with this name: 1) Even though he was born as recently as 1987, JPL (real name Joni Ljungqvist) is considered one the biggest rising talents on the trance scene. In 2006, JPL also had a huge hit in his A Boy Called Joni alias, which featured on many compilation albums, including In Search Of Sunrise 5 by Tiesto. Ljungqvist has also remixed a track called Stealth for Kyamoto, whilst collaborating on projects with fellow rising stars Carl B and Galen Behr.

artist.name: Chris Lake feat. Laura V
artist.bio: Globally recognised as one of the most exciting, forward thinking and cutting edge producers on the scene, Chris Lake's rare ability to create tracks that fuse elements of house, electro and techno has not been lost on his fellow peers. His innovative productions continue to receive wave after wave of support from such luminaries that include Sasha, Danny Howells, Justin Robertson, Sander Kleinenberg and Carl Cox, whilst Pete Tong leads the way in championing the unique sound that has established Chris as one of the world's elite.

artist.name: Jay Lumen feat. Antonia Lucas
artist.bio: His real name is Csaba Lumnitzer. Music is part of his life since his childhood years. He learnt music in a conservatoire for eight years, which provides a good basis to his ambition of making music. Besides composing music he became to be more and more open to the dj scena. In the beginning he played at parties that he organized on his own, then later he started with his career with complying occasional invitations.

artist.name: Matt Cerf vs. Eric Meza feat. Jaren
Leonid Rudenko
artist.bio: Leonid Rudenko is a house/trance producer from Moscow, Russian Federation. He released four singles: Stardisease (2006), Summerfish (2006), Real Life (2008), Destination (2008), and four remixes. He is mostly known for being featured on In Search Of Sunrise 6.

artist.name: Shifted Reality
artist.bio: http://www.shiftedrealitymusic.com Hailing from Novosibirsk, Russia, Alexander Smirnov a.k.a. Shifted Reality (aliases A2M with Michelle Koeth, Shifted Reality & Santerna, Shifted Reality & Endforest, Substanze, Sasha Madden) began producing music without a formal music education at age 15, with a simple and amateur program from the eJay series. A year later, Alex began producing dance music with Propellerheads ReBirth RB-338 which he's still uses to this day. Alex also used Fruityloops to incorporate VSTi synths into his music, as well as to expand his overall production knowledge.

artist.name: Mark Pledger vs. Super8 & Tab
artist.bio: Mark is one of ?Trance?s fastest rising stars? (iDJ Magazine) and half of acclaimed production duo, Smith & Pledger. His productions have been played all over the world by every major player from Paul Oakenfold to Tiesto & PVD. He has also earned regular (BBC) Radio 1 plays from Judge Jules & Dave Pearce.

artist.name: The Quest
artist.bio: The Quest is a moniker of Benno De Goeij, better known as 1/2 of Rank 1 w/ Piet Bervoets and 1/2 of Kamaya Painters w/ Tijs Verwest (aka Ti

artist.name: Global Experience
artist.bio: A collaboration of DJ Shah and Brian Laruso, who have released 4 songs, Tennessee/Dakar in 2005 and Zanzibar/San Salvador in 2006. Zanzibar was featured in Tiesto's "In Search of Sunrise 5" compilation.  A new song, Madras, was featured on Tiesto's "In Search of Sunrise 6: Ibiza" compilation.

artist.name: Super8 & DJ Tab
artist.bio: Super8 & Tab are the antidote to anyone who says the trance scene has gone stale. By combining dark and driving progressive elements with more traditional melodic trance sounds, the pair have created a unique sound that has had the worlds A-list DJs clamouring for their music.  Super8 & Tabs

artist.name: BT
artist.bio: Brian Transeau (born Brian Wayne Transeau on October 4, 1971, in Rockville, Maryland) is a musician who records under the stage name BT. Classically trained from the age of 13, he attended Berklee College of Music in Boston for one year before dropping out and moving to Los Angeles, California, and then back to Washington, D.C..  Brian Transeau is the father of a young daughter, Kaia. He lives and composes his works in his Los Angeles home/studio in which he has a few Apple G5's and 8 AMD dual-core Opteron 64-bit desktops which he uses for his techno-wizardry.

artist.name: Karen Overton
artist.bio:
Karen Overton is known for her voice in the very popular Progressive House track Your Loving Arms, the Club Mix of which was mixed into DJ Tiesto's "In Search Of Sunrise 5" (2006) and Armin van Buuren's "A State of Trance 2006".  She's also a pop singer, and she writes her own songs.  
 Karen Overton was born in 1983 in Brighton England. She attended the K-Bis School for Performing Arts where she began writing music. After a couple years she moved to London where she began modeling. While modeling she kept writing songs and working with artists like Kelly Le Roc and Big Brovaz.

artist.name: Electro-Prompt
artist.bio: This is chilled-out, mellow drifty music sometimes set to a rapid drumbeat; pleasant as well to hear French vocals, alternating with a Slavic language.

artist.name: Fonzerelli
artist.bio:
Alias for Aaron McClelland, a dj and producer from Dublin, Ireland.  McClelland is also known as :  Fonzerelli
 Yer Man  The song Moonlight Party was his break into the International world of music.

artist.name: Coast 2 Coast feat. Discovery
artist.bio: trance group from ireland

artist.name: Rui Da Silva
artist.bio: Rui da Silva is a Portuguese producer and DJ, whose single "Touch Me" (featuring the vocals of Cassandra Fox) topped the UK Chart in 2001. At the time, he was the only Portuguese musician to have a UK hit and hence was the first to score a UK number one.  Rui started producing house music in 1992, just as club culture was getting established in Lisbon. Noticing the lack of dance music labels in Portugal, Rui teamed up with DJ Vibe to form Kaos Records, the first label in Portugal specialized in house and electronic music.

artist.name: Phatzoo
artist.bio: Twisted Tweak was one of the highlights of Marco V?s brilliant recent Combi:Nations mix album and the V-Man himself rates it as one of his tunes of the summer. The guy behind Phatzoo is Stefan Engblom, who has had some success under the Phasio guise, with one of his records going double platinum in, randomly, Japan. He is also part of the hot new act Dada Life who I expect to be big in 2007. Twisted Tweak has already seen a release on Sweden?s Just For Fun Records and has been snapped up by Marco V, along with a remix by himself, for his In Charge label.

artist.name: Ben Brown
artist.bio: Ben Brown was born in Indianapolis, USA in 1983 to a family of modest means. With his father in the computing industry and his mother being somewhat of a musician, it seemed inevitable that Ben would get into some kind of trouble with computers and music. His youth consisted of the usual childhood activities but music and its various influences left the greatest impression upon him.  Fast forward to the fall of 2006 when Ben moved to Chicago, both to pursue an graduate degree and also to engross himself in a thriving progressive, trance, and house music scene.

artist.name: Julian Jeweil
artist.bio:
"About JULIAN JEWEIL
 Julian Jeweil, dj producer and high value from the french electronic scene discover techno at the "enfanthome" party in Marseille, the Sun City on the french riviera. This event were a revelation, the start of never ending passion. To 2001, Julian played on many underground parties from his region, this same year he got into Fight Klub crew. He became resident, and played in more than sixty parties. In two years he succeed to push himself high and became a inescapable dj.

artist.name: The Blizzard
artist.bio: There are 3 bands/groups that share the name 'The Blizzard':  1. Norwegian trance producer duo (Lars-Christian Nyheim & Tore Vatle Jensen). Debut single "Kalopsia" released in 2007, receiving support from many of the world's biggest DJs.  2. Dunedin, New Zealand based drum'n'bass/techtronica/dubstep producer and DJ.  3. Italian independent goth metal group, active from 2000 until 2006.

artist.name: Three Drives On A Vinyl
artist.bio: Erik de Koning, alias Enrico, has been producing music for 12 years now and is famous for "WaterVerve" (in some countries also called WaterWave). However, one is probably most impressed by his work under the name of Three Drives (co-productions with Ton TB)."Greece 2000", "Sunset on Ibiza", "Carrera 2" and "Air Traffic" are just a few titles that did very well, especially in the UK.  Erik has produced an enormous amount of tracks but how did it all start? His musical career started in 1990. He used to work, together with his buddy Mark van Dale, at Mid-town records.

artist.name: George Acosta vs. Mike Shiver
artist.bio: Trance, whether you like your trance melodic and uplifting, or hard and fast, trance by any definition is here to stay. From the warehouse parties of the late 80?s to car commercials in 2001, trance has become part of the new millennium, part of our lifestyle. And all because of DJs like George Acosta. George proves every time he puts a needle on a record that "trance", whatever the label, has changed, evolved, become a lifestyle, a culture? as well it should.

artist.name: Mojado
artist.bio: several artists share the name Mojado one is an electronic music group made up of experienced DJs/Producers Mr Sam (Samuel Paquet) and Dimitri Andreas. Their sound is a combination of tribal, techno, house and trance. To date they have released 6 singles, 2 albums, and 4 12" samplers for their latest CD "Skiz

artist.name: Deadmau5 & Glenn Morrison
artist.bio: Seems Deadmau5 has teamed up with Glenn Morrison, of which much detail is not available. So far they are known to have put together the house track "Contact", so far only seen on whitelabel. See info about Deadmau5 here

artist.name: Billie Ray Martin
artist.bio: The non-stop Electronic Cabaret of Billie Ray Martin "The singer is Billie Ray Martin and she?s one of the living legends in modern music history and one of the best voices on planet earth." DJ Hell ?Billie Ray Martin does it better...She is the thinking man?s diva, never being afraid to take a chance and push forward? Dean Thatcher To anyone with a soul, the return of Billie Ray Martin is long overdue.

artist.name: Moussa Clarke feat. Fisher
artist.bio: Moussa Clarke is an inspirational DJ/producer with a worldwide reputation for igniting dancefloors from London to Moscow to Tokyo and back again. Never far from the madding crowd ? apart from when he?s cooking up monster basslines and electrochemical beats in the studio ? he?s also founder of the thriving London-based label and DJ agency Oven Ready.
