Born in Switzerland, half English, half Senegalese, he found his feet in France and Italy, and then travelled the globe before moving to the UK aged 12.

artist.name: Jessica
artist.bio: For the japanese visual kei band called "Jessica" go to ? ???????.

artist.name: CRW
artist.bio: CRW or C R W Members: Andrea Remondini, Mauro Picotto Source:http://www.discogs.com/artist/CRW Pics from:http://www.andrearemondini.com/

artist.name: Above and Beyond
artist.bio: Above & Beyond are a trance music group formed in 2000. The group is famous for remixes and their own productions. The group's tracks are regularly played by well-known DJs, such as Tiësto, Armin van Buuren and Paul van Dyk. They are also known under other aliases, like Tranquility Base, OceanLab, Dirt Devils and Rollerball. Jono Grant and Paavo Siljam

artist.name: JES
artist.bio: Singer Jes Brieden, also known as JES, is the singer of As the Rush Comes (with Gabriel & Dresden as Motorcycle), Like A Waterfall (with Solar Stone), Everything With You (with D:Fuse) and Ghost (with Deepsky). Jes Brieden is a singer, songwriter and producer. Born and raised in New York City, she studied art and singing at art school. She first began experimenting with music making in friends’ studios. By age 16, she was already making her first vocal recordings as a reference vocalist, and had also worked as a backup singer for several major recording labels.

artist.name: Cliff Coenraad
artist.bio: From Cliff himself the following description:  Writing biographies really sucks! So sue me if it sucks, send your complaints to info at cliffcoenraad dot com or just sit this one through. Anyway, for some of you who are interested, I can tell you some things about me...  My mom told me that I was born in Tilburg, The Netherlands, on April 27 in 1982. (You do the math) I think I was at the age of twelve when I got interested in music, before that time I was only watching cartoons like “The Transformers” and “Mask” on Sky Channel.

artist.name: Alex Dolby
artist.bio: Alex Dolby was born in the rich land of Ciociaria some years ago He got involved in music production after having attended several clubs nights around Italy. His influences have to be searched in djs as Lory-D, Speedy-j and Leo Anibaldi but also in the italian house protagonists as Ralf, Flavio Vecchi and Ricky Montanari. As soon as he got his own studio he started producing tracks which were the fusion of electronic and house music. He worked hard and he reached his own style, the same characteristic music flavour that nowadays calls so much attention on him.

artist.name: Coast 2 Coast
artist.bio: trance group from ireland

artist.name: Filo & Peri feat. Vanessa Valentin
artist.bio: FIL0 & PERI BIOGRAPHY:  Five short years; that?s the short span of time it has taken New Yorkers Filo & Peri to go from newborn duo to international DJ/producer superstars. In the highly competitive world of DJing, that?s a tremendous feat in itself!  Then when you figure into their resume consecutive listings in the prestigious DJ Mag Top 100 DJs Poll, signings to Armin van Buuren and Paul Van Dyks?s recording labels, both a Billboard Number 1 and UK Top 40 hit...

artist.name: Gouryella
artist.bio: In 1999, successful Dutch artists Ferry Corsten and Tiësto joined forces to create the trance partnership of Gouryella. To highlight their importance in the trance scene at the time, there were 20 separate CD releases of the 4 Gouryella tracks from 9 different labels. Incidentally, the name of Gouryella comes from the Aborigine word for Heaven. Gouryella is known to have released six tracks: Gouryella, Gorella, Walhalla, In Walhalla, Tenshi and Ligaya.

artist.name: Jay Lumen feat. Nina Simone
artist.bio: His real name is Csaba Lumnitzer. Music is part of his life since his childhood years. He learnt music in a conservatoire for eight years, which provides a good basis to his ambition of making music. Besides composing music he became to be more and more open to the dj scena. In the beginning he played at parties that he organized on his own, then later he started with his career with complying occasional invitations.

artist.name: John O'Callaghan feat. Brian Kearney
artist.bio: "One of the most exciting producers in the world today." Paul van Dyk, 2007 John O'Callaghan's rapid rise to fame upwards through the ranks of world's DJ/producer elite has been nothing short of meteoric. He has stamped his authority on the global Trance community over the past 18 months emerging as one of the most prolific authorities in one of the most competitive scenes in the industry. Having long since won favour with the scenes major players through a catalogue of floor shaking releases & jaw dropping DJ performances...

artist.name: Andy Bagguley
artist.bio: Andy has created his own demand through his relentless determination yet laid back friendly attitude which has caught the attention of the music industry and its fans and taken him as a guest DJ to many of the UK's leading events including The Gallery, Serious, Goodgreef, Slinky and Crasher amongst others. Andy was also promoter and resident DJ for PaSSion @ The Emporium from 2003 through till 2007 in which time he acquired a great following of fans for his faultless sets be it warm-up, peak time or end of the night.

artist.name: Gold & Diaz - Dont You Want Me (Thomas Gold O
Jones & Stephenson
artist.bio: "The First Rebirth" is one of the best known early rave tracks from 1993. Over the year 1994 and 1995 they released sequels called "The Second Rebirth"; "The Third Rebirth" and later on "The Fourth Rebirth".  Several remixes of those records have been made and are now available as Bonzai Classics.

artist.name: Algarve
artist.bio: Algarve is a progressive/trance DJ/Producer from Sweden.  His real name is Ludvig Holm.  He has worked closely with Selu Vibra and Sebastian Brandt.  He currently has releases on Supra Recordings, Armada Music, and Somatic Sense.  He is known for his single "Seashore".

artist.name: Chris Lake feat. Emma Hewitt
artist.bio: Globally recognised as one of the most exciting, forward thinking and cutting edge producers on the scene, Chris Lake's rare ability to create tracks that fuse elements of house, electro and techno has not been lost on his fellow peers. His innovative productions continue to receive wave after wave of support from such luminaries that include Sasha, Danny Howells, Justin Robertson, Sander Kleinenberg and Carl Cox, whilst Pete Tong leads the way in championing the unique sound that has established Chris as one of the world's elite.

artist.name: Chicane feat. Maire Brennan
artist.bio: Chicane is a pseudonym used by UK-based electronical composer, musician and producer Nicholas Bracegirdle. He was born on 28 February 1971, in London, England. Chicane is known for the single Offshore, an Ibiza anthem included in thousands of compilations in both chill-out and dance form; Saltwater, which featured vocals by Clannad member M

artist.name: Kirsty Hawkshaw meets Tenishia
artist.bio: Kirsty Hawkshaw (born 26 October 1969, London) is a British female dance/electronica/house musician and songwriter who is known for her signature vocals.  Hawkshaw is the daughter of the British production music/film music composer and disco record producer Alan Hawkshaw. Her father and her love for dance music inspired Hawkshaw to pursue a career in music.  At a rave event in 1991 she was noticed by producers Ian Munro, Kevin Dobbs and Nigel Walton, who at the time were known as A.S.K. It was through this meeting that they would form a dance act called Opus III.

artist.name: Lolo
artist.bio: Laurent Véronnez (born December 10, 1977), is a Belgium-based progressive trance music artist. He has created more than 500 tracks for more than 35 projects. His most notable aliases are Airwave and Lolo.  He lived in Brussels until he was 20 years old, experimenting with computers and synthesizers at his home. After sending his first demonstration to Lightning Records

artist.name: Under Sun vs. Signum
artist.bio: This is a collaboration project between Sebastian Brandt and Marcus Schossow.

artist.name: Neal Scarborough
artist.bio: Neal Scarborough first established himself as a DJ through prime time shows on top Dublin dance stations Kiss, Pulse and Club FM. His sound of melodic trance with a hard edge soon had him playing Dublin clubs such as The Temple Theatre, Club Mono and various other venues throughout Ireland, confirming him as a firm favourite amongst Ireland's clubbing community.  In 2004, Neal first collaborated with John O'Callaghan on a number of different projects, the most successful coming under the guise of Inertia.

artist.name: DNS Project
artist.bio: Rene Pais, better known as dns Project, was born on the 25th of March, 1988 in a small Estonian town called Prnu. His interest in music started at the age of 7, when he started to take piano classes. After taking them for like 2 years, he went to music school. In the beginning, it was quite cool there, but with years, it became more boring and boring... When he had been there for already like 5 years, he decided to quit. Then he bought a cheap portable keyboard (PSR-340) and started playing it. When he heard some good tunez on the radio, he often tried to play along it on the keyboard.

artist.name: Mike Koglin vs. Energy Dai
artist.bio: Mike Koglin burst onto the scene in 1998 with his club anthem and UK top20 hit 'The Silence', one of the defining tracks of the UK trance phenomenon which put Mike firmly onto the map as one of the key players in dance music.  Since then the Grammy-nominated Producer, Remixer and DJ has has released aconstant string of productions, under his own name or under one of his various aliases, as well as over 70 remixes in the last 7 years.

artist.name: Agnelli & Nelson
artist.bio: Agnelli & Nelson, the collective name of Northern Irish pair Chris Agnelli and Robbie Nelson (who also produce under the names Afterburn, Cortez, Green Atlas, A&N Project, and Quincey & Sonance), writers and producers of dance music, are notable for helping to define the genre of Trance music since 1997.  Since 1997, Chris Agnelli and Robbie Nelson have been writing and producing dance music, of which their hits El Nino and Everyday have become classics of their genre. They have to date produced five top 30 hits in the United Kingdom, and countless remixes, from Armin van Buuren to U2.

artist.name: Joakim Daif vs. Likuida pres. Aerodive
2000 and One
artist.bio: 2000 And One a.k.a. Dylan Hermelijn. Back into time, the year is 1989 when he joint up with Daniel (Dj Dano), together as 2000 And One. Signed up with Lower Eastside Records to do their first EP entitelded 2000 And One - The Sound of Planet Earth. As one of the first to do underground acid in the Netherlands. Later he got more in touch with the Detroit sound, as we know him now for. 2000 And One brings the melody into the funk and back, with the Detroit flavour on top of it.

artist.name: Workidz
artist.bio: Workidz alias David Nagy is based in Budapest, Hungary. He is one of the well-known producers in Europe nowadays.  More than 30 official albums (mainly 4 Track Eps) and for about 10 remix vinyls available of him around the world. As a Dj he visits mainly german night clubs.    He started his career in year 1997 in a dj group that played pop & dance music. There he studied everything about mixing music, and after a year he played house music in different parties in Hungary (at that time as Mukky).

artist.name: Skin
artist.bio: 1) Solo artist formerly of Skunk Anansie 2) British 4 piece Hard Rock band 3) Swans 4) Japanese "Superband" consisting of members of disbanded successful bands. The correct tag is S.K.I.N.. 5) Percussion group based on the North Coast of New South Wales, Australia 1) Deborah Anne Dyer (aka "Skin") (born 3 August 1967, Brixton, London, England) was the lead vocalist of britrock band Skunk Anansie.

artist.name: Dubfire
artist.bio: Dubfire (aka Ali Shirazinia)--one half of the Grammy Award winning and four-time nominated electronic music duo Deep Dish--has joined forces with Global Underground for the April 10 release of his first solo mix album Dubfire GU31 – Taipei. The 2-CD mix set is a sweeping change from anything you would have previously expected to hear from the Deep Dish member and it features the finest in house, electro, techno, and even industrial music.

artist.name: Alucard vs. Solarstone
artist.bio: There is more than one artist with this name: 1) Alucard is a punk band from Sterling Heights, Michigan, a suburb of Detroit. They refer to their style of music as "shredcore," playing fast and melodic punk rock. They recently released their debut full-length, entitled After Dark. In October 2007, guitarist Mike Supina began playing with A Wilhelm Scream, following the departure of Chris Levesque. In January 2008, he became a permanent member. 2) Alucard is also the name of a band in Belgium who play a style of music known as dark romanticism. They have released one EP.

artist.name: Mind One
artist.bio: German based duo Mind One has spent the last few months in their studio working on new tracks and remixes. As always it was important to them to create the significant Mind One Sound. This claim is impressively proofed by their new single 'Hurt Of Intention' which arose in collaboration with the the newcomer singer Rebekka Thenu. Groovy beats in a combination with an exceptional voice, a lush bassline and powerful melodies manufacture a sound that can't be fixed to just one musical direction. This mixture fascinates in clubs as well as on the radio.

artist.name: Prayag
artist.bio: Prayag's music aims to be spiritual as well as sensual, rocking as well as thought provoking, kick-(you-know-what) as well as soothing. Like the confluence of the Ganga, Yamuna & the Saraswati, they are about influences from different shores intermingling to create a new sound that experiments freely with soundscapes, defies genre barriers, and yet is as uniquely Indian as it is rooted in rock.  They don?t believe in hatred.

artist.name: Heikki L
artist.bio: When Heikki was ten years old and he got his first stereo system set up in his room, he stole all of his parents' cassette tapes and listened to them until they were worn out. He then moved onto hunting down music from his friends and neighbours.  At the age of thirteen Heikki met a local DJ who handed him a tape that was filled with techno and house music. Inspired by this Heikki bought his first record player and mixer, spending all his pocket money on 12? singles.

artist.name: Doug Laurent
artist.bio:
being influenced by frankfurt's electronic music scene and its legendary airport club "dorian gray", german sound mastermind DOUG LAURENT started deejaying back in 1985.
 shown on many occasions behind the turntables, he pushed crowds worldwide to experience a variety of emotions with his progressive but melodic trance style.doug also established himself as the worldwide renown producer of more than 350 released tracks, represented by over 80 international labels (both major and independents).

artist.name: E-Craig
artist.bio: There is more than one artist by the name "E": 1 E's real name is Mark Oliver Everett and he is the driving force behind the band Eels. He released two solo albums under the moniker "E": Broken Toy Shop and A Man Called E. 2 E is also the name of a Chinese alternative rock band. 3 E was also a punk rock band from Caracas, Venezuela that existed around mid 2002-mid 2003 that featured Archi from atte and IL from Boom Boom Clan,Las Américas, La Fiera Del Viniland Los Druppies.

artist.name: Coby
artist.bio: There seem to be loads of groups/artists that go under the name 'Cody' but the one i know are a rock n roll band, not sure where they're from or anything about them but i have a demo cd a mate lent me years ago.

artist.name: Mike Koglin vs. P.O.S.
artist.bio: Mike Koglin burst onto the scene in 1998 with his club anthem and UK top20 hit 'The Silence', one of the defining tracks of the UK trance phenomenon which put Mike firmly onto the map as one of the key players in dance music.  Since then the Grammy-nominated Producer, Remixer and DJ has has released aconstant string of productions, under his own name or under one of his various aliases, as well as over 70 remixes in the last 7 years.

artist.name: Ayla
artist.bio: Short: German Electronical Trance Producer and Dj, by the name of Ingo Kunzi (born on November 7, 1969) Ingo Kunzi is probably best known for his work under his Ayla alias, but also has popular releases under his other main alias - Tandu The name - Ayla (Turkish) - was inspired by the name of a girl, who was in the studio during his first recording. His track Ayla, which is his best known track, was remixed by another popular German producer and Dj - .Taucher.

artist.name: Amex
artist.bio: Rory Allen Phillips Has been Involved with such projects as The Impossibles, Slowreader, and his newest project is called Rory and the Artificial Heart. Andreas Marx (amex) does produce Techno-DNB together with his studio partner Kaiza, see http://www.last.fm/music/amex%2B%2526%2BKaiza

artist.name: Wamdue Project
artist.bio: Basically a solo project for Atlanta producer Chris Brann with the help of DJ cohorts Deep C and Udoh, Wamdue Productions' recordings provided one of the few convincing home/club fusions which err, if at all, on the side of the dancefloor. Unlike the large community of artists more allied to their headphones than a bassbin, Wamdue productions are easy club favorites, and though they record for the strictly mainstream label Strictly Rhythm, Wamdue marries intense warmth gained from R&B and house to the tighter rhythms and hard effects of Detroit techno.

artist.name: Fragma
artist.bio: Fragma, or the Fragma Project are a German house/trance group comprising four members. Founded in 1998 by brothers Dirk and Marco Duderstadt, they produced their first single Toca Me with experienced producer Ramon Zenker. When it was released the following year it topped several dance charts around the world, and reached number 11 in the UK charts.  In 2000, a mash-up was produced, taking the music of Fragma's Toca Me and placing the vocals from Coco's I Need A Miracle over the top and renamed Toca's Miracle which gained further attention from DJs Pete Tong and Judge Jules.

artist.name: Frontline
artist.bio:
There is more than one artist with this name:  
 1) Frontline are a NZ hip hop duo consisting of Samoan-European MC David Dallas (also known as Con Psy) and producer and DJ Nick McLaren (DJ 41:30).  After meeting in 2001 in Auckland, the pair formed some tracks together & released a street album 'What You Expect?'. During this time McLaren produced tracks for the likes of the 'Deceptikonz', 'Mareko' and more while Dallas completed a BSc in computing. Without any formal broadcasting, the album moved over 1200 copies.

artist.name: Niels van Gogh
artist.bio: Niels van Gogh from Augsburg, 27 years of age and DJ by profession, has been already working at the turntables of innumerable clubs and events such as the Love Parade, Rave on Snow, the Nature One Festival and the Energy Rave in Switzerland.  Between 1997 and 2000 he was resident DJ in the the Pleasure Dome Club in Augsburg. Since the beginnning of 2000 he has been the resident of the Poison Club in Duesseldorf.

artist.name: Club Nouveau
artist.bio: Club Nouveau is an R&B band that was formed by producer/performer Jay King in 1986 in Sacramento, California, subsequent to the break up of the Timex Social Club. Other members of Club Nouveau included original members Denzil Foster, Thomas McElroy, Samuelle Pratter, and Valerie Watson.  From their debut album, Love, Life, and Pain, which showed up in 1986, they scored four consecutive hits: "Jealousy" (essentially a rewrite of and response to Timex Social Club's hit "Rumours"), "Situation #9", a remake of Bill Withers' "Lean on Me", and "Why You Treat Me So Bad".

artist.name: Robert Miles
artist.bio: Robert Miles (born Roberto Concina, November 3, 1969, in Neuch

artist.name: Freaks
artist.bio: There are 2 artists that go under the name "Freaks"; 1) Duo Justin Harris & Luke Solomon who run the Music For Freaks label. Born in 1994, their initial releases visited mid-tempo house, filter disco and minimal techno genres. More recent tracks such as "The Creeps" and "Where Were You When The Lights Went Out" have seen the band progress into a live act, with Stella Attar on vocals and Jonny Rock on guitar alongside Justin & Luke on keyboards and percussion. They have also remixed Kasabian, Damon Albarn and Chicken Lips amongst others.

artist.name: Adam White feat. Liz Cirelli
artist.bio: Hailing from London, Adam White has been a recognised professional DJ for the past 10 years. Adams thriving musical interests led to the successful completion of his Grade 8 piano by the age of 16. Adams continued enthusiasm for music led to the study of Music Technology at HND level. His time at college initiated his immense enthusiasm for dance music, and subsequent passion for DJing. The recent years have seen Adams DJing career excel to a highly professional level, resulting in regular bookings at some of the worlds most prestigious clubs including Ministry Of Sound...

artist.name: DJ Rolando a.k.a. The Aztec Mystic
Mark Norman feat. Jes
artist.bio: Mark Norman are the award winning Dutch production duo, responsible for a series of high profile original productions and remixes. Dubbed by Tiesto as his hot prediction for the future, dance floor anthems such as Touchdown, Phantom Manor, Overkill, RUSH, and Mark Norman pres. Celine have assisted in their meteoric rise from hopefuls to fully fledged international artists in just a few years.  Signed to Black Hole Recordings on Tiesto?s own Magik Muzik label, original tracks such as Stream, which was featured on Tiesto?s DVD ?Another Day at the Office?...

artist.name: Artic Quest
artist.bio: An alternate spelling of Arctic Quest. Arctic Quest was born Emiel R. Ten Hoor and raised in Dutch city Amersfoort in 1976. Playing piano since the age of 9, his musical interest and talents were obvious from the start. And by mainly playing jazz, rhythm and blues a solid base was formed for a bright future.  The introduction of personal computers early 90's, wakened his electronic interests and he changed the piano for software like Scream Tracker and Impulse Tracker.

artist.name: San
artist.bio: There are several artists named San. One of them is an alias used by Benno De Goeij of Rank 1. Following is the description for another San: When you like a dj and producer that plays and writes music with lots of energy, breakbeat or 4/4, aggressive basslines and lots of percussion, San suites the job perfectly. After delivering tunes under various monikers, such as the worldwide classic tune 'Solid Sessions - Janeiro' and the SanProject stuff, San got stuck into his own sound and started releasing under his own name; SAN, to showcase his diversity and wide selection of musical taste.

artist.name: Ferry Corsten vs. Cerf, Mitiska & Jaren
artist.bio: Ferry Corsten is a Dutch DJ, producer and recorder who first started out in 1991 producing underground hardcore gabber tracks, he soon expanded into clubhouse and trance music. But don't put Ferry into the trance corner, because his sound encompasses several genres of electronic music. In 1999 Ferry Corsten was voted Best Producer of the Year at the Ericsson Muzik Award in London. In 2000, he was awarded Best Remix for Adagio for Strings (Ferry Corsten remix) at the Dancestar 2000 awards.

artist.name: Dash Berlin feat. Cerf, Mitiska & Jaren
DJ Miss Babayaga & DJ Josh Blackwell
Lucca
artist.bio: DJ Lucca began performing as a DJ in 1999. She is influenced by the melodic groovy techno of Italian producers. She cooperates with Davide Squillace in the studio, is interested in the productions of Danilo Vigorito, Markantonio, Rino Cerrone, Gaetano Parisio, Marco Carola, and among her favourites also belong Slovenian‘s Valentino Kanzyani and Umek, Canadian DJ Preach and Brazilian Renato Cohen. In 2002, Lucca started building her own studio and one year later she released her successful debut Mirage 01 on Aquatrax.

artist.name: Sydney Blu
artist.bio: Constant and determined effort can break down barriers, and for Canada’s leading lady behind the decks, carving her top spot among today’s finest burgeoning DJs is the result of her hard work. For the past six years, Sydney Blu has been DJing her electro-tinged, dirty tribal house sets to packed dancefloors across North America. “DJing was something I looked at and instantly knew I wanted to do,” says Blu, who has built a following in gay-friendly and underground clubs.

artist.name: Lee Haslam
artist.bio: Lee Haslam is a UK trance, tech trance and hard dance producer who cemented his formidable reputation as manager of hard dance label Tidy Traxx. While at Tidy he amassed an impressive discography of tracks including Liberate, El Diablo Adentro (The Devil Inside) and Music Is The Drug, an undisputed classic of the hard trance genre. More recently, Lee left Tidy to set up his own label, Digital Remedy, which so far has showcased Lee's talents as a trance and tech trance producer.

artist.name: Kings Of Leon
artist.bio: Kings of Leon are a Grammy Award-winning alternative/garage rock band which formed in Mt. Juliet, Tennessee, United States in  2000 . The band consists of brothers Nathan Followill (drums/backing vocals), Caleb Followill (vocals/rhythm guitar), Jared Followill (bass) and their cousin Matthew Followill (lead guitar).  The group's name is derived from Nathan, Caleb, and Jared's father and grandfather, both named Leon.

artist.name: Tropical Highlight
artist.bio: Joγo Guillerme Sheffer (26) started to produce in the year of 1998, since then he only appreciated electronic music, his first musical project was called "Neoplastik" where its style did not follow any specifc style or influence, already then, Joγo liked to join diverse types of styles such as house, minimal, tribal, dark, progressive, trance, etc...  In 1999 Joγo started to apear as Dj in some local parties in Sγo Paulo - Brazil where he has a studio. At this time Joγo already had a new project of full on/trance called "MasterRage".

artist.name: Sunny Day Real Estate
artist.bio: Sunny Day Real Estate was an alternative rock band formed in Seattle, Washington in 1992. The band helped bring the emo subgenre from an underground musical phenomenon to a wider audience. The band's lineup was Jeremy Enigk (vocals, guitars), Dan Hoerner (guitar), Nate Mendel (bass) and William Goldsmith (drums).  The core of Sunny Day Real Estate formed in 1992, originally under the name Empty Set.

artist.name: 4Mal
artist.bio: 4Mal is one of the most brilliant musical alliances on the Russian dance scene of the recent years. Anton Guzev and Evgeny Svalov duet formed in 2002 and in the spring of 2005 really made themselves known in the Western world of dance music. They were the first of all the Russian musicians to make their debut on the famous British label

artist.name: Oliver Moldan vs. Harada vs. Nadia Ali
Wolfgang Gartner
artist.bio: He’s been called the next Deadmau5. Pretty much every track he’s released in the past year has dominated the Beatport charts. DJs and producers are dissecting his production style and attempting to emulate it. He’s 2008’s “It” boy. And he’s been working under a pseudonym all this time. Now, in conjunction with the release of his latest single, ‘Bounce/Get It’, Wolfgang Gartner from United States is revealing his true identity - Wolfgang Gartner is actually the acclaimed house producer, Joey Youngman.

artist.name: Weltschmerz
artist.bio:
Weltschmerz is the resulting depression when one compares their ideal state of the world with the actual state of the world.
  Weltschmerz is also the combined efforts of  Tena Schelp and Erich Filthmilk.
 Tena is best known for as Deletist where she plays dark electro dirges. She also plays with the punk band Beat Cops and produces the long running punk comix Bitter Pie.  Erich was formally building, running and destroying  oversized metal robots in ART FeALA  and Survival Research Laboratories.

artist.name: SS
artist.bio: Very early Japanese hardcore punk band.

artist.name: Wally Lopez feat. Aura
artist.bio: Wally Lopez has happened to be one of the best ones in our country to be one of djs and producers but reputed of the international panorama. House of the year 2001 by its success has gained the prize to the best disc “Patricia Never Leaves The House”, the “Best the Newcommer International” of IBIZA DJ AWARD 2002 (that previously I take Steve Lawler and Hernan Cattanneo), name to the best disc of year 2002 by Night Disc (Weekend Record) and chosen like BETTER DJ HOUSE by magazines DEEJAY and DJ1.

artist.name: Apparat
artist.bio: Apparat is a German electronic musician (Sascha Ring) living in Berlin and since 1999 he has been running the Berlin based record label "Shitkatapult" together with T. Raumschmiere. Starting out with dance floor-oriented techno, he later started to create ambient music and recently became "more interested in designing sounds than beats". Recent music is closer to glitch or IDM, accompanied with classical string instruments and other sounds. He works with his own tool created in MAX/MSP framework. Effects are controlled by midicontroller.

artist.name: ATFC
artist.bio: Rising house DJ and producer ATFC - aka 28-year-old Aydin Hasirci - has emerged as the latest addition to the list of famous Old Skoolers.  The OSN was first tipped off about Hasirci's Bournemouth Uni roots by IDJ magazine's Music Editor, Matt Anniss - himself an Old Skooler. And after further investigation, the OSN can confirm Anniss' tip-off to be spot on.  Hasirci, whose moniker stands for Aydin The Funki Chile, has been spinning vinyl for around fourteen years and owns his own sound production company, Onephatdeeva Productions.

artist.name: Paul Johnson
artist.bio: There are two artists using the name Paul Johnson:  :1:: Paul Johnson, Chicago house Music Producer  Born and raised in the birthplace of House Music, Paul Johnson has released over 130 E.P's himself and a vast amount of music for some of the most consistently underground dance labels before hooking up with Peacefrog. 12" releases on the likes of Cajual / Relief and Dance Mania led to his debut album release 'Bump Talkin' in 1994.

artist.name: Robin S vs. Laidback Luke & Steve Angello
Michal Poliak
artist.bio: Michal Poliak is one of the most expressive person in the Czech Republic dance scene. He is respected not only as a DJ, but mainly as a very promising and talented producer, who met with a good responce not only at home ground, but also abroad.  Let´s have a look at period when Michal, BB Mike at that time, start with DJing  Beginnig of his career and  first gig are connected with his activity in Canada in 2001, where he played as a DJ at some local illegal party within the first month of his stay there.

artist.name: Jose Del Valle feat. Priscilla Due
Jerry Ropero
artist.bio: JERRY ROPERO  The beginning of Jerry Roperos career, was located in Belgium, when nine years ago, he became a member of "N.B.G.(Natural Born Grooves), known for their smashing hits "Forerunner" and "Groovebird"!  5 years ago ,in Hamburg, Germany, his biggest project was born, when he got together in the studio with the excellent vocalist Terri B. and , the voice from several other projects like "2 Eivissa", "Future Breeze", etc. and Dj Maui!

artist.name: Stockholm Syndrome
artist.bio:
When Stockholm Syndrome played their farewell show in September 2005, at the Dutch SXSW festival in Tilburg, the place was packed. The people there witnessed a great swan song from one of Holland's most innovative hardcore bands at the time.
 The band lived for only five years but managed to play a shitload of shows, not only in prestigious Dutch venues like Paradiso, Goudvishal, 013, Melkweg and Vera, but also in numerous bars and squats all over Europe, with bands such as JR Ewing, Oil, Shai Hulud, Malkovich, Restless Youth, Textures, The Hope Conspiracy, Nine, Dead Stop, and many more.

artist.name: Sultan & Ned Shepard feat. Kuba Oms
My Digital Enemy
artist.bio: WHO ARE

artist.name: Manuel De La Mare
artist.bio:
Dj, Producer and A&R, Manuel De La Mare aka Mr Sara Galli is born in Italy in the year 1979 and he lives in Pistoia a little town near Florence, Tuscany.
  
 He begins musical studies at 9 years old, and his passion grows day by day playing guitar, sitar, and, later, keyboards spending thousands hours in jazz, rock & funk bands. In 1997 he starts producing chill out and house performing it live in many clubs. He discovers a new amazing sensation watching people dancing his own music. Here starts his dj career when someone requests to extend live performances with a dj-set.

artist.name: Spencer & Hill
artist.bio: correct your tags to SPENCER & HILL

artist.name: Slyde
artist.bio: First up is Robin 12Tree, hailing from Wiltshire in the West Country, possibly accounting for his love of cheddar. Robin joined a band called Impact at the age of fourteen; questionable band names were to be a recurring theme in his brief rock career. After a brief spell in Nottingham playing bass and guitar in bands Sex Planet Venus and Vampiros Lesbos (who later went on to become cult rockers Six By Seven) Robin moved to London...

artist.name: Lee Coombs
artist.bio: Famous breakbeat dj. Maybe you dont know him by name, check the song Lee Coombs & Andy Gardner - Obsessional Rhythm. He is a member of the Finger Lickin Records.  "Lee Coombs kick-started his DJing career in the late 80s, having produced his first track under the guise of The Invisible Men. By '91 he went on to found Paradise Records, Pumpin' Vinyl and the acclaimed cult electro Zoid and Thrust series before moving to London where a chance meeting with Finger Lickin' label boss, Justin Rushmore, led to Lee being taken into the fold...

artist.name: Robyn
artist.bio: Robin Miriam Carlsson aka Robyn (born June 12, 1979) is a Swedish singer and songwriter, living in Stockholm, Sweden. She scored massive successes in the summer of 2007 with her hit single "With Every Heartbeat" which was most notably #1 in the UK, but also had chart success in her native Sweden, the Netherlands, Ireland and Germany. She is best known in the US for her 1997 song "Do You Know (What It Takes)".

artist.name: Deux
artist.bio: 1) French Minimal Electro Pop - From the early Eighties to the beginning of the 90's DEUX, a French Electro Band from LYON produced few records rare to find today. By the end of 2006 DEUX has produced a new album called AGGLOMERAT containing a part of over ten years of electronic music. 2) Deux is a project by David Penn & Toni Bass. "Xpand" made a moster hit all over Europe. 3) Deux was a Korean dance/hiphop duo with members Lee Hyun Do and Kim Sung Jae, active in the first half of the 90s.

artist.name: Dani Moreno
artist.bio: Dani Moreno is a DJ from Barcelona.

artist.name: Dada Life
artist.bio: Dada Life is a Swedish house/electronica band, consisting of Olle Corneer and Stephan Engblom.  Dada Life are signed to Mylo's Label, BREASTFED Records.

artist.name: John Paul
artist.bio:
John Paul are an experimental group with three members, Charlie Candlin, Jack Sapsed and Adam Bradfield. 
 Drawing heavily on absurdist notions within music, they attempt to represent the unnameable problems that lie within the subconcious of the modern person. 
 They describe their vocals as coming from 'average men who jokingly blurt out what they think is nonsense, unaware of the deep truths they communicate'.

artist.name: Surkin
artist.bio: "22 years old Surkin (born Benoit Heitz) comes from southern France but lives and works in Paris. He dropped out of art school four years ago and never looked back. A former four-to-the-floor hater (rap was all he cared for until 2003), Surkin got into dance music through Detroit ghettotech and

artist.name: Audio Bullys
artist.bio: In 2003, Audio Bullys dropped their debut album 'Ego War' and emerged from the United Kingdom to re-ignite a rapidly fading state of dance music. Blending choice cuts of house, hip-hop, punk, soul and UK garage they joined Basement Jaxx, Stanton Warriors and The Streets to lead a movement that cracked chin-stroking, head-bobbing hipsters square in the jaw. Now, the Bullys return to the scene of the crime with the new album 'Generation'.

artist.name: PUZIQUe
artist.bio: PUZIQUe is a collaboration between Boys Noize and D.I.M.. Their records are released on Boys Noize's own label. Their first 12" vinyl was released in August 2007. Tracklisting: A Don't Go (6:56) B1 Cissor (4:39) B2 Suite 9 (5:33)

artist.name: Tonka
artist.bio: Tonka refers to five different artists: 1. A german DJ, formally known as DJ Tonka. 2. Gareth Dolloway, a musician known for video game music arrangements. 3. A peruvian electropop band. 4. A Thrash metal band from Kristiansand, Norway. The band released one full-length album in 1999 called ...This Present Darkness... 5. An emo band from South Carolina with members that went on to be in Assfactor 4.

artist.name: Guy J
artist.bio: Israeli electronic music producer. Recent activity comprises a series of successful releases on Bedrock Records, including his debut album "Esperanza", released in September 2008.

artist.name: Paolo Mojo
artist.bio: Paolo Mojo's sound might be difficult to pin down, but this broad, innovative approach to his craft is making him a name on everyone's lips in 2004. His style incorporates elements of house, funk, techno, breaks, electro, disco and acid. ?I?ve never understood this 'genre' bollocks? he says. "To me the best DJs always select the best bits from a wide range of sounds and put them together in a way that just makes sense to people."

artist.name: Moby
artist.bio: There is more than one artist with this name: 1) Moby is an American electronic musician and is also the name of his live band. Born Richard Melville Hall on September 11, 1965 in Harlem, New York. Moved to Darien, Connecticut at the age of 2. He has also released music under the names Voodoo Child, Barracuda, U.H.F., The Brotherhood, DJ Cake, Lopez, On the Rim of the Wheel a Nail, and Brainstorm/Mindstorm.

artist.name: Marc Houle
artist.bio: Marc Houle plays synthesizers and makes techno.

artist.bio: Lloyds TSB Adverts... D:

artist.bio: Benjamin Bates is jumping for joy on the cover of his new CD Recyclomania. And rightfully so! His second album is a personal document that successfully evokes a variety of moods, ranging from ecstasy on the first single

artist.name: Fake Blood
artist.bio: An anonymous producer from London. IF SWALLOWED SEEK MEDICAL ASSISTANCE. WILL STAIN CLOTHES. WILL SOUND SPECTACULAR. 1/2 of The Black Ghosts. A.K.A. Theo Keating, Touche

artist.name: MGMT
artist.bio: MGMT is a neo-psychedelic group which formed in 2002 in Brooklyn, New York, United States. The band consists of multi-instrumentalists Andrew VanWyngarden (vocals, guitar, keyboards, drums) and Ben Goldwasser (vocals, keyboards, synths, drums), both alumni of Wesleyan University. Originally the band was named "Management," but it was later changed when they found out there were several other bands with that name.

artist.name: Tim Healey
artist.bio: Tim Healey aka Electric Tease, Microtek, Sephalopod, Squid  Took part in these groups: Allen & Healey, Back Door Hussies, Blind Apple Rogers & Jim Jim The Dog Boy, Coburn, Coburn vs. Cobain, Dallas Kiss, Filthy Beasts, Goat Ranch 7, Metrognomes, Mezcal, Monsta Kok, Mr. Resistor, Neuro Electric, Paris & Healey, Pharmarama, Quirk, Quixotic, Simplicity, Slide vs. Healey, Supakane, Triple X, Unconscious Collective, Updata

artist.name: Black Daniel
artist.bio:
A innovative transatlantic fused concoction of the blues, swaggering, street-life soul and a general rock and roll nonchalance coupled to deep electro tinges, in their relatively short time together Black Daniel are already flirting with fame and mainstream acclaim, having toured with Kasabian throughout Europe last year and off the back of a string of dates at sharply hip London venues.
  
 With a passionately deep and richly developed sound, both on record and in their live shows, Black Daniel bring a considerable humour...

artist.name: Coburn
artist.bio: Coburn is an electronic music project (Pete Martin & Tim Healey), who became famous with the track "We Interrupt This Program" which was used as the theme song to the ytmnd.com fad "NEDM" which stars Happy Cat.

artist.name: Kidda
artist.bio:
After falling into the river Tees during a stevedoring incident in 1998, Ste McGregor washed up on the fair shores of Brighton in early 1999.
 With a ramshackle pile of vinyl and old calculator bits, he set about changing the music world forever. These formative years were creatively fruitful, nailing tonnes of animated promos for Midfield General (Midfielding), Lo Fidelity Allstars (Sleeping Faster) and a whole host of lousy tribute acts.

artist.name: Milton Channels
artist.bio: Milton Pineda or known as Milton Channels begins his taste by electronic music from the 5 years old, from his early age he was interested in the sounds like the tribal, trance and house. For one and half year he has been working in his musical productions that are full of groove. his productions go from minimal groove to electrotech. his performances are full of strange music but full of diversion all the night.

artist.name: PTY LTD
artist.bio: Brisbane-based funk/electro/jazz/chill collective. Word.  PTY LTD

artist.name: Leftfield
artist.bio: Leftfield were a duo of electronica artists and record producers, Paul Daley (formerly of A Man Called Adam and the The Brand New Heavies) and Neil Barnes, formed in 1989 in London, England. The pair were pioneers in the fields of intelligent dance music (idm), pioneering the fusion of house music with dub and reggae. They furthermore were among the first electronic musicians to incorporate live guest vocalists, along with The Chemical Brothers.

artist.name: Tim Davison
artist.bio: A regular at The Gallery at Turnmills in London, Tim was selected as one of their
