artist.bio: Chris Bourne has garnered worldwide acclaim throughout the music industry over the past decade. He signed the

artist.name: Laura Kidd
artist.bio: The frontwoman of grunge pop band She Makes War who is about to release a collaboration with top UK dance producer Michael Gray called "Automatic". Listen to her other material at http://www.last.fm/music/She+Makes+War and check out www.myspace.com/laurakiddmusic too.

artist.name: Armin van Buuren feat. Gabriel & Dresden
Moussa Clarke
artist.bio: Moussa Clarke is an inspirational DJ/producer with a worldwide reputation for igniting dancefloors from London to Moscow to Tokyo and back again. Never far from the madding crowd

artist.name: Nirvana
artist.bio: There are numerous artists using the Nirvana name on Last.fm, 8 are listed in order of prominence: 1) Nirvana was a popular and highly influential American grunge band. The band formed in Aberdeen, Washington in 1987, and was part of the Seattle grunge scene of the late 80s. Other Seattle grunge bands such as Pearl Jam, Alice in Chains and Soundgarden also gained in popularity, and, as a result, alternative rock became a dominant genre on American and Canadian radio and music television during the early-to-mid '90s.

artist.name: Silversun Pickups
artist.bio: Silversun Pickups are an American alternative/indie rock band from Los Angeles, California that have diverse influences ranging from The Velvet Underground to shoegazing bands like Slowdive and My Bloody Valentine to (critics have suggested) The Smashing Pumpkins. The band is signed to Dangerbird Records. They released their debut Pikul EP in July of 2005, and their full length album Carnavas on July 26, 2006.

artist.name: Loverush UK! feat. Molly Bancroft
artist.bio: Loverush UK! is founded by Mark Loverush & Kinky Roland. Loverush UK! have enjoyed great success in 2007 with their singles featuring Boy George, Marcella Detroit , Shelley Harland and Kirsty Hawkshaw. Their sound is full on euphoria with uplifting vocals hooks, but their packages on the release cater across the board.   Kinky Roland, originally from Berlin, Germany came to London in the late eighties.

artist.name: Hybrid
artist.bio: 1) Mike Truman and Chris Healings have been writing, producing, touring and DJing all over the globe for the best part of a decade and have amassed nearly 250 productions to date. The duo have written three LPs, 'Wide Angle' which was released in 1999,

artist.name: Rennie Foster
artist.bio: Rennie

artist.name: Neztic
artist.bio: Since the very beginning, Neztic was attracted to breaks and house music in all its variations, styles in which he fused characteristic percussive elements and rhythms of Latin music and Chicano funk.   After several participations in events and compilation albums like Technogeist, Love Parade and Maximas Texturas, Neztic decided to get more involved into nightclubs, djing and club oriented productions.

artist.name: M83
artist.bio: M83 (named after the spiral galaxy "Messier 83") is electronic artist Anthony Gonzalez. Gonzalez and former member Nicolas Fromageau founded the group in 2001 in Antibes, France. M83's style owes a lot to the shoegaze genre, in that there is much emphasis on tonality, extensive use of reverb effects and often softly-spoken lyrics at times submerged in instrumentation. All five of M83's albums were well received, in particular Dead Cities, Red Seas & Lost Ghosts, their second album, which allowed them to break through to a larger audience.

artist.name: Adam the Tree feat. Kasandra J.
Get Far
artist.bio:
Get Far is an Italian dance music project leaded by Mario Fargetta, international DJ and Producer.
 In some of his projects he worked with The Ministry. Shining star is mixed by several DJ's.

artist.name: Alongshore
artist.bio: Vladimir Grankin, born in Riga in Latvia, is better known under his aka Alongshore or Type. He started his musical career at a very young age by taking piano lessons where he discovered his passion and his talent for music as the most high expressions of his art and himself. Vladimir studied all types of musical genres but he found his true passion in dance music. As a musician, he spent the last 3 years in his studio for developing his technique and designing his sounds. Over the years he developed a specific taste for Trance music.

artist.name: Der Mystik & Alex Reliic pres. Perplexity
Tiesto pres. Alone In The Dark
Embliss
artist.bio: Born in Rotterdam, The Netherlands, Tim Brandwijk has been addicted to music since childhood. After playing around with the piano and keyboards, he found his way into music tracker programs such as Scream Tracker and Impulse Tracker and started to write his own tunes. With releases ranging from hardcore to club, drum&bass and pop, Tim gained popularity in the international tracker scene under the Mindblizzard moniker.

artist.name: Mesmerized
artist.bio: The band has been founded in June 1997 by Beton (bass/vocals) and Gacek (drums), under the name Demonicon. At the beginning, only cover's were played, but soon they started to write their own music. In 1998 the name changes to Mesmerized. This whole year all members spent on honing their skills and recording the first "garage" demo-tape. Early next year, the current guitarist enters the band - Wrak.

artist.name: Roger Shah pres. Savannah
artist.bio: He was born in Esslingen, nearby Stuttgart in Germany. His birth name is Roger-Pierre Shah. He is also known as, Sunlounger, Dj Shah, Black pearl, magic island etc.  He started his career in 1996 and year after year he reaches top 10 dance chart positions in Germany.  In 1999 he released his first solo single, the “claps” which went on the top 5 of all dance charts and got attention from the most importants DJs in Europe.

artist.name: Ronny K.
artist.bio: Ronny K. was born on 1st August 1974 at Trinec, Czech Republic. In 1991 he started his career as a DJ. He was learning to mix on vinyl decks (later on CD players) under the direction of professional DJs. After 4 years of practice he DJs solo and starting to produce his own music. His first projects were called Exhibit, Sonic Empire and FM FACTORY, which rised in 1997 and was devoted to commercial genre of music. The first album of this project, called The Album, arose in 2001. It included debut tracks like 17 story, Get up, Give you more, Mrazik 2001, Malo je malo.

artist.name: Black Pearl
artist.bio:
1.)Ralph Fritsch and Roger P. Shah (Sunlounger) are the two trance producers who make up Black Pearl. "Bounty Island" was released as a 12" on Armin van Buuren's A State of Trance label in Dec 2006. It has also featured on Armin's mix CD "A State Of Trance Year Mix 2006"
 "Coral Sea" was their second hit in March 2008  2)Heavy drums and a good dose of soul -- both of which make Black Pearl stand out a bit from many of their late 60s contemporaries! There's a definite bluesy undercurrent to the group's music...

artist.name: ATB pres. Jades
artist.bio:
"Wrong Medication" was an entry for the IdeenSounds project in Germany. Written by
 by Rudee, songwriter/producer, ATB (DJ/producer) with vocals from Jan Löchel (singer/songwriter). Rudee (co)produced tracks for several ATB albums and is finally getting his own career as a performer. Very talented musician.  Barely breathing
 Don

artist.name: Sergei Shkuroff
artist.bio: Playing records since early 1999, Sergei Shkuroff made his way up from small underground basement raves to biggest clubs in Finland, like Laserpoint, Säde, Millennium, Tranzexperience, Housenation and Labyrinth as well as international events like Godskitchen, Gatecrasher, Tidy, Storm and legendary Eden, spinning alongside such a names as Westbam, Marusha, Cosmic Gate, Scot project, Lisa Pin Up, Agnelli & Nelson, Rank 1, Signum, Matt Darey, Mike Koglin, Thrillseekers, Lange, John 00 Flemming, Airbase, Gareth Emery, Airwave, David West, Orkidea and Proteus to name just a few.

artist.name: Epos
artist.bio: There are 3 projects called Epos: 1) Epos (aka Epos 7116) is a one man band from Milan, Italy. His music spaces from power metal to epic metal to prog metal. It's very difficult to classify Epos music into a unique style. Epos has released only a 3 songs EP called Between myth and history, which can be listened at http://www.myspace.com/eposmetal. 2) Epos is a name of a project of 2 german dj's and producers: Roger P. Shah & Pedro Del Mar. So far they released only one track behind this alias called "Vivagio"

artist.name: Global Illumination
artist.bio: Global Illumination is an alias of dutch producers Freek Geuze and Johan Vermeulen, also known as Chunk & Twist and Fine Taste.

artist.name: High Noon At Salinas
artist.bio: Alias of DJ Shah

artist.name: Icone
artist.bio: Icone is Wim Van Gelder, a Belgian artist who brings epic, energetic vibes to the trance scene! Some of his music can be freely downloaded under a copy-left license on Dance-industries.com. He has also some music for sale on his website

artist.name: Olmiq
artist.bio: Olmiq is Jindrich & Marek Zavodnik, both sharing their studio in Trsice, Czech Republic They have been composing electronic music since 1995. Back then it had all started as a project called OLMIQ OX being influenced by progressive bands such as Orbital, Chemical Brothers and Fluke. They successfully performed live on quite a number of gigs across the country. So far the project has released 4 demo CDs.

artist.name: Magic Island - Music for Balearic People
Jonathan Martin
artist.bio: Jonathan Martin was born June 17, 1994 in the state of New Jersey, and today lives in Orlando, Florida, rapidly expanding his music career. Ever since the age of 6, he has been in love with electronic music, and loves it even more today. When he was 6 years old, his father, a New York club DJ, introduced him to house music, and taught him how to beatmatch and how transitions were done. Jonathan loved how two tracks could be mixed together seamlessly, and continued to practice until he became ready for his first gig.

artist.name: Ron Malakai
artist.bio:
"Ron Malakai", born as Kamil Orman, the 18th of May 1987, in Lodz, Poland. He presently is living in Kraków. 
 Kamil began forming his musical taste slowly. Everything that he liked related with electronic music. While in school in 2005, he was trying his skills as an amateur program e-jay. That wasn't quite enough for him. After he learned FL Studio, madness of creation fully started. In the same year in September He made his first track in an unknown genre. During the next half year he perfected his skills and earned elementary knowledge about music production.

artist.name: Dave 202
artist.bio:
Dave202 (real name: Davide Tropeano) is a swiss Trance DJ.  He published his first own production in May 1998. It was the Latenight Compilation Vol. 1 of Oxa Club, where he has been a resident for the last couple years.  And then in summer his career really started to take off.
 Dave202 was the main man at the Streetparade 2000. He mixed the official Streetparade Compilation "Believe in Love". Dave produced the title song (the accompanying red-hot videoclip was a smash hit all summer long, by the

artist.name: Black Pearl vs. Jonas Steur feat. Julie Thompson
Bissen pres. The Crossover
artist.bio: Georg Bissen is a German national living in New York. He has written and collaborated on well over a thousand pieces of music and projects in his still brief professional music career. Bissen got his start in the music business six years ago, when he began working in New York City as a composer and engineer in the music for advertising industry. He formed his own music production company MetaTechnik soon after, which now boasts two offices in New York and Los Angeles.

artist.name: Reconceal
artist.bio:
Blaz Vrecko, a man behind Reconceal, spawned interest in producing music quite
 early on, but his productions really kicked on after connected to the world wide
 web, interacting and sharing in the mod making scene.Continously showing interest
 in trance music, he first produced a trance song in 2001. With increasingly 
 powerful software and practice, he continued in trance scene, reaching the quality
 he found sufficient in 2005. Curently following the uplifting, melodic trance vibe,
 he got his first release on Alter Ego sublabel, Inov8 recordings in 2007. Entitled

artist.name: Treasure Fingers
artist.bio: With over 10 years of international DJ

artist.name: Reboot
artist.bio: aka Frank Heinrich. German producer with records on Cadenza, Below and Combi Int. Makes organic minimal techno with a deep feeling.

artist.name: Justin Martin
artist.bio: Info taken from residentadvisor.net  There's a new breed of house music bubbling under in a certain American city, but it's not coming out of Chicago or New York - this time it's from San Francisco. Claude VonStroke's 'Who's Afraid of Detroit?' was one of the biggest tracks of 2006 and the label it came out on is Dirtybird Records, the Bay Area brainchild of VonStroke and DJ/producer Justin Martin.

artist.name: Friendly Fires
artist.bio: Friendly Fires is a dancepunk band which formed in 2006 in St Albans, England. They consist of Ed MacFarlane (vocals), Edd Gibson (guitar) and Jack Savidge (drums). The band released their self-titled debut album on 1 September 2008. It contains the singles "Paris", "Jump in the Pool", and "Skeleton Boy". Formed out of the ashes of First Day Back, the St Albans, United Kingdom hardcore band they formed while still at school, Friendly Fires make razor-sharp post-punk that burns through the memories of all the dismal, skinny jeaned ‘80s revivalists you’ve been hearing these past few years.

artist.name: Mr Oizo
artist.bio: Mr. Oizo (pronounced 'Monsieur Oiseau') is the pseudonym of French music producer Quentin Dupieux.  Dupieux is most famous for his electro track "Flat Beat", which became a hit all across Europe in 1999 for being featured in a series of Levi's jeans TV advertisements. Dupieux also directed the ad, which featured a yellow puppet named Flat Eric nodding his head to the sound of the track while riding in a pickup truck. Flat Eric later appeared in the music video for "Flat Beat".  After "Flat Beat", Oizo released his first album in 1999, Analog Worms Attack, featuring a single of the same name.

artist.name: The Hours
artist.bio: There are many places this biography of The Hours could begin.  It could begin in Sheffield, England at the tail end of punk, where a ten-year old Antony Genn is standing at the stage door of The Top Rank waiting for The Clash to turn up so he can grab Joe Strummer's autograph.  Then again, it could begin over a decade later as the same Antony Genn settles into a swivel chair and clocks in for his first day producing Joe Strummer's solo album.

artist.name: Dido
artist.bio: Dido Armstrong (born 25 December 1971) is an english BRIT Award-winning and Grammy Award-nominated singer and songwriter. Dido was born in London, UK on Christmas day; she was christened Dido Florian Cloud de Bounevialle O'Malley Armstrong. She lived with her poet mother and publisher father in London. One day she looked up the story of her first name. "I thought it was strange that I was called after a woman who killed herself in ancient literature. It's great for me now but there's no denying that I hated it. That was just another thing that made me stand out."

artist.name: Sam Taylor-Wood
artist.bio: Taylor-Wood was born in London, England. She is a graduate of Goldsmiths College.  Before breaking out as an artist, Taylor-Wood worked at the Royal Opera House and managed the Camden Palace nightclub. In 1991, her work began to appear in a number of group exhibitions alongside that of contemporaries from Goldsmiths. Her breakthrough came in 1994 with the work Killing Time in which four people mimed an opera score.

artist.name: David Guetta feat Chris Willis
artist.bio: David Guetta (born November 7th, 1967 in Paris) is a French DJ.  He was the pioneer of French house with Up & Way, a garage-style track with vocals by Robert Owens released in 1992

artist.name: Veronicas Veil
artist.bio:
Jacksonville, FL
 Jordyn- Female vocals, Composition; Randy- Male vocals, Composition; Jesse- Lead guitar; Mike- Bass guitar; Tim- Percussion  
 In a world consumed with greed, hate, apathy, & despair, it is easy to overlook what truly matters in life. Since March 2006, Veronicas Veil has been reaching fans from around the globe with their influential lyrics, alluring melodies, and compelling instrumentation.

artist.name: Kid Cudi
artist.bio: Kid Cudi, whose birth name is Scott Mescudi, is a Hip-hop/Electronica artist from Cleveland, Ohio. His musical career and style is centered around one dream, to "Be on the moon". His first album, a single called "Day N' Night" was released on iTunes on February 5th, 2008. Through his premier on iTunes and through word of mouth, his success continues. His debut album will be released shortly, while a mixtape has been released to satsify the curiosity and thirst of his listeners for more Kid Cudi.

artist.name: Andy Chatterley
artist.bio: Andy Chatterley is a Grammy nominated remixer, producer, BMG/Universal songwriter, recording engineer and studio owner.   At seventeen, he produced his first track with legendary synth creator David Vorhaus. He also set up his first label Sperm Records with Richard Schiessl and Nicol Chelmiah, founded back in 1993. He was a co-producer of Conscious in the heady hardcore days, with Platipus Records' Simon Berry. He also currently remixes under the title Flash Bang.

artist.name: Little Dragon
artist.bio: Little Dragon is a music group based in Gothenburg, Sweden. Yukimi Nagano on vocals together with her close high-school friends Erik Bodin (drums), Fredrick Källgren (bass), and Håkan Wirenstrand (keyboards), Little Dragon's first release was a double-A-side 7" single on Off The Wall and then signed to Peacefrog (home to José and Findlay Brown), "Twice" / "Test". Nagano was born and raised in Gothenburg to a Japanese father and American mother; she grew up listening to American folk because of her mother, but always had an affinity for R&B.

artist.name: Meck
artist.bio: Meck is the DJ and recording alias of Craig Dimech, the former head of free2air recordings and now Frenetic Music, one of the UKs most respected labels. Having started his A&R career at Ministry Of Sound imprint Incentive Music,  Craig has been responsible or had a hand in countless Top 10 and Top 20 UK hits and scores of underground sensations which have placed his skills firmly in the epicentre of cool, clubbing culture.

artist.name: Tiga
artist.bio: Tiga is the stage name of Montreal-born DJ/producer Tiga James Sontag (born 1974). He graduated from Selwyn House School, a prestigious school in Westmount. Before producing music, he was involved in the promotion of rave parties in his native city during the early 1990s, also Tiga was involved in the creation of world renowned afterhours club SONA. In 1994, he opened a record store named DNA Records, and in 1998 founded his own label, Turbo Recordings.

artist.name: Dirty Vegas
artist.bio: Dirty Vegas is an electronic/dance/club trio from London, made up of Steve Smith, Paul Harris, and Ben Harris. (no relation) The group first gained public attention in North America when one of their songs, Days Go By, was used in a Mitsubishi Eclipse commercial. This song is their biggest hit to date. The group's first album, the self-titled Dirty Vegas, contained a mix of electronic/club instrumentals and similar tracks with vocals by Steve Smith. This album was influenced by The Crystal Method and The Chemical Brothers, but with a slightly more laid-back approach.

artist.name: Sneaky Soundsystem
artist.bio: This is an incorrect tag for Sneaky Sound System

artist.name: Grace Jones
artist.bio: Grace Jones (born Grace Mendoza on May 19, 1948, in Spanish Town, Kingston, Jamaica) is a model, singer and actress. Raised in Syracuse, New York, she found success in the 70s as a model, working in New York and Paris (where she shared an apartment with Jerry Hall), before rising to public prominence as a singer and personality. Jones secured a record deal with Island Records, which resulted in a string of club hits.

artist.name: Silicone Soul
artist.bio:
There are two completely different artist, who get scrobbled under this Name. The first, and more popular, is Silicone Soul:  Craig Morrison and Graeme Reedie are Silicone Soul and they are known both as a respected DJ team, and for their stellar composition and production of deep and emotive house music. 
 It has been 5 years since Silicone Soul conquered the world with their stunning homage to Curtis Mayfield,

artist.name: Paul Ritch
artist.bio: Paul Ritch took the minimal scene by storm in 2007. After no more than a year after his first release, the young Parisian had already played top clubs such as City Hall Barcelona, Fuse Brussels and Goa and had released tracks on Get Physical, Resopal and Minisketch as well as on Kickboxer under his Handicraft alias.  His sparse, intricate, funky, latin-influenced & electro-led alike, pacy rhythms are helping lead the evolution of minimal towards some seriously fun territory.

artist.name: London Elektricity
artist.bio: London Elektricity has become a byword for groundbreaking 'fast soul music', ramming venues, destroying drum & bass crowds, leaving huge smiles from the Big Chill to Glastonbury and beyond, London Elektricity Live has always been 'out of this world'. The LE saga began way back in '96, and up until 2002 LE was a double-act. Tony Colman and Chris Goss made their mark in 98 with the epic Song In The Key Of Knife, and subsequent critically acclaimed debut album Pull The Plug. In 2002 Tony took on the project solo, as Chris concentrated on taking the NHS empire to the next level.

artist.name: Fred Numf
artist.bio: You may think you

artist.name: The Thrillseekers
artist.bio: The Thrillseekers  Steve Helstrip has been at the very forefront of the global dance scene for over 7 years now. From his breakout hit 'Synaesthesia', through to the anthems 'Dreaming of You' and most recently 'By Your Side', he has continued to produce a powerhouse of the most emotive, evocative music going. He has remixed for luminaries such as Tiesto, Timo Maas, Sonique and Chicane, lending them all his trademark melodic, euphoric sound.

artist.name: Mr Pit
artist.bio: Real TAG IS : Mr. Pit

artist.name: Jav D feat. Mat Zo & Einat
Tiësto
artist.bio: Born as Tijs Verwest in Breda, Netherlands, Tiësto is one of the greatest trance DJs on the scene. He started out DJing professionally at school parties, and then moved on to become a resident DJ from 1985 to 1993 at several clubs in The Netherlands. It was at a club called 'The Spock' where things really took off for Tiësto; he stopped producing hardcore/gabber tracks and started to produce his own sound from 10pm until 4am on weekends. In the mid 1990s, Tiësto started to produce trance and the rest, as they say, is history.

artist.name: Allende
artist.bio: Allende is a finnish trance producer located in the city of Kotka. He is also behind projects a98, Magic Dust and Magnetic Flux. For more info, full biography, discography and free downloads head to the official website at http://www.allendemusic.com/

artist.name: Noel Sanger
artist.bio: Noel Sanger is a self described progressive house, electro, and trance DJ and producer located in Virginia. He has played all over North America, South American and Japan.

artist.name: Marcus Schössow
artist.bio: Marcus Schossow has probably been to more places than most 22-year-olds – in fact to be fair, probably more places than most 72-year-olds! The up and coming DJ and producer is in huge demand around the world and spends most weekends tearing up dance floors from his home in Europe to far flung places like America, Australia, the Middle East and beyond.   In between trekking the globe, wowing the crowds and wiping the floor musically, Marcus also finds time to record his highly successful ‘Tone Diary’ radio show.

artist.name: Kane
artist.bio: As it happens there are 3 bands named Kane:  One - KANE is a Dutch rock band from The Hague, formed in 1998. The two original members were Dinand Woesthoff (lead singer) and Dennis van Leeuwen (guitarist, vocals). They added drummer Martijn Bosman in 2002 after the former drummer had left the band. Their music can be described as soft guitar rock. Nowadays, they are one of the best selling bands in The Netherlands and, after The Golden Earring, one of the most successful rock bands in Dutch music history.

artist.name: Ian Carey
artist.bio: Ian Carey. He has sold well over 1 million records across all formats. He has DJed on all continents of the world from Thailand to Canada to Russia to the Ukraine, to Japan, Australia, South Africa, South America and of course all over Europe and North America.  He has been a regular on the Defected in the House parties and Hed Kandi Clubnights in different locations around the world.   His discography, label associations and partners read off like a VIP guest list for a Miami Winter Music Conference Industry Party.

artist.name: JASEfos feat. Claire Van Der Boom
Cape Town
artist.bio:
L-Vee aka Airwave teamed up with Ferry Tayle for this one. Ferry is a relatively new producer from France, who is also (partly?) responsible for Alex M.O.R.P.H. pres. Everest - 'Orée', a track which just got a release on the UK-based Monster Tunes label.
 Cape Town is of course no stranger to the trance scene. Over the years, a batch of wicked tunes was released using this project name, including the massive 'Cinema' from 2003 and 'Flight Of Icarus' which was released back in 2004.

artist.name: Nenes
artist.bio: The Nenes are a group of four women who sing Okinawan folk songs, and perform on traditional instruments and in traditional costumes. While Okinawa is today considered part of Japan, it has its own distinct culture, of which residents are very proud. Okinawa is also a tropical island and resort oriented locale, which many people enjoy visiting. Traditional Okinawan music is usually played on a three stringed instrument called a sanshin, which is similar to the Japanese shamisen, and perhaps related to the banjo.

artist.name: Chicken Lips
artist.bio:
Chicken Lips are Andy Meecham, Dean Meredith & Steve Kotey
 Andy & Dean were formerly two thirds of Bizarre Inc.

artist.name: John Dahlbäck
artist.bio:
Born in Stockholm, Sweden 1985. Moved to a small village outside Stockholm at an early age. Both his mother and father are musicians, and almost everyone in his family too. Got in touch with house music by his older cousin Jesper Dahlbäck and John started to produce the music after that.
 His first track got released by Pawel Kobak's label Route 33 and the first 12" came on the Chicago-based label Deep4life.

artist.name: Odyssee
artist.bio: Multiple artists are known as Odyssee 1. A German symphonic progressive rock group. Consists of Volker Franke (drums, percussion), Silvio Dalla-Torre (bass), Friedhelm Wolff (keyboards), Werner Kiente (piano, guitar, vocals), and Rainer Schön (guitar, vocals). 2. Odyssee is Daniel Wanrooy and Robin van de Wiel. They are also known as Progression and Inbox. Under this alias, they have released four singles: Frontline / Evolution (on Black Hole Recordings), Maya / Yucatan, Sleepless, and 2Morrow / Cruise Control.

artist.name: Saltwater
artist.bio: Saltwater is a quartet made up of quality "Hard-Uplifting Trance" producers: Plasticmen and of course Alphazone.   Plasticmen is made up of Dj Backslash and Thomas Woznik. They are responsible the 2001 Hard Trance floor burner "How U Like Bass?"   Alphazone is made up of Alexander Zwarg & Arne Reichelt, who started off producing progressive material. Later the renowned Alphazone style (a more melodic DuMonde perhaps) was born and this has set the stage for their future, most wanted, productions.

artist.name: Yahel & DJ Miss T
artist.bio: A collaboration between Yahel and DJ Miss T. They had only one release together, Skywalker/Going Up (1999), released under Black Hole Avanti.

artist.name: Kalafut & Fygle
artist.bio: Jan was born in the crazy month April '79 in Kosice, the 2nd biggest city of Slovakia. His passion for music started with Depeche Mode tracks, then turned to the rock scene, where bands like Iron Maiden or Helloween were stars. In 1998 he heard his first trance track and was shocked by the melodics of this music style. Jan found the program FastTracker II and started to compose his own first tracks.

artist.name: Paul Van Dyk & Starkillers & Austin Leeds Featuring Ashley Tomberlin
Evil Robot
artist.bio: Jonas Steur pres. Evil Robot

artist.name: Setrise
artist.bio: After being born on the 5th of August 1991, Melle Bakker lived throughout the whole world in which he got in contact with many different styles of music. From Classical, Hip-Hop, Pop, R&B to Trance which he discovered back in the Netherlands. All these styles were to be combined in his own style house which he started in 2006. Gradually Melle started to love melodic House & Trance more and more. In 2007 he started under the artist name Setrise, which stands short for Sunset to Sunrise.

artist.name: Tempo Giusto
artist.bio: Tempo Giusto is a young producer-DJ from Turku, Finland. Starting his electronic dance music career early 2007, Tempo Giusto is currently considered as one of the most prolific producers in the world and is already recognized by several international labels that release his music such as Shah-Music, Monster Tunes, Colorful Recordings, Bonzai Music and RealMusic Recordings to name just a few. Tempo Giusto is also the co-owner of Finland’s most active digital dance label, Echelon Records.

artist.name: Dave Walker
artist.bio: David Walker was born on January 25, 1945 in the Birmingham area of the U.K. He shortened his name to Dave Walker before starting his career. He became part of several bands, notably Savoy Brown and Fleetwood Mac.  Dave started his career in the early 1960s with a Brumbeat R & B band called The Redcaps. He first joined the band playing rhythm guitar, and later took over the spot of lead vocalist after Ronnie Brown "King" left.

artist.name: Epicentre
artist.bio: Epicentre is an industrial project/band by Tor Holm. Check out http://www.myspace.com/epicentremusik for more info. ________________________________________________ Epicentre is also the name of a Danish electronica-band from Silkeborg aging around 18. Their debut album is to be released in fall 2007. Their music is both acoustic and electronic with influences from pop, rock, jazz and classical music. Anders Bach, 18

artist.name: Sam Sharp
artist.bio: Sander Van Doorn is a DJ/Producer in a league of his own. With production alias such as Sam Sharp, Purple Haze and Sandler, he has grafted for years Every single one of his original productions such as club anthems like “AKA” “Dark Roast” “Bling Bling” “Adrenaline” “Eden/Rush” “Hoover/Craft” and “Error” are supported by the godfathers of dance that include Paul Oakenfold, Paul Van Dyk, Armin van Buuren John Digweed, Ferry Corsten, Marco V, Tiesto and the list goes on.

artist.name: Markus Schulz vs. Andy Moor
artist.bio: A collaboration between progressive trance producers Markus Schulz (U.S.) and Andy Moor (UK). Their lone track to date is Daydream, featured on Markus' 2007 artist album Progression.

artist.name: Gareth Emery vs. Majai vs. Elevation
The Editors
artist.bio: This is an incorrect tag for Editors, without "The". If this non-artist appears in your charts, do last.fm and yourself a favor. Fix your tags.

artist.name: Filo and Peri with Eric Lumiere
Will Atkinson
artist.bio: 'Will Atkinson', a name that in 2008 seemingly came out of nowhere, but rapidly went on to be absolutely everywhere. With a legion of fans including Judge Jules, Sander Van Doorn, Scot Project, and Marco V to name a few, and is one of the most played producers on Radio1 dance shows.  Amazingly, his debut release was the instant classic 'Cloud Surfing' which went on to gain worldwide support, rave magazine reviews, overwhelming sales, and considered by many as the Trance record of the summer, and quite possibly the year.

artist.name: Dousk
artist.bio: John Ntouskos, aka Dousk, is a new artist from Greece. Born in Athens in 1979, he completed his classical music studies in 1999. The studies included classical piano, jazz and electronic music production/engineering. Dousk, along with Jose Zamora, is the founder of the JDK Project. He is currently studying economics at the University of Patras in Greece, though most of his time is spent in front of a computer in his home studio. dousk has also produced music for radio and TV ads during the past two years.

artist.name: Apologist
artist.bio: There are two notable artists called 'Apologist':  1) Prog/electro house duo Sam Perez and Matteo Bruscagin AKA Apologist. The pair hail from the holy land of cosmic disco

artist.name: Keemo & Tim Royko feat. Cosmo Klein
Alphabeat - What Is Happening? (Arnej Tech Re
Synthika
artist.bio: Synthika is an electronic music collaboration project launched in 2007 by two Finnish brothers and producers Tempo Giusto and Ima'gin. Synthika's production caters for several genres and ranges from progressive house to melodic trance and punchy electro. Their style is fresh and elaborate, the sound distinct and the melodies captivating while all of the production is essentially highly danceable club material.

artist.name: Kenneth Thomas & Chad Cisneros feat. Keo Nozari
Stratosphere
artist.bio: Stratosphere started over 12 years ago with creating musical compositions. These were experimental songs, in which he discovered the multiple methods of soundcreation and production. The first few tracks were more in the industrial direction. With the purchase of his first soundmodule, things went rolling. More melancholic sounds were created and the first soundscapes came to life. Through his higher education years, his musical direction was found, and with the growth of his equipement, the ideas went in the same direction.

artist.name: Dennis Sheperd & Cold Blue feat. Chloe Langley
Scot Project
artist.bio: Taught how to spin by his brother at 13, Frank Zenker alias Scot Project bought his first electro record in 1983 and had begun DJing by 1986, playing breakdance tracks at local youth clubs. Fascinated by the first acid and house tracks in the late 1980s, Scot Project began to incorporate these new sounds in his sets, showcasing music from the house, hip hop and techno scene.  By 1990 he had landed several residencies around Frankfurt and two years later began building his own studio, closely followed by his first single; 'X' released on Overdose in 1995.

artist.name: Repercussion
artist.bio: Dark Ambient / Atmospheric

artist.name: Probspot
artist.bio: 'Probspot' is a progressive house/trance music project of Swedish producer Rikard "Rico" Fredriksson. The first release of this project of his, is a track titled 'You and Me', which was released in 2002 on the 'Dedicated Musique' label. His other aliases are 'Rico Soarez', and 'Zinfandel' (most recently). The first release under the Rico Soarez alias was a progressive trance track titled 'TV Dinner', released in 2004 on the 'Electronic Elements' label. 'Zinfandel' is his latest alias, under which name he remixed Patrick Björkman's progressive house/electro track 'Crunchalizer'.

artist.name: Starkid
artist.bio:
Adam Spears aka Starkid was a talented electronic music producer from Nagadoches, Texas.
 He produced beautiful tunes such as Crayons, who was featured on Nick Warren's Global Underground double cd "Reykjavik".
 Crayons is the only single he released as Starkid, while together with Blak Jarrel he produced a song called Apricot, for 3 beat breaks records.
 He unfortunately died on July the 31st, 2004, in a car accident.

artist.name: James Holden
artist.bio: James Holden is far from your average DJ-producer.   The wunderkind James Holden has finally come of age, and has delivered up the debut album to prove it: and at 28, about time too! For although the world seems strangely intent on fixing him in his early twenties (or more specifically, a series of internet sites who have seemingly overlooked the fact that biography ages require a yearly update!), the time has come to acknowledge that DJ and producer James Holden is not quite so young anymore.

artist.name: Adam White & Andy Moor pres. Whiteroom
Firewall
artist.bio: SINCERE:  Released 10/03 on A State of Trance, a division of Armada Music (Holland). Written and produced by Lange. Additional remix and production on track 2 by Andy Perring. 'Sincere' is a powerful driving, instrumental trancer from Lange, available here in the form of two similar mixes, both of which follow the same format and structure.  KILIMANJARO:  Released 4/04 on Lange Recordings. Written and produced by Lange. 'Kilimanjaro' is Lange's second release under his Firewall guise.

artist.name: Luke Chable & Danny Bonnici vs. Lolo
Jon Rundell
artist.bio: "I think Jon's a jewel in the crown. He's been a great support to me. Put him in front of 30,000 people and he really goes for it. At the moment he's better than most top DJs I could mention." Carl Cox, 2007.

artist.name: Ferry Corsten feat. Betsie Larkin
artist.bio: Ferry Corsten is a Dutch DJ, producer and recorder who first started out in 1991 producing underground hardcore gabber tracks. He soon expanded into clubhouse and trance music. But don't put Ferry into the trance corner, because his sound encompasses several genres of electronic music. In 1999 Ferry Corsten was voted Best Producer of the Year at the Ericsson Muzik Award in London. In 2000, he was awarded Best Remix for Adagio for Strings (Ferry Corsten remix) at the Dancestar 2000 awards.

artist.name: Acute
artist.bio:
andre acute schneider was born in ukraine and now lives in the city of tel aviv. he has been making electronic tracks with his computer since childhod. fusing his passion for early new wave artists, autechre and the baroquish nature of idm. 
 official releases includes the now impossible to find "ryuch" album on his own "pleasent recordings" label from 2002, "acute album" was released on the "ak-duck" jerusalem based label in 2004, two years later he release a split ep with fellow electronic musician nir segev titled "Acute / De Pleted - Ducks Don't Swim In Swamps - Vol.

artist.name: Aquateca
artist.bio: Trance producer from Yekaterinburg (Russia), real name: Viktor Shimyako.

artist.name: Luminate
artist.bio: Englanniksi räppäävä 20-vuotias Luminate on saanut ensimmäisen julkaisunsa valmiiksi. Alunperin Kongosta kotoisin oleva, Helsingissä asuva Luminate on työskennellyt yhdessä niin Boy Miken & Brandonin, kuin suomeksi räppäävien Kymppilinjan ja Tuomon&TK:n kanssa. Taustoista vastaavat Suomen kovimmat tuottajat, Boy Mike & Sakke, sekä Fakir Boyz mixtapelta tuttu Eazy Ima.

artist.name: A State Of Mind
artist.bio: ASM stands for A State of Mind, and ASM productionz is an independent label doing its best to pro- mote a new positive state of mind in hip hop and to explore the various creative tangents that have branched off from it, as well as those from which it originated.  People tend to have a very narrow view of what hip hop is about, and equate it with what they see on MTV and hear on commercial radio. Based upon what the general public is force-fed by the Network Corporations that unfortunately have a near monopoly on the market these days...

artist.name: Astrid Suryanto
artist.bio: Astrid Suryanto has a story like no other, with a personality and sound to match. Born February 7th, 1982 and raised in Sumatra, Indonesia, with one channel on the TV and monkeys running across the roof, she now inhabits a studio in New York where she writes and produces an array of electronica, having captured the imagination of big name DJs, industry figures and the public alike.   NY label Statra was playing the demo CD that Astrid had sent in when Victor  Calderone, a renowned producer, remixer and DJ in demand with Madonna...

artist.name: Above & Beyond feat. Zoë Johnston
artist.bio: Above & Beyond is a trance music group formed in 2000 by Jonathan "Jono" Grant, Tony McGuinness, and Paavo Siljamäki. The trio are popular in the trance scene for their uplifting trance productions and collaborations with many vocalists. They are consistently voted as one of the top DJs and are currently ranked number 4 in the official DJ Magazine top 100 poll. They also host their own weekly radio show, Trance Around the World.

artist.name: William Orbit
artist.bio: William Orbit (born on 30 July 1956, as William Mark Wainwright aka Billy Bubbles) is a British musician and record producer, best known to the public for producing Madonna's album Ray of Light, which received four Grammy Awards. He has also co-produced several unreleased Madonna songs originally recorded for other albums that were never used. Also, he produced "13" by Blur, and remixed some of the songs on the album.

artist.name: Singularity
artist.bio: A three-piece band from Colorado, SINGULARITY have dispensed nearly all their RUSH influences in favor of an extremely classy and spacey symphonic rock. They are one of the greatest USA underground progrock talents. The music and lyrics reflect the band's diverses influences, which include RUSH, MARILLION, SPOCK'S BEARD, GENESIS, and many others.  SINGULARITY's debut CD is resolutely inspired by some RUSH epic songs, combining several music aspects in the vein of RUSH and a few bunches of MARIILION tune at times.

artist.name: Andy Duguid with Mr Sam feat. Solarstone
Lisa Miskovsky
artist.bio: Lisa Miskovsky (born March 9, 1975 in Obbola near Umeå) is a Swedish musician. Lisa Miskovsky quickly placed herself on the Swedish rock music charts with her debut album Lisa Miskovsky and single Driving One of Your Cars with Swedish releases in 2001. Following this release, she received two Swedish Rock Bear awards; one for Best Swedish Newcomer, and the other for Best Swedish Female Artist of the Year.

artist.name: Thomas Datt & Bissen feat. Tiff Lacey
Tiësto pres. Alone In The Dark
Alt+F4
artist.bio: 1) Alt F4 is a young progressive rock group from Switzerland. www.altf4.ch . 2) Alt+F4 consists of the two young finnish producers Joonas Hahmo and Matti Kotala. Before Matti and Joonas joined forces both of them have already been active in the finnish music scene since several years as producers as well as DJs. For Matti and Joonas making music is more than just using machines it´s about creating a vibe that takes the listeners on a journey.

artist.name: Yamin feat. Marcie
artist.bio: Marcie  is an Internationally Renowned Singer/Songwriter and Recording Artist with releases on various Major Electronic labels like Flashover, Robbins, System Recordings, Deepblue, Shah Music, Alphabet City, and more.   Her tunes have had the support of the Top DJ's like Tiesto, Armin van Buuren, Paul Oakenfold, Paul van Dyk, Ferry Corsten, Markus Schulz, DJ Shah, Abpve & Beyond, Solarstone, Gabriel & Dresden, and Aly & Fila.

artist.name: Armin van Buuren feat. Jacqueline Govaert
Blake Jarrell pres. Trasher vs. Laurent Garnier
Ronald van Gelderen
artist.bio:
Dutch dj and producer. Formerly known as kid vicious, but produces now under his own name. Other aliasses of Ronald are N-Fluence, Formologic, Electrobics and Masai.
 Ronald released his tracks in the past on tsunami, the former label of ferry corsten & robert smit. Nowadays he releases his tracks under high contrast recordings, a sublabel of be yourself music.

artist.name: Signum feat Scott Mac
artist.bio:
There is more than one artist under the name of Signum  1. Signum from Netherlands
 2. Signum from Serbia
 3. SignuM from Lithuania (rock band)  Signum is the combination of two talented producers in the European music industry. They are Pascal Minnaard, (age 29) and Ronald Hagen (also age 29). Both live in Zoetermeer, a little city nearby Hague, their home base in Netherlands.  Pascal & Ron first met each other in high school.

artist.name: Peter Martijn Wijnia pres. Majesta vs. DJ Shah feat. Adrina Thorpe
Armin van Buuren feat. Justine Suissa vs. Kandi & Nickson
Paul van Dyk feat. Hemstock & Jennings
artist.bio: Grammy nominated artist and globally acclaimed DJ and Producer Paul van Dyk continues to dominate the electronic music charts and appears at the pinnacle of every Top DJ list across the globe. His fifth original album In Between was released August 2007 and features collaborations with David Byrne and Jessica Sutta of the Pussycat Dolls.  PvD is renowned as one of the hardest working artists, with sold-out tours that cross each continent, headline spots at every major festival, and a hugely successful recording career.

artist.name: Dash Berlin feat. Cerf, Mitsika & Jaren
Thomas Coastline
artist.bio: This promising music producer was always attracted to dance music. His career started six years ago with a hardtrance & rave project Bass Detect. He managed to release two remixes for Czech dance groups. As the time went by, he realised that hardtrance & rave production is not his cup of tea. He reoriented to trance music, which included the emotional elements he was seeking. It was in this music he could finally use his experience both from his producer career and also from sound design of a newly created music radio (DanceRadio.cz).

artist.name: Dash Berlin with Cerf, Mitiska & Jaren
Bardo State
artist.bio: Bardo State tells the story like you have never heard it before. Their debut album Mariposa beholds a rare synthesis of classical & pop, an exquisite intersection between ambient & opera. Bardo State is a world filled with emotional compositions and passionate arrangements that will appeal to audiences of all cultures & ages.  The duo Wijn & Broekhuyse have been associated with classical music since their younger days.

artist.name: Armin van Buuren feat. Cathy Burton
DJ Ange
artist.bio: MY DEBUT TRACKS 'S.E.A.' & 'IRON COVE' AVAILABLE ON AUDIO JELLY AND ARMADA ONLINE NOW! FULL RELEASE DECEMBER 22nd 2008 'S.E.A.' is already #60 on AUDIO JELLY TOP 100 LIST! AS SUPPORTED BY M.I.K.E., SIED VAN RIEL, ALY & FILA, SOLARSTONE + MORE! =============================== Become a Fan - Join my Page & Group on Facebook: Group: http://www.facebook.com/home.php?ref=home#/group.php?gid=19402304416&ref=t

artist.name: Eddie Sender
artist.bio: Eddie Sender as producer/dj was born in 1985 in slovak town Senica. His real name is Eduard Palkovsky. His major production is uplifting trance and progressive trance. His career started with remix of track Pilgrim, because it was played by Armin Van Buuren in his show A State Of Trance in year 2006. Eddie signs contracts with some Uk and Holand labels since year 2006 for example: Wildchild (sublabel of Baroquerecords), KYR recordings, Totaldigital (sublabel of Bonzai music)...

artist.name: Tiësto pres. Alone In The Dark: Inferno
James Doman
Tyler Michaud & Mat Zo feat. Marcie
Dereck Recay
artist.bio: The music is his world. There is no any other more beautiful thing in the world than the music which develops day by day. He’s taken up the music since 1998 passing over the organ and xylophone in the kindergarten. Beginning with music blocks and often funny and crazy programs, he’s been learning and preparing himself for ten years to professional programs and instruments. Trance and its varieties are his passion though he likes diverse kinds of music. The music he presents is for everybody who interprets it in different way.

artist.name: Heartstrings
artist.bio: Heartstrings is Maciej Telezynski. Born 28.10.1985 (autumn seems to be weaving through all of his songs), grew up in a peacefull district of Gdansk, Osowa. After finishing Music School in 1999 (faculty of piano), picked up a guitar and it has became his main instrument. From that moment he have gave up piano and touches it once a year to play Christmas songs. First, fascinated by the sound of his teenage heroes (Nirvana, Pearl Jam, Soundgarden), he made his songs electric.

artist.name: Der Dritte Raum
artist.bio: Der Dritte Raum ("The Third Room") is the alias of producer Andreas Krüger and live co-pilot Ralf Uhrlandt. In 1994 D3R signed with Sven Väth's Harthouse label, debuted with Elektro Disco EP, followed soon after by the full-length album Mental Modulator in the same year. They went on to release another full-length on Harthouse (Wellenbad) then, after that label's demise, signed to Virgin Schallplatten GmbH for their 3rd album Raumgleiter, 4th album Distanz, and latest release Klubraum.

artist.name: Maroon 5
artist.bio: Maroon 5 is a Grammy Award-winning American pop rock band. Formed in Los Angeles, United States, the group comprises five members: Adam Levine (lead vocals, rhythm guitar), James Valentine (lead guitar, backing vocals), Jesse Carmichael (keyboards, rhythm guitar, backing vocals), Mickey Madden (bass guitar), and Matt Flynn (drums, percussion). Maroon 5 has won several awards for its debut album Songs About Jane. Released in June 2002, the album enjoyed major chart success, going gold, platinum, and triple platinum in many countries around the world.

artist.name: Indecent Noise & P.A.F.F. pres. Slavic Force
Oceania
artist.bio: Oceania is a New Zealand band which combines Maori music and modern music. The band's lead singer is Hinewehi Mohi. Music is written and performed by Mohi and Jaz Coleman of Killing Joke fame. Visit Hinewehi Mohi's website for more information.

Martin Roth & Alex Bartlett - Off The World (Lange Remix
Gerry Menu
artist.bio: Gerry Menu is an alias of dutch progressive house DJ/producer DJ Remy. It is an anagram of his real name - Remy Unger.

artist.name: Xpander
artist.bio: Andrew (aka Xpander) was born in Moscow in 1982. He got into drum & bass about 10 years ago, and 5 years later he started making his own tunes. Now, he's more deeply works with the drum & bass sound. He makes about 2 or 3 tunes a month. At the moment he is more into the darkside of drum & bass, making some dark tunes, but he also has some soft stuff. His favorite artists at the moment, and also most inspiring artists, are TZA, SilentKiller, Limewax, Technical Itch, Dylan and B-Key. Also he DJs, he has played at many parties over Russia, and will be playing in other countries over 2006.

artist.name: Corrugated Tunnel
Secret Cinema
artist.bio:
Introduction
 Jeroen Verheij aka Secret Cinema started producing as Meng Syndicate in 1990. His first record 'Sonar System ' came out on the Hithouse label in Belgium (ARS) and was an instant rave classic. In 1993 Michel de Hey recognized Jeroen 's excellent producing skills and convinced him to release his music on Michel 's Immaculate Music record labels. A string of tracks that shattered dance floors and charts followed under many aliases like Grooveyard, Point Blank and his most powerful identity: Secret Cinema.

artist.name: Third Floor Tiger
artist.bio: Tudor Moore - Third Floor Tiger  Growing up in the Manchester suburbs with his parent

artist.name: Claes Rosen
artist.bio:
Twentysix year old music producer. It all began in the 1990's when he started off in a program called, fasttracker II. The vibes kept coming and through the years of music production he has come across several types of styles. From commercial music, to dark and severe twelve inch dubplates (L-WIZ). Now in 2007, he's hooked mostly on house music, but his skills do not end there.  
 - Claes Rosen MySpace page

artist.name: Liquid Light
artist.bio: www.djliquidlight.com www.myspace.com/djliquidlight More information coming soon...

artist.name: Sebastien Leger
artist.bio: Incorrect tag for Sébastien Léger
