artist.bio: Mutant Clan is a project of Timo Maas and Sante Pucello aka Santos.

artist.name: James Yuill
artist.bio: James Yuill is an English folktronica musician from London, currently signed to the Moshi Moshi record label.

artist.name: Aeron Aether
artist.bio: Aeron Aether (Gábor Kovács) is a Hungarian composer, producer and a “researcher-experimentalist” of electronic sound. :) Besides studying electrical engineering, he dedicated his whole life to composing and listening music, which he lives and breathes. Unfortunately he studied music for only a few years, where he learned the tricks of playing cello, but what really impressed him were the synthesizers, realizing he could achieve stunning extraterrestrial sounds with this instrument.

artist.name: Oko Tek & Delphi feat. Michelle Guiterrez
Atmos
artist.bio: Originally from Poland, Atmos (Tomasz Balicki) is a Swedish progressive/psychedelic trance producer.  He is most famous for his 1999 hit, "The Only Process", released on various compilations.  Along with other Swedish artists like Noma, Vibrasphere and Human Blue, Atmos was responsible for introducing and popularizing the new minimal and progressive form of psytrance circa 2000. His music is characterized by a combination of deep pulsating beats and basslines with subtle understated melodies and soaring atmospheric sounds, as heard especially on his debut album "Headcleaner".

artist.name: Anton 'Tony' Abdel Ahad, Philip Solomon & Ronny Kirby
Ronny K. & Auren Leen featuring Marcie
Tracy Lawrence featuring Brad Arnold of 3 Doors Down
Armin van Buuren featuring Ray Wilson
Musica Antiqua New York & Mary Jane Newman
Norah Jones & The Peter Malick Group
Dash Berlin with Cerf Mitiska & Jaren
Mike Emvee
artist.bio: Mike Emvee has always felt a need for his own sound since the age of 10 when he heard his very first typical electronic dance track. This has greatly inspired him throughout the years creating a large impact on his life. A large influence of Mike's work and inspires him musically is Sam Sharp. Mike Emvee has a diverse taste of epic and energy as well as progressive trance and house in which there are many DJs to also be inspired from.

artist.name: 3rd Moon
artist.bio:
3rd Moon are Polish trance producers Kamil Bigaj (Cell X) and Krzysztof Pretkiewicz (N2O, Nitrous Oxide)
 March 2006 saw a quite impressive debut for the duo. Having been hammered by the likes of Armin van Buuren, and Above & Beyond on their respective weekly radio shows from late 2005, "Diving in the Sky" was finally released on both 12" vinyl and CDr format. This was followed up 9 months later with the equally solid "DNA/RNA". Both of them on Somatic Sense Recordings sub-label Profuse.

artist.name: Hans Zimmer & James Newton Howard
artist.bio: Hans Zimmer (born September 12, 1957) is an Academy Award, Grammy, and Golden Globe award-winning film score composer from Germany James Newton Howard (born June 9, 1951 in Los Angeles) is an Academy Award nominated film score composer. Zimmer and Howard collaborated on the score for the 2005 superhero film Batman Begins and its 2008 sequel The Dark Knight.

artist.name: Roy Gates
artist.bio: At the start of his successful career as a DJ/producer, Roy Gates immediately had a Dancesmash on Radio 538. This debut single “How Deep” instantly had a high score on the hit lists and was on the play lists of many radio and tv/stations for weeks.  With “On My Way” as a successor it rapidly became obvious that his musical development was unstoppable. “On My Way” was supported by top DJ´s like: Armin van Buuren, E-Craig, DJ Jean, DJ José and Randy Katana. “On my Way” was playlisted on TMF and Slam!FM for weeks.

artist.name: Medea
artist.bio: There are multiple bands using the name Medea: 1) A Dutch Casual Silence keyboard player Henry Meeuws who has released two symphonic metal albums so far: "Individual Unique" (2003) and "Room XVII" (2006) 2) A four piece doom / sludge outfit from Little Rock, Arkansas.

artist.name: Winterlight
artist.bio: Winterlight is the music made by Tim Ingham, a laptop and an occasional guitar. When he was younger he bought a delay pedal and dreamed of being Robin Guthrie or Vini Reilly. He played in bands that worshipped My Bloody Valentine and the Cocteau Twins in equal measure, although the nearest they got to success was standing next to Slowdive at the Old Trout in Windsor. After a while other things became more important and he stopped making music.

artist.name: Sander van Dien
artist.bio: Sander Van Dien's real name is Sander Van Der Waal and has so far released just the one track under this name, that being 'Terms', released on the Twisted Pulse label in 2004. In 2005, he teamed up with Ralph Barendse to form the duo First State.

artist.name: GTR
artist.bio: There is more than one artist with this name:  1) GTR was a supergroup founded in 1986 by ex-Genesis guitarist Steve Hackett and Yes and Asia guitarist Steve Howe. Other members included vocalist (and former milkman) Max Bacon (ex-Moby Dick, Nightwing, Bronz), bassist Phil Spalding (ex-Bernie Torme, Toyah, Mike Oldfield, Original Mirrors), and American drummer Jonathan Mover (ex-Marillion, later of Steve Vai fame).

artist.name: Cosmic Gate feat. Tiff Lacey
artist.bio: See Cosmic Gate and Tiff Lacey These two have teamed up for several vocal tracks, including tracks for the 2009 album, Sign of the Times.

artist.name: Tiger Stripes
Camille Jones
artist.bio: With the latest smash hit “The Creeps” from her 3rd album - “Surrender” - the multi talented Danish-born singer, musician, composer, arranger, and producer Camille Jones has struck gold. But insisting grooves and intriguing vocals isn’t all Camille Jones has to offer. Her new album also presents high quality songwriting in the classic sense, combining mature lyrics about love, rejection, and pride with melodies to keep.

artist.name: Copyright feat. Mr V and Miss Patty
Camille Jones vs. Fedde Le Grand
Carl B vs. JPL
artist.bio: Carl B: (born Carl Barrdahl on October 10, 1984) is an upcoming Swedish trance DJ and music producer. Since he started in 2004, he has already released more than 15 singles and 20 remixes.. Carl B is one of the most well known Swedish disc jockeys over the world. He has released hit singles like Social suicide, Chasing leaves, Just a thought.. He has also created remixes to artists like Tiësto, Armin van Buuren and Talla 2XLC. Since the break through for Carl B, he has been traveling around in Europe to play at night clubs.

artist.name: Hole In One
artist.bio: Hole in one is an alias of Marcel Hol, a Dutch techno, house and trance producer. He had many releases under this alias, but Life's Too Short (first released in 1996) is probably the most famous. He also released a full length artist album, Tales From The Planet Onhcet II. He is also known as Anaconda, Bizarre, Supreme!, Dajjamondo, Greyhouse, Marcel Hol, Organza and Techno Matic.

artist.name: Adrian Lux
artist.bio:
Adrian Lux is a young dance music producer and DJ based in Stockholm, Sweden. 
 He is a part of the La Vida Locash movement and released his debut single Strawberry in late 2008. Adrian has by many people been hailed as Eric Prydz successor.

artist.name: Catcher
artist.bio: There are 3 artists named Catcher. 1. An alias of the guys behind Transa and Cascade. 2 . The illegitimate love child of Trevor Bennett's many and varied musical interests and influences. A singer and composer from a young age, Trevor has balanced with his love for industrial and hard rock a heavy involvement in classical music, choral and a capella singing, musical theatre, operatic performance, and dabblings in jazz, electronica, and metal.

artist.name: Sebastian Ingrosso Laidback Luke Vs. Felix
Calvin Harris
artist.bio: Calvin Harris (born 17 January 1984), is a Scottish singer, songwriter and record producer. He was born and grew up in Dumfries, Scotland. His first album 'I Created Disco' was released on 18 June 2007. The album contained up-tempo electroclash songs that were influenced by music from the 1980s. To promote 'I Created Disco', Harris embarked on a tour of the UK, supporting Faithless and Groove Armada.

artist.name: Who's Who
artist.bio: no one knows who's who but who's who hoo hoo! banging handbag electro stomping bass heavy house!

artist.name: Mark Norman vs. Hole In One
Moguai
artist.bio:
Moguai Biography (english)  If you think of Germany’s Rhine-Ruhr area you might perhaps think of closed coal-mines, football and beer in the first place, but these regions have far more to offer. Especially the electronic music scene between Düsseldorf and Dortmund is very vibrant and Moguai is definitely one of its most important representatives.  
 DJ - producer / remixer - label owner - radioman

artist.name: Transistor
artist.bio: There is more than one artist with this name: 1. Mexican electronica artist Edgar Medina 2. An industrial band from Germany (side project of Polarlicht 4.1) 3. An alternative pop/rock band from Greece (official site: http://www.transistor.gr/)

artist.name: Miles Dyson
artist.bio: On top of arguably being the top electro-house artist on the international scene at the moment, Miles Dyson is owner of the publishing company Plasmapool Media Entertainment and it's 12 labels.

artist.name: Acid
artist.bio: ＡＣＩＤ (1) is a Japanese rock band, founded by Siam Shade's former vocalist, Hideki. They started in 2003, after Hideki found enough members and a second singer. Surprisingly, in 2005 he announced that he would be leaving the vocals entirely to Junpeito focus on keyboards. The band consists of Daisuke, Masamitsu, and Kim on guitars, Sei-ichiro on drums, Yuta on bass, Junpei on vocals, and Hideki on keyboards.

artist.name: Matt Skyer
artist.bio: Mateusz Stanisz aka Matt Skyer (b.1991) - Electronic music producer from Lubatowa, Poland. Thanks to his interest and passion he experiments on Trance music and has been enthusing about electronic music, mainly Trance, for a long time. He produces the following types of music: Tech – Trance, Electro – Trance, Progressive and Uplifting trance. There is still a lot of work to be done by him, but in spite of him being young he wants to gain experience so that he could achieve his aims.

artist.name: Kenneth Thomas and Chad Cisneros ft. Keo Nozari
Sebastian Ingrosso
artist.bio: Part of what has become known as the 'Swedish House Mafia' along with Steve Angello, Eric Prydz and Axwell.

artist.name: Alex Kenji
artist.bio: Alessandro Bacci (28), aka Alex Kenji, is an internationally renowned and respected DJ/producer with over 10 years experience of producing, DJ’ing, and performing. As well as ‘Alex Kenji’, he has released records under host of pseudonyms including: Yoshie Chandler, Combo, Green Sugar, HouseLovers, D.L.D., Orange Love, Kaiko, Itchy Bit and many others.  His tracks have featured on the BBC Radio1 Essential Mix and in the DMC US House Chart and he counts the likes of: Pete Tong, JUSTICE, Kaskade, Hernan Cattaneo...

artist.name: Antoine Clamaran
artist.bio: Antoine Clamaran is a French house music artist and music remixer. Clamaran was born in Paris. In the early 90's, his local fame interested Maxximum FM, the leading parisian dance radio station at that time. Impressed by his mixing gift, Clamaran gained a huge audience and started to be booked for one off parties. But Palace headquarters (Palace in Paris is the equivalent to Studio 54 in NYC) asked him to run the mythical Gay Tea Dance every Sunday, instead of French icon Laurent Garnier.

artist.name: Lifecycle
artist.bio:
1)  Lifecycle - New School Hardcore
 One of the few H8000-bands that didn't play the typical H8000-sounds... New School 
 hardcore with female vocals... The band was started up by Steve Noyelle, together with Vincent Merveille (SOY, Kingpin...) They started up in '96... The band had a lot of trouble with Line-up changes... (Always the drummers and bass-players...) Original Line up was: 
 Steve Noyelle: Guitars, 
 Karel Deweerdt: Guitars, 
 Vincent Merveille: Drums, 
 Sofie Vantomme: vocals,
 Jurgen Degryse: Bass...

artist.name: Bloc Party
artist.bio: Bloc Party are an English indie rock band. In 2005, the band released their critically acclaimed debut album Silent Alarm. Their second studio album, A Weekend in the City was released on February 5, 2007 in the United Kingdom and February 6 in the United States. A third album, Intimacy, was released in August 2008 as a download and later as a CD release on October 27. The band consists of Kele Okereke (vocals, guitar), Russell Lissack (guitar), Gordon Moakes (bass, vocals) and Matt Tong (drums).

artist.name: Mark Maitland
artist.bio: Mark Maitland is one of the most proactive hard house/techno DJ’s in the North East of England. With initial breakthrough bookings in and around Newcastle, he quickly expanded onto a national platform. With residencies at Promise, Come Together and backing from hard house label Energy UK. Mark Maitland has all off a sudden become notable face on the Hard Dance circuit.  With dates that have included “Godkitchen’s” mighty Arena tour in 2004, “Vicious Circle” and “Frantic” rooms @ Come Together Events, “GoodGreef” @ Tall Trees, and Newcastle infamous “Quality”.

artist.name: Reflekt feat. Delline Bass vs. Bloc Party
Forerunners
artist.bio:
Forerunners +++Money Shot+++
 ‘Dragonfly’
 (Solaris Recordings)
 5/5  It’s taken longer than we would have liked, but Brenden ’Forerunners’ LaBonte has finally come good on a sequel to the formidable ‘Lifecycle’. Cut from the same cloth, ‘Dragonfly’s dynamic beats & lush, tropical harmonies culminate with a spellbinding, celestial main-line. Stan Void’s mix builds well on the original’s themes, but it’s Ilya Malyuev who ultimately tips those 'Money Shot's scales. His labyrinthine prog-staged number captivates with an intoxicating sound-bank of wistful effects and studio-wizardry.

artist.name: Planet Funk
artist.bio: Planet Funk is an anglo-italian electronic dance musical group, formed in 1999. Members are Sergio Della Monica, Alex Neri, Domenico 'GG' Canu, Marco Baroni, and Alessandro Sommella (the Ghost extra member), in addition to a series of guest singers in collaboration, like Dan Black, Sally Doherty, Raiz and John Graham. Their first single, "Chase the Sun", reached #5 on the UK Singles Chart in 2001 and is the popular advert break music for PDC darts which the crowd always joins in with.

artist.name: Phunk Investigation
artist.bio: Phunk Investigation hail from the premier league of Italian Dance Music. This successful duo have been impressing us for years with their top class productions, from their incredible mainstream work with George Michael 'Flawless' and The Ones to their skilfully crafted club grooves and dubs. Phunk Investigation are known for producing and remixing artists such as Way Out West, Sophie Ellis Bextor, Light House Family, Rhythm Masters, Simple Minds, Boy George...

artist.name: Franky Rizardo vs. MSTRKRFT vs. Dave Lee
Andy Caldwell
artist.bio: Andy Caldwell first hit the scene in 1994 with his debut single "Superfunkidiculous" which quickly became an underground club hit, leading to a collaboration project with childhood friend Gabriel René. The pair (along with sultry singer/songwriter Gina René and turntablist Mei-Lwun Yee) formed the highly acclaimed outfit Soulstice. Caldwell and René produced and wrote music for the band's stellar 2001 debut Illusion and subsequent remix collection Mixed Illusions (both released on San Francisco's seminal electronic imprint OM Records).

artist.name: Roger Martinez
artist.bio: Roger Martinez took an exceptionally early interest in music. By the age of 3, he was banging out beats on anything and everything at hand and playing records (from Deep Purple to James Brown) on his parents discarded turntable. At age 9, Roger bought his first house compilation, House Party Vol. I (Quazar, Lucien Foort) and from that moment knew that he would someday become a DJ. Too young to even sneak into clubs, he caught onto the bourgeoning House scene through seminal radio shows like Van Diepens Dance Department.

artist.name: ID vs. Kenny Dope pres. The Bucketheads
FLG
artist.bio: FLG = Fedde le Grand see: http://www.last.fm/music/Fedde+le+grand/+wiki

artist.name: Paul Anthony & ZXX vs. Queen T - Bang (Wolfgang Gartner Re-edit)
Richard Dinsdale
artist.bio: House music: it's more than just a feeling. For young turk Richard Dinsdale, it's a way of life.  Although only a sprightly 24 years old, this new kid on the house block's been living, breathing and bleeding dance music for the best part of a decade. His mouth-watering mix of tech-tinged electro and bass-heavy house is a regular fixture at leading London nightspot The Cross, his solid, groove-led productions snapped up by UK labels Renaissance, Kinky Vinyl, Big Love and Toolroom.

artist.name: DJ Fresh
artist.bio: DJ Fresh is one of the members of the Bad Company UK / )E|3( group who has gone on to make some very memorable songs by himself recently. The drum & bass DJ Fresh (Dan Stein) is part owner of Breakbeat Kaos and a prolific UK drum and bass producer.

artist.name: Cast and Company of Fiddler on the Roof
London Festival Orchestra, Molly Picon, Robert Merrill, Stanley Black & The London Festival Chorus
Parrket
artist.bio: After some years dedicated to sound engineering and music making theory, Mladen Glavinic from Zagreb finally formed his solo project in 2001. Since then he played his live acts at most of the big events in Balcan as well as in some other parts of Europe. His style is ranging from deep progressive sound to hard/brutal tech-trance and full-on. Equipment used for his music creation is mostly hardware (Roland JX 305, Yamaha AN1X), but the important part is software as well (Cubase SX, VSTi).

artist.name: Jimmy Van M feat. Steve T
Faskil
artist.bio:
Biography
 Born in 1972, in Brussels (Belgium), Faskil aka. Jean-Christophe Detrain, started to show interest in music by messing around with Trackers on PC. Those basic composition softwares allowed him to make his first steps in sound crafting.  In 1995, he teams up with fellow Radio Campus partner in crime El Borbah to form the band Bump & Grind. They release their first album, deCreate, on newborn belgian label Exit Records.

artist.name: Paul van Dyk feat. Lo-Fi Sugar
16 Bit Lolitas feat. Jennifer Horne vs. Gabriel & Dresden feat. Molly Bancroft
Dave Graham
artist.bio: 1. Dave Graham is a composer and instrumentalist based in London. He is a founder member of both prog-pop duo Cnut and orchestral doombience outfit regolith. He has performed across Europe, and released music on many indie labels including Erkrangkung Durch Musique, Uncharted Audio, Angelika Kohlermann and Concrete Plastic. He is inspired by harmony, rhythm and nature and his music is always an attempt to communicate something about the nature of reality and of perception.

artist.name: Jimmy Van M
artist.bio: There are only a handful of people in the world who have the drive to tackle all of the work Jimmy Van M has done for electronic music. He's talented, smart and creative. He's got a great sense of humor and as a social DJ he's not one to shy away from pictures with his fans. But above all that, he has an incredible knowledge and love for music. Since the inception of his career he's had that passion that sets him apart from others. Over the last decade and a half few individuals could claim the type behind-the-scenes influence on American dance culture as Jimmy Van M.

artist.name: Quivver
artist.bio: Quivver was originally signed to A&M Records, where, along with writing partner Neil Barry, they released 2 tracks (as mentioned above), both tracks making huge dents on the dancefloors of the World. During this period John was also recording under the name of Skanna and had a label of the same name where he released around ten 12"'s that received attention from people like Fabio and Grooverider, Doc Scott etc….

artist.name: Supernova
artist.bio: There is more than one artist with this name: 1. A pop punk band founding in California in 1989. They are most well known for their song Chewbacca from the movie Clerks. They often dress in space suits and claim to be from the planet "Cynot3", and have appeared on the Nickelodeon series, "Yo Gabba Gabba!", on more than one occasion. 2. Folk style band from West London who feature many self penned tracks from 2 albums. Also acclaimed for their cover songs. 3. A Pop girl band founding in Chile, mid 90's. They released 2 albums: Supernova and Retráctate

artist.name: Filippo Moscatello
artist.bio: 2008 signals a new chapter for Berlin based Italian Filippo Moscatello, with his choice to retire his DJ Naughty alias representing a shift back to his techno and house roots after a decade of eclectic electro mischief.  Metamorphosis and reinvention are key themes. Equally prolific as remix artist and producer, Filippo has reinvigorated tracks for artists of the calibre of Goldfrapp, Fischerspooner and Kosheen, and many other artist.

artist.name: Cevin Fisher
artist.bio: Cevin Fisher is an American house producer, born October 26, 1963 in East Orange, New Jersey.  He is best known for songs such as "The Freaks Come Out" (as Cevin Fisher's Big Freak) and "(You Got Me) Burning Up," the latter of which featured vocals by Loleatta Holloway.

artist.name: Jon Gurd
artist.bio: With a CV that already boasts its own record label, radio show, world class productions and DJ appearances alongside many of the DJ greats, it’s evident that at the age of just 22 Jon Gurd has already matured into a highly respected artist. He pushes an intelligent, underground sound that encompasses house and electro, delivered in a very distinctive fashion. As a former resident at Slinky in Bournemouth, Jon has starred alongside the likes of Dave Clarke, Billy Nasty and Mauro Picotto, whilst his latest residency for Portsmouth based Punchfunk has resulted in sets alongside Justin Robertson...

artist.name: Oasis
artist.bio: Oasis is an English rock group, originally formed in Manchester, United Kingdom in 1991. They enjoyed a period of huge success following the release of their first album, Definitely Maybe and during the second, "(What's the Story) Morning Glory?", with praise from across the spectrum and the accumulation of several major awards. Many critics have since said this was the peak of their musical career to-date.

artist.name: Simon Neale & Dave Spoon featuring Laura Vane
Pulse
artist.bio: There are multiple groups going by the name of "Pulse". 1. The first produces minimalist techno which is primarily uptempo electronic sounds. Their album Surface Tensions (Eye Q Records, 1995) is credited to T. Eckart and DJ Good Groove, whose real names are Tommi Eckart and Klaus Löschner. Their song Cariño (Silencio) appeared on Trance Europe Express 3 and has been remixed on numerous compilations.

artist.name: Dataworx
artist.bio: http://www.myspace.com/dataworxdigital

artist.name: Girl Nobody
artist.bio: Vancouver's Girl Nobody formed in 1999 and has since become one of the few bands that can offer cerebral charm and sexual bravado within a lullaby of pop swoon, all the while continually stretching musical parameters. The band's stunning live shows, along with their critically acclaimed self-released debut album The Future Isn't What It Used To Be (2004), proved that the hype Girl Nobody had been generating was warranted.

artist.name: DJ Paulo & Todd Dutkevitch featuring Tinta
Empire Of The Sun
artist.bio: Empire of the Sun is a collaborative project between Pnau's Nick Littlemore and Luke Steele of The Sleepy Jackson. Steele's vocals were recently featured on Pnau's self titled album. Empire of the Sun's debut album, Walking on a Dream, was released on the 4th of October 2008. The first single from the album is also called Walking on a Dream and the second single will be We Are the People. The video for We Are the People was shot in Mexico and a trailer can be viewed on Empire of the Sun's homepage.

artist.name: Paul Kalkbrenner
artist.bio:
city: berlin friedrichshain
 style: very electronic music  1985-90
 learns to play trumpet and theory of music.  1992/93
 first gigs at some east-berlin youth clubs.  1994/95
 dj at walfisch, exit/kitchen, vereinsheim,
 praxis dr. mc coy, halle weissensee  1996
 buys first production equipment.  1997/98
 editor, operator and producer at ard, zdf, rtl, premiere  1999
 first releases  2000
 release of the 1st album „superimpose“ (BPC016). first tour around germany together with bpitch artists.  2001

artist.name: Bertie Blackman
artist.bio: " The real deal..... one of our finest talents" - Rolling Stone Australia  “I see things in a funny way,” Bertie Blackman says. “I come from a family of painters, so everything I do is pretty visual. You can see and feel my music.”  Bertie burst onto the Australian music scene in 2004. Her stunning single ‘Favourite Jeans’ was a statement of intent. In a pop world filled with fashion followers, Bertie is forging her own path.

artist.name: Chris Kaeser
artist.bio:
Chris Kaeser was born in France to musician parents and started his musical odyssey from an early age. Chris has been producing music since 1988, releasing his first disc in 1991 and producing with his nephew David Kaeser and fellow French star Antoine Clamaran throughout the 90’s.
 After a short break, Chris returned in 2004 with a release on Electron Records under the moniker ‘Black Widow’. Determined to build on this success, Chris continued on Pool E Music with a first EP, the‘Nightlife EP’ including the hit ‘Over’ which stayed at No.

artist.name: Arno Cost
artist.bio: At 22 years old, Arno Cost is one of the most french growing producers of this year. Discovered by Mathieu Bouthier of Serial Records in January 2006, he signs with his friends Norman Doray (producer of Jetlag) and Pierre de la Touche, the track "Let U Go", which knows a very big success on french radio stations and with international Djs (Didier Sinclair, Antoine Clamaran, Hoxton Whores, Ben Macklin, Narcotic Trust, Muttonheads...).

artist.name: Matisse
artist.bio:
Several bands called Matisse:
 1) lithuanian experimental band 
 2) Matisse is an alternative rock band from Athens, Greece formed in 1999. They took their name from the famous French painter Henri Matisse.  Matisse was originally formed in 1997 by Aris Siafas, Giannis Massouras, Grigoris Κolias, Petros Tsolis, Kostas Synodinos and Basilis Zervos without making any significant actions as a band. The band became active, when they started performing and writing songs for the first time in January 1999.

artist.name: Who Da Funk feat. Jessica Eve
Axwell, Ingrosso, Angello & Laidback Luke feat. Deborah Cox
Hernan Cerbello
artist.bio: Hernan Cerbello is an Argentinean dj & producer that made his way to underground scene because of the selected music style of his sets and productions. Electro, tech, disco & funky are the main flavors he can present.  In his career that began back in 94, he shared booths with talented and renowned local and international djs such as Joshua Collins, Rachel Starr, Ryan Pappa, Rowan Blades, Cass, Dave Twomey, Luke Fair, Kasey Taylor and many others. All this events taking place in the main clubs of Argentina: Pacha, Big One, Mint Club, SuperClub, Lost & New Millennium and Qiu (Mexico).

artist.name: Sebastian Ingrosso vs. Fatboy Slim
artist.bio: Part of what has become known as the 'Swedish House Mafia' along with Steve Angello, Eric Prydz and Axwell.

artist.name: Hawk feat. Sasja
artist.bio: Collaboration between Norwegian trance producer/DJ Håkon Lofthus (Hawk) and Danish singer/song-writer Sasja Borjeson. 'Emerald Mine', a progressive vocal trance song, is the first and only (as of March 2008) production of this collaboration. This was released in August 2007 from the 'Real Deep' label along with remixes by Hawk, Deepwide, Digital Nature, Ilya Maleyauv and Andrew Parsons.

artist.name: Everything But The Girl
artist.bio: The married duo of Ben Watt and Tracey Thorn successfully pulled off one of the greatest stylistic changes in modern music; originally a folk-pop group with jazz influences, their fortunes changed when Todd Terry successfully remixed 'Missing' (from Amplified Heart). Since then, EBTG have become more widely known as an electronic act, with Walking Wounded being a well-received example of their latter-day sound.

artist.name: Cream Sound feat. Stereo Tip Project
Stalker
artist.bio: At least six groups/artists share the name Stalker. 1) Stalker was a Finnish rock group during the 80s. 2) Stalker is one of the two fathers of the netlabel 1bit wonder, hailing from Lipsia/Germany. Deejaying since 2000, he started making music himself in 2004. Educated in Techno and House, his production stlye concentrates on deep, dubby and minimal structures. (Source: www.1bit-wonder.com).

artist.name: Groovewatchers
artist.bio:
Groovewatchers is Peter Luts & Ward Houbrechts.  
 Peter Luts is a Belgian trance producer born on December 14, 1971. Peter’s musical career started at the age of 12 when he got a small organ. Shortly after that, he bought his first synthesizer and started composing his own tracks. He got involved in several bands, but soon he realized his skills and talent would lead him to composing and producing music on his own.

artist.name: Sebastien Drums, Eric G & Tom Geiss
Cazals
artist.bio: Cazals: a short history  OK, so let’s begin with some things you may already know about Cazals: 1. They’ve known Pete Doherty since they were boys, and have toured with Babyshambles. 2. On account of living in London and - y’know - knowing how to dress well, some people think they’re fashonistas; 3. All five of ’em used to live together. In Whitechapel; 4. A couple of them made cameo appearances in Nathan Barley. 5. They used to put on all night warehouse parties – most notably Cazalaid, organised to raise money after ALL their equipment got stolen – in London’s east end.

artist.name: Schlock!
artist.bio: Schlock! (aka "Michael Jackson" or, in real life, Gianluca Licciardi) is an Italian electronica artist, who uses found sounds and MIDI along with distortion, heavy bass and heavily distorted vocals to create his music. He has so far released two albums solely via the Internet, the concept album broken blossom and It's Like Having a Madman In The House.

artist.name: Fischerspooner
artist.bio: Fischerspooner is an electroclash duo and performance troupe formed in 1998 in New York City. The name comes directly from the last names of the band members; Warren Fischer and Casey Spooner. Spiking extremely retro electropop tendencies (recalling Kraftwerk, early Depeche Mode, and Gary Numan) with a modern approach to programming, Fischerspooner produces a quirky, robotic, and strangely subdued kind of dance music. Their albums can be seen as soundtracks to their stageshows, as opposed to recordings which are performed live.

artist.name: Costello
artist.bio:
Costello began in the summer of 2003 as a three-piece pop-punk outfit comprised of Mitchell Ohlman (vocals/guitar), Kendal Byxbe (Bass) and Alex San Juan (Drums). After mulling around the LA Punk scene playing scattered shows and recording numerous demos, 2004 saw the departure of drummer San Juan.
 This was the moment of truth for Ohlman and Byxbe. After a brief hiatus, both decided this band was where their passion lay and they we're going to move forward full steam. After an extensive search Costello settled on bay area metal veteran Erik Shapiro to be their skinsman.

artist.name: Perpetuous Dreamer
artist.bio: Alias of Armin van Buuren.

artist.name: Sebastien Drums vs. Tom Geiss & Eric G
Özgür Can & AGS feat. Max Lodin
Dino Barretta & Alex Colie feat. Luca G
Buddy Rich, Charlie "Bird" Parker, Curly Russell, Dizzy Gillespie & Thelonious Monk
Mozart: Requiem In D Minor, K 626 - Sequentia: Recordare, Jesu Pie
Rune Gustafsson, Jojje Wadenius, Jan Schaffer, Henrik Jansson, Dregen & Stefan Blomquist
Mr. Sam, The Tribute & Tim Coltrane
Mr. Sam Vs. Tim Coltrane presents The Tribute
Artento Divini
artist.bio: Artento Divini started spinning the wheels of steel at the age of 19.  Within a short while he was spinning at his own parties. It didn't take long before he got in contact with the owner of the Scala Dance Theatre (Netherlands) where he became resident DJ. Artento performed besides great names like: Marco V, Bas & Ram and Hennes & Cold. The Friday nights became so successful and Divini's name was set.

artist.name: Antidote
artist.bio: There is more than one artist with this name: 1) Hardcore band from New York. Antidote's Thou Shalt Not Kill EP was self-released in 1983. The drummer, Arthur, had played with the Misfits, and John Bloodclot does back-ups on "The Real Deal". Antidote got back together in the late 80's/early 90's and put out a full-length record. 2) A punk band from Holland. Formed in 1996 and still together as of 2008.

artist.name: Canyon Boulevard
artist.bio:
Canyon Boulevard
 Progressive House / Tech House  Based out of Vancouver, BC, Ferry MSH and Jamie Kuse form the production and DJ Duo "Canyon Boulevard".  Their first single, a trance hit entitled "Kimchi" gained support worldwide after Markus Schulz released it on his ColdHarbour Recordings imprint on Armada Music. It was featured on several top selling compilations, including Markus Schulz' "Armada at Ibiza", which went on to be a #1 seller on iTunes.  They have formed their on imprint, Neon Element Recordings, which is home to the rest of their releases in 2008/2009.

artist.name: FC Kahuna
artist.bio: Same as FC/Kahuna.

artist.name: Omnia
artist.bio: There are 2 artists with this name - Omnia is also an electronic dance music producer, their track Stick in monday was featured in the Trance Mix Mission Podcast.  Omnia are also a  Pagan folk band based in the Netherlands playing mostly self-composed music, with a couple of traditionals from places like Ireland, Brittany and Afghanistan.  The music is 100% acoustic – no synthesisers, no electric instruments, no programming.  They have released several CDs on their own Pagan Scum label, as well as a live DVD.

artist.name: Andy Moor & Ashley Wallbridge feat. Meighan Nealon
Marco V vs. Rex Mundi feat. Susana
Delphic
artist.bio: Delphic are an electronic/indie four piece from Manchester that aim to be the future sound of Manchester mixing euphoric electronica with anthemic songs for a post dance world. They are made up of Dan Theman (drums), James Cook (vocals), Matt Cocksedge (guitar) and Richard Boardman (multi-instrumentalist).

artist.name: Thomas P. Heckmann
artist.bio:
Thomas P. Heckmann started doing techno-house music professionally in summer 1991with his first release EXIT 100 - LIQUID .
 After doing all sorts of electronic music since age eleven - including synthi pop, industrial, ebm, experimental
 - he was attracted by the likes of KLF and 808 STATE´s early stuff, that lead him into the new acid and techno styles in 1989 .
 His first release as EXIT 100- Liquid on the just started label FORCE INC was a good start into the then small techno world .

artist.name: Sander van Doorn vs Marco V
Joker Jam
artist.bio: A trance project by Uwe Hölters. Most famous for his single Innocence.

artist.name: Ben Nicky
artist.bio: DJ, Producer and Label manager Ben Nicky is one of the brightest new stars on the trance scene at the moment. His next release due to be out later this summer ‘Special Moment’ is now signed to arguably the biggest record label in trance, Paul van Dyk’s, Vandit Digital, His skill behind the decks has earned him a residency at the Syndicate Superclub in Bristol as well as appearances at events run by all the major brands on the scene. He was nominated for ‘best newcomer’ at the prestigious worldwide trance awards last year as well as having his interview published on their website.

artist.name: Derrick May
artist.bio: Leading purveyor of the "techno" genre, he and band of brothers Juan Atkins and Kevin Saunderson, began their quest together in the early eighties.  Music was their alterior motivation to the grimey streets of Detroit and their answer to the decrepit existence of such an industrial landscape.  It was this and the soul of motown, parliament funk, and moody soundscapes that their music came alive and began to reach the world.  A cutting edge dj and producer, Derrick continues to woo fans the world over.

artist.name: DJ Smash pres. Fast Food
artist.bio: Beskrivelse:  DJ SMASH needs no introduction to Russian club scene. The Best DJ 2006 according to Night Life Awards, producer of several tracks and remixes that became top-list in 2006-2007, resident of such Moscow clubs as "Dyagilev", "Osen'", "Opera". His specific sound comes out of House, Progressive and Trance and high-power smashing bass.  The band FAST FOOD was founded on the 1st September 2007. A team of eager guys, having rejected their jobs for the sake of Art, set up a challenging voyage along the avenues of international show business.

artist.name: Oliver Lang
artist.bio: The arrival of Oliver Lang at the forefront of dance music has been as well-timed as one of his mixes. As we drift into 2007, it’s been the most successful year for the Mixmag Future Hero, playing across the planet to all the hottest and most exclusive venues.  As we two-step our way through the noughties Oliver Lang continues to put his foot on the accelerator, bursting with ambition and productivity, continuing his admirable mission to kick the ass out of nightclubs up and down the nation, both himself and with his music as weapons.

artist.name: Miro
artist.bio: There are various artists, who use the name Miro. 1) Mads Arp & Steen Thøttrup has released records by the name Miro since 1990. Appeared on more than 250 compilations, released 50 x 12" on labels such as Hooj Choons, Effective Records & Skyline Records. Appeared on Cafe del Mar more than 10 times and released tunes such as Emotions of Paradise, The One I Run To and By Your Side. www.miromusic.com

artist.name: DJ Fist
artist.bio: This Colombian DJ began his musical career at the age of 17. In 1992 DJ Fist joined the first all electronic radio station in Colombia "La X 91.9 FM" Fist took an interest in producing after having heard the tribal sounds made by house authorities such as Ralphi Rosario, Peter Rahoufer, Junior Vasquez, and Danny Tenaglia, whose tracks created the bases of the sound Fist was looking for to produce.

artist.name: Itamar Sagi
artist.bio: Hills from the hot spot of Tel Aviv with his roots based in underground Techno grooves, Itamar spotted as one of the new breeds of the latest techno wave. Already well respected , making his name bigger from day to day, with his unique and floor filler productions, who catched the intention of legends as Laurent Garnier, Josh Wink, Carl Craig , Francois K and many others. It wasn’t long till Itamar got his recognition at the worldwide market, Inc reviews and interviews in the most popular dance magazines and radio stations all over the world.

artist.name: DJ Hell
artist.bio:
Born in Munich, Helmut Geier -aka DJ Hell- is considered one of the most reputed German DJs of the 90's.
 DJ Hell's eclectic style has been developed from numerous styles : Dark, Gothic, Detroit, and Electro, although he is mostly known as a "Punk DJ".
 DJ Hell runs the International Deejay Gigolos label and is resident at the Ultraschall club.
 He has also collaborated with other artists such as LAURENT GARNIER and Mijk Van Dijk.

artist.name: Chain Of Command
artist.bio: A UK Hip Hop crew featuring Manage, Conflix, CLG and  Syanyde.Coming out of South London, Speakers Corner regulars Chain of Command are a hardcore collective of MCs, DJs and producers known for their commitment and dedication to the scene. Fresh from touring the UK alongside US heavyweight Saigon and Scram Jones, I caught up with the group to discuss their upcoming album, their influences, free Hip-Hop, and have a look inside the minds that mainstream media outlets overlook in favour of the more conformist artists...

artist.name: Buddy Guy
artist.bio: Buddy Guy (born George Guy, July 30, 1936 in Lettsworth, Louisiana) is an American blues music and rock music guitarist, as well as a singer. Known as an inspiration to Jimi Hendrix and other 1960s blues and rock legends, Guy is considered as an imporant proponent of Chicago blues made famous by Muddy Waters and Howlin' Wolf. He has influenced both widely known and local blues guitarists.  Guy is known for his showmanship; for example...

artist.name: Xpansul
artist.bio: Santiago Ferrer, also known as Santi Xpansul, started djing in 1993. Since then, he has played in most of the biggest clubs and festivals all over Spain and Europe.  Regarding music styles, after more than thirteen years behind the decks, we could say that Santi Xpansul’s sound is techno. Nowadays, his sets are a journey through electronic dance music, in which the “axis” Detroit-Chicago-Berlin-Cologne is the driver and all his other musical influences are the passengers.

artist.name: Lulu Rouge
artist.bio: Lulu Rouge is one of a kind on the Scandinavian electronica scene. Not because Lulu Rouge has been around for many years, but the two young men in Lulu Rouge have both been around, crashing clubland for the last decade. DJ T.O.M has been Trentemøller's partner for the last 3 years touring around the world in nearly every major club you can think of. But he is more than just music. T.O.M has recently established the ArtRebels online network community with focus on design, art and music culture. T.O.M is currently also part of Bobi Brothers out now on Kickin Music (UK).

artist.name: Milez Benjiman
artist.bio: Milez Benjiman is a sonic sounding stomp of cyborg funk! fused with glorifying melody touched with conscious lyrical power & sent to hook you from root 2 roof-top. MB explores… beats/rhythms and song-poetry… that tell stories of a social & physycosomusical nature & with a serious overtone of heavy slide-style dubsta vibez! Still Milez Benjiman oozes sexual & sensual refrain,… totally leaving you wanting more!

artist.name: Giallos Flame
artist.bio:
AUTHENTIC 70'S TERROR !!  The GIALLOS FLAME are the nastiest authentic analogue sound of 70's terror...
 Following on from the legends of Italian horror & Giallo 
 composers such as Fabio Frizzi , Goblin & the De Angelis brothers , the flame burns bright with the ancient shrieking oscillators of Fulci !  Past soundtracks include the winner of Quentin Tarantino's
 Grindhouse competition "Hobo with a shotgun" & the infamous forthcoming cult classic "Black Devil Doll"from the lewis brothers (Rotten Cotton , Blackest heart media).

artist.name: Twelve
artist.bio: Twelve is a solo project of Chris Olley, lead singer and guitarist of the Nottingham, UK rock band Six by Seven. Twelve's songs are more heavily electronic than most of Six by Seven's, and are stylistically varied, including both guitar and electronics driven songs and elaborate textures along side more straightforwards songs. Olley has described Twelve as an "experiment". During Six by Seven's 2005-2006 breakup, Twelve was Olley's primary project, though in 2006 he also launched an electroclash project called Fuck Me Usa.

artist.name: Chymera
artist.bio: Chymera hails from Cork, the real capital of Ireland, and is currently a globe trotting citizen of no fixed abode. He makes his own brand of techno with a Detroit influence. Simple but refined, full of melody, power and emotion.  Chymera has been making electronic music since 2002. Opening strides on the international circuit in 2006 saw him charted by Carl Cox at number 1 (Descent EP - Supreme records) and release on respected UK house label Urban Torque (As "I Am An Exit").

artist.name: Mulatu Astatke
artist.bio: Mulatu Astatke (var. Astatqé) is an Ethiopian musician and arranger. He is known as the "Father of Ethio-Jazz." Born in 1943 in the western Ethiopian city of Jimma, Astatke was musically trained in London, New York City, and Boston, where he was the first African student at Berklee College of Music. He would later combine his jazz and Latin music influences with traditional ethiopian music. In 2005, his music appeared on the soundtrack to the Jim Jarmusch film Broken Flowers (actually, it inspired the film).

artist.name: Middlewood Sessions
artist.bio: 2006. Sheffield, South Yorkshire, England. Probably around tea-time. Long-time lovers of all things jazz, funk, soul and hip hop, Alex Beauchamp and Mark Slater hand pick a skilled collective of like-minded players and form Middlewood Sessions with one purpose in mind: to forge heavyweight dancefloor jazz jams and widescreen downtempo beats influenced by their shared musical inspirations.   With strong initial support from Gilles Peterson, their debut 'Fall Back'...

artist.name: Ame
artist.bio: Ame is a duo consisting of Kristian Beyer and Frank Wiedemann, born in 1973 in Karlsruhe/Baden, Germany. They describe the style of their music as deephouse, detroit and musicwithsoul.

artist.name: Jamie Jones
artist.bio: Welsh-born Jamie, is a special breed of artist, his sound continually grows more diverse as he continues always to take risks to develop his unique style. Many sides to his sound have been explored on labels such as Cocoon, Freak n'Chic, Get Physical and Pokerflat in the past couple of years, each building on his loyal and flourishing global following.

artist.name: Elio Riso
artist.bio: By no other way could be in Elio Riso, an italian-root argentinian who believes in great parties, nice people and specially in good music. His affair with music begins by the end of 80’s and nowadays it is his funniest and most faithful lover.  Elio Riso is not only a dj but also a well-known producer, since his remixes are worth to be noticed. Hence, there’s a whole new way in popular argentinian music.

artist.name: Umek
artist.bio: Born in 1976, in Ljubljana, Slovenia, Uroš Umek began DJing in 1993. He and his friends helped develop the dance music scene in Slovenia, and between them they were responsible for putting on the first large scale parties in Slovenia. The result has been that Umek is Slovenia's most famous techno DJ, and a prolific producer. His current style is the combination of many different roots, which the more long term Umek fans may recognise. Starting with a rough, uncompromising edge he quickly built a reputation in the studio. However, more recently he has moved towards a funkier sound...

artist.name: Nic Fanciulli
artist.bio: When clubbers discuss who is the hottest rising talent in house music in the last 3 years one name keeps reappearing; that name is Nic Fanciulli.  Nic is a young, fresh DJ, producer and re mixer. He started in music at 16, where he worked in the local record shop and DJ�d in the local bars, in his hometown of Maidstone, Kent. It was here that he earned his first proper break courtesy of the town�s house institution Club Class. Aged just twenty he became main room resident for the night which he continues to be fully committed to.

artist.name: Dave Clarke
artist.bio:
There are three artists with the name Dave Clark(e).  Dave Clarke (* September 19th, 1968 in Brighton, England) is a Techno Producer and DJ, often given the status The Baron of Techno.
 Dave Clarke has a well-deserved reputation as one of the greater techno and electro DJs in the world but he’s always been an outsider, from his stormy childhood in the 1980s to his tempestuous relationship with the media today. Being a fan of radio; Dave does share his contemporary insights willingly on UK, Belgian, Turkish and Dutch radio (for 3VOOR12 WhiteNoise).

artist.name: James Talk
artist.bio:
BIOGRAPHY:  Be it via his DJing or studio work,
 James Talk’s unique funky tech and acid house sound can already hold claim for causing mayhem on many of the world’s finest dancefloors, and all at the age of just 23. Hailing from the murkiest waters of Southampton, James has already achieved a tremendous amount at such a young age and it seems like things aren't slowing down either.  2006 has been spent by Talky laying the foundations and releasing his first mix compilation; the second installment of the Thinking Out Loud series.

artist.name: Shin Nishimura
artist.bio: Shin Nishimura, one of the top well known Japanese DJ has started hiscarrier from Shanghai, when there was absolutely no Dance music scene. Shinstarted his own organized party called "PLUS" and introduced various ofartists though the party, and succeeded to buildup the club music scene. Hisfirst world wide Mix CD release, "Live in Shanghai"(Technorient) was massivehit and make his name go around. Year of 2001, he had gig at the biggestrave party "MAYDAY" in Germany, and Shin went back to his home, Japan.

artist.name: De La Soul vs. Kurd Madvrick
Pet Shop Boys
artist.bio: Pet Shop Boys are a British synthpop/pop music duo, consisting of Neil Tennant who provides main vocals, keyboards and very occasionally guitar, and Chris Lowe on keyboards and occasionally on vocals. They formed in London, UK in 1982. The longevity of Pet Shop Boys' career is generally attributed to their ability to create melodic pop/dance music with intelligent lyrics and striking style. They are the most successful duo in pop music, particularly in Europe.

artist.name: Alex Gold
artist.bio: Alex Gold needs no introduction as one of the world's finest DJs and recording artists. Having played to sell-out crowds in over 20 countries including the USA, Australia, Japan and South Africa, and in more diverse regions such as The Philippines and Russia, it is the States that have provided Alex's greatest fan base. He has toured the US extensively, playing at all the major venues including the infamous Club Space Miami (where he was bi-monthly resident for two years) Exit NYC, Buzz and Glow Washington, Giant LA, Spundae San Francisco and Avalon Boston.

artist.name: Made By Monkeys ft. Darcy Conroy
Yvel & Tristen ft. Chriss Of The Quasa
Paul Anthony & ZXX ft. Jen Bonesteel
Rick Pier O'Neil
artist.bio: Rick started his career like DJ in various clubs and in parallels the one of producer who it will become his principal activity. Influenced by the “new house sound” of the Nineties in France, he released some tracks like Sequential Feat Kleph "Chocho locco", Tribal Nation "In Guetto".... In 1999, He creates his first label RPO TRAXX with tendency house and latino house. The same year, in USA, Rick Pier O' Neil signs a 5 in Billboard dance charts with the 1st title group Sussex House "Good Feel".

artist.name: Speedy J
artist.bio: Speedy J (real name Jochem Paap) is a Dutch techno producer based in the city of Rotterdam. His breakthrough came with the release in 1992 of the techno track Pullover. Subsequently his material became more mellow as he moved away from the hardcore sounds that were then becoming popular in Belgium and the Netherlands. His debut album Ginger was released in 1993. A further, more introspective, release, G-Spot followed in 1995. Afterwards his work, including Public Energy No.

artist.name: Tikaro, J. Louis, Ferran feat. Clarence
The Drill
artist.bio: THE DRILL -A.K.A Matt Schwartz (born October 26th, 1971 in Haifa,Israel) is a Producer residing in the UK. He's responsible for many crossover club hits under many different names such as Dada Feat. Sandy Rivera and Trix -'Lollipop' and Deepest Blue. He usually releases all his underground releases via his label, 'Destined Records' Matt has also worked with many great bands such as Massive attack, JTQ and Arthur Baker to name a few.

artist.name: Nova
artist.bio: There are 13 different bands named Nova: 1. A Finnish progressive rock group. 2. A Finnish rap artist 3. A Dutch electronic music group 4. A French pop rock band. 5. An Italian gothic/neo-folk group. 6. An Italian progressive rock/jazz fusion group. 7. An American jazz fusion group. 8. A Swedish dance (lindyhop/foxtrot etc) band 9. A Russian pop rock group. 10. An alias of electronic music producer L-Vee (aka Airwave) 11. An American alternative rock band.

artist.name: Matt Darey
artist.bio: Matt has been one of the pioneers of today’s dance scene being a major influence on today’s world class DJ’s. Throughout his 17 year career of producing & writing house, trance, breaks and progressive and much more he has sold well over 2 million albums & singles with numerous top 10 & top 20 chart hits.  His Nocturnal radio show is the worlds fastest expanding multi genre dance radio show now broadcast on 116 FM stations worldwide. In recent years Matt has been  playing his unique “Nocturnal” blend of many styles including electro, progressive, tech, trance and occasional house & breaks.

artist.name: Felix Baumgartner & Juan Kidd ft. Lisa Millett
Jaydee
artist.bio: Robin 'Jaydee' Albers started his deejay career in 1978 as the resident dj in Rhenen, Veenendaal, Arnhem, Den Bosch, Enschede, and lots of other places. Jan Steeman of the AVRO Radio offered Robin a deejay contract in 1984 and from that time Robin started his long radio career at the national radio.  In 1984 Jaydee also started the Dutch mixing championships and lots of deejays from then are the stars of today such as DJ Jean, Michel de Hey, Erik E. DJ Gizmo, Ruud van Rijen, Orlando Voorn, Guan Elmzoon and many more.

artist.name: Oko Tek & Delphi ft. Michelle Guiterrez
Nadia
artist.bio:
Nadia is a Canadian Dance singer. 
 In 1995, Nadia signed a record deal with New Music Records based out of Montreal releasing a number of hit singles heard over the radio stations across Canada. She also signed many of those singles abroad. 
 Her first Album “Kiss of Destiny” was released in Russia, Japan and Saudi Arabia. She was featured as a performer on Much Music’s “Electric Circus” and Musique Plus “Bouge De La” as well she performed regularly in Ottawa, Montreal, Toronto, and Quebec city for various events.

artist.name: SCSI-9
artist.bio: SCSI-9 are Anton Kubikov & Maxim Milutenko. Anton Kubikov was born in 1975 in Moscow. He started his career in 1994 playing at one of the first Moscow techno clubs - Ermitage. From January 1995 until January 1996 he was a resident in Relax club in Moscow. Very soon he became a popular figure at the Moscow DJ scene and was constantly invited to perform at such popular Moscow clubs like Treasure Island, Metro, Moby Dick, Ptuch, Utopy, X-Dance and others.

artist.name: Martin Solveig
artist.bio: Martin Solveig was born in 1976. At the age of 13, he got his first turntables and that influenced him to take up a career in electronic music rather than the classical music he was learning. He started his first residency at Paris's leading club Le Palace with the support of Claude Monnet.  Martin Solveig then moved to another famous Paris nightclub Les Bains Douches where he worked with famous DJs such as Todd Terry, Roger Sanchez and Bob Sinclar. His popularity further increased with the Pure parties at the Queen Club either as a DJ or as an art director.

artist.name: D-Force
artist.bio:
D-Force began writing music in his early ages. From the age of 9 ( back in 1985 ) he was playing music on his Atari600XL, at this time he discovered the possibilities of making own music on this device. From this moment on he never stopped producing music for the Demo scene.  Througout the years severeal albums where made as the latest cd is called :"The New CD!". This cd contains song from the DemoScene as well as the song Roading for the MicroDisco series.
 The cd was partially made during his Internship in Romania. Most of the songs where inspired by this country.

artist.name: Sono
artist.bio: As the group Sono, Lennart A. Salomon, Florian Sikorski and Martin Weiland polish synthie pop until it gleams, sprucing it up for the third millennium. In their Hamburg studio, where international mainstream hits are usually mixed, forthright megalomania is the gas pedal and false modesty the brake. Why? For pop to sound great, it has to be thought of on a grand scale.  If music is also supposed to be understood as language, then Sono speaks Esperanto. In German Sono simply means “Klang” (sound, tone) – perhaps only an onomatopoeic coincidence, but perhaps also a promise.

artist.name: Armand Van Helden ft. Duane Harden
Swanky Tunes
artist.bio: Of all the exciting new electro sounds coming out of the East these days - Swanky Tunes ranks among the most noteworthy. The group formed in 1998, experimenting with different electronic stylings in pursuit of their own sound. At first, there were techno sounds mixed with vintage synthesizers. Then the group moved into a distinctly big-beat influenced sound. These days, hints of the French-house scene, early Depeche Mode, electro-80's, and the contemporary electro-house movement are all finding their way into the mix.

artist.name: Cicada
artist.bio: The name 'Cicada' refers to more than one band. The first Cicada: Member Since: 12/19/2005 Band Website: www.cicadamusic.com Band Members: Aaron Gilbert, Alex Payne, Heidrun Bjornsdottir. Official biog for new album "Roulette" released on iTunes 1st June, in shops 8th June. We were flying back from Russia in this cranky Tupelov plane,” recalls Alex Payne explaining how Cicada came up with the title ‘Roulette’ for their new album, “We joked that it would be Russian roulette whether we made it home or not.

artist.name: Menini & Viani ft. Christian Key - La La Land (M&V re
Peter Gelderblom
artist.bio: Peter Gelderblom started his career at the age of 14 at LaBaraque Club near Rotterdam, The Netherlands, in 1979. He played there for 6 years. After that he resided at the biggest club in Rotterdam, Ramblas Club, for almost 10 years.   He was a storemaster at the local Midtown Record in Rotterdam, opened his own club on a boat, and produced records for Blue Records. He met Rene Amesz there and build a studio, bought a record shop. Today he runs both a club, a shop and a studio.

artist.name: Jimmy Van M ft. Steve T & Marc Mitchell
All Seeing I
artist.bio: Real Name: Jason Buckle, Richard Barratt, Dean Honer

artist.name: Sei A
artist.bio: Sei A (real name Andy Graham) had his first release back in 2003 alongside Gordon Logan under the pseudonym Seinan. Many releases followed, alongside more recent solo productions under his 'Droido' moniker. Throughout this time Andy has built a great fanbase of some of the worlds leading DJ talent including Miss Kittin, Laurent Garnier and Ben Watt.   All Sei A productions are impossible to categorize and that’s what makes his music so unique.

artist.name: Yo Majesty
artist.bio:
Yo Majesty is an American hip hop group consisting of rapper Shunda K and singer Jwl B. The group is produced by U.K. based electro duo Hard Feelings UK.
 Yo Majesty's style is generally described as a mix of underground hip hop, party rap and electro. Both Shunda K & Jwl B are natives of Tampa, Florida. The group was formed when the two met at a local gay club. Yo Majesty has recently toured with Peaches and there is a long list of acts lined up to collaborate with Yo Majesty including UK hit-makers Basement Jaxx.

artist.name: Marco Carola
artist.bio:
Born in Naples on February 7, 1975, Marco Carola has emerged in the last four years as one of the city's most influential exponents of Techno and electronic music.   
 Growing up in the Neapolitan sunshine, by the age of 13 he got behind the skins of his first drum kit which he played for several years before ultimately being addicted to buying and playing records. In 1990, when the Italian House scene was enjoying its golden age alongside the madness of Acid House...

artist.name: The Mole
artist.bio: The Mole (real name Colin de la Plante) is a Canadian DJ / Producer who has toured the world with his trademark techno sound. He has also released numerous records under various monikers, through a variety of imprints. Furthermore, he is a member of the experimental group, Modern Deep Left Quartet, which features all members of Cobblestone Jazz. In Groups: The Bacon Smugglers, Bodensee, The Modern Deep Left Quartet, Shannon & The Mole

artist.name: Sidney Samson
artist.bio: Sidney started DJ-ing in 1995 at the age of 14. During that time he mainly played R&B and HipHop tunes in the local clubs. In 1999 he switched his style completely over into housemusic. In 2003 Sidney became the resident dj of the Exxellent nights at one of Hollands biggest club ‘The Matrixx’. Besides his residency he played at clubs across the country. Sidney is also very busy with producing and remixing.

artist.name: Matias Aguayo
artist.bio:
Matias Aguayo 
 Genre: Electronica 
 Active: '90s, 2000s
 Instrument: Producer
 Representative Album: "Are You Really Lost" 
 ...lives between Buenos Aires and Paris, djing, making music, performing concerts alone and together with Marcus Rossknecht with their project "BROKE!".
 Born 73 in Santiago de Chile he musically grew up in Cologne, Germany,
 where he spent the whole 90ies living and contributing to the scene of this city which would have such a deep influence on dancemusic. He was there, as clubkid and dj (e.

artist.name: Fever Ray
artist.bio: Fever Ray is the solo project of Karin Dreijer Andersson, who is one half of the Swedish electro act The Knife (the other half is her brother Olof Dreijer). Andersson was also the lead singer and guitarist for the defunct indie pop group Honey is Cool. The first, self-titled Fever Ray record was released digitally on January 13, 2009 and its first single "If I Had A Heart" was released on December 15, 2008.

artist.name: The Jon Spencer Blues Explosion
artist.bio: The Jon Spencer Blues Explosion (since 2004 known simply as Blues Explosion) is an American punk blues band, which was formed in New York in 1990. Singer Jon Spencer was previously the leader of the noise punk band Pussy Galore before hooking up with Judah Bauer (guitar) and Russell Simins (drums) to form the Blues Explosion, a band that was part of the 1990s alternative rock boom. This bass-less combo had their breakthrough in 1993 with the album "Extra Width" on Crypt Records. In 1994 "Orange", a more accessible album followed along with a growing base of fans.

artist.name: Peaches
artist.bio: Merrill Nisker (born 1968 in Toronto), better known as Peaches, is an electroclash artist whose songs are mainly focused on sexuality. She lives and works in Berlin. She plays almost all the instruments for her songs, programs her own electronic beats, and produces her records.  Her songs have been featured in movies such as Mean Girls, My Little Eye, Lost in Translation, Waiting, and Jackass: Number Two. Her music has also been featured on Showtime's The L Word television series. Peaches performed guest vocals on P!nk's album Try This, on the song "Oh My God".

artist.name: LCD Soundsystem
artist.bio: LCD Soundsystem is the musical side project of producer James Murphy, co-founder of New York City dance-punk label DFA Records. Formed in 2002, the music of LCD Soundsystem can also be described as a mix of dance and post punk, along with elements of disco and other styles. The band covered songs from Joy Division and Siouxsie and the Banshees. During live performances, Murphy is accompanied by Al Doyle (guitar, percussion -- also of Hot Chip), Phil Skarich (bass), Nancy Whang on the keyboard and Pat Mahoney on the drums.

artist.name: Air Liquide
artist.bio: Air Liquide is a German electronic band composed of musicians Ingmar Koch (AKA "Dr Walker") and Cem Oral (AKA "Jammin' Unit"), formed in 1991 in Cologne, Germany. They are known for their heady mixture of dub, electro beats, intricate acid techno and austere sonic sensibilities.  They released several works via their own label Blue and acclaimed English techno label Rising High Records. EMI brought the defunct Harvest imprint back online to house their experiments.

artist.name: Housemeister
artist.bio: Housemeister is flying high over Berlin, filling the gaps between Techno, Electro and punk. He likes his very own definition of dancefloor craze. After 12 years as dj, he released his first album 2006 on Boysnoize records. "Enlarge Your Dose" reflects his intense life as a master-raver as well as his hilarious brain-twisting humour. The rebel without a pause finds himself well positioned on bpitchcontrol, Boysnoize and his ALLYOUCANBEAT label.

artist.name: Mr. Oizo
artist.bio: Mr. Oizo (pronounced 'Monsieur Wah-zoh') is the pseudonym of French music producer Quentin Dupieux.  Dupieux is most famous for his electro track "Flat Beat", which became a hit all across Europe in 1999 for being featured in a series of Levi's jeans TV advertisements. Dupieux also directed the ad, which featured a yellow puppet named Flat Eric nodding his head to the sound of the track while riding in a pickup truck. Flat Eric later appeared in the music video for "Flat Beat".  After "Flat Beat", Oizo released his first album in 1999, Analog Worms Attack, featuring a single of the same name.

artist.name: Arnaud Rebotini
artist.bio: http://www.myspace.com/arnaudrebotini

artist.name: Plastikman
artist.bio: Plastikman is probably the best known of Canadian DJ Richie Hawtin's production aliases. The Plastikman project helped push the minimal aesthetic of detroit techno to relative popularity in the early-mid 1990s, largely on the back of the drum machine track "Spastik", but also via the sound of a "devilfish" modified Roland TB-303.

artist.name: Duality
artist.bio: There are at least two artists/bands named Duality.   1 - Progressive/uplifting trance-project was founded in 2007 by two producers from cold russian Siberia - Matthew Preffekt and Alex August.   2 - Progressive Death metal band from Tampere, Finland.   (2)Early history: Duality was born from the ashes of a Metallica/Megadeth cover band, originally implemented by Matti Auerkallio (guitar) and Tero Heinonen (drums) in Valkeakoski, Finland.

artist.name: Dynamic Emotion
artist.bio: The "Dynamic Emotion" duet was founded at the beginning of 2008 year by DJ Toy & Max Northbeat in town Krivoy Rog, Ukraine. The name of project reflects essence of its participants. Sometimes Toy is a Dynamic, and Northbeat is an Emotion, and sometimes on the contrary. From it it turns out that basic elements in music of duet this loud Speaker and Emotion. Basic style of project is a Progressive Trance, but boys are not be fastidious other styles of electronic music, such as breaks, progressive/tech house and other It is not important for them...

artist.name: Mario Ayuda & Paul Hind pres. PokeMoon
Wardt
artist.bio: Born Christmas 1988, Wardt van der Harst AKA RE-WARD is a youngster inspired by one of the legends of today’s trance scene, Tiësto. He was 12 when he heard ‘Flight 643’. That moment was the moment he decided to save money for dj gear. Later on he bought software to produce music in that style. Like the most producers he began with some old tracker software, moved up to Fruityloops and he’s now using Reason as most important tool to make his music with.

artist.name: Cosmic Gate feat. Denise Rivera vs. Nenes
Randy Katana
artist.bio: Randy Katana originally came from the Dutch Antillean Islands (Aruba, Curacao and St Maarten), where for many years he worked as resident DJ at many of the trendiest clubs on the Islands. He also spend many years playing drums in Brass Bands, which on the islands where specialized in Carnival music. This is where Randy acquired the Latin tribal soul that he projects in his music today.   Shortly after moving to Amsterdam in 1988, he started his own record company BPM Dance and opened one of the most successful online vinyl shops till this day: Only-Djs.

artist.name: Santiago Niño & Damien Heck feat. Antonia Lucas
Madagascar
artist.bio: Madagascar is a band from Baltimore, MD. They make a unique instrumental folk music from accordion, glockenspiel, saw, guitar, percussion, ukulele, melodica, and other acoustic instruments.  They have released two albums: Forced March (2005) and Goodbye East, Goodbye West (2007) on the Western Vinyl label. In 2007 the band released a DVD of songs from Forced March (plus outtakes) set to animations by The King of Russia.

artist.name: Tigran Oganezov
artist.bio: Hailing from Western Ukraine this 27 year old DJ/producer is regarded by many as one of the leading new artists from his country. With his devastating sound appearing reguarly on many big Dj tracklistings and his international DJ career about to launch,Tigran Oganezov has become an exciting new addition to the global tech trance ranks!  His unique sound was born in 2008 when he shedded the hardcore roots to concentrate on a new found love for making tech trance. Bookings in his homeland soon started when Ukranian club promoters heard Tigrans productions and promo mixes.

artist.name: Miss Melody
artist.bio: Miss Melody has music in her blood. Born in Spain, where her father owns a club in Benidorm, she is raised with music. Already at eighteen she was helping in her father's club, playing music in Benidorm. During the summer, when organisers of major festivals flocked to the sunny coastline, she soon became well-known throughout the whole of Spain. Melody soon played clubs such as the Palladium, the Ministry of Sound, Privilege and Ku.

artist.name: Chris Lake feat Nastala
artist.bio: Chris Lake is a British House music DJ/producer. Lake first became recognized for his bootleg remixes of The Prodigy's "Climbatize", Leftfield's "Phat Planet", and Eurythmics "Sweet Dreams". which he did under the alias "Cristophe D'Abuc". His 2006 track with vocals from Laura V, "Changes", reached the UK Singles Chart.peaking at #27. "Changes" was first released in 2005 on Alternative Route Recordings and was licensed to Universal Music for a full worldwide release in Summer 2006. It reached #10 on Billboard's Hot Dance Airplay chart.

artist.name: Oceanlab feat. Justine Suissa
artist.bio: OceanLab is a vocal trance group formed in London, England in 2000, consisting of vocalist Justine Suissa and the three members of Above & Beyond; Jonathan Grant, Tony McGuinness, and Paavo Siljamäki.

artist.name: Reii
artist.bio: REII is an underground, alternative, artificial project of something that should be a piece of rock-metal music influenced on bands like Nirvana and Dir en Grey for example.

artist.name: Jonas Steur & Leon Bolier vs. Axwell & Sebastian Ingrosso
Ali Wilson, Matt Smallwood & Tristan Ingram
Omen
artist.bio:
1. OMEN is an American Heavy Metal band that was formed in Los Angeles in 1983 by guitarist Kenny Powell, as he left the band Savage Grace.
 The other three founding members were: lead singer J.D. Kimball, bassist Jody Henry and drummer Steve Wittig.
 They quickly signed a record deal with the uprising label "Metal Blade Records" and released 4 albums and one E.P. before splitting up in 1989.
 Kenny Powell later on founded a new band called Stepchild and released an album with them.

artist.name: Diablo
artist.bio: There are at least three artists and two other things named "Diablo." 1. A Four piece Finnish melodic death metal band formed in 1995. 2. A Korean thrash metal band. 3. An experimental Chilean screamo/post rock band 4. An Amiga demoscene musician active in the early and mid 1990s 5. Referencing to the popular RPG, Diablo or Diablo II. 1) Diablo was born in the late 1990s and recorded it´s first mini-album Princess� catching a record deal with Poko Rekords. The first album Elegance in Black was released in 2000 and was described as a powerful punch in the face.

artist.name: Soul In The Machine feat. Chrysta Bell
Kurd Maverick
artist.bio:
GIAN aka KURD MAVERICK 
 From a very early age Gian loved music, playing several music instruments and having a good ear for music - that's why he found his way to a well-known Turkish/Kurdish group at the age of 15.  
  
 He soon proved himself to be not only an excellent musician but also a good entertainer. His first contact with the "Djing" was in 1997 when a friend introduced him to the wheels of steel. He was really fascinated with the almost infinite sound structures which he could obtain by two turntables and mixers and soon decided to get deeper into this high art of presenting.

artist.name: Mike Koglin
artist.bio: Mike Koglin burst onto the scene in 1998 with his club anthem and UK top20 hit 'The Silence', one of the defining tracks of the UK trance phenomenon which put Mike firmly onto the map as one of the key players in dance music.  Since then the Grammy-nominated Producer, Remixer and DJ has has released aconstant string of productions, under his own name or under one of his various aliases, as well as over 70 remixes in the last 7 years.

artist.name: Gran Vitaly ft. Talya El Mejor
Kismet
artist.bio: There are at least six artists by this name. Kismet is an indie rock quintet originated from Utrecht, Netherlands. Influenced by the likes of Cursive, Depeche Mode, Blonde Redhead and The Get Up Kids, the group was founded in the winter of 2002. After releasing two E.P.s the bands line-up solidified in 2006 and started focussing on a debut full-length album. Kismets sound is characterized by their dynamic compositions, combining complicated songstructures with a seemless melody and catchy vocals.

artist.name: Dusty Kid
artist.bio: les and within the raw energy of electronic music. He released his first EP at 19 and produced under various monikers on labels such as Boxer Recordings Köln, Kling Klong and Systematic. He is currently working on his debut album and describes his live set as "a sort of eclectic techno with influences from the 80's restrained with acid house.. in few words.. a big beat soup!'

artist.name: Julien Jabre
artist.bio: Great french DJ. His greatest hit "Swimming Places" was remixed by producers like Sebastian Ingrosso, Sabaudia Gabin and Peter Heller. His favourite styles are house, latino house and electronica.

artist.name: Starkillers
artist.bio: Nick Terranova. And His signature blend of catchy vocals, booming bass lines and genre-defying range are always in full effect on tour or at his "Dirty Sound" residencies at Late Night Empire in Las Vegas, crobar Chicago, Lizard Lounge in Dallas, On Broadway in San Diego, Bleu in Detroit, and Bliss in San Antonio. The energy and sexiness that are hallmarks of Terranova’s live shows are also his trademarks as a producer and remixer - a dance music "triple threat." That dirty vocal track your girlfriend keeps singing in the shower? It’s a Nick Terranova production.

artist.name: Natalino Nunes vs Kobbe and Mar-C
Microtrauma
artist.bio: Microtrauma started up their musical ways in 2005, after a few years they began to release their own Music on Labels like Elected Tunes and Microtonal Records. www.myspace.com/microtrauma Thanks for your great Feedback!

artist.name: Amiel
artist.bio: 1) Amiel Daemion or just Amiel (born c. 1981) is an Australian singer who began her international singing career at age 9 with a haunting ecology song: "What About the Children?". She contributed the vocals for Josh Abrahams/Puretone's song, "Addicted To Bass" (peaking at #15 on the Australian Aria Singles Chart under the first name in 1999, and recharting in the top 100 under the second name with more remixes in 2002. This version also debuted and peaked at #2 on the UK Singles Chart.) She also contributed to songs on the Moulin Rouge soundtrack.

artist.name: International Departures
artist.bio: "International Departures" is the bi-weekly radio show from Myon & Shane 54, who despite their short history together, already achieved notable success in the international dance music scene.  They've been voted "Guestmix Of The Year" on Above & Beyond's massively successful radio show "Trance Around The World", scored a Beatport Number One remix with Andy Moor's "So Much More" or played amongst the big names at Armin Van Buuren's ASOT 400 party, where the line-up was selected by those millions who listens the influential radio show week by week.

artist.name: Ashley Wallbridge & Andy Moor feat. Meighan Nealon
68 Beats
artist.bio: 68 beats is one project of Robbie Rivera.  Found on Wikipedia :   Riberto Louis Rivera, better known as Robbie Rivera, is a prolific house music producer and DJ born in Puerto Rico. He has an extensive catalog of original productions and remixes to his credit, ranging from tribal to progressive house, as well as incorporating garage and latin elements. As a solo artist he has hit #1 on the Hot Dance Music/Club Play chart twice: in 2001 with "Feel This 2001" and again in 2003 with "The Hum Melody".

artist.name: Marten Fisher
artist.bio: Dutch producer Marten Fisher started producing in the early nineties. At first with a Commodore computer and a couple of low quality speakers. He organised some local illegal parties and was mostly found on the crowded side of the decks ;) From 2000 on he produced for labels like Bad Girls, XXXFlicks and Dub=Records and now for 90wattsrecords. Besides his passion for music, he spends a lot of time in his working place making paintings.

artist.name: Maetrik
artist.bio: Eric Estornel, under the names MAETRIK, MARIEL ITO, and simply ESTORNEL - has been contributing to his musical world around him since 93. First a dj, and later developing his skills as a producer, Eric has always searched for the future of electronic dance. Not being confined by rules of styles or genres is most important to Eric, as he makes his way through a political and fickle industry.   Eric as Maetrik has released music on such respected labels as Treibstoff, SubStatic, Morris Audio, Onitor, Immigrant, Iron Box Music, and many others.

artist.name: Ariel Curtis
artist.bio:
BIOGRAPHY
 With more than 10 years experience as a Dj Producer Ariel Curtis has now travelled over 1 million Kms around the World with him music played in the 5 continets.Also he have a great experience in live performances among other experiences.At the moment Ariel Curtis has more than 100 Tracks betwen Original and Remixed productions Released in excellent labels such as:No Smoking, Bellarine Records, Bit Records, Ansia Records, Reticent Records, Soulstar Records/ClubStar, Source Of Gravity, Hunya Munya.

artist.name: Milton Jackson
artist.bio: Released his first EP aged 19 on Solemusic's Tronicsole imprint. Known for his dark, almost techno influenced deep house music. Milton Jackson tends to fuse straight driving beats with eclectic, techy production styles. His first and so far only long player, 'The Bionic Boy' was received well by critics and the house fraternity and it spawned the Pepe Bradock influenced 'Sunlight'. After having mainly appeared on Glasgow labels such as Solemusic and Glasgow Underground, 2006 sees Milton spread his wings with EPs due out on Freerange...

artist.name: Yvel & Tristan Feat. Chriss of The Quasar
Adam Jace
artist.bio: Adam Jace lives and breathes house music. His sound is described as unique and forward thinking, breaking down genre boundaries effortlessly and representing club-focused music at its very best.  As a DJ, he has played all across Sydney, holding down an ongoing 2 year residency at Habit as well as playing guest spots for one of Australia’s leading underground club brands, Sweetchilli. In 2008 Adam played his first set of international gigs when he toured Thailand, playing 6 slots across the country and headlining some of Bangkok's biggest clubs.

artist.name: Liquid Vision vs. Shadowfall ft. Alphadelt
Tikaro, J. Louis, Ferran ft. Clarence
Marlo
artist.bio: There are multiple artists on Last.fm with the name 'Marlo'.    The first and better known 'Marlo' is most famous for being in the video "Freestyler" by Bomfunk MC's.
