He is a talented DJ, drummer, actor and model who comes from Finland.    The second band 'Marlo' is a band from Washington State known for their Indie/Electronica sound.  There are two members of Marlo, Danny VanHollebeke and Timmy Hudson.  Their latest (and only) album is known as "Secrets of the Universe".  Their songs include Diamond Smuggling, Alone and Honored Out, 22, Earth Suit, and Mr.

artist.name: The Bloody Beetroots ft. Steve Aoki
Astronivo
artist.bio: Astronivo an electronic phenomenon created by Guy Astrogano and Niv Konforty.

artist.name: Garbage
artist.bio: Garbage is a Scottish-American rock group formed in Madison, Wisconsin, in 1994. The band consists of Duke Erikson, Shirley Manson (former lead vocalist of Angelfish), Steve Marker, and Butch Vig (who had made his name as a producer, including Nirvana's album, Nevermind). Garbage released a string of increasingly successful singles in 1995–1996, culminating in the hit Stupid Girl. Their debut album, Garbage, was an unexpected smash, selling over 4 million copies and reaching double platinum status in the UK, USA and Australia.

artist.name: Rui Da Silva ft. Cassandra Fox
Luke Wan
artist.bio: AKA Luke Fair

artist.name: Kosheen
artist.bio: Kosheen are a Bristol-based trio formed in 1998. The band includes Sian Evans (vocals), Darren "Decoder" Beale and Markee "Substance" Morrison (both producing, mixing, guitars etc.),. The band's third album "Damage" was released in the UK on Moksha on 10th September 2007. Damage is a mixture of inspirations from electronic influence from "Resist" and guitar tunes from "Kokopelli". The sound of "Damage" synthesizes elements of dark electro / synthpop / downtempo / vocal / electronica information.

artist.name: Daniel Ortega
artist.bio: Daniel Ortega is a singer/songwriter working in Hamburg and Münster, Germany. He is also the drummer and background-voice of Miyagi. http://www.myspace.com/danielortegajan http://www.miyagi-music.de

artist.name: Lula
artist.bio: There are 5 artists named Lula: 1: Lula - Singer & DJ from Austria (Claudia Radbauer) 2: Lula - Italian band 3: Lula - German singer and songwriter 4: Lula - Spanish Powerpop Trio 5: Lula - Thai singer 1.) Lula or Lula Grelhada (real name: Claudia Radbauer) is an Austrian vocalist and songwriter. After visiting New York in the early 1990s, Claudia Radbauer became enamored with the city's club scene and house music. As a 26 year-old club regular at Sound Factory, and later Twilo, she eventually befriended Danny Tenaglia, who introduced her to some of the world's hottest DJs.

artist.name: Joey V
artist.bio: Joey V is a 22 year old DJ & Producer, but a DJ & producer that goes uncompared to others! He is what they call an obsessed DJ. His obsession began at just 13 years of age where he would spend almost every minute of the day over his decks determined to teach himself to mix and learn new things, This has lead to him picking up a completely unique style of DJing and flawless trickery which has to been seen live to be fully appreciated.

artist.name: Sneaker Pimps
artist.bio: Sneaker Pimps are a downtempo/electronica band which formed in Hartlepool, England in 1995. The band best known for their first album Becoming X released in 1996, and particularly its highest charting single "6 Underground". As line of flight and Frisk, DJs and childhood friends Chris Corner and Liam Howe (from Middlesborough and Hartlepool in the NE of England) released two EPs: "Soul of Indiscretion" and "World as A Cone" in the early 1990s.

artist.name: Bush II Bush
artist.bio: BIOGRAPHY  Within the last three years, Bush II Bush have become one of the most respected DJ/Producer teams worldwide. Originally from Dusseldorf, Germany, Andry Nalin & Gregor Wagner AKA Bush II Bush have seen their reputation rise with a number of innovative productions and remixes to their credit. Their first singles rose to the top of the German buzz charts and just a short while later, Bush II Bush released the hit “Piano Track” on SAW Recordings and it became one of the biggest hits of 2005.

artist.name: Just A Band
artist.bio:
Just A Band is an Electro duo from Bordeaux. They are Tom Deluxx & Stella.
 Signed to Homework Records.   Discography :
 “We Are” EP
 “Burn It Out” EP
 "To Hell With Gravity" EP

artist.name: Felix Da Housecat
artist.bio: Felix da Housecat (born Felix Stallings in chicago, Illinois) is an electro music DJ and record producer. Felix is commonly regarded as a member of the second wave of chicago house. He entered the dance music elite not only via his recordings (under a number of aliases, including Thee Maddkatt Courtship, Aphrohead and Sharkimaxx), but also for his ownership of Radikal Fear Records, one of the premiere Chicago labels of the 1990s.

artist.name: The Officials
artist.bio: The Officials are Richard Hellier and Ed Samuels, two music producers that are working together for more than 15 years. After many years they invested time and energy to promote and develope the old funk style, thay started to be more pasionated by dance music in the last years. So, one of their results of the passion, is this EP on Sequential. The main music is electro-house. A few electro gooves, more house rhythm, and two remixes besides the original mix. As for this one, the things work just in a great mood, summer, melodic and groovy.

artist.name: Cream Sound
artist.bio: Cream sound is a vocalist and producer from Russia.  In 2007 - 2008 she signed some new tracks to the labels like Morphosis, Pure Substance and Carica Records. Her tracks got support by many djs and radios, among them Andy Moor, Ronski Speed, Snake Sedrick, Mental X, Stefan Mone (Discomania Distribution), Rafy Nieves (Billboard DJ Reporter), George Kyrimis (Digital Communications), Solarstone, Cor Fijnerman, StereoK,Miss Napalm, Thomas Wagner (Fraud Recordings), Kenneth Thomas, Paul Oakenfold, Jaytech...

artist.name: Abdomen Burst
artist.bio: Abdomen Burst is a rising star in the exploding Russian progressive scene. He first garnered attention with his 2008 debut release on Morphosis Records, and is poised to break out with his upcoming release on Toes in the Sand.  Music runs in the family -- his father was a drummer in a live band, influencing the breakbeat rhythms in Abdomen Burst's productions. Combined with atmospheric sounds and beautiful melodies, his work contributes to the current renaissance of progressive breaks, as well as helping to establish Russia as a major force in the dance music world.

artist.name: Alkatraz
artist.bio: At leas two artists are using this name: 1. There is Alkatraz a polish rock group founded by Roman Kostrzewski from polish metal act called Kat 2. A light Jazz / Soft Rock band, with an album titled "Doing a Moonlight" released in 1976.

artist.name: Kris Menace
artist.bio: Kris Menace (born Christophe Höffel) is an electronic musician. He began to work as a producer and writer in the mid 1990s for different projects and started using the pseudonym "Kris Menace" in 2005. Menace is the owner of the house label "Work It Baby". Menace's debut single (in collaboration with Lifelike), Discopolis, was released on Vulture Music in 2005 and was one of the most anticipated house tracks and an Ibiza anthem within the same year. Discopolis was later picked up by Defected Records and re-released with various remixes and a video directed by Seb Janiak.

artist.name: Delete
artist.bio: Delete aka Sergio Muñoz is a  DJ/Producer from Venezuela. He has certainly started to make a name for himself, and all at the tender age of only 22 years old! In a very short space of time Sergio has not only mastered the art of dj-ing but has also turned his hand to his own productions, which are starting to make waves in the dance community. Sergio's style is very much his own, fusing deep house grooves with the more minimal techno side of the electronic house revolution. His first productions were very influenced by house music.

artist.name: Blue Six
artist.bio: Musician, producer and remixer Jay Denes, better known as Blue Six, was born in Newark, NJ. After moving to N.Y.C., the newcomer failed to get seriously involved in the local music scene until hip-hop producer Bob Power hooked him up with Dave Boonshoff. Jay Denes began working on his own freestyle project soon after naming himself Blue Six. Released by Naked Music, his debut full-length record called Beautiful Tomorrow delivered a mix of electronic music, soulful pop, and smooth jazz, featuring contributions from multi-instrumentalist Marc Anthony Jones.

artist.name: Swedish House Mafia
artist.bio: The Swedish House Mafia is a group of four popular house DJs and producers; Eric Prydz, Axwell, Steve Angello, and Sebastian Ingrosso.  However Sebastian Ingrosso has stated that because Eric Prydz has moved to London he is no longer considered part of the Swedish House Mafia. The trio remain close with Eric Prydz aka Pryda, supporting many of his tracks in their sets.

artist.name: Soulsearcher
artist.bio: Marc Pomeroy is one half of the world-renowned remix team "Jazz-N-Groove Productions" and co-owner of the critically acclaimed record label Soulfuric Recordings.  He also records under the monikers of "Urban Blues Project", "Deepstar" and "Soulsearcher", as well as remixing for everyone from Loleatta Holloway to Busta Rhymes to Sounds of Blackness.  Marc is originally from Gainesville, Florida, and has a colorful musical heritage.  Drawing on influences ranging from Steely Dan to MSFB, he is an accomplished producer, song writer and musician.

artist.name: Gregor Tresher
artist.bio: In the field of electronic music, Gregor Tresher is by no means a debutant. For more than seven years the thirty-year old DJ and producer from Rhine-Main area gathered merits modernizing the algorithms of electronic music. It has been his "Still EP" in 2005 that upgraded him into the Champions League of European Techno producers and many highlight releases like "Neon", "Full Range Madness" or "The Now People" on labels like Great Stuff, Datapunk, Cocoon or Terminal M convinced the readers of German magazine "Raveline" to vote him as "Best Producer 2006".

artist.name: Chelonis R. Jones
artist.bio: Chelonis R. Jones is an American artist who left his home of New York for the shores of Europe, in order to pursue a blossoming career in the world of arts.  Armed with his paintbrushes, unpublished manuscripts, songs and poems, he decided to commit himself fully to the vitriolic world of the struggling artist and their sometimes fruitful plight. Working as a songwriter and playing vocalist in more than twenty rock/pop groups and pulling a handful of small artshows for his paintings were hardly usual.

artist.name: Oliver Huntemann
artist.bio: 2006: Electronic Dance Music dominates the urban club culture since more than 15 years. Between many highs and lows techno music has proven, that it is here to stay. Not many techno artists managed to do that in the same manner. Bremen based recording artist and DJ Oliver Huntemann definitely belongs to the few activists, who kept on holding up the torch since the beginning. Brought up in the funky northern german countryside, he soon found himself heavily infected by the fascinating world of music.

artist.name: Namito
artist.bio: Namito is one of the most pleasant DJs you could hope to meet. Far from the wannabe stars that dominate the scene Namito truly loves his career and relishes every moment he spends playing or producing. While other DJs strive for fame and recognition, Namitos down_to_earth  attitude and approach to his music make him one of the few real DJ_Artists. Rarely do you find such a dedicated individual, the man goes to bed with his logic audio manual for gods sake!

artist.name: Superflu
artist.bio: Superflu est né en 1994, à Lille, autour des chansons que Nicolas bidouillait sur son 4 pistes à la maison. Nicolas, Sonia, Sébastien ont tourné dans les salles et les bars du Nord. Et puis Gauthier qui faisait leur son et, à l'occasion, quelques premières parties, les a rejoints à la basse. Pas de batterie : l'essentiel des chansons repose sur les guitares et les voix. En 1996, une moitié du groupe émigre à Paris où habite déjà Gilles.

artist.name: Xenia Beliayeva
artist.bio: So that we do not misunderstand each other: Xenia Beliayeva is not an easy to enjoy sweet snack, neither as a producer nor as a DJ. Her arrangement of electronic music brings forth the demanding creatures of the night, which approve the sound as a central stylistic medium, but last but not least she adds a further sensual element with the addition of her voice. Not only "Ultra Glamour", but also "Hellraiser", to speak in her song titles. But first let�s start from the beginning.

artist.name: Minimal Man
artist.bio: ((**There are now two music artists known as Minimal Man: the original Minimal Man (aka Patrick Miller) began performing & recording in 1979 in San Francisco, CA.))   Formed by Patrick Miller in San Francisco in 1979, Minimal Man cut two albums of dark industrial punk rock ("The Shroud Of" and "Safari") before Miller relocated to Europe in 1985, where he continued as a prolific creator of music and visual art, and as a collaborator with Tuxedomoon. His four European albums are "Sex With God", "Slave Lullabyes", "Hunger Is All She Has Ever Known" and "Pure".

artist.name: Marc Romboy vs. Chelonis R. Jones
Technasia
artist.bio: Technasia, also known as Charles Siegling, is a musician and DJ raised and based in Paris. Until 2008, the group also consisted of other founding member, Amil Khan, raised and based in Hong Kong. After meeting in China during the 90's, they felt it was time to put South East Asia on the world map of electronic dance music and started their musical duo and label Technasia in 1996. In 2008, Amil took the decision to quit the duo in order to commit exclusively to raising his newly born child. He remains however until today a very strong input in all label and artist management related issues.

artist.name: Nick Curly
artist.bio:
Nick Curly began his career at the tender of age 15 when he became the resident DJ at the legendary Vibration Club in the Karlsruhe region of Germany.  Ten years later and he is now the resident DJ at the Loft Club in Ludwigshafen, as well as at the Soho Club in Mannheim,
 A regular at clubs around Germany for much of the past decade, Nick is now becoming a sought after DJ in other European territories.

artist.name: Pete Namlook & Jochem Paap / IMPS / Mano
Slam
artist.bio: 1. Slam is Stuart McMillan and Orde Meikle. Synonymous with Glasgow’s underground club scene and their sound-searching record label, soma, the duo have garnered a reputation as international DJs, accomplished recording artists and respected collaborators. Their schedule regularly takes them to clubs worldwide confirming their status as one of a handful of artists that truly shape their genre. Resident at Fabric, London and Pressure, Glasgow, they are about to undergo their 10th annual Slam tent at Scotland’s T in the Park festival (15 000 capacity).

artist.name: I:Cube
artist.bio:
At 25, Nicolas Chaix had already developed a deeply personal universe through intensive listening to Paris free radios (Aligre, Libertaire, Nova, FG), and frantic scrutinizing of all things graphic-related not mentioning his obvious frequent participation in Paris’ burgeoning rave and free party scene.
 After sending several demos to Gilb'r, at the time one of Radio Nova's main sound-programmers, Chaix signed to the newly founded Versatile and produced the label's first release, Disco Cubizm, under his I:Cube nickname.

artist.name: Loko
artist.bio: Loko is a French electro-rock artist influenced by Muse, Jeff Buckley and French writer/poet Charles Baudelaire. You can download his album "Ronces & Invisibles Fanés" here: http://glengrant2000.free.fr/loko/

artist.name: Wigald Boning
artist.bio: Wigald Boning (*1967) is a german comedian, composer, musician, moderator and journalist.

artist.name: Andrew Bird / Izmar / The Detroit Experiment / Biosphere
Quince
artist.bio: Quince is an indie rock band from Erie, Pennsylvania and also a techno producer from The Netherlands.   Quince the producer: Bram Sluiter has been releasing techno productions on the delsin and spring collective label since 2003. He first used the name 'Quinn' which he later transformed to 'Quince'. His debut full length cd is called En.vi.sion and was released in june 2007.  Quince the band: The groundwork was laid in the winter of '99 with Joe Stadler (Vocals, Guitar) and Steve Marzka (Drums), lifelong friends, puting together a band with the best intentions but did not fare well.

artist.name: Yagya
artist.bio: Icelandic producer Yagya (Aðalsteinn Guðmundsson) has been creating atmospheres through melody and sounds for more then a decade. A definitive member of the Thule Musik collective, Yagya also is known for his work as half of Sanasol and also the famed Plastic.  A student of computer science at the University of Iceland Yagya spends his free time creating music on his computer. He concentrates on atmospheres and moods and tries to reflect the beauty of the world around him in the sounds of his music.

artist.name: Sigur Ros / Pj Harvey & John Parish
Purple Haze
artist.bio: There is more than one artist represented here:  1. Purple Haze is an alias of Sander Van Doorn, and is best known for the 2005 trance smash hit Adrenaline.  2. Purple Haze is the name of a co-ed a cappella group from Northwestern University.  They were created in 1997 and have since produced 5 albums: "Three Seconds..." (1999), "Hooray for Everything" (2000), "Out of the Band" (2002), "Streaked" (2004) and "Rutherford P. Haze" (2006).  They have been featured four times on the annual national compilation "BOCA" (Best of College A Cappella).

artist.name: Stoneface & Terminal vs Rex Mundi feat. Susana
The Mystery
artist.bio: 1) The Mystery are a Female Fronted Melodic Metal/Hard Rock band from Germany (Heiligenhaus, North Rhine-Westphalia) formed in 1996. With 4 Albums under their belt, Soulcatcher was the most recent one released in 2008. Korry Schadwell - Vocals Daniel Kahn - Guitar Christian Jesko Rüther - Bass Alex Thunder Martin - Drums Stefan Weitzel - Guitar http://www.the-mystery.de/ 2)Ron van den Beuken produced The Mystery (‘Mystery’) which got a lot of popularity from DJs like Dave Pearce (BBC Radio 1) and Johan Gielen.

artist.name: Joe Garrett
artist.bio: Joe Garrett aka Temple One was born on the 24th october 1986 in the south of england. From since Joe can remember, music has always been an interest to him but it wasn’t untill around the 98-99 period where Joe really took to the sound of ‘Trance’.  Fasicnated by the sound and melodys, Joe began to collect and listen to all the trance he could get hold of… and was especially inspired by the ‘Gatecrasher’ compilations. Joe’s love for Trance grew so he decided to take it further by taking up DJing…with little experiance at the time, Joe spent most of his free days practicing.

artist.name: James Hannigan
artist.bio: Visit James Hannigan's new Myspace page here: http://www.myspace.com/jameshannigan James Hannigan is a composer with involvement in a variety of industries. Starting his career in-house at EA in the mid-1990s after a short stint in television, he later returned to freelance work, basing himself at the world famous Pinewood Studios complex in West London. Since then, James has accumulated four BAFTA nominations for music and a win with Electronic Arts in 2000.

artist.name: Fabio XB & Ronnie Play feat. Gabriel Cage
Afrojack
artist.bio: Afrojack is a Dutch DJ from Spijkenisse. Most notably, he scored his first hit in the Dutch charts in 2008 with the track Drop down (do my dance) together with The Partysquad.

artist.name: Djuma Soundsystem
artist.bio: Djuma Soundsystem is Norwegian Mikkas and Danish Lars B who both live in Copenhagen. They met first time when they DJed at one of Copenhagens longest running club nights, the Sunday club "Offline", and quickly became unseperable friends and production partners.  Mikkas and Lars’ producer career started in a for club music producers somewhat odd way; In 2001 they composed and produced the music for the ballet "Off The Record" for The Royal Danish Theatre in Copenhagen. A ballet that merged classical music with elements of new electronic genres.

artist.name: Niyaz
artist.bio: Formed in 2005, Niyaz is a band based in Los Angeles that consists of Azam Ali, Loga Ramin Torkian and Carmen Rizzo. Azam Ali and Loga Ramin Torkian were and remain members of previous groups (Vas and Axiom of Choice, respectively) and Carmen Rizzo is a solo artist, half of Povi and a prolific producer. They came together to produce an album of world-dance music. Most of the songs on the self-titled album are recorded in either Urdu or Farsi, both of which Ali speaks fluently.

artist.name: Infusion
artist.bio: Infusion is a dance/electronica group from Melbourne, Australia formed by Frank Xavier, Manuel Sharrad and Jamie Stevens. It was initially involved in the Australian rave scene, penning the anthem "Green".  The first Infusion album was released in Australia in 2000. "Phrases and Numbers" had several singles, including "Legacy" and "Starwater, It's Alright", both of which were favorites of DJ Dave Seaman who had in turn released remixes of Infusion songs on his "Audio Therapy" label.

artist.name: Tiesto & Josh Gabriel feat. Kirsty Hawkshaw
Thom Yorke
artist.bio: Thomas Edward Yorke (born 7 October, 1968 in Wellingborough, Northamptonshire, United Kingdom) is best known as the lead singer of the British alternative rock band Radiohead. He has also recorded as a solo musician. His debut album, The Eraser, debuted July 10th 2006 in the UK and July 11th in the US. Two singles were released from the album, "Harrowdown Hill" and "Analyse". The song "Black Swan" was used as the end theme to the 2006 film adaptation of Philip K. Dick's novel A Scanner Darkly. "Analyse" was also used on the end credits of the film The Prestige.

artist.name: Sgt Slick
artist.bio: Sgt. Slick is also known as Melbourne DJ Andy J and has certainly immersed himself in the world of clubs and club music over the last 10 years. In that time he has DJ'd all over the country, run a record label, remixed countless club tunes, fronted a national radio mix show, won ARIA awards, mixed top selling mix cd's, been profiled nationally on tv, and released tunes under no less than 10 aliases! Phew… Andy’s main musical outlet is his ever evolving, elusive alter ego Sgt Slick. Under that name he produced one of Australia’s finest house music moments in “White Treble, Black Bass”.

artist.name: Syntax
artist.bio: At least two artists share the name Syntax: 1) "Syntax" are a London based electronic duo formed by MIKE TOURNIER and Jan Burton in 2002. Mike Tornier is well known for his work as a 'groove technician' with 90s electronica setup "Fluke". Jan Burton (vocals), influenced by bands like "The Doors" and "Pink Floyd", calls himself 'Mr Five Piece Band and Guitars.' The first single "Pray" (2002) made top 30, was a dancefloor smasher and was leading them to a contract with the Illustrious label.

artist.name: Nocturnal
artist.bio: 1. Nocturnal is a thrash/black metal band with three members, with stage names Vomitor, Evil Avenger and Hellbastard.  They are some seriously killer thrash. The roots of NOCTURNAL go back into the year 1997 where a band called BESTIAL DESECRATION recorded their first demo. To make a long story short, BESTIAL DESECRATION split up in 2000 and the only founding member renamed the band into NOCTURNAL.

artist.name: Björk
artist.bio: Björk Guðmundsdóttir (born 21 November 1965) is an avant-garde singer-songwriter, composer, music producer, and occasional actress, whose work includes six solo albums and two film soundtracks. She is best known for her expressive vocals, broad soprano vocal range, and a diverse and eclectic musical style which incorporates influences from many different genres, including pop, alternative rock, jazz, ambient, electronic, classical, folk and trip hop.

artist.name: Lützenkirchen
artist.bio: LÜTZENKIRCHEN is the German producer Tobias Lützenkirchen. He's also known for the electronic projects LXR, LK-Pro, Bully Boys, Mike Litt, L.Y.T.Z. & Electronauts.

artist.name: Shane 54
artist.bio:
Előd Császár has been a well-known pop artist in his home country of Hungary for more than a decade. In that time he has released 10 albums either as an artist and / or producer, scored numerous nationwide hits, and done tons of remixes for a wide range of Hungarian artists. 
 Two years ago, after finishing his first international job, remixing Spandau Ballet's smash 'Gold', he decided to turn his energy entirely to the electronic dance music scene. With that 'Shane 54' was born…

artist.name: Mike Shiver vs. Mathias Lehtola feat. Andrea Britton
Danny Howells
artist.bio: There are very few DJs who stand out in the world of dance music today, but Danny Howells is without doubt one of them. From his early years of DJing at Bedrock nights in his home town of Hastings, to the 10+ hour sets in New York today, one thing remains the same - a complete love of all music. It's this passion and plenty of hard work that has helped Danny to get where he is today. It's no coincidence that he's been placed in DJ Magazine's top 20 DJs in the world for the last 3 years.

artist.name: Fiord
artist.bio: F I O R D  Smoldering from the infamous Slowburning Studios at the bottom of the South Pacific this sultry electronic duo have been writing captivating beats and storming dance floors across the globe for the past 8 years.  With the birth of their new baby FIORD there is ONE rule – “there are no rules".  This kind of thought process is quite something, as FIORD unfolds, their sounds reek of a new approach, producing a textured timeless rhythm far hotter than any branding iron ready to stamp its mark.

artist.name: Sole & Spirit ft. Ali Damasi & Jessie Colasante
Trentemoller
artist.bio: This is an incorrect tag for Trentemøller. If this non-artist appears in your charts, do last.fm and yourself a favor. Fix your artist tags.

artist.name: Paul Oakenfold
artist.bio: Paul Oakenfold (born August 30, 1963 in Greenhithe, Kent[1] England) is a world famous DJ and producer, whose works have helped define the mainstream of trance.  Not only does Paul Oakenfold produce records, but he also mixes them. In 1987 he spent several months in Ibiza with a few friends and fell in love with dance club music. Oakenfold produced "Happy Mondays' Pills 'n' Thrills and Bellyaches" before producing for U2, Massive Attack, Simply Red and New Order (to name a few), many of which were released on his label Perfecto Records.

artist.name: Way Out West ft. Trisha Lee Kelshall
Tiesto & Josh Gabriel ft. Kirsty Hawkshaw
Jamie Harrison
artist.bio: Jamie at the age of 20 is a hard working DJ who loves his music and entertaining a crowd of up for it clubbers. Going on holiday to Ibiza in 2005 , his eyes were opened to the joys of underground dance music. Along with his main love Trance Jamie came home and began to immerse himself in the music scene, clubbing every weekend and practising his djing In 2005 Jamie left school got a job working with his dad as a DJ Jamie began with small parties , and in 2006 was offered a residency on a weekly basis at 1 of Nottingham's biggest bars.

artist.name: Olav Basoski
artist.bio: Born and raised in Haarlem, The Netherlands, and a descendant of a Polish soldier, Olav Basoski (b. 14/10/1968). He started his career as a DJ at the age of 15. In 1987 he bought his first recording equipment and started to produce his own music. Olav made more than 100 records but not always under the name "Olav Basoski". He has used many pseudonyms including "Sil", "Yokiboys", "Samplitude" and "Pancake".

artist.name: Technotronic
artist.bio: Technotronic is a studio-based house music project from Belgium, formed by Jo Bogaert (a.k.a. Thomas De Quincey) in 1988. Together with Ya Kid K (born Manuela Kamosi, 1973, Zaire), he produced the hit single Pump Up the Jam which was originally intended as an instrumental. An image for the act was put together utilizing Zairian-born fashion model Felly (allegedly without her permission) as its album and single cover art and "singer" in the music video. Ya Kid K went on to provide vocals on several other Technotronic tracks.

artist.name: Micah
artist.bio: Micah is a name used by several musical projects.  In just a few short years Micah Lukasewich has built his name and sound on a solid sense of melody and rhythm that is well known throughout the progressive dance world. Producing since 1997, Micah pushes his boundaries with each new production/remix, and they are plentiful with at least one or two original tracks or remixes released per month within the year 2005 alone!.

artist.name: Human Resource
artist.bio: Human Resource was founded in 1990. Their first record "Dominator" became an European hit almost overnight. Due to this huge success, and the success of their second album "The Kicking Noise of Rotterdam", the group spends years on the road touring the globe. By the end of the 90’s, after many changes of the line up, the band ceased to exist and co-founder Guido Pernet was the only one left.  In 2004 he decided to restart the group with oldschool house legends Maurice Steenbergen and Zeno Zevenbergen.

artist.name: Angelic
artist.bio: There are two artists called "Angelic":  1) Angelic consists of Darren Tate and the husband/wife team of Judge Jules and Amanda O'Riordan.  2) Angelic (Lukas Termena) is a polish ambient/chillout producer.

artist.name: Mike Shiver vs Matias Lehtola feat. Andrea Britton
Bad Boy Bill
artist.bio: Bringing back the funk for all of us!  Bad Boy Bill is a DJ from Chicago, Illinois, USA. He plays an assortment of house music.  Bad Boy Bill began his DJ career in 1985 during the Chicago House music movement of the mid and late 80's working with Mike "Hitman" Wilson and Julian "Jumpin" Perez of the then WBMX dj mixing team known as the Hot Mix 5. Bill's popularity began to grow by dj'ing parties throughout Chicago and the Suburbs opening for the Hot Mix 5 dj's.

artist.name: Tiesto
artist.bio: Tiësto, born Tijs Michiel Verwest on 17 January 1969), is a Dutch trance DJ and record producer. He was appointed Officer of the Order of Orange-Nassau in 2004 by Queen Beatrix. He has become one of the world's most famous people in the trance and electronic dance music scenes. Although he has used many aliases in the past, he is best known for his work as DJ Tiësto. On his latest productions, however, he has dropped the "DJ" label and is now known simply as "Tiësto", an alias which is a twist on his childhood nickname.

artist.name: Federico Franchi
artist.bio: Federico Franchi is an Italian techno DJ, better known under his pseudonym Zenith DJ Name Variations: DJ Zenith, Zenith, ZJ Other Aliases: The New Frontier Y2K, Trance Nation, Vana Imago Groups: Zenith vs Avex (ZX or Zax), Zenith & Dana, Zenith featuring Energy Squad Federico started to produce techno at the age of 14 and in 1994 founded the label Trance Communications Records (TRC). The most of the early tracks produced were trance and progressive techno, but today he is known for his hardstyle tracks.

artist.name: Red Hot Chili Peppers
artist.bio: Red Hot Chili Peppers are a funk rock band who are based in Hollywood, California and was formed in 1983, in Los Angeles, California. Since 1998, the band has consisted of founding members Anthony Kiedis (vocals) and Michael "Flea" Balzary (bass) along with longtime members John Frusciante (guitar) and Chad Smith (drums). The band initially formed for a one-off support act for a friend's band, calling themselves Tony Flow And The Miraculously Majestic Masters Of Mayhem.

artist.name: UNKLE
artist.bio: UNKLE revolves around British producer and mo'wax Records head James Lavelle, working in collaboration with many others. From the sleeve notes for the latest release End Titles...Stories For Film released in July 2008, the current line-up is stated as James Lavelle and Pablo Clements, also a member of the Psychonauts. The original line-up was James Lavelle, Tim Goldsworthy (now a member of DFA) and Kudo (Major Force West, Skylab). This incarnation released several EPs and singles, usually involving collaborations with other Mo'Wax affiliated artists.

artist.name: Menno de Jong feat. Leon Bolier
Little Boots
artist.bio: Victoria Hesketh (born 1984), known professionally as Little Boots, is a British electronica musician. She sings, plays synthesizers, the Yamaha tenori-on and the stylophone. She was the former lead singer/synth player in Dead Disco. Hesketh was born in Thornton-Cleveleys near Blackpool, Lancashire and now lives in London. She attended Rossall School, Blackpool Sixth Form College and then the University of Leeds, gaining a first-class honours degree in Cultural Studies, with a dissertation on "The concept of originality in the music of Jamie Cullum".

artist.name: Enola
artist.bio: eNola is a French-speaking band.

artist.name: Wally Lopez
artist.bio: Wally Lopez has happened to be one of the best ones in our country to be one of djs and producers but reputed of the international panorama. House of the year 2001 by its success has gained the prize to the best disc “Patricia Never Leaves The House”, the “Best the Newcommer International” of IBIZA DJ AWARD 2002 (that previously I take Steve Lawler and Hernan Cattanneo), name to the best disc of year 2002 by Night Disc (Weekend Record) and chosen like BETTER DJ HOUSE by magazines DEEJAY and DJ1.

artist.name: Dash Berlin with Cerf Mitiska and Jaren
Roell Sapphire
artist.bio: Roell Sapphire (real name Roel Ruigrok) was born (1978) and raised in a small city near Rotterdam called Vlaardingen. As a kid he was already interested in music and anything that had to do with pressing buttons. When he was a little older one of his friends had bought a set of decks and it didn’t take long for Roell to get familiar with it and it turned out he was quit talented. Not very long after that roell bought his own set and records and started making his own mix tapes.

artist.name: Chris Gavin
artist.bio: Dj, Producer, A&R Red Hammer music (Progressive house, minimale techno)Marseille, France.  Chris Gavin starts music at 5. His first influences were Genesis, Toto and rock sounds from 80’s. After piano and guitar lessons, his musician career really starts as studio and concert guitarist in the south of france under managing of Barry Kingston, the artistic director of one of the most famous french artist for ages : Michel Polnareff.

artist.name: Module
artist.bio: Module is the live electronic/classical project of New Zealand Musician/producer Jeramiah Ross. Official MySpace site: http://www.myspace.com/modulenz Official website: http://www.module.co.nz

artist.name: El Provost ft. D.Ham & Tina Penni
Angelo D'onorio
artist.bio: Angelo D'onorio started in the early nineties spinning funky techno-house. He was a resident for Mazzo, Paradiso and the legendary RoXY. He played all over the country including festivals like Lowlands, Pink Pop, Mysteryland, etc. Angelo has been rewarded with three Best Dutch Dj awards, and has become one of the most popular DJ/ Producers in the country.  After releasing his underground hit “To The Floor” (supported by people like Carl Cox) Angelo travelled around the world doing gigs in Brazil...

artist.name: Nosmo vs Kris B
artist.bio: Since the duo's first production, Nosmo & Kris B have have been an international success. This first track, ”One for the Road” caught the ear of Sasha, who featured it on his Essential Mix live from Miami. The praise and support of this first release lead to the formation of their live/electronic group Grayarea; the band and single were both quickly signed to top UK label Hope Recordings. After gaining the respect of the DJ community, they quickly became fan favorites when John Digweed featured a live recording of them as a guest set on his Kiss 100 show.

artist.name: Dim Chris & Sebastien Drums ft. Polina
The Chemical Brothers ft. Noel Gallagher
Haley
artist.bio: Haley is Haley Gibby, a vocalist known for her work with house producer Kaskade on songs such as Move For Me and Step One Two, as well as the group Summer of Space.

artist.name: Soul N Spirit ft. Ali Damasi & Jessie Colasante
Consoul Trainin
artist.bio: Consoul Trainin also Knows as John Efthimiou (Jay Eff) Born In a small City Called Agrinio. In The Begiining he start with Collecting Cds And Vinyls. At the Summer of 1996 he started his first radio Show in a local radio station broadcasting house and dance music, possibly the first radio show in that way in his city. During the radio show he stars lessons in Piano for 2 years and after that he keep on learning alone.

artist.name: The Juan Maclean
artist.bio: Prior to becoming one of the most significant acts on the DFA label, John Maclean was a member of Sub Pop band Six Finger Satellite. Initially, Six Finger Satellite fit in with the remainder of the Sub Pop roster, but after one EP, they took a sharp turn into herky-jerky post-punk that was inspired by Devo, Big Black, and Suicide instead of Black Sabbath, The Stooges, and Led Zeppelin. By the time they went to record their final album, 1998's Law Of Ruins, krautrock began to play a major role, and so did LCD Soundsystem's James Murphy...

artist.name: Doves
artist.bio: Doves are an alternative rock band from Manchester, United Kingdom consisting of Jimi Goodwin (vocals, bass) and twin brothers Jez Williams (guitar) and Andy Williams (drums). They are joined on stage by Martin Rebelski (keys). They are known for their large, epic sound, which combines dovetailing guitar lines with driving percussion and a penchant for atmospherics. Unusually, both Williams brothers have also contributed lead vocals.

artist.name: Made By Monkeys feat. Darcy Conroy
Eastman
artist.bio:
Drew Eastman is a music writer and producer  Simply known as Eastman   Also produces and remixes under the names : electrikPeople, Cal Gomez, Miss Moon, Balearic Musica,K:Haus Krew, ClubRoyale,eastman&avitas.
 Born in germany in 1971 he moved to london in the early 90's to concentrate on producing music.
 in 1997 he started his first record label called E2UK Recordings and in 1998 he released his first 12" on e2uk by Miss Moon.

artist.name: Sharam feat. Daniel Bedingfield
artist.bio:
Sharam Tayebi world came to the year 1970 in the capital Tehran Iran, but grew up in the United States. From the early 90. Iran, together with other people - Alim "Dubfire" Shirazinianim, creates a well-known duo Deep Dish. 
 In autumn 2006 presented solo Sharam production, "Be The Change", dedicated to his friend, astronaut Anousheh Ansari. And in December had its premiere recording of "PATT (Part All The Time)". It is known to remix the song Eddie Murphy "Party All The Time", which in 1985 was number one in the U.S..

artist.name: The Do
artist.bio: This is an incorrect tag for the dø. If this non-artist appears in your charts, do last.fm and yourself a favor. Fix your artist tags.

artist.name: Huoratron
artist.bio: Huoratron is the musical solo project of Aku Raski, a bearded powerplant of a man. With his harsh yet incredibly danceable sounds he has been rocking dancefloors for years already. Behind the outrageous name (“Whore-a-tron”) is Aku Raski, who was involved in the retro electro group Nu Science around the turn of the century, and released his solo debut “Koottava” MCD in 2000. In year 2002 Huoratron was born, first as a project, where Raski very effectively used two Game Boy consoles to produce experimental electro.

artist.name: Grum
artist.bio: Electro/ Disco House/ Breakbeat artist from Leeds, UK.

artist.name: Keri Hilson
artist.bio: Keri Hilson (born December 5, 1982) is an American R&B singer and songwriter signed to Zone 4/Mosley Music Group/Interscope Records. She is part of a collective of writers and producers known as The Clutch.   Hilson has been writing music for other artists since 2001, including Britney Spears, Ciara, Usher, and Ludacris. Despite having made a name for herself as an arranger and background vocalist, lending her vocal talents to many of the songs she wrote on...

artist.name: John Roman
artist.bio: John Roman is a producer/DJ from London, Ontario. Blending elements of electro, hip-hop, b-more and metal, Roman strives to create the most raw and aggressive dance music possible. In 2009, Roman went from being a virtual unknown to major international blog exposure. Today his tracks are being spun in clubs (Canada, USA, Denmark, France, Russia, Taiwan etc.) and on radio (St. Louis, Berklee College Radio, University of Iowa's IC Essential Mix, Cadiz Spain's Fresh FM etc.) around the world. And the hype keeps building...

artist.name: Popof
artist.bio: http://www.myspace.com/popofheretik

artist.name: Designer Drugs
artist.bio: WEBSITE: www.designer-drugs.net MYSPACE: http://www.myspace.com/designerdrugsclubmusic FACEBOOK: http://www.facebook.com/pages/Designer-Drugs/21951474675 TWITTER: http://twitter.com/designerdrugs

artist.name: The Subs
artist.bio: Rambunctious. That's the least you can say about Belgian beatbastards The Subs. Having already released a couple of underground dance maxis - 'You Make Me Spill', 'Fuck That Shit', 'Substracktion' - over the past years, they hit it hard in 2008, with 'Kiss My Trance', a punktrance-juggernaut of a hitsingle.  The track started off as a joke, the band wanted to see how far they could push the limits of the trance-genre and get away with it.

artist.name: Who Made Who
artist.bio: This is an incorrect tag for WhoMadeWho. If this non-artist appears in your charts, do last.fm and yourself a favor. Fix your artist tags.

artist.name: Santogold
artist.bio: Santigold (born Santi White on September 25, 1976) is an alternative rock musician, songwriter and producer from Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, United States who formerly went under the stage name Santogold. She is perhaps best known for the song L.E.S. Artistes which became a hit in the UK and on American alternative radio. In February 2009, she officially changed her stage name to Santigold as a result of infomercial jeweller Santo Gold threatening legal action against White and her label Downtown Records. However, the title of her debut album will remain Santogold

artist.name: Passion Pit
artist.bio: Passion Pit is an electronic band that formed in Cambridge, Massachusetts, United States in 2007. They consist of Michael Angelakos (vocals, keyboards), Ian Hultquist (keyboards), Ayad Al Adhamy (synth, samples), Jeff Apruzzese (bass) and Nate Donmoyer (drums). Passion Pit was a vocab word used in a class Mike took in school. It's a slang word for a drive-in movie theatre where kids used to go to make out.

artist.name: IAMX
artist.bio: Some musicians are meant to be heard but not seen - merely an auditory experience and nothing more. IAMX, on the other hand, isn’t merely a band... it's an event - a full-on aural and visual attack with the dynamic and inimitable English musician and songwriter Chris Corner (of Sneaker Pimps) leading the charge. With the European marketplace going bonkers for his blend of dramatic synth-rock, darkness-infused pop, and intricately-constructed indie dance, IAMX, currently based in Berlin, has been headlining festivals in Austria, Belgium, Czech Republic, Poland, etc.

artist.name: Audiojack
artist.bio: Audiojack is an English electronic music duo comprising Jamie and Rich, who met in Ibiza in 2002. Signed to Ralph Lawson’s 20:20 Vision Recordings for their solo productions and forthcoming debut album and with remixes under their belt for labels such as Renaissance, CR2, Leftroom Limited and Lot 49, Audiojack have proved to have a unique ability to produce credible underground music whilst appealing to a wide enough audience to surpass the average sales and airplay of many of their peers.

artist.name: Chris Winch
artist.bio:
Chris Winch is:  * a producer.
 * from Dumbarton, Scotland.
 * signed to Mode2 Records.
 * crap at writing bio's  if anyone wants to make this better.
 please do.  :)

artist.name: Serenade
artist.bio: There are 3 artists with the name Serenade: 1) Serenade is a Japanese Doujin band. 2) Doom/death metal band from UK (Glasgow, Scotland). Discography: - 1994 - Let Loose The Beauty Within (demo) - 1995 - The 28th Parallel - 1996 - Let Loose the Beauty Within / The Radiance from a Star (split with Harmony) - 1998 - The Chaos They Create - 2000 - Plague of Time - 2001 - The Serpents Dance 3) Serenade is also a spanish trance producer also known as Angel Ace (Michael Delving), and is most commonly known for his single "Most Beautiful Happened.

artist.name: Balearic Session
artist.bio: Roger Pierre Shah http://www.djshah.net http://www.myspace.com/rogerpshah

artist.name: Groovezone
artist.bio:
Real Name: Frédéric De Backer.
 Name Variations: "GrooveZone" <or> "Groove Zone"

artist.name: Yeah Yeah Yeahs
artist.bio: Yeah Yeah Yeahs is a rock band formed in New York City in the late summer of 2000. The band consists of Karen Orzolek (vocals), Nick Zinner (guitar) and Brian Chase (drums). Their music melds genres ranging from new wave to art punk and garage rock using heavy guitars, synthetic sounds, and screaming, erotic, bluesy vocals. Karen O is known for her energetic, animated stage presence, complemented by her outrageously colorful costumes designed especially for her by friend Christian Joy.

artist.name: Orbital
artist.bio: Orbital is an electronic duo consisting of brothers Phil Hartnoll and Paul Hartnoll formed in London, England whose career lasted from 1989 until 2004.  They reformed in 2009. Orbital took their name from Greater London's orbital motorway, the M25, which was central to the early rave scene and party network in the South East during the early days of acid house. One of the biggest names in British electronica during the 1990s, Orbital were both critically and commercially successful, being particularly known for an element of live improvisation during their shows, a rarity with techno acts.

artist.name: Electrixx
artist.bio:
Let’s talk about Electrixx, a project, that’s born with a lot of names. So there’s Erikk aka Tiefenrausch, who met Stigma 23 aka Monolith aka Electronic  Bitch - these two guys started in the beginning 
 of 2003 a Live Project named Electrixx.  Over nine years of experiences in the music business was the reason for the excellent start with many releases in a very short time. 2004 they released their first hit “Frequenzstörung”...

artist.name: Benny Benassi vs. David Bowie
artist.bio: Marco Benassi, better known as Benny Benassi (born in Milan, 13 July 1967) is an Italian disc jockey and a euro house/electroclash artist. He usually works in studio with cousin Alle Benassi. The two also produce tracks together under the name Benassi Bros. The duo started DJing in the late 80s in their hometown, before moving to Larry Pignagnoli's Off Limits production studio in the mid 90s, creating music for various acts, including Whigfield, J.K. and Ally & Jo.

artist.name: Arisen Flame
artist.bio: Arisen Flame - Maciej Węsek was born in Koszalin (Poland) in 1990. His adventure with sounds began a long time ago when heard about electronic music. He was impressed by this style that he wanted to make his own music Day by day he have been trying to improve his skills and wide knowledge about producing. His first remix "DJ Shah ft Kelly Llorenna - Lift Me Up (Arisen Flame Remix)" which he made in summer 2008 was played by Dj Shah in his set: Music for Balearic People 015. That gave him a motivation and made feel that he wanted produce music seriously.

artist.name: Daniela Nardi
artist.bio: “Somewhere between Sting and Joni Mitchell, her musical world is fine, smooth, filled with light and human depth.” -Eric Hauswald Radio France The recent journey of Toronto-based songstress Daniela Nardi may have been a turbulent and traumatic one, but she has emerged in triumphant style with The Rose Tattoo. This musically evocative and deeply emotional work reflects life lessons learned, and fuses passion, poetic power, and musical and vocal skill, to striking effect.

artist.name: Luke Terry
artist.bio: 21 year-old Luke Terry is the brink of something big, but first impressions are of his dedication to music rather than his accomplishments within the trance scene.  A genuinely modest character, Luke will be the last person to bring his rapidly progressing music career into a conversation. Don’t get us wrong, Luke’s passion for music is obvious. It’s all he talks about. However, what he usually neglects to mention is that his music has gained support from just about every big name trance DJ on the planet. “The furthest I’ve ever been from home by myself is Birmingham,” jokes Luke.

artist.name: V-Sag
artist.bio: Vasilis Sagonas was born on January 28, 1983 in Larissa, Greece. Music has always been a part of his life, having formed a strong understanding and appreciation for it even as a young child. His two older sisters, also passionate towards music, nurtured his enthusiasm and influenced his tastes from an early age. While growing up, he studied the piano for nearly 6 years, which formalized his knowledge of music theory. In 1998, he purchased his first computer to start composing his own electronic music.

artist.name: Nic Chagall feat. Jonathan Mendelsohn
artist.bio: Claus Terhoeven aka Nic Chagall is best know one half of the German trance duo Cosmic Gate, though more recenly has found success as a solo artist, with a number of successful releases on High Contrast Recordings, most notably of which is the highly acclaimed vocal anthem "What You Need".  In his solo guise "Nic" has also remixed a number of other artists tracks, most recently of which is his beautifully techy remix of Filo & Peri's smash hit "Anthem".

artist.name: Tomcraft
artist.bio: Established as one of Europe's best Tech-House scenes hitmakers, Thomas Bruckner aka TOMCRAFT has catapulted himself this past year through various charts in different countries.  But he not only gained attention as a producer of various chart hits, he also established himself as an internationally requested Top DJ with unrivaled success since 1993.   This has been seen time and again with appearances in Germany at MAYDAY, LOVE PARADE, ENERGY...

artist.name: BWO
artist.bio: Bodies Without Organs is a Swedish electro pop group, formed in 2004. Since early 2006 they have usually been presented under the shortened name BWO. In Sweden they have enjoyed considerable commercial success throughout their career, so far notching up 13 Top 40 singles, including a Number 1 with "Temple of Love", and four Top 10 albums including a Number 1 with Halcyon Days, and have won several major Swedish music awards.

artist.name: Matan Zohar
artist.bio: UK born, Matan Zohar (aka Mat Zo, Reif, Unripelemon), still a teenager, has made a sudden appearence on the EDM scene. After 3 years of producing varied electronic music, ranging from Drum and Bass to Trance, he discovered Progressive House. This discovery lead him to being trcklisted by some of the worlds top DJs. But still a teenager, Mat Zo is at the beginning of a long career.  Since his transition into Progressive Dance music, he explored all the flavours the genre had to offer including, Electro Prog...

artist.name: Ilya Soloviev
artist.bio: During the past few years, trance music has been constantly evolving, turning inside out the old classical definition of itself. That rapid evolution has brought to the global dance scene a completely new generation of DJs and producers, challenging the legends and storming the crowds around the world. That new elite includes such now recognized names as Sean Tyas, Richard Durand, Sander van Doorn and Markus Schossow. There is still one name which has been lately widely mentioned as next big thing to emerge – Russian DJ and producer Ilya Soloviev.

artist.name: B-Cult
artist.bio: At home on the French Riviera, B.cult is a reflexion of the Cote d’Azur- cosmopolitan yet personal, carefree yet deep. His professional route began during the summer of love in 1988. Moving from the Riviera’s capital, Nice to London he became the resident of the Player, a members bar in the heart of Soho. En passant par Paris, Nantes, and Martinique in the West Indies, he is now found in Osaka, Berlin, and numerous cities throughout France.

artist.name: Jesse Garcia
artist.bio: Jesse García The momentum for Jesse Garcia as a DJ started building in 1987 when he followed his vocation and submerged in the magic world of music. To satisfy his expanding artistry, apart from working as a DJ and producer, Jesse currently feels a position of A&R at two record labels: Tribal Spain and Electric Spain Recordings.   As a result of the labels’ successful performance, and Jesse’s work as producer for the labels, Jesse Garcia has become one of the most popular DJs at the national level.

artist.name: Pezzner
artist.bio: Dave Pezzner is an accomplished and internationally respected producer and composer of various styles of electronic music. As one half of powerhouse duo Jacob London, Dave has credited over 15 vinyl releases and over 30 remixes shipped worldwide.  In addition to his work as an electronica artist, Dave is a composer for television, advertising and games and has composed works for American Idol, The Discovery Channel, Nordstrom, and T-Mobile.

artist.name: DOP
artist.bio: dOP is a brand new trio from Paris, which is made up of Clement Zemtsov (beat programming), Damien Vandesande (keyboards and horns) and last but not the least Lelli (lyrics and vocals). Having released two very highly rated EPs on Milnormodern and Circus Company in 2007, they are about to embark on a tour of Europe’s top clubs in 2008. Don't miss them on stage, as they have a unique musical approach to dance music that is all their own. With their first album "Between The Blues" slated for release in October 2008, the future is looking very bright for the Frenchmen.

artist.name: Paul Woolford
artist.bio:
Through his work as Dj, Producer, Dancefloor experimentalist, Remixer, 
 Collaborator and label owner, Paul Woolford has succeeded in bringing a rare 
 level of artistry to the world of modern dance music and in doing so, made an 
 enduring global impact. His name is synonymous with high-quality.   As we enter 2009, the projects through Woolford's Intimacy studio include Morgan Geist "The Shore" for Environ(for which Beatportal awarded a 'Bomb Alert' and DJ Mag included in their 'Killers'), The Juan Maclean "Happy House" for New York's DFA, DJ Hell feat P.

artist.name: Makam
artist.bio:
There are more artists named Makam.  1) The Indonesian Makam was formed in February ’95 at the great river valley, Solo-central Java.
 First known as SUCKER GRAVE, the band is composed of five nocturne creatures, Petrus Arcwinter (Vocals), Djomboth Androsarkas (Guitar), Zephyri (2nd Guitar), Kris (Bass), Julious Kamadath (Drums).
 There are a lot of influences from this former band in their music, but Northern Black/Death Metal was a shining beacon in the dark for their music genre.

artist.name: STL
artist.bio: There are two artists known as STL:  1) Stephan Laubner.  2) A Kenyan female singer.

artist.name: Kerri Chandler
artist.bio: Few artists in the music business reach the level of accomplishment and status that Kerri Chandler has achieved. He is known throughout the universe as one of the original creators of the deep house sound and his "basslines" are now legendary. Kerri grew up in the New Jersey area during the days of the infamous Zanzibar club with resident DJ Tony Humpries. Kerri's father was a DJ as well, which gave Kerri a rich background in the origins of the New York Underground Sound (known also as "Garage" music).

artist.name: Whirlpool Productions
artist.bio:
German trio, formed by Eric D. Clark, Hans Nieswandt and Justus Köhncke. 
 The group is active since early 90's.

artist.name: Liquid Liquid
artist.bio: Liquid Liquid was a New York City post-punk band that was active from 1980 to 1983. Their track "Cavern", from the Optimo EP, recorded by Don Hunerberg was sampled (actually played by the Sugar Hill house band) on Grandmaster Flash and Melle Mel's "White Lines (Don't Do It)". Since the band’s inception in 1980, the sounds of Liquid Liquid have haunted the clubs. The original records were pressed in very limited quantities on the 99 label, and can now fetch high prices. Though the pressings were small the impact the music has made is lasting and far reaching.

artist.name: Alexandro Jodorowsky
artist.bio: Alejandro Jodorowsky or Alexandro Jodorowsky (IPA: /a.le.ˈxan.ð̪ɾo xo.ð̪o.ˈɾov.ski/) (born February 7, 1929, in Tocopilla, Chile) is an actor, director, producer, composer, mime, comic book writer and psychotherapist born to Ashkenazi Jewish parents of Russian origin. In 1973 he adopted Mexican citizenship, but some years later he was naturalized as French. He is particularly known for having directed a handful of esoteric, surreal and shocking films, and for having written several comic books.

artist.name: Tony Lionni
artist.bio: Born Liverpool England 36 years ago. Gained an interest in music of black origin through my father who bought and occasionally dj´d....soul-disco and jazzfunk records and took me diggin for records with him from the age of about 8 years old in liverpool. First records at the age of about 7 were Say it loud black and proud by James Brown, War of the worlds and probably a stevie wonder album. Started diggin in the racks of my fathers records at the age of 14 around 85 when Hip hop was popular looking for breaks and taking regular trips to manchester Spin Inn records...

artist.name: Anton Pieete
artist.bio: Anton Pieete, all the way from Amsterdam, Holland. Anton first started getting interested in electronic music after his grandfather gave him his old synthesizer in 1997. Within a year he started making techno music and soon discovered dj'ing. With a 3 years scholar of audio design education behind him and after a couple of strong releases that received huge support by artists such as Adam Beyer, Sven Vath, Regis, Richie Hawtin and Ben Sims, he started a cooperation project with Bart Skils.

artist.name: Luke Solomon
artist.bio: Luke began his professional DJ career in 1990 having practiced hard at his Friday night residency at Middlesex University student Union, where he met cohort Justin Harris. During this period he started working at a local Barnet record shop selling house music and soul music whilst holding down a part time job as a fishmonger. Following this his career within the industry was secured whence he got a job at Freetown, then home to Robert Owens, Felix the Housecat, Jamie Principle and Masters at Work.

artist.name: Harry Axt
artist.bio: Harry Axt (real name Daniel Sternberg) came on board the Grand Petrol team in 2004, ripping it up with the first release in 2005 "Spielt Auf Der Schnorchelsäge". The 2nd release "Rettet Die Welt" came out April 2006 and has been favourite of many techno DJs and producer's around the twelve planets. Many UFO's use his music as their sole means of communication around the galaxy. Harry has been in contact with many of his Alien friends and is planning to throw many intergalactic parties in our universe.

artist.name: David Labeij
artist.bio: David Labeij (27) started dj-ing in 1998. As soon as the minimal scene emerged in Europe, David was one of the first to start promoting the "clicks and cuts" full heartedly in the Netherlands, through spinning, and organizing the infamous "Berlin Underground" nights in Amsterdam, with appearences by Richie Hawtin, Zip, Magda, Ricardo Villalobos, Sammy Dee, Tom Clark and Ata. Simultaniously he started producing his own material.

artist.name: Cajmere
artist.bio: DJ Cajmere (aka. Curtis Alan Jones / Green Velvet) is a popular DJ based in Chicago, IL. One of his most popular songs is: Percolator, which started a dance craze in Chicago called the percolator ("It's time for the percolator"). It is known nationally in clubs. For more information on DJ Cajmere check out: www.myspace.com/cajmere

artist.name: Just Two Ordinary People
artist.bio: Just Two Ordinary People are a Micro House project from Mainz, Germany, consisting of producers and DJs Tilman Schwarz and Michael Fluhr.

artist.name: Ummet Ozcan vs. W&W
artist.bio: Ummet Ozcan is a Dutch talented DJ and producer, he was born in 1982 in the middle of Holland. He started DJ'ing at his age of 14, inspired by Western and Eastern cultures (his parents are from Turkey). www.ummetozcan.com

artist.name: Luke Terry & Sean Truby pres. Northern Assault
Roger Shah & Chris Jones Pres. Openminded
Synergy
artist.bio: There are 4 Synergys. Synergy is the trademarked name used by synthesist Larry Fast for his musical endeavors. The first Synergy album, the confusingly titled Electronic Realizations for Rock Orchestra, came out in 1975, and over the next several years, Fast pushed the boundaries of electronic music and technology. In addition to his own releases, he has played on albums and tours with Peter Gabriel, Nektar, Bon Jovi and Tony Levin.

artist.name: Intro
artist.bio: There are several bands called Intro.  Intro is an American R&B trio from Brooklyn, New York. It's members are Kenny Greene, Clinton, Wike, and Jeff Sanders. Intro released two albums (for Atlantic Records) and had a string of US hits in the 1990s. Their biggest hit, "Come Inside", featured Sabrina Morrison on vocals. Intro's lead singer, Kenny Greene, died from complications of AIDS in 2001. One of their most beautiful songs and oh so true was "Funny How Time Flies." Now that I think about it.

artist.name: Christopher Lawrence & Dave Aud� feat. Jen Lasher
Lee Canning
artist.bio: Lee Canning heads up Reactor Records, a digitally based dance label which distributes and promotes dance producers all over the world. Lee began dj'ing 5 years ago and moved into production after spending many years playing guitars and drums. Moving into the trance genre Lee has produced recently some great tunes which are set to explode.

artist.name: Fischer & Miethig pres. Alliance Of Joy feat. Stine Groove
Trance Arts
artist.bio:
Artist name Tortsten Nieland, Munster Germany  Musicstyle is Electro, Techno/Trance
 Hobby is making this music, started 10 years ago

artist.name: Nick Rowland
artist.bio: Nick Rowland is a well-established hard dance producer and DJ from the UK, who started out as one half of popular hard trance duo Rowland & Wright (also known as PBS, Phatt Bloke & Slim and The Coalition). He also worked on a number of tracks with Nick Rafferty as NR².

artist.name: Tim Besamusca
artist.bio: His tracks have been played by the likes of DJ Shah, Duende, Andy Moor, Michael Splint and many more! He released tracks and remixes on labels like Bittersweet Records, Future State Records, Paria Records and 3345 Recordings. Tim's style can be described as highly energetic trance with a strong focus on melodies, harmonies and solid basslines, but don't be surprised when he serves up a progressive or even a straight up house tune!

artist.name: Lank
artist.bio: Though only 20, Lank, Peter Golyán from Hungary, has been dealing with music composition for 7 years now. Thanks to the impact made on him by folk, classical and electronic music, he has an eclectic style, his tracks range from chill-out to tech-house.  With several compositions behind, he joined Strictly!, one of Hungary’s most ambitious party series in 2002. From that year on we can talk about him as both a DJ and a producer, who is now well-known throughout the country.

artist.name: Camilo
artist.bio: Camilo Echeverri was the winner of XS Factor 2007 in Colombia. Camilo was born on the 16th March 1994 in Medellin, Colombia, but when he was 4 years old he moved to Monteria. He likes mny different styles of music, including Rock, Pop, Jazz and Rap. He likes to play in a band, use the computer and go out with his friends.

artist.name: Chris Fortier
artist.bio: Chris Fortier is an electronic music pioneer who is always listening for the future of music. He runs Fade Records based out of New York City and DJs worldwide virtually every week of the year, from Argentina to Romania to Australia to the USA. Known for his progressive house productions with collaborator Neil Kolo as Fade, and for their multi-platinum remix of Delerium's "Silence", Chris now focuses on the underground and what's next in techno, breakbeat, and house all over the globe.

artist.name: Soulfinder
artist.bio: Dublin based DJ and producer Soulfinder (Stephen Hogg) has been involved in music since he was 10, listening to all kinds of dance music ranging from Cosmic Baby to Moby. After taking up Djing as a teenager, he quickly saw himself advance to the next level, playing at most of the top radio stations and major clubs in Ireland. It wasn't until 2006 that he decided to take up producing, with noticeable result; Nick Warren quickly picked up his tracks Forte and Colour of Love, and charted the first one in his March top 10.

artist.name: Harold Heath
artist.bio:
Harold’s debut album on Urbantorque, “Hole Funk” has cemented his position as one of the finest producers on the UK house scene today.  (…"...this is one immaculate debut." 5/5  iDJ Magazine).
 The album was another in a long line of consistently high quality releases that have appeared on some of the most well respected underground house labels over the last few years; Labels including Bushwacka's Oblong, UK outfits Urbantorque, Sensei, Reverberations, Lost My Dog, Freaked, Boxa, Uhuru Beats, as well as overseas labels Detour...

artist.name: Alex Colle & Dino Baretta feat Luca G
Einmusik
artist.bio:
EINMUSIK was the 'Techno Boygroup'  has been consisting of the DJs CRANQUE and UNIQUE, together with the producer NICOL from Hamburg. The music of EINMUSIK is somewhere between Minimal Pop and bombastic Techno, without ever losing sight of what some critics might call Kitsch.  Real Name:	Samuel Kindermann
 Profile:	Einmusik is the solo project of Hamburg, Germany based producer and songwriter Samuel Kindermann.

artist.name: DJ Dozia
artist.bio: His real name is Dozia Blakey. Philly House producer. Works with Scuba and King Britt (Ovum Rec.). Owner of the label Nou Lion Recordings.  Every city's club scene has its secret weapon. New York has Joe Claussell, Toronto has Freaky Flow and Sneak, San Fran has Mark Farina and Philadelphia has Dozia Blakey. You might not know him, but his music is familiar to DJs and club people worldwide. Tunes like the hypnotic 'Pop Kulture', the smoothness of 'Steal Away' or the deepness of 'Shape Shifter', has made him a household name in the industry.

artist.name: Chicane feat. Bryan Adams
artist.bio: Co-Work between UK Electronical Musician, Composer & producer Nicholas Bracegirdle - Chicane, & Canadian Singer, Song Writer, Composer & Musician Bryan Adams 'Don't Give Up' first appeared on the Chicane album "Behind The Sun" (2000). "I had just finished mixing 'Cloud No. 9' for Bryan and had the rough riff and the chorus to 'Don't Give Up' done. I wondered just what the gravelly-voiced fella would sound like over it, and it turned out to be not such a bad idea. It became Mr Tong's essential new tune of the millennium and catapulted all the way to the top spot.

artist.name: Michael Angelo feat. Jenry R vs. Leona Lewis
artist.bio: There are at least 2 artists with the name Michael Angelo, one is an obscure American psychadelic band and the other a guitar player.  Michael Angelo Batio (pronounced "Bah-tee-ohh") is an American instrumental rock guitarist from Chicago, Illinois. He attended Northeastern Illinois University and received a bachelor's degree in music theory. Having played guitar since the age of ten, Batio is often referred to as the fastest guitar shredder of all time.

artist.name: Andy Moor vs. Lange
artist.bio: There is more than one artist with this name:  1) Andy Moor (real name Andrew Beardmore), was born in 1980. DJ/producer/remixer from Stoke On Trent, UK. This is a discography of all releases by his (Sworn, Dub Disorder, Dwight van Mann) and related projects (Indigo, Leama & Moor, Tilt, Whiteroom, Zoo DJ’s) known by me.  This DJ/Producer and musician’s talents were picked up on at 5 years old when he had his first keyboard and instantly started playing songs which he subconsciously knew.

artist.name: Eric G
artist.bio: Analog synth enthusiast and instrument builder. In the DIY network he is mostly known for his EHS-30 modular synthesizer. EriÑ's music is strongly influenced by Tangerine Dream, Klaus Schulze and Jean Michel Jarre circa Oxygene.

artist.name: Gustav
artist.bio: There are 2 artists with the name Gustav:  Gustav (Eva Jantschitsch) is a one woman band from Austria that makes music with her laptop and an assortment of instruments she plays. She uses a multitude of languages including French, German, and English. She has released her second album in May 2008.  Gustav (Pascal Vonlanthen) is a chansonier from Switzerland singing in german and french. He released 5 albums for the most part together with different bands/orchestras.

artist.name: Pedro Del Mar With Ciro Visone & Sara Pollino
Estigma
artist.bio: Roberto Reynoso (Estigma) was born the 18 of January of 1983. During his chilhood, he was influenced by electronic music. He dreamed about being a musician. His family was his main source of inspiration. He begun his career in electronic music at the age of 15 when he started participating in events, making sets with a high quality trance composed by his own productions. This productions are exceptionally good because of Estigma’s amazing ear at the time of creating new melodies. As time went by he improved his technique,experimenting with new sounds and interwaved styles.

artist.name: Paul Rigel
artist.bio: Pawel Zietkiewicz aka. Paul Rigel is 17 years old music producer, interested in making trance and progressive tunes. He discovered his first music maker, when he was 13 - it was eJay. He really liked it, but there was a real want, to release himself much more...  First person who showed him such software was Maciej Domanski - his very good friend. It was very hard in the beginning, but Maciej showed him, how the program works...

artist.name: Flack.su
artist.bio: Breakbeat producer from Budapest / Tata, Hungary. More info: http://www.myspace.com/flacksu

artist.name: Zero Cult
artist.bio: ZERO CULT is a solo project of Emil Ilyayev.  Emil was born in 1975, in the USSR and now lives in Israel. He started making music in 1994, by forming an electro-acoustic music band.  In 1997, Emil teamed up with his friend Alex and created a new synth-hard-rock project, called "Legion of Foreigners ".  They recorded a demo CD and received excellent feedback.  In 1999, each one went to his own direction, and Emil decided to get into the electronic scene and started producing music in his home studio.

artist.name: Gabriel & Dresden feat. Molly Bancroft vs Wippenberg
Flash Brothers
artist.bio: The Flash Brothers are a group of Israeli brothers who produce electronic music. They consist of Ruven, Ilan and Shmuel Flaishler. They have featured releases on labels such as Hooj Choons, Silver Planet, and Bedrock Records. Their singles have been featured on numerous DJ mixes, such as those by John Digweed, Dave Seaman, and James Holden. They have a weekly Radio-Show on Frisky Radio, called House of Flash Their song 'Amen (Don't Be Afraid)' made it onto the H&M in-store playlist in 2004.

artist.name: Beyonce
artist.bio: Please fix your tags/vote for correction. It's Beyoncé, not Beyonce. Don't get it twisted.

artist.name: Ruff Driverz Presents Arrola
artist.bio: Ruff Driverz were the aliases of British DJ / remixers Brad Carter and Chris Brown. The duo also recorded under the names 2000BC and Transit.  Between 1997 and 2000 the duo scored a string of dance hits in the UK. But two of their biggest hits in that country were also major smashes on the Billboard Hot Dance Club Play chart in the United States in 1999: The flamenco-inspired "Dreaming" (featuring Katherine "Arrola" Ellis and credited as "Ruff Driverz Presents Arrola"), which peaked at #20, and "Waiting For The Sun," which was their highest charting record, peaking at #2.

artist.name: Atrium
artist.bio:
1- Atrium was an Italo-Disco project-alias created by Giorgio Conti. Several artist put their voices on the songs by Atrium such as Giacarlo Pasquini, Gino Caria and Claudio Magnani.
 Musical Team: Giacomo Maiolini, S. Dall'Ora and Laurent. G. Newfield.
 Singles: "Funny Dancer", "Going Crazy", Over & Over", "Dr. Jeckyll", "Week-End" or "Jolly Dancer".  2- Atrium are House music production supremos Steve Mac and Paul Harris.

artist.name: Empire Of The Sun vs Axwell
Crystal Fighters
artist.bio:
We are Crystal Fighters.
 We make fast dance music with Basque instruments, synthesizers and our voices.
 We play new material at every show, come and see us live.  From somewhere high above the old hills of our home,
 The love will come to conquer.  
 * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * * *   “there is nothing more alive or energetic than Crystal Fighters” Dazed & Confused  "Single most exciting live show in dance music" Mixmag  “Crystal Fighters stand out as one of the most interesting prospects by a mile– something genuinely new sounding” NME

artist.name: Ash
artist.bio: There are at least three bands called Ash: 1) Ash are an alternative rock band that formed in Downpatrick, Northern Ireland in 1992. The media originally pegged Ash's music as britpop when the band first found mainstream success. The current line-up of the group is as follows:Tim Wheeler (vocals and guitar), Mark Hamilton (bass guitar) and Rick McMurray (drums). Ash's full-length debut "1977" was released in 1996 and followed 1994's mini album "Trailer".

artist.name: Atom
artist.bio: Most famous for the classic progressive pioneering trance hit, You're Not Alone, in 2001/2002 and now the new 20 single release from the CD Atom-You're Not Alone, Atom brought a new look and imitated sound to the trance/dance scene. Being one of the first male singers in a female dominated market, and against the record companies wishes, he even added rock guitars, now heard all over modern dance music. Atom has produced and written for many, many artists.

artist.name: Ashley Wallbridge and Andy Moor vs. Nadia Ali
OMID 16B
artist.bio: Omid Nourizadeh A South Londoner with Persian roots and founder of the London-based record labels Alola (1993), Disclosure (1994) and Sexonwax (2002). At first releasing singles by himself, he then moved on to releases from other artists such as Pete Moss, House of 909, Loudeast, Charles Webster, YMC, Vince Watson, NAV, and Mr C. One of his earliest hits was "Snow" under the alias ORN, which got licensed to BMG and became a club hit.

artist.name: KJ Sawka
artist.bio: Kevin Joseph Sawka was born October 10, 1977 in Seattle, Washington. Kevin attended Heritage Christian School up until 4th grade, when he moved to Kenmore Elementary School. At an early age Kevin was involved in sports, as alot of young people are, excelling in baseball and soccer. Due to an accident with an Exacto knife Kevin decided to sideline his catchers mitt and exchange it for drums.His middle school years were spent at Lake Stevens Middle School for 7th-8th grades and 9th grade at Skyview Middle School.

artist.name: Rasmus Faber ft. Emily McEwan - Are You Ready (Jerome Isma
Marco V feat Kashassi
artist.bio: From well-known tracks like 'Indicator', 'Simulated' and 'Godd' through to present-day productions such as 'Second Bite', 'More Than A Life Away' and 'Red Blue Purple', and his successful updates of widely regarded classics such as 'Café Del Mar' and 'Loops & Tings Relooped', Marco V's discography is considerably extensive. On the decks he develops his personal style, incorporating anything from electro to techno.

artist.name: David Akermanis
artist.bio: David Akermanis is an up and coming producer/DJ, belonging to the new breed of talented producers making his hometown of Toronto, a centre of excellence in house music.   He's already shown he has top productions and garnered support from Matt Darey, Enesto vs. Bastian, Solarstone, Tom Colontonio, Airbase and Gabriel Lukosz of Basic Perspective.   His unique progressive sound stands out amungst the crowd and David is quickly carving out his own niche in the world of house music.

artist.name: Schubert
artist.bio: Franz Peter Schubert (January 31, 1797 – November 19, 1828) was an Austrian composer. He wrote some 600 lieder, nine symphonies (including the famous "Unfinished Symphony"), liturgical music, operas, and a large body of chamber and solo piano music. He is particularly noted for his original melodic and harmonic writing.  Schubert was born into a musically knowledgeable family, and received formal musical training through much of his childhood.

artist.name: Moony
artist.bio: There is more than one artist with this name:  1) Moony (real name Monica Bragato) is a musician from Italy known for the many dance tracks coming from her debut album Lifestories. Among the notable singles from the album are "Dove (I'll Be Loving You)", "Acrobats", and "Flying Away".  Raised in Venice, Moony was first noticed singing in the Venetian club scene and was tapped to do vocals for a number of songs by DJ and producer Cristiano Spiller.

artist.name: Telepopmusik
artist.bio: Télépopmusik is a French electronic music group with three members. The group's first album was Genetic World, and several singles from the album have been released since. The group's second album, Angel Milk was released in 2005. According to Telepopmusik's official MySpace page, their next album will be available in the fall of 2008. [1]  Télépopmusik consists of musicians Fabrice Dumont (bassist of the pop band Autour de Lucie), Stephan Haeri (also known as 2 square for his solo projects), and Christophe Hetier.

artist.name: Fedde Le Grand
artist.bio: Fedde le Grand's adventure began when he started to spin at the Danssalon in Eindhoven, one of Holland’s finest clubs at those days. He has fulfilled his residency on Sundays for more than two years, where he performed for the always critical gay crowd who only expected the best every Sunday.  After been there…done that, his career took off, and now Fedde performs all over The Netherlands at the best clubs, and club nights like: Sneakerz at Panama (Amsterdam), HouseQuake at Escape (Amsterdam), the award winning Love Boat (Amsterdam)...

artist.name: Android
artist.bio:
Android is Cristian Reyes main project, formerly KampfProject (2003-2004) and Kampf (1991, 2000). Android's music is kinda minimalistic with some IDM elements. His sound tries to mix Lo-Fi and analog synths. Rhythm section and sequencies are based in percussive sounds gotten from synths and "vintage drums". The sampling process is intended to achieve a sound as analog as possible.
 On March, 2003 under KampfProject moniker he develops some new material with Cristhian Toro.

artist.name: Trance Arts feat. Claire Willis
artist.bio:
Artist name Tortsten Nieland, Munster Germany  Musicstyle is Electro, Techno/Trance
 Hobby is making this music, started 10 years ago

artist.name: Mikas
artist.bio: Young Michael Anguelov’s interest in music began at age 12. He played the clarinet, drums, and guitar.
