He pictured himself a rock superstar, banging his guitar into tiny pieces after stringing a screaming rip. But his rock star dreams were overshadowed the day he fell upon the hypnotic draw of dance music.   Already an accomplished musician, the move to mixing was a smooth transition. At the fresh age of 20, he invested in turntables and a mixer, and a few years later found a venue to display his talents, managing a club in Quebec City.

artist.name: DK Project
artist.bio: David Bugyi (a.k.a. daveB) and Steven Skerlec (a.k.a. Kaspa) are the boys behind DKProject. The first contact with trance music was in the early years of the new millenium. The track was a remix of Ayumi Hamasaki's M by Above and Beyond. After a few years of listening to trance, they came across a few sequencer programs and began to produce. The early stage tracks were simple melodies, but after the years they gained some experience.

artist.name: Unity
artist.bio: There is more than one artist with this name: 1. The original Orange Country straight edge band, heavily influenced by Washington D.C.'s Minor Threat. Guitarist, Joe D. Foster, went on to play in No For An Answer and later formed the band Ignite. Pat Longrie and Pat Dubar, drummer and singer respectively, went on to form the influential Uniform Choice. Pat Dubar - Vocals Joe D. Foster - Guitar John Lowe - Bass Pat Longrie - Drums 2. Unity is a Christian rock band from Karis, Finland. http://profile.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=user.viewprofile&friendID=130002830

artist.name: Thomas Gold feat. Lee Cabrera
artist.bio: Having topped the beatport charts with his remix of Delerium Silence in summer 2008, Thomas Gold has achieved yet another big success in the international electro-house scene with “Everybody Be Somebody” and “Losing My Religion” and is causing quite a stir with two brand-new remixes for his buddies Alex Gaudino and Antoine Clamaran. So, what can we expect in 2009 from Thomas Gold?  “I love to produce with other artists to get new and fresh ideas. It´s always fun and innovative. But I feel now that I have to focus a bit more on my own stuff.

artist.name: Oriol Farre feat. Xavi Alfaro [Tune Of The Month]
Jaimy
artist.bio: Back in the day, Jaimy was one of the first producers who succeeded in making a living with house music.  He obtained his first record deal at the age of 19 and being adopted by Amsterdam’s Outland Records, just before their period of grandeur, Jaimy was responsible for a lot of the music coming out of the Outland studios. He collaborated with many Dutch DJs, and produced most of the other dance floor smashes.

artist.name: Joey V [Tune Of The Month]
artist.bio: Joey V is a 22 year old DJ & Producer, but a DJ & producer that goes uncompared to others! He is what they call an obsessed DJ. His obsession began at just 13 years of age where he would spend almost every minute of the day over his decks determined to teach himself to mix and learn new things, This has lead to him picking up a completely unique style of DJing and flawless trickery which has to been seen live to be fully appreciated.

artist.name: Mark Sherry feat. James Allen feat. Stua
artist.bio: Raised in the Ayrshire coast of Scotland... Mark Sherry has been burning through the dance industry for well over a decade. Working with local talent (the Casio Brothers) through to international success with Public Domain. Mark has only recently started releasing under his own name. With appearances at Trance Energy, Defqon and many more international stages Mark keeps true to his style of progressive trance with a hard hitting edge. From small influentual venues to the worlds largest dance arenas Mark Sherry is a name to look for on the billing.

artist.name: Re:Locate feat. Mark Sixma
artist.bio: There are at least 2 artists known as Relocate: 1) Re:Locate is an alias of Paul Moelands, young trance producer, also known as Octagen, Palanya and Scratch Bandicoot. Rocketed into the trance scene late 2003, Paul Moelands has become one of the leading upcoming producers that trance land has to offer nowadays! Both "Re:Locate – Waterfall" and "Octagen & Arizona (his project with Thomas Bronzwaer) – Starburst" releases were shot into orbit and picked up by every self respected DJ around!

artist.name: Thr3shold feat. Detune
artist.bio: Agustin Viegas (Mr V, Austin V) a talented producer, and Diego Presas (DJ Deathmind) who was already performing as a professional DJ and producing his own parties Riseup! meet each other in 2002. Both guys with huge musical background and a similar taste in music showed up an instant chemistry that would carry them into making Thr3shold.  As a result, they started an innovating mixture of styles like Trance, Uplifting, Tech, Hard & Psy.

artist.name: Dash Berlin feat. Matt Cerf feat. Jaren feat. Mitiska
artist.bio: Dash Berlin's latest tune is called "Man On The Run" The dub is featured in episode 301, 302 and 304 of A State Of Trance with Armin van Buuren and on the Global DJ Broadcast from June 7th 2007 with Markus Schulz. The vocal mix is featured in episode 311 and 312 (It has been voted as "Future Tune" from the users of www.trance.nu) of A State Of Trance, and on the Global DJ Broadcast from August August 9th.

artist.name: Sander Van Doorn feat. Robbie Williams
artist.bio: The astonishing rise of Sander van Doorn isn’t really so astonishing really when you consider the staggering amount of talent flowing through his veins. In just 5 years he’s clocked up more hit records, dance floor destroyers and sell out gigs than most DJs do in a lifetime, and his journey is still in its infancy.  He’s a Dutchman, which in this day and age is nothing unique, for Sander is among many from the Netherlands blessed with musical genius, a genius that continues to take the world by storm.

artist.name: Moi Caprice feat. Nicka
artist.bio: Danish 4-piece indie band, moi Caprice, rose to underground fame when they hit the no. 1 slot on the Danish Alternative Chart as the first unsigned band ever. The highly dramatic "The Sun & the Silence" held the top slot for 3 consecutive weeks at the end of 1997, proving the band among the most promising of the dawning Danish underground. Still situated far from any music scene, in the farthest reaches of Northern Jutland, moi Caprice took to the road playing some of the largest scenes and festivals in Denmark before signing with the underground label Lidocaine at the end of 1998.

artist.name: Lizzy Pattinson
artist.bio: Elizabeth "Lizzy" Pattinson is a British singer and songwriter. She has had three top twenty hits in the UK.  Lizzy has performed with Aurora and Milk & Sugar. She sang also the 2004 No. 1 Billboard Hot Dance Club Play track "Let The Sunshine In." She's the sister of actor Robert Pattinson and Victoria Pattinson and attended Wimbledon High School.

artist.name: DJ Fist feat. Carlos Tejada
artist.bio: This Colombian DJ began his musical career at the age of 17. In 1992 DJ Fist joined the first all electronic radio station in Colombia "La X 91.9 FM" Fist took an interest in producing after having heard the tribal sounds made by house authorities such as Ralphi Rosario, Peter Rahoufer, Junior Vasquez, and Danny Tenaglia, whose tracks created the bases of the sound Fist was looking for to produce.

artist.name: Oceanlab feat. Above & Beyond
artist.bio: OceanLab is a vocal trance group formed in London, England in 2000, consisting of Jonathan Grant, Tony McGuinness, Paavo Siljamäki (Above & Beyond) and the vocal talents of Justine Suissa. Discography: Upcoming Singles Albums 2009-06-07: Sirens Of The Sea Remixed 2008-07-21: Sirens of the Sea Singles 2001-08-09: Clear Blue Water 2002-09-11: Sky Falls Down 2003-04-07: Beautiful Together 2004-02-02: Satellite 2008-04-07: Sirens of the Sea 2008-07-07: Miracle 2008-11-14: Breaking Ties

artist.name: Robert Nickson feat. Daniel Kandi
artist.bio: If you visit a club it probably won't be too long before you are hearing one of Robert's productions. Robert is currently one of the most highly sought after producers of the moment. His productions also appear on nearly every dance CD that hits the shops. There's no escaping this guy, he's here to stay.  Robert's background is a multi-national affair with his Father from England and Mother from Norway.

artist.name: Klaas
artist.bio: Klaas’ fascination of putting on electronic sounds was aroused within the Cologne club scene in the late 90ies: He debuted with several releases and approached ambitiously the art of mixing sounds. Soon after, the open-minded Cologne based DJ moved forward to the energetic electro-sound producing his first electro-vinyl Slip & Slide with Micha Moor for the Cologne label Scream and Shout Recordings, which paved directly the way onto the playlists of reputable DJ celebrities. From then on, there was no way to stop him making a go of his passion.

artist.name: Kristine W.
artist.bio: Kristine W – a fixture on the dance scene since her 1996 hit-packed, Rollo produced debut album, “Land of the Living” – is a rare blend: a showy singer with astounding vocal fire power and a confessional songwriters ethic. Her new project, “The Power of Music” is a full length album comprised of 16 tracks – 12 brand new songs plus her last 4 Billboard 1 hits – “Walk Away”, “The Boss,” “Never” and “Love is the Look.” “The Power of Music” will be available June 2009.

artist.name: Starchaser
artist.bio: STARCHASER is a THE CLUBBERS' artist Trademark and Productiuon  The Clubbers Productions started in 1995 in a little town near Milan.  They produced first demos and started contacting record companies. In January 1998 they manage to get their first records released. In 1999. the first satisfactions: two of their productions were included in some techno compilations. In the same year, they conceived the project BLACK SPIDER.

artist.name: Marcus Schossow feat. Thomas Saqstad
artist.bio: The years have passed since Marcus released his first single "Stockholm" in 2003. The huge hit supported by ALL major top jocks, was Marcus' major debut into the scene.  When Marcus was 15 years old he entered a local DJ competition, completely crushing swedens no. 1 DJ, Marcus was hailed as THE biggest upcoming talent in Sweden. After that Marcus wanted to touch people with his own productions aswell. So he started producing his own tracks.

artist.name: Andrew Bennett feat. DJ Tatana
artist.bio: Andrew Bennett is one of the most talked about up-and-coming artists on the dance scene at the moment. Over the past two years he has released various tracks and remixes, which have received world wide recognition and praise. But Andrew Bennett is anything but a newcomer on the scene: he has been spinning the decks since 1996, he is a resident DJ at the acclaimed “Trance Nation” events and has secured regular DJ slots both in and outside of Germany, like in world-renowned clubs as “Space” on Ibiza as well at the biggest events and festivals.

artist.name: Matt Cerf feat. Jaren feat. Mitiska
artist.bio: DJ/Producer Matt Cerf started his career in 1998 after attending a rave during his Junior year at McGill University, in Montreal, where he was studying Agricultural Engineering. He quickly dropped schooling to study the ins and outs of music production on his own. In 2000, he and three friends created the group Second Sun and Matt's first track, Empire, quickly caught the attention of DJ Paul Van Dyk. Empire was signed to Paul's label, Vandit, and Second Sun appeared on Quebec’s version of MTV, Music Plus.

artist.name: Bart Claessen feat. Dave Schiemann
artist.bio: Barthezz (Bart Claessen) was born in the Netherlands on January 22nd, 1980, always loved music and got his first piano lessons at the age of seven. Impressed by electronic music at the end of the nineties, he worked hard during high school to buy his first studio equipment: a synth, a sampler, an Atari computer and a small mixer. With this equipment, he changed the attic of his parental house into a small studio and there it all began..

artist.name: PQM vs. The Killers
artist.bio: PQM (real name Manuel Napuri) is a producer who has released records on labels such as Yoshitoshi and Renaissance. He is probably most well known for his single, You Are Sleeping, which has been featured on multiple compilations, such as James Holden's Balance 005 release and Deep Dish's Global Underground: Toronto DJ mix. It has also been remixed by Luke Chable.

artist.name: Dimitri Andreas
artist.bio: Dimitri has been absorbing and sweating music from a very early age. His first releases date from his ending revolting puberty and got well tasted by the big techno names like Carl Cox, Mark Broom, Luke Slater and many others. His first stepping-stone was the release of his 'Panther EP' on the prestigious and artistically highly appreciated label MUSICMAN. The EP sold well, received many positive critics and got him invitations to DJ at major European parties like I Love Techno.

artist.name: Tikaro, J. Louis & Ferran feat. Clarence
Alpinestars
artist.bio: The Alpinestars: Richard Woolgar and Glyn Thomas, two Manchester based artists with a fetish for electricity, presenting their second long player, White Noise. A multi-dimensional amalgam of middle-European influences, it comprises 11 tracks of driving machine-funk, moody elegies and class-A disco music. Depeche Mode, Giorgio Moroder, Phoenix, and New Order are some of the people who it may remind you of. Quite possibly at the same time.

artist.name: Shur-i-kan
artist.bio: Shurikan aka Tom Szirtes'  is a musician/composer/keyboardist from London.   As a young man playing keyboards with various jazz, funk and rock bands around London, Tom was working on his own material on the side. At his first solo gig he was discovered by renowned producer Tom Middleton (Jedi Knights, Global Communication) who released Shurikan's debut track "Niomi's Dream" on the Jedi's Night Out compilation for Mixmag.

artist.name: Matthew Dear
artist.bio: In the span of a few years, Texas-born, Detroit-based Matthew Dear has established himself as one of America's foremost minimal techno producers. Dear and Ghostly International founder Sam Valenti IV met while the two were attending the University of Michigan at Ann Arbor. In 1999, Dear collaborated with ghettotech pioneer Daisha on Ghostly's inaugural 12", "Hands Up for Detroit." In 2001 he released "Irreparably Dented," his debut 12" on Ghostly International's more dancefloor-oriented Spectral Sound subsidiary.

artist.name: CPM
artist.bio: Only few producers in the dance music industry have the ability to make everyone of his tracks sound and feel completely different. Blendind styles and grooves, Christian has been consistently releasing variated music from 2005 until today under his alias CPM, Christian Malloni and The Candy Dealers (With house music rising star Jay West).  His first work as CPM (Dirty Mellow EP) was released on Proton Radio´s own label, being Proton one of the most important internet radios on the electronic scene.

artist.name: Fedde Le Grand vs. Kid Cudi
artist.bio: Fedde le Grand's adventure began when he started to spin at the Danssalon in Eindhoven, one of Holland’s finest clubs at those days. He has fulfilled his residency on Sundays for more than two years, where he performed for the always critical gay crowd who only expected the best every Sunday.  After been there…done that, his career took off, and now Fedde performs all over The Netherlands at the best clubs, and club nights like: Sneakerz at Panama (Amsterdam), HouseQuake at Escape (Amsterdam), the award winning Love Boat (Amsterdam)...

artist.name: Alan Connor vs. Mike Melange
artist.bio: From a musical family, Alan began singing and songwriting in his early teens and initially cut his teeth with several established local bands before forming the duo Equator with fellow Yorkshire musician Darren Fox. Together they signed a US record deal that provided them with useful insight into the music business, if not a hit record. Ultimately however, Equator was consigned to history and Alan stepped out on his own.

artist.name: PPK
artist.bio: PPK (also known as ППК in Cyrillic letters) were a trance duo hailing from Russia, the members' names being Sergei Pimenov and Alexander Polyakov. Their most famous single, ResuRection was available to download freely on mp3.com for about a year - millions of people downloaded it, this caused them to sign a contract to Paul Oakenfold's Perfecto label. The song was based around the melody of the theme to the 1979 Russian (Soviet) film 'Siberiade'. It has had many remixes to date and is still a widely played classic dance track.

artist.name: Mr. Hudson feat. Kanye West
artist.bio: Correct your tags please. "Mr Hudson" - that's right. Mr Hudson, (formerly Mr Hudson & The Library) is a band based in London, England whose members hail from both that city and Birmingham. This duality was the inspiration for the title of their debut album A Tale of Two Cities, which was released on 5 March 2007.[1] They are signed to music producer Kanye West's G.O.O.D. Music label & Mercury Records.

artist.name: Ron van den Beuken
artist.bio: Ron van den Beuken is a Dutch Trance DJ. He studied Law and at the University of Maastricht. His first electronic track was "C'est Muzique". He got known for artists projects like Floyd, The Mystery and the great synergy remix of the Coldplay track "Clocks" under the pseudonym Clokx. His tracks like "Timeless", "Endless", "Sunset" and "Find a Way" are well known to fans of club music all over the world.

artist.name: Rank 1 vs. Gareth Emery
artist.bio: They’re one of Europe’s most established and respected dance acts. Their debut release, ‘Airwave’ was the first Dutch record ever to hit the #1 position in the European dance charts and went Top 10 in the UK. Over the last 8 years, they have continued to pack the record boxes of world’s A-list spinners with floor-monsters like ‘Symsonic’, ‘Such is Life’, ‘Breathing’ & ‘Life Less Ordinary’… Performing to tens of thousands of dance fans every week, they play at some of the biggest dance events in the world. Meet Piet Bervoets & Benno de Goeij - better known as Rank 1!

artist.name: Three Drives vs. Gareth Emery vs. Delerium
artist.bio: Erik de Koning, alias Enrico, has been producing music for 12 years now and is famous for "WaterVerve" (in some countries also called WaterWave). However, one is probably most impressed by his work under the name of Three Drives (co-productions with Ton TB)."Greece 2000", "Sunset on Ibiza", "Carrera 2" and "Air Traffic" are just a few titles that did very well, especially in the UK.  Erik has produced an enormous amount of tracks but how did it all start? His musical career started in 1990. He used to work, together with his buddy Mark van Dale, at Mid-town records.

artist.name: Arnej vs. Above & Beyond feat. Zo� Johnston
artist.bio: Music first claimed a presence in Arnej’s life during his childhood, which saw him endure the musical taste of his father. The various genres of music continuously bumping in his household conspired to turn him off from music and drive him towards the more conventional interests of a small town kid.  Music regained weight in Arnej’s life at the tender age of 14, when an early computer-composed electronica track snagged his interest.

artist.name: Gareth Emery vs. Above & Beyond pres. OceanLab
artist.bio: Ranked at number 23 in the world in the 2008 DJ Mag Top 100 Poll (up 8 places from 2007) and tipped by both Paul van Dyk and Ferry Corsten as a future star, Gareth Emery is well on his way to becoming a fully paid up member of the global DJ elite. His podcast (The Gareth Emery Podcast) has fans all around the world and is regarded as one of the most consistent and exciting podcasts around. In 2009, Gareth Emery launched his own label - Garuda and has released tracks such as Exposure, Metropolis etc.

artist.name: Sunlounger feat. Kyler England vs. Jakatta feat. Seal
artist.bio: There are two artists with the name Sunlounger: 1. An alias of German producer, electronic composer and DJ Roger Shah, also known as DJ Shah. 2. An earlier incarnation of rock band G.U. Medicine. 1. Roger Shah has released a number of tracks as Sunlounger, such as "White Sand" in 2006 and "Aguas Blancas" in 2007. The first Sunlounger album, "Another Day On The Terrace" was released in 2007, and comprises two CDs, "Chill" and "Dance".

artist.name: Gareth Emery vs. Delerium vs. Andy Moor & Ashley Wallbridge feat. Meighan Nealon
artist.bio: Ranked at number 23 in the world in the 2008 DJ Mag Top 100 Poll (up 8 places from 2007) and tipped by both Paul van Dyk and Ferry Corsten as a future star, Gareth Emery is well on his way to becoming a fully paid up member of the global DJ elite. His podcast (The Gareth Emery Podcast) has fans all around the world and is regarded as one of the most consistent and exciting podcasts around. In 2009, Gareth Emery launched his own label - Garuda and has released tracks such as Exposure, Metropolis etc.

artist.name: John O'Callaghan feat. Sarah Howells vs. Dave Gahan
artist.bio: 1) John O'Callaghan is an Irish DJ, mainly producing electronic music. He also produces music under the alias of Joint Operations Centre, Mannix and Stenna. He has also collaborated with fellow Discover artists such as Bryan Kearney, Neal Scarborough (as Inertia), Thomas Bronzwaer (as Lost World) and Greg Downey. His best known track is Big Sky, done with vocalist Audrey Gallagher, formerly of the 90's alt-rock band Scheer.

artist.name: Duderstadt vs. Store 'N' Forward vs. Above & Beyond feat. Richard Bedford
artist.bio: At the age of 15 and 13 Dirk and Marco Duderstadt discovered a hobby and indeed a talent: making music. As the hobby can be very expensive, the two had to fight their way as LJ´s and DJ´s through several clubs. They finally found a lasting home in the Old Daddy in Haltern.  At the beginning of 1998 they had with some effort saved for a little studio in which they produced the herbinger track, which in turn would end up fliping their lives upside down.

artist.name: Bissen vs. Ronski Speed feat. Sir Adrian
artist.bio: Georg Bissen is a German national living in New York. He has written and collaborated on well over a thousand pieces of music and projects in his still brief professional music career. Bissen got his start in the music business six years ago, when he began working in New York City as a composer and engineer in the music for advertising industry. He formed his own music production company MetaTechnik soon after, which now boasts two offices in New York and Los Angeles.

artist.name: John O'Callaghan feat. Sarah Howells vs. Lost Tribe
artist.bio: 1) John O'Callaghan is an Irish DJ, mainly producing electronic music. He also produces music under the alias of Joint Operations Centre, Mannix and Stenna. He has also collaborated with fellow Discover artists such as Bryan Kearney, Neal Scarborough (as Inertia), Thomas Bronzwaer (as Lost World) and Greg Downey. His best known track is Big Sky, done with vocalist Audrey Gallagher, formerly of the 90's alt-rock band Scheer.

artist.name: Tiesto vs. Markus Schulz vs. Andy Moor
artist.bio: Tiësto, born Tijs Michiel Verwest on 17 January 1969), is a Dutch trance DJ and record producer. He was appointed Officer of the Order of Orange-Nassau in 2004 by Queen Beatrix. He has become one of the world's most famous people in the trance and electronic dance music scenes. Although he has used many aliases in the past, he is best known for his work as DJ Tiësto. On his latest productions, however, he has dropped the "DJ" label and is now known simply as "Tiësto", an alias which is a twist on his childhood nickname.

artist.name: Bissen vs. First State feat. Anita Kelsey
artist.bio: Georg Bissen is a German national living in New York. He has written and collaborated on well over a thousand pieces of music and projects in his still brief professional music career. Bissen got his start in the music business six years ago, when he began working in New York City as a composer and engineer in the music for advertising industry. He formed his own music production company MetaTechnik soon after, which now boasts two offices in New York and Los Angeles.

artist.name: Christian Cambas feat. The Static Age
artist.bio: Christian Cambas is a producer/DJ from Athens, Greece. Being involved in music production professionally since 1998, he has shown his many production facets ranging from Drum&Bass to straight up Progressive House. As a DJ while living in the U.S. and attending the Berklee College of Music, Christian was surrounded by House music, although he was primarily playing and producing Drum&Bass at the time.

artist.name: Super8 & Tab vs. OceanLab
artist.bio: See Super8 & DJ Tab

artist.name: Nadia Ali vs. Orkidea vs. Perpetuous Dreamer
artist.bio: As with any great era of music, there are always a handful of tracks that can be considered genre defining. For dance music -from the late 90's to the new millennium - there were only a select few tracks that caught fire around the world. Most of these tracks came from the godfather's of the recent dance music explosion: We're talking about tracks like Underworld's "Born Slippy," and The Chemical Brother's "Block Rockin' Beats.

artist.name: Bissen vs. Albert Vorne
artist.bio: Georg Bissen is a German national living in New York. He has written and collaborated on well over a thousand pieces of music and projects in his still brief professional music career. Bissen got his start in the music business six years ago, when he began working in New York City as a composer and engineer in the music for advertising industry. He formed his own music production company MetaTechnik soon after, which now boasts two offices in New York and Los Angeles.

artist.name: Myon vs. Ronski Speed feat. Aruna
artist.bio: There are 3 artistes named Myon: 1. Myon is an artist name variation of Hungarian trance producer Márió Égető (Mÿon), better known as Orange Project. The alias Mÿon was created to define a separate style in his music and was first introduced with the progressive vocal trance song called Albion. This track contains a reversed vocal sample of US group Andain's 2003 progressive vocal trance hit Beautiful Things. Albion was released in December 2007 from the Dutch trance label In Trance We Trust along with a radio edited version of the original track.

artist.name: Tomcraft vs. Adam White & Andy Moor pres. Whiteroom
artist.bio: Established as one of Europe's best Tech-House scenes hitmakers, Thomas Bruckner aka TOMCRAFT has catapulted himself this past year through various charts in different countries.  But he not only gained attention as a producer of various chart hits, he also established himself as an internationally requested Top DJ with unrivaled success since 1993.   This has been seen time and again with appearances in Germany at MAYDAY, LOVE PARADE, ENERGY...

artist.name: Tomcraft vs. The Doppler Effect
artist.bio: Established as one of Europe's best Tech-House scenes hitmakers, Thomas Bruckner aka TOMCRAFT has catapulted himself this past year through various charts in different countries.  But he not only gained attention as a producer of various chart hits, he also established himself as an internationally requested Top DJ with unrivaled success since 1993.   This has been seen time and again with appearances in Germany at MAYDAY, LOVE PARADE, ENERGY...

As a DJ while living in the U.S. and attending the Berklee College of Music, Christian was surrounded by House music, although he was primarily playing and producing Drum&Bass at the time.

artist.name: Adiva feat. Vicky Fee vs. Stardust
Above & Beyond vs. Mr. Pit vs. Cosmos
artist.bio: Above & Beyond is a trance music group formed in 2000 by Jonathan "Jono" Grant, Tony McGuinness, and Paavo Siljamäki. The trio are popular in the trance scene for their uplifting trance productions and collaborations with many vocalists. They are consistently voted as one of the top DJs and are currently ranked number 4 in the official DJ Magazine top 100 poll. They also host their own weekly radio show, Trance Around the World.

artist.name: Above & Beyond vs. Mr. Pit vs. Above & Beyond vs. Andy Moor
artist.bio: Above & Beyond is a trance music group formed in 2000 by Jonathan "Jono" Grant, Tony McGuinness, and Paavo Siljamäki. The trio are popular in the trance scene for their uplifting trance productions and collaborations with many vocalists. They are consistently voted as one of the top DJs and are currently ranked number 4 in the official DJ Magazine top 100 poll. They also host their own weekly radio show, Trance Around the World.

artist.name: Signum feat. Anita Kelsey
artist.bio:
There is more than one artist under the name of Signum  1. Signum from Netherlands
 2. Signum from Serbia
 3. SignuM from Lithuania (rock band)  Signum is the combination of two talented producers in the European music industry. They are Pascal Minnaard, (age 29) and Ronald Hagen (also age 29). Both live in Zoetermeer, a little city nearby Hague, their home base in Netherlands.  Pascal & Ron first met each other in high school.

artist.name: Dakota vs. Talla 2XLC
artist.bio: Dakota is the name of at least three groups, one of which is also an alias for well known Trance producer Markus Schulz.

artist.name: Myon & Shane 54 vs. Conjure One feat. Sin�ad O'Connor
Super 8 & Tab vs. Andy Moor vs. Orkidea
Signum feat. Anita Kelsey vs. Tiesto feat. BT
artist.bio:
There is more than one artist under the name of Signum  1. Signum from Netherlands
 2. Signum from Serbia
 3. SignuM from Lithuania (rock band)  Signum is the combination of two talented producers in the European music industry. They are Pascal Minnaard, (age 29) and Ronald Hagen (also age 29). Both live in Zoetermeer, a little city nearby Hague, their home base in Netherlands.  Pascal & Ron first met each other in high school.

artist.name: Pryda vs. ATB feat. Heather Nova
artist.bio: Pryda is an alias of the Swedish musician Eric Prydz. Other aliases used by Prydz include Cirez D, Moo and Sheridan. Pryda's music has been released under the labels Pryda Recordings, Pryda and Pryda Friends. The music released by Pryda falls into a variety of electronic-music sub genres, most notably house (Including electro house and tech house).

artist.name: Rank 1 vs. BT
artist.bio: They’re one of Europe’s most established and respected dance acts. Their debut release, ‘Airwave’ was the first Dutch record ever to hit the #1 position in the European dance charts and went Top 10 in the UK. Over the last 8 years, they have continued to pack the record boxes of world’s A-list spinners with floor-monsters like ‘Symsonic’, ‘Such is Life’, ‘Breathing’ & ‘Life Less Ordinary’… Performing to tens of thousands of dance fans every week, they play at some of the biggest dance events in the world. Meet Piet Bervoets & Benno de Goeij - better known as Rank 1!

artist.name: Andy Moor vs. Orkidea vs. Darude feat. Blake Lewis vs. Cara Dillion vs. 2Devine
artist.bio: There is more than one artist with this name:  1) Andy Moor (real name Andrew Beardmore), was born in 1980. DJ/producer/remixer from Stoke On Trent, UK. This is a discography of all releases by his (Sworn, Dub Disorder, Dwight van Mann) and related projects (Indigo, Leama & Moor, Tilt, Whiteroom, Zoo DJ’s) known by me.  This DJ/Producer and musician’s talents were picked up on at 5 years old when he had his first keyboard and instantly started playing songs which he subconsciously knew.

artist.name: Applescal
artist.bio: Applescal's real name is Pascal Terstappen.  This ambitious bedroomproducer was born in Haarlem, Holland, 20 years ago. He lived most of his life in Breda, where he came in touch with electronic music and software synthesisers. After four years of messing around he finally began to recognise the sounds of his computer as being the Music he had always heard in his head.  In the summer of 2007, Applescal moved to the capital city of Amsterdam.

artist.name: Serge Devant feat. Hadley
artist.bio: Not very long after his humble beginnings studying classical music in the former Soviet Union, Serge’s early electronic career is already marked with the achievements of a seasoned veteran. He hit the coveted DJ Mag Top 100 List, became the youngest resident DJ at New York’s legendary Crobar and has rapidly garnered major corporate support. Clothing maker Armani Exchange has recently snatched him up to represent the brand while global giant Coca-Cola has brought Serge on board with an exclusive track for the 2008 Olympics in Beijing.

artist.name: Example
artist.bio: Example is a rapper from Fulham, West London in the United Kingdom. Formerly signed to The Beats label run by Mike Skinner (The Streets) His first album, a mix-tape called "We Didn't Invent The Remix" Feb 2007 feature's samples from a diverse mixture of artists including Lily Allen, The Rolling Stones, José González & also Britney Spears on the Infamous Toxic Breath. He followed that in Sept 2007 with his official debut album, (released on The Beats) called "What We Made" produced by Rusher. which was received well by the British public.

artist.name: Loverush UK! feat. Carla Werner
artist.bio: Loverush UK! is founded by Mark Loverush & Kinky Roland. Loverush UK! have enjoyed great success in 2007 with their singles featuring Boy George, Marcella Detroit , Shelley Harland and Kirsty Hawkshaw. Their sound is full on euphoria with uplifting vocals hooks, but their packages on the release cater across the board.   Kinky Roland, originally from Berlin, Germany came to London in the late eighties.

artist.name: Smashing Pumpkins
artist.bio: Smashing Pumpkins are an influential American alternative rock band, formed in Chicago, Illinois in 1988. Billy Corgan and James Iha met in a record store, and began performing in local nightclubs with their bassist, D'Arcy Wretzky, using a drum machine. Playing with a drum machine frustrated both the band and their audience, and so Chicago jazz drummer Jimmy Chamberlin was hired soon afterwards.

artist.name: Estuera
artist.bio: Estuera is the main alias of Belgian trance DJ and Producer Jonas Steur. The tracks released under this name are "Tales From the South" (2004), "Travels" (2004), "Red Shores" (2005) and "Flow" (2006). Jonas also plans to release his first studio album under this alias in early 2007.

artist.name: Kinky Roland feat. Alec Sun Drae
artist.bio: Born Roland Faber, a German pop/electro/lounge artist based in the UK. www.myspace.com/kinkyroland

artist.name: Vimana vs First State feat. Kate Miles
artist.bio: Vimana is the name of two different artists:  Before the famous Gouryella name was created, Ferry Corsten and Tijs Verwest had already teamed up together for another project. Under the name ‘Vimana’ they produced 2 tracks together: ‘We Came’ and ‘Dreamtime’. In 1999, the vinyl release came out on Tiësto’s ‘Black Hole Recordings’ label with ‘We Came’ on the A side and ‘Dreamtime’ on the B side.   In March 2002 the US based label ‘4 Play Records Inc.’ re-released the track on CD with remixes done by Graham Gold, Dace Audé, JOY and Dave Dresden (from Gabriel & Dresden).

artist.name: Dash Berlin
artist.bio: Dash Berlin's latest tune is called "Man On The Run" The dub is featured in episode 301, 302 and 304 of A State Of Trance with Armin van Buuren and on the Global DJ Broadcast from June 7th 2007 with Markus Schulz. The vocal mix is featured in episode 311 and 312 (It has been voted as "Future Tune" from the users of www.trance.nu) of A State Of Trance, and on the Global DJ Broadcast from August August 9th.

artist.name: Jose Nunez & Harry Choo Choo Romero
Ercola feat. Daniella
artist.bio: A Finnish house/techno/hip hop artist. http://www.myspace.com/ercola

artist.name: White Stars
artist.bio: 'White Stars' is a Trance duo formed by Marko Kantola and Sauli Viinamäki from the city of Oulu in northern Finland. In August 2007 the duo signed their first contract with the Finnish record label Finity Records. Their first EP 'Always Alone/My Mind' was released in October 2007, and after it's release the EP rose to the Official Finnish Single Chart, peaking at #12.  Their newest release is the digital-only "Triangle Wave EP", released on Finity Digital in August 2009. The EP contains three tracks, which are titled "Two Hollow Souls", "Erica" and "Like A Wind".

artist.name: Dr. Willis & Junkyard Dog vs. Dean Newton & Huggie
Paul van Dyk vs. Rex Mundi feat. Susana
artist.bio: Grammy nominated artist and globally acclaimed DJ and Producer Paul van Dyk continues to dominate the electronic music charts and appears at the pinnacle of every Top DJ list across the globe. His fifth original album In Between was released August 2007 and features collaborations with David Byrne and Jessica Sutta of the Pussycat Dolls.  PvD is renowned as one of the hardest working artists, with sold-out tours that cross each continent, headline spots at every major festival, and a hugely successful recording career.

artist.name: Amurai feat. Emma Hewitt
artist.bio: Manvel Ter-Pogosyan was introduced to Trance music by ATBs famous track, 9PM (Till I Come). Born in Yerevan, Armenia, in 1987, Manvel was constantly exposed to music while growing up in a family appreciative of the arts. After immigrating to the United States in 1991, he continued to surround himself with beautiful music which led him to engage in music composition and production. In the years to come, passion and inspiration would take control as song after song was produced.

artist.name: ROGER SHAH pres.
artist.bio: Roger Shah (Real Name: Roger-Pierre Shah) (formerly known as DJ Shah) is an German Electronical Composer, Producer & Dj. He started his career in 1996 and year after year he reaches top 10 dance chart positions in Germany. In 1999 he released his first solo single, the “claps” which went on the top 5 of all dance charts and got attention from the most importants DJs in Europe. In October 2005 he gave his debut on Tiesto's own label Blackhole with 'Shah & Laruso pres.

artist.name: Roger Shah feat. Chris Jones
artist.bio: Roger Shah (Real Name: Roger-Pierre Shah) (formerly known as DJ Shah) is an German Electronical Composer, Producer & Dj. He started his career in 1996 and year after year he reaches top 10 dance chart positions in Germany. In 1999 he released his first solo single, the “claps” which went on the top 5 of all dance charts and got attention from the most importants DJs in Europe. In October 2005 he gave his debut on Tiesto's own label Blackhole with 'Shah & Laruso pres.

artist.name: Frase
artist.bio: t only 23 years old Frase is fast becoming the hottest tip of the UK trance scene with a string of critically acclaimed productions and dj sets at some of the UKs biggest and most respected clubs. With massive support from the likes of Armin van Buuren, Paul van Dyk, Ferry Corsten and John Askew, 2007 looks set to be the year that Frase joins the trance elite as a name to be reckoned with.  2005 was a breakthrough year for Frase.

artist.name: Avernus
artist.bio: There is at least two bands who shared that name. (1) Bulgarian Industrial project (2) American Metal Band http://www.myspace.com/avernusproject The Bulgarian Industrial project. Biography {1) Avernus is a Bulgarian Industrial project,risen from the ashes of time with one purpose:paying a homage to the mighty Legacy of Kain series. The project was founded in July 2009 from one wandering soul with the name Borislav Vakinov,in the old town Veliko Tarnovo.

artist.name: Ira Losco
artist.bio: Ira Losco was born 31 July 1981 in Sliema, Malta. She started her career when she joined a college band, named Tiara. They released a track called "Teleport Me" for the Green Label Collection CD, and an album called "Hi-Infidelity" in 2001, which included tracks like "Basketball" which is their biggest hit.  Late in 2001, Ira also released an album called "Butterfly", which included hits like "Summerbreeze" featuring top Maltese dj J.Joy & "Butterfly" featuring top Maltese rapper IQ, which is a cover version of Claudette Pace's entry for the Malta Song For Europe 1996.

artist.name: Boy 8-Bit
artist.bio: Boy 8-bit; a young and upcoming producer famous for his infectious "bleep" electro-styled tracks inspired by the computer games of old.    Boy 8-Bit's name hails from the days of old. Using an Amiga computer to produce in his youth, he dealt in 8-bit samples and hence the name.  Although still relatively unknown, his EP "Suspense is Killing Me" received great critical acclaim on the underground Electro/Synth circuit.

artist.name: Platnum
artist.bio: There are at least 2 artists with this name.  1. Platnum are a three-piece bassline vocal group from Manchester, UK, consisting of male vocalist Aaron Evers and female vocalists Mina Poli and Michelle McKenna. The group formed for a local talent show, Urban Superstars, in around 2004. They did not win the competition, but used their entry track, Over the Heartache, to showcase their talents to established members of the UK Bassline scene. The track proved popular, and a remix, by DJ Jamie Duggan, was awarded Bassline Heaven's Tune of the Year Award in 2006.

artist.name: Sharkslayer
artist.bio: Sharkslayer is the side project for Sir Nenis & DJ Pushups of the Top Billin establishment. Dedicated for the more tech-and-house sounds of club music, their productions will slay dancefloors anywhere. As being high on dubstep, ghettohouse and tech-house, not to mention the love for soul, boogie & dancehall, they create a unique blend of club music that's the sound of now. They're already picked up for remix duties for such labels as Mad Decent, Trouble & Bass and Plant Music, causing a stir at blogs and getting club play from such top DJ's as Diplo...

artist.name: Claudia Cazacu feat. Augrey Gallagher
artist.bio:
Moving to the UK from Romania 7 years ago Claudia Cazacu soon found herself at home in the London club scene. Attending events week after week it wasn’t long before she decided her destiny was a life behind the decks. 
 Launching her career in 2006 Claudia Cazacu has in a short space of time propelled herself to become the most anticipated new DJ on the scene. 
 UK appearances have included The Gallery, Inside Out, Goodgreef, Sundissential, Riot! & Wildchild.

artist.name: Hardwell
artist.bio: Let us introduce to you – Hardwell!   At just 21 it’s fair to say he’s ‘been around’ if you take into consideration his achievements over the past 18 months. His passion for music, in particular his love of all things house, has helped this multi-talented producer climb his way to the top. Hardwell’s overall talent is recognised by the dance music industry as a new, exciting and refreshing take on a scene that continues to evolve and with an apparent everlasting shelf life!

artist.name: Rodriguez Jr.
artist.bio: Rodriguez Jr. is also known as one half of French Dance Act The Youngsters, signed to Laurent Garnier's F-Com - releasing albums 'Lemon Orange' in 2001 and 'the Army of 1-0' in 2004, as well as a plethora of EP releases. On the solo tip, Rodriguez Jr. has released on F-Com (check his emotive, deep techno track 'Aelckxgeland' released in 2006 - part of the 'Alternative Schemes For The Younger' EP) and has remixed Alexkid's 'Nightshade' for F-Com, Bentobox's 'Yakiniku' EP for Alexkid's Imprimé label and Philip Morgan Lewis' 'Love' EP on Soul Management.

artist.name: Julie Thompson
artist.bio: Julie Thompson has always been heavily influenced by the varying rock genres in music over the last 3 decades. Although her natural versatile voice and honest songwriting style has always retained poppy melodic sensibilities, her roots vary, encompassing mid 70’s to early eighties alternative rock, the Seattle grunge era and early nineties alternative movement right up to today’s with a little electronic influence displayed by the of which she However the colourful character to her voice led...

artist.name: Sergio Fernandez
artist.bio: Sergio Fernandez is a multifaceted, Madrid based DJ, producer and events promoter. He started mixing from an early age in small, local clubs and little by little, he realised his calling could convert itself into a career. His present style varies from exquisite progressive house to more intense tribal beats.   As a DJ he has performed in the most important clubs and events throughout Spain such as  Phrenetic, Rave State, Deluxe, Beat Freak official party at Home (Madrid), No Data (Bilbao), Techno Dreams (Galicia), Kaotika Eletronic Music Festival (Toledo) Voloko (León).

artist.name: Sour Grapes
artist.bio:
Sour Grapes started out around 1993 with Pak Twisted on Drums, Cory Bannister on Guitar and Steph Twisted in Vocals. After two bass player changes (Don Levandier and Derek McKinnon) things settled down with Andrew Gregory on Bass.
 The current band recorded a demo tape in 1995 entitled Ingrid? in their ratty old jam space above some steele processing plant. Shortly after the demo was released the band went through another line up change. Pak moved off the drums and onto the bass and old time friend Mike Bourque became the drummer.

artist.name: Deko-Ze n Gavo - Explosive! (Kid Massive audiodamage vocal mix) [Hi
Fluke
artist.bio: Formed in the late 1980's by three friends living together in London, Fluke started out making dreamy pop before the explosion of acid house influenced them. It was the growing electronica sound that influenced their early singles (Thumper, Joni, Slid) and their techno-rock debut album The Techno Rose Of Blighty. They signed with Virgin for their next albums Six Wheels On My Wagon (1993) and OTO (1995), which proved Fluke to be a driving force in the progressive house and trip-hop scenes.

artist.name: Moony - I Don't Know Why (DJ Chus & Jerome Isma
Drumattic Twins
artist.bio: Nick Slater and Lanx's (aka Kevin Lancaster) stage name was the consequence of having amplified attacks of drum-machine seizures in their loft. Even the strongest prescriptions could not calm the frenzy of 12 years of multi-faceted producing and DJing that would ensue before they landed at Finger Lickin'.  The Drumattic Twins' biography constructs their musical biology. As children of the dance revolution would remember, many moons ago, Nick and Lanx were known as the chart topping Shades of Rhythm.

artist.name: Cosmic Gate feat. Kyler England
artist.bio: Cosmic Gate is a German trance, progressive trance and hard trance duo made up of Claus Terhoeven (aka Nic Chagall) and Stefan Bossems (DJ Bossi). They are best known for their singles "Exploration of Space", "The Drums", and "The Truth." Cosmic Gate has done remixes for popular DJs including Dj Tiesto, Armin van Buuren, and Ferry Corsten. Cosmic Gate's heavy, analogue trance sound is considered by many to be the definition of hard trance. Discography Albums: * Rhythm & Drums (2001) * No More Sleep (2002)

artist.name: Luca
artist.bio: There is more than one artist with this name:  *********************************************************  Luca - Drum & Bass Producer from New Zealand. Signed to Samurai Music.  *********************************************************  (american Luca) This Tucson, AZ band plays a blend of rock, pop, folk, and americana with some jazzy and soulful elements thrown in for good measure. Singer/songwriter/guitarist/keyboardist Nick Luca has worked with many great artists while working at Wavelab Studio.

artist.name: Serge Devant feat. Emma Hewitt
artist.bio: Not very long after his humble beginnings studying classical music in the former Soviet Union, Serge’s early electronic career is already marked with the achievements of a seasoned veteran. He hit the coveted DJ Mag Top 100 List, became the youngest resident DJ at New York’s legendary Crobar and has rapidly garnered major corporate support. Clothing maker Armani Exchange has recently snatched him up to represent the brand while global giant Coca-Cola has brought Serge on board with an exclusive track for the 2008 Olympics in Beijing.

artist.name: Remot
artist.bio: Remot's rise to prominence started on the Hip Hop news website hiphopdx.com, where he has won numerous production-based contests, remixing well-known songs such as Nas' "Surviving the Times", Styles P's "Blow My Mind" and Stat Quo's "G.R.I.T.S." Most notable achievement so far, however, is securing victory in the American Gangster Remixtape Contest, in which 130 different producers from around the world submitted their remixed versions of Jay-Z's American Gangster album in 2008. hiphopdx
